377	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:11:02	2024-11-22 07:10:26	14302	2023-09-26 00:00:00	MAD02Niños	Una aventura familiar inolvidable	una-aventura-familiar-inolvidable	<strong>\\r\\n<span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Disfruta de planes y momentos divertidos en familia en Madrid</span>\\r\\n</strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Disfrute de Madrid en familia con un emocionante itinerario que incluye parques, museos, deliciosa comida y actividades para niños y adultos. Desde paseos por Madrid Río hasta visitas culturales y diversas opciones culinarias, esta experiencia ofrece diversión para todos.</span>	13	pexels-emma-bauso-2253879.jpg	2	<p style=\\"padding-left: 40px;\\">Te recomiendo que empieces dando un paseo por <a href=\\"#madridrio\\"><strong>Madrid Río</strong></a>, hay 17 zonas de ocio infantil y los niños disfrutarán un montón. Cerca de Madrid Río te recomiendo comer en <a href=\\"#costellorio\\"><strong>Costello Rio</strong></a> , los postres son una delicia, cerca también tienes <a href=\\"#bartoboggan\\"><strong>el Bar Toboggan</strong></a> y luego un café en <a href=\\"#bitesmecafe\\"><strong>Bite me cafe.</strong></a><br />Por la tarde si te gusta patinar puedes hacer un plan diferente patinando en el <a href=\\"#rollingchamartin\\"><strong>Rolling Chamartin</strong></a> (allí puedes alquilar patines). Si te quedas por la zona, puedes cenar en <a href=\\"#comicplanet\\"><strong>Comic Planet</strong></a>, ideal para los amantes del universo Marvel.</p>                	<p>Por la mañana propongo empezar desayunando en la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#chocolateriasangines\\"><strong>Chocolatería San Ginés</strong></a> y después ir a un lugar muy especial, la <a href=\\"#casamuseodelratonperez\\"><strong>Casa-Museo del Ratón Pérez</strong></a>. Gustará tanto a adultos como a niños. Ya que estás en el centro, te recomiendo un paseo por el <a href=\\"#palacioreal\\"><strong>Palacio Real</strong></a> , <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#jardinesdesabatini\\"><strong>los Jardines de Sabatini</strong></a> , y <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#plazadeespana\\"><strong>la Plaza de España</strong></a> donde verás a Don Quijote y Sancho. Si te apetece un plan al aire libre puedes ir a la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#casadecampo\\"><strong>Casa de Campo</strong></a> y caminar hasta el lago. Para comer, puedes optar por algo más tradicional como un cocido madrileño en <a href=\\"#labola\\"><strong>La Bola</strong> </a>o algo oriental como en el <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#yatai\\">Mercado Yatai</a>.</strong></p><p>Por la tarde te sugiero algunas visitas culturales <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#elmuseodelasilusiones\\"><strong>El Museo de las Ilusiones</strong></a> , un paseo por el barrio de huertas y cena en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#lapizzateca\\"><strong>La Pizzateca</strong></a> o <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#tabernaalsurdehuertas\\"><strong>La</strong> <strong>Taberna al Sur de Huertas</strong></a> si ya conoces este museo te sugiero el <a href=\\"#museodelferrocarril\\"><strong>Museo <strong>del</strong> Ferrocarril</strong></a> que también es muy interesante. Si opta por esta última también puede cenar en las opciones anteriores, están muy cerca.</p>                	<p>Hoy te sugiero que empieces a desayunar en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#laemilita\\"><strong>La Emilita</strong></a> o en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#chocolateriachurreriachococo\\"><strong>Chocolatería Churreria Choco&co</strong></a> y desde allí podréis disfrutar del día en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#micropolix\\"><strong>Micropolix</strong></a>, el parque preferido de todos los niños donde pueden tener un trabajo o conducir un coche, descubrirán una ciudad en miniatura, tiene fácil combinación con el transporte público, para los padres que no quieran quedarse allí, hay un centro comercial cerca.<br />Si decides comer allí te sugiero que lo hagas en el restaurante diariamente y luego vayas al parque del barco pirata, los niños pueden disfrutar y los padres pueden tomar un café en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#terracedelavega\\"><strong>La Terraza de la Vega</strong></a> , cerca hay un McDonalds también.<br />Si decides volver a Madrid, es fin de semana y te gusta el teatro te sugiero que vayas al <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#teatroluchana\\"><strong>Teatro Luchana</strong></a> , tiene una cartelera infantil muy divertida. Si prefieres dar un paseo hasta el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#templodedebod\\"><strong>Templo de Debod</strong></a> para ver el atardecer puedes terminar cenando en un lugar que nos encanta en el centro es <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#laexcentrica\\"><strong>La Excéntrica</strong></a> además tienes muy cerca una mítica de Madrid que se llama <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#casamingo\\"><strong>Casa Mingo</strong> .</a></p>\t\t	377	pexels-emma-bauso-2253879.jpg	1184,1185,1186,1187,1188,1189,1190,1191,1192,1193,1194,1195	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	367,368,376,390,372,384,370,366,374,383,389,380,365,378,385,379,382,373,375,377,369,371,362,387,388,386	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=1TxtN5tKcu8IFJG2uaw9nLyMVFxRMLZ8&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtBqng0gq5j8	price_1Q2TJrAFILSEnUZXfQ7mwwJZ	1	S	N	Disfruta de planes y momentos divertidos en familia en Madrid	\N	\N	Una aventura familiar inolvidable	prod_QuotDjJTOTiudu	price_1Q2zFQAFILSEnUZXrCwD9sUl		https://buy.stripe.com/test_00g3fl4sZbSe3sI6r5		plink_1Q3AnnAFILSEnUZXEKmgbm9P	3Dias	14	N
378	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:11:15	2024-11-22 07:10:26	11673	2023-09-29 00:00:00	Mad03 history	Immerse In Madrid\\ s History	immerse-in-madrids-history	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">A walk through the history of Madrid</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Enjoy an experience through historic Madrid, tour the Madrid of the Austrias, the gardens and parks of the city and discover the most delicious gastronomy of the most mythical places of the capital.</span>	14	palacio-real-1.jpg	2	<p>I propose you to start by the Madrid de los Austrias, if it is good I take the opportunity to have breakfast on the terrace of the <a href=\\"#cafedelosaustrias\\"><strong>Café de los Austrias</strong></a> I take a coffee and a toast with tomato, the place is curious because it is in the square where Cervantes was buried. Other times I stop in <strong><a href=\\"#chocolateriasangines\\">San Ginés</a> </strong>to have a chocolate with churros for breakfast. Then I walk around the area of the <a href=\\"#sabatinigardens\\"><strong>Sabatini Gardens</strong></a>, the <a href=\\"#templodedebod\\"><strong>Debod Temple</strong></a> and get to the Plaza España. If you like sweets in the Plaza del Cordon there is a store where you can buy all the sweets that are made in the convents of Spain. The place is called <a href=\\"#eljardindelconvento\\"><strong>El Jardín del Convento</strong></a>.  </p><p>If you decide to enter the royal palace, better, if you go early in the morning there are less people, at the end of the day the entrance is free but the line is huge. To eat I recommend <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#lalatina\\">Cava Baja Street</a></strong> if you go up the <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#callemayor\\">calle Mayor</a></strong> you can take some tapas in the cava baja , my favorites are: Vermuteria la bolita Negra, Taberna el Tempranillo, la perejila, Casa María or los huevos de Lucio<strong>.</strong></p><p>For the afternoon, I love the Plaza de la Cebada, my favorite without a doubt <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#elviajero\\">El Viajero</a>.</strong></p><p>Then a good option is to go to see the church of the <a href=\\"#virgendelapaloma\\"><strong>Virgen de la Paloma</strong></a>. Over there you can have dinner in <a href=\\"#lafalda\\"><strong>La falda</strong></a> or in <a href=\\"#loscaracoles\\"><strong>Los caracoles.</strong></a></p>                	<p>For today I propose you to start the day having a <a href=\\"#timhorthons\\"><strong>Tim Hortons coffee </strong></a>and then visit the <a href=\\"#museolazarogaldiano\\"><strong>Lázaro Galdiano Museum</strong></a> or the <a href=\\"#sorolla\\"><strong>Sorolla Museum</strong></a>. For lunch I would opt for <a href=\\"#mamacampo\\"><strong>Mama Campo</strong></a> or <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#grossonapoletano\\">Grosso Napoletano</a></strong>, both are very good options. In the afternoon, I suggest that you visit the <a href=\\"#museuminthechamberistation\\"><strong>Museum in the Chamberí Metro Station</strong></a> before you can have a coffee at <a href=\\"#aryabakery\\"><strong>Arya Bakery</strong></a>.  If you already know it, I suggest the <a href=\\"#museoarqueologico\\"><strong>Archaeological Museum</strong></a>, a classic that never disappoints.</p><p>For dinner my best options are <a href=\\"#trattoriapulcinella\\" data-wplink-edit=\\"true\\"><strong>Trattoria Pulcinella</strong></a> or <a href=\\"#zingara\\"><strong>Zíngara</strong></a>. Next to Zíngara, there is a very small store with a delicious cheesecake.</p>                	<p>Today I propose you to visit the <a href=\\"#palaciodeliria\\"><strong>palace of Liria</strong></a> has priceless treasures and is beautiful, then walk down towards Plaza de España to the subway stop, you can also walk across the Gran Via. If you want to eat in a classic place I suggest <a href=\\"#labola\\"><strong>La bola</strong></a> or <a href=\\"#casabotin\\"><strong>Casa Botin</strong></a>. If you prefer something quick I suggest<a href=\\"#institutocervantes\\"><strong> Cervantes Institute</strong></a>, where you can then make a virtual tour to enter the house of letters. Nearby you have the <a href=\\"#retiro\\"><strong>Retiro Park</strong></a> to take a walk to the Crystal Palace and have a coffee near the lake. If you already know it, you can enter the <a href=\\"#iglesiadelosjeronimos\\"><strong>church of the Jerónimos</strong></a> and take advantage of the 2 free hours at the <a href=\\"#museodelprado\\"><strong>Prado</strong></a>.On the way out, take a walk through the ?barrio de las letras?. Nearby I like the restaurant <a href=\\"#lolasimola\\"><strong>Lola si mola</strong></a> or the Peruvian <a href=\\"#tambo\\"><strong>Tambo</strong></a>. Nearby you have <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#elgolfo\\"><strong>El Golfo Comedy Club</strong></a> and<a href=\\"#blackbird\\"><strong> Blackbird </strong></a>if you want to disconnect at night.</p>\t\t	378	palacio-real-1.jpg	1196,1197,1198,1199,1200,1201,1202,1203,1204,1205	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	409,408,422,391,414,396,415,417,394,421,395,398,406,413,400,403,419,401,405,397,407,412,416,418,393,392,404,420,402,410,399,411	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=1xPRlwhQm1oi4ywv_jW_8SL3uhV_1440&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	1	N	S	A walk through the history of Madrid	\N	\N	Immerse In Madrid\\ s History							3Dias	15	N
379	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:11:27	2024-11-22 07:10:26	14300	2023-10-01 00:00:00	MAD06 - SEXANDCITY	Shopping y tardeo	shopping-y-tardeo	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Una experiencia de compras de lujo en la capital española</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nPasee por las zonas más exclusivas y cool de la capital, disfrute de lo último en moda y tendencias. Tómate un \\"tardeo\\" en los locales de moda y come en los restaurantes más instagramers.	15	pexels-borko-manigoda-1778412.jpg	2	<p>Comenzamos el plan en la zona de lujo de Madrid. Puede desayunar en <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#lepainquotidien\\">?Le Pain Quotidien</a>»</strong> en la calle Serrano. En esta parte no sólo están las grandes marcas, sino también tiendas muy monas donde encontrar cosas interesantes. Estos son mis imprescindibles en la zona: <a href=\\"#monisqui\\"><strong>Monisqui</strong></a>, <a href=\\"#brownie\\"><strong>Brownie</strong></a>, <a href=\\"#renatta\\"><strong>Renatta&go</strong></a> o <a href=\\"#bimani\\"><strong>Bimani</strong></a>. La zona está llena de tiendas así que disfrutarás un montón. Para comer, hay que ir a la calle Jorge Juan. Ahí tienes el restaurante <strong>?<a href=\\"#lamaquina\\">La máquina»</a></strong>(un éxito seguro), puedes pedir la tortilla de patata que es una delicia o el tomate con ventresca. También tienes <a href=\\"#amazonico\\"><strong>Amazónico</strong></a>, un local de moda con comida brasileña (muy recomendables la picaña y el solomillo). Para tomar algo después sugiero el sky lounge <strong>?<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#picospardos\\">Picos pardos»</a></strong>. Por la noche, si os apetece un plan más cultural, os sugiero cenar <a href=\\"#sweetspace\\"><strong>Sweet Space</strong></a> en <a href=\\"#belmondo\\"><strong>Bel Mondo.</strong></a></p>                	<p>Hoy te propongo un plan de spa y bienestar, un poco de mimo siempre viene bien. Puedes reservar una cita en el <a href=\\"#hamman\\"><strong>Hammam al andalus</strong></a> si está muy concurrido puede acudir a la <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#wellness\\">Experiencia Wellness Boutique</a></strong><strong>, </strong>donde hacen masajes, tratamientos faciales y corporales. Cuando salgas te sugiero que vayas a comer a <a href=\\"#ramses\\"><strong>Ramses</strong></a>, un lugar de primera. Te recomiendo que pidas la ensalada César. Luego puede pasear por el <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#ayuntamiento\\">Ayuntamiento de Madrid</a>,</strong>  para cenar sugiero <a href=\\"#lafondalironda\\"><strong>La fonda Lironda</strong></a> en chueca o también puedes comer en <a href=\\"#zest\\"><strong>Zest</strong></a> un delicioso risotto de queso. Por la noche sugiero unas copas en <a href=\\"#thejunglejazz\\"><strong>el jungle jazz</strong></a> o en la <a href=\\"#destileriadelamazonico\\"><strong>Destilería del Amazónico</strong></a>.</p>                	<p>Hoy propongo un doble plan. Por un lado, si lo tuyo son más las compras, te propongo ir al <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#lasrozasvillage\\">?Rozas Village»</a>, </strong>el outlet más famoso de Madrid. Allí mismo tienes cafeterías para tomarte un buen café. Si quieres una experiencia más personalizada, puedes contratar a un personal shopper en la web. Tienes todo el tiempo de las tiendas. Para comer puede acercarse a <a href=\\"#donsoba\\"><strong>Don Soba</strong></a> (restaurante japonés con un menú barato y de buena calidad?) <strong>?<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#casadecomidaselgranclavel\\">Casa de comidas de Gran Clavel?</a></strong> Luego te sugiero un paseo hasta la Puerta del Sol y Gran Vía, allí tienes <a href=\\"#zapshop\\"><strong>Tienda Zap</strong></a>. Para la noche recomiendo <a href=\\"#aurora\\"><strong>Aurora</strong></a> (suele tener mucha fama reserva cuanto antes) y si quieres quedarte en Gran Via puedes subir <a href=\\"#eljardindediana\\"><strong>?El jardín de Diana?</strong></a> (verás los restos de las bombas de la guerra civil) también puedes caminar hasta el <a href=\\"#retiro\\"><strong>Retiro</strong></a> y terminar en <a href=\\"#florida\\"><strong>Florida</strong></a> sin duda una vida nocturna mítica en Madrid. Dispone de varios espacios según el plan que más te apetezca.</p><p>Espero que disfrutes de mi plan en Madrid. Asegúrese de reservar con antelación.</p>\t\t	379	pexels-borko-manigoda-1778412.jpg	1206,1207,1208,1209,1210,1211,1212,1213,1214,1215,1216	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	429,444,432,427,425,442,441,445,434,447,433,439,436,428,423,424,446,430,440,435,426,431,438,443,437	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=1GbSHvHdG1u58yfRKoBJs4dugXZxzqNU&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtUb5otaG8P7	price_1Q2TJsAFILSEnUZXDXjbvSVZ	1	N	S	Una experiencia de compras de lujo en la capital española	\N	\N	Shopping y tardeo	prod_Quot8btDSVXzxF	price_1Q2zFQAFILSEnUZXnJpCQRV7		https://buy.stripe.com/test_bIY5nt5x3f4qe7m7va		plink_1Q3AnoAFILSEnUZXfcBPh7e3	3Dias	16	N
380	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:11:41	2024-11-22 07:10:26	12065	2023-10-01 00:00:00	SV15 Barrios 3 days	Seville\\ s Famous Neighborhoods	sevilles-famous-neighborhoods	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Discover Seville\\ s enchanting and famous neighborhoods ? the city\\ s captivating essence awaits exploration!</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nDive into this unique experience to soak up the vibes and atmosphere that fill the streets of the city\\ s most iconic neighborhoods. Strolling through Seville\\ s neighborhoods is like taking a journey back in time, where every corner tells a story and every alleyway hides delightful surprises waiting to be uncovered. Let yourself be captivated by the unparalleled charm of these places steeped in history and culture.	16	barriosevilla2.jpg	1	<p>I?ll start with <strong>TRIANA</strong>, on the other side of the river, where art and tradition are in the air. Its streets are filled with ceramic workshops and pottery shops where the scent of earth and clay blends with the sound of potter?s wheels. Bars and taverns along the banks of the Guadalquivir River offer unparalleled views of the Torre del Oro and a lively atmosphere full of Andalusian flavor.</p><p>If you start early in the morning, you can have breakfast at <a href=\\"#labaronesa\\"><strong>La Baronesa</strong></a>, and then visit its lively <a href=\\"#mercado\\"><strong>market</strong></a> and food market. In its lower levels are the remains of the <a href=\\"#jorge\\"><strong>Castle of San Jorge</strong></a>, the headquarters of the former Inquisitorial Tribunal. A curiosity of the neighborhood is that you can find the only place in Seville where you can eat ?pajaritos? (little birds) at <a href=\\"#ruperto\\"><strong>Bar Casa Ruperto</strong></a>, where many are surprised when they hear for the first time that these ?pajaritos? are actually fried quails. If you want to visit some of its famous chapels, apart from Los Marineros, I recommend the <a href=\\"#estrella\\"><strong>Brotherhood of La Estrella</strong></a>. If it gets dark in Triana, you can stroll along Betis Street and its terraces with a great variety of flamenco bars (like <a href=\\"#lola\\"><strong>Lola de los Reyes</strong></a>) and all kinds of music (for example, <a href=\\"#embarcadero\\"><strong>El Embarcadero</strong></a>).</p><p>Crossing the river over the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#triana\\"><strong>Isabel II Bridge</strong></a> (the oldest iron bridge preserved in Spain), we begin our stroll through the <strong>ARENAL</strong> neighborhood:</p><p>The walk from the bridge to the <a href=\\"#torredeloro\\"><strong>Torre del Oro</strong></a> is spectacular. We will pass by the <a href=\\"#maestranza\\"><strong>Real Maestranza de Sevilla</strong></a>, known as the oldest bullring in the country and the official venue for the bullfighting events held during the Seville Feria de abril. It is one of the world?s temples of bullfighting, a stage of dense history and Sevillian tradition, with a beautiful museum and the possibility of stepping on the sand. And to finish, you can visit the <a href=\\"#caridad\\"><strong>Hospital de la Caridad</strong></a> and its gardens.</p><p>El Arenal is a place steeped in history that has become a top spot in Seville to enjoy gastronomy. There?s a formidable range of experiences with all kinds of establishments, from grocery stores and fried food shops to bars and restaurants. For lunch in the Arenal area, you can try <a href=\\"#sarmiento\\"><strong>Taberna Casa Sarmiento</strong></a>, or if you want something more sophisticated, <a href=\\"#pesquero\\"><strong>El Pesquero</strong></a> specializes in fish and seafood (closed on Mondays).</p><p>If you?re looking for a more immersive experience, one option I recommend for dining today or any other day is to try <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#sazon\\"><b style=\\"font-family: var(--global-body-font-family);\\">SAZÓN The Folk Cook</b></a>, SAZON is the world\\ s first platform to provide Spanish food homely prepared by locals at their own houses, where you would taste it in complete privacy.</p>                	<p>Today, we?ll explore the <strong>SANTA CRUZ AND HISTORICAL CENTER</strong> neighborhood, a tourist area par excellence. With its narrow cobbled streets and flower-filled patios, it?s a labyrinth of charm and mystery. Here, whitewashed walls and wrought-iron balconies create an atmosphere that evokes the soul of old Seville. The cool shade of the orange trees and the sound of flamenco guitars in the taverns turn each street into a unique sensory experience. In this area, you must not miss:</p><p>The marvelous <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#catedral\\"><strong>Gothic Cathedral</strong></a> (the largest in the world). You?ll be fascinated by its history, architecture, and the vast collection of artworks it houses. In addition to its imposing vaults, the enchantment of the Patio de los Naranjos, the Colombina Library, the chapels filled with works of art; one of its major attractions is La Giralda, its bell tower, consisting of two distinct yet perfectly united parts, providing an example of the melting pot of cultures present in the city.</p><p>?<a href=\\"#archivo\\"><strong>The General Archive of the Indies</strong></a>, which will remind you of the glorious past as the gateway to trade with the Indies and today an absolute reference in the documentary study of the Spanish presence in America.</p><p>?<a href=\\"#alcazar\\"><strong>The Royal Alcazar</strong></a>, a palace that represents the magnificence of Mudejar art. Its interior decorations are beautiful, with each room and courtyard adorned with geometric patterns, greenery, and tiles. The expansive gardens with fountains, water jets, and flower beds are worth a visit.</p><p>There?s much to see in this area. You can grab a beer at the well-known Plaza del Salvador and then venture into the <strong>ALFALFA</strong> neighborhood for lunch, for example at <a href=\\"#chari\\"><strong>Bar Kiko de la Chari</strong></a>. This place is a bit hidden, but it?s worth it. It?s a family-owned establishment where the grandmother does the cooking, and you?ll find locals on its terrace.</p><p>With a full stomach, everything looks much better. If you want to have a coffee or a drink, you can head up to <a href=\\"#eme\\"><strong>the EME Terrace</strong></a> (with spectacular views) and continue with the route:</p><p>?<a href=\\"#pilatos\\"><strong>Casa de Pilatos</strong></a>, and its famous surrounding streets in the Jewish quarter. Don?t miss visiting Pimienta Street, of great historical importance for the Jewish tiles that are still preserved and the legends that revolve around it.</p><p>?<a href=\\"#verde\\"><strong>Verde Street</strong></a>, a street that holds many stories and legends where you can admire the House of the Padilla. In the area, if you want to relax, you have the Las Termas de Híspalis Spa.</p><p>In this area for lunch/dinner, I recommend <a href=\\"#chicota\\"><strong>La Chicotá</strong></a>, a typical Sevillian tapas bar with images of Holy Week, or treat yourself at the <a href=\\"#marco\\"><strong>San Marco Santa Cruz restaurant</strong></a>, located in ancient Arab baths from the 12th century. If you want to have a drink, you can go to <strong>Garlochí</strong>, which cannot remain you indifferent</p>                	<p>We can?t leave without visiting the <strong>LA MACARENA</strong> neighborhood. A visit to the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#macarena\\"><strong>Macarena arch and its basilica</strong></a> is a must. As we enter its walls, we head to the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#feria\\"><strong>Feria Market</strong></a> to have a beer at any of its stalls or at <a href=\\"#cerveza\\"><strong>El Rey de la Cerveza</strong></a>.</p><p>We can also take the opportunity to visit the <a href=\\"#algaba\\"><strong>Palace of the Marquises of Algaba</strong></a>, lesser-known but well worth a visit, and it?s free! This palace belonged to a noble family that held the title and inhabited the residence for centuries. Its interior houses an impressive collection of works of art and furniture from different historical periods, bearing witness to the opulence and artistic taste of its owners. The ceilings of the Leonor room are a marvel, as well as its central courtyard.</p><p>For lunchtime, we head to the vibrant <strong>LA ALAMEDA</strong> neighborhood, a young and avant-garde pulse in the heart of the city, a melting pot of cultures and trends. Its bars and terraces are meeting points for Sevillians and visitors looking for new culinary and cultural experiences. Here, I recommend trying tapas at the fun <a href=\\"#lolapordios\\"><strong>Lola por Dios</strong></a>, or if you like Mexican food, <a href=\\"#lupe\\"><strong>La Lupe Taquería</strong></a>.</p><p>After lunch, you can head to the area of the <a href=\\"#bellasartes\\"><strong>Fine Arts Museum of Seville</strong></a>, which is also free for EU citizens (otherwise, the price is only ?1.50).</p><p>To conclude your visit, if you want to treat yourselves, have dinner at the RECOVECO restaurant (<a href=\\"#unuk\\"><strong>UNUK hotel terrace</strong></a>) to end on a high note. Or if you want to enjoy an authentic flamenco show, visit the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#pena\\"><strong>Torres Macarena Flamenco Cultural Club</strong></a>, where you can also have tapas and drinks (check schedules and shows).</p><p>We recommend booking restaurants and events in advance to ensure availability, as well as checking opening hours.</p><p>I hope you enjoy my city and come back soon. We?re here for anything you need.</p><p>See you soon!</p>\t\t	380	barriosevilla2.jpg	1217,1218,1129,1103,1219,1220,1221,1222,1110,1223,1224	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	151,157,1,48,467,451,160,122,109,460,475,24,126,138,465,59,470,469,206,199,94,20,210,96,6,18,457,123,147,8,26,478,466,166	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=1qLOm69ZiVAvip3rZ-w-TVIS6hJdZJIM&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	1	N	S	Discover Seville\\ s enchanting and famous neighborhoods ? the city\\ s captivating essence awaits exploration!	\N	\N	Seville\\ s Famous Neighborhoods							3Dias	17	N
381	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:11:54	2024-11-22 07:10:26	12110	2023-09-28 00:00:00	SV06 Sevilla Secreta 3 days	Discover The Secret Seville	discover-the-secret-seville	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Explore the corners that make Seville a fantastic city that never ceases to amaze you</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nEmbark on a unique adventure to uncover the hidden treasures of Seville. During this experience, you\\ ll dive into the city\\ s rich history as you explore stunning buildings with centuries of intertwined stories, stroll through streets steeped in secrets and legends, and savor meals at one-of-a-kind restaurants that will take your taste buds on an unforgettable journey. Get ready for an experience that will leave you in awe of the authenticity and charm of Seville like never before.	17	cerveceria-giralda-sevilla.jpg	1	<p>On your first day, if you?re going to wander around the old town of Seville and the Santa Cruz neighborhood, there are various points on the route that you shouldn?t miss:</p><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a href=\\"#venerables\\"><strong>The Hospital de los Venerables</strong></a>: located right in the heart of the Santa Cruz neighborhood, its history dates back to the 17th century and is closely linked to charity and social assistance in the city. It was founded in 1675 by Archbishop Manuel Arias y Porres, with the purpose of housing and caring for older priests and needy elders. The name ?Venerables? refers to the priests who, due to their advanced age or economic difficulties, needed special care and attention.</li></ul><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a href=\\"#plazadelcabildo\\"><strong>Plaza del Cabildo</strong></a>, undoubtedly my favorite square in the city. The tragic event known as ?El Motín del Trigo? took place in 1587 right here. Popular discontent over the high cost of wheat triggered a revolt that left a deep mark on the city?s memory.</li></ul><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a href=\\"#calleverde\\"><strong>Calle Verde</strong></a>, a street that holds many stories and legends where you can admire the beautiful courtyard of ?El secreto de la calle Verde? from the window.</li></ul><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\">The charming <a href=\\"#plazasantamarta\\"><strong>Plaza de Santa Marta</strong></a>, which you access through a discreet street in Virgen de los Reyes square. In this tiny square, you?ll find a 16th-century cruise from the San Lázaro hospital. Its beauty lies in the fact that it has a crucifix carved on one side and a piety on the other.</li></ul><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a href=\\"#columnascallemarmoles\\"><strong>The Roman Temple Street Marbles</strong></a>.</li></ul><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\">The <a href=\\"#libreriaverbo\\"><strong>Verbo bookstore</strong></a> located in the building where the old Imperial Theater was.</li></ul><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a href=\\"#santamarialablanca\\"><strong>The Church of Santa María la Blanca</strong></a>, a jewel of the Baroque in the heart of the history of this church dates back to the 13th century when a synagogue was erected in the same place. This synagogue, known as the Major Synagogue of Seville, was one of the most important in the city?s Jewish community. However, with the expulsion of the Jews from Spain in 1492, the synagogue was converted into a Catholic church.</li></ul><p>For dinner in the area, I recommend the <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#elpatiodelpali\\">El Patio del Pali</a></strong> Restaurant (closed on Mondays and Tuesdays, I recommend making a reservation) or if you want something less formal, <a href=\\"#lasteresas\\"><strong>Las Teresas</strong></a> is a very authentic and local option. </p><p>If you?re looking for a more immersive experience, one option I recommend for dining today or any other day is to try <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sazon\\"><b>SAZÓN The Folk Cook</b></a>, SAZON is the world\\ s first platform to provide Spanish food homely prepared by locals at their own houses, where you would taste it in complete privacy.</p><p>To end the day, stop by the charismatic <a href=\\"#garlochi\\"><strong>Garlochí</strong></a> for a drink.</p>                	<p>Today we?ll continue in the city center as there are many things to see. We?ll head to the <a href=\\"#algaba\\"><strong>Palace of the Marquises of Algaba</strong></a> (it?s free and closes at 2 pm), and then proceed to the <a href=\\"#sanluisdelosfranceses\\"><strong>Church of San Luis de los Franceses</strong></a> (closes at 5 pm), a lesser-known architectural gem. If you want to have breakfast in the area, you have <a href=\\"#feria83\\"><strong>Feria 83</strong></a> offering various brunch options.</p><p>For lunch in the area, I recommend grabbing something at <a href=\\"#losclaveles\\"><strong>Los Claveles</strong></a> (a local Sevillian place with Holy Week decor and a variety of tapas). After lunch, we can visit the <a href=\\"#palaciodeduenas\\"><strong>Dueñas Palace</strong></a> (open from 10 am to 8 pm), which is sure to captivate you, a beautiful place with a lot of history. We?ll continue with a stroll through the Alameda and have a drink on a charming terrace like the one at the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#patioalameda\\"><strong>Patio de la Alameda hotel</strong></a> (closed on Mondays), or for something more bohemian: <a href=\\"#viajerosedentario\\"><strong>El Viajero Sedentario</strong></a>.</p><p>For dinner, if you enjoy flamenco, very close to the Basilica of Macarena, you have the <a href=\\"#torresmacarena\\"><strong>Peña Flamenca Torres Macarena</strong></a>, with a show and a charming terrace where you can have some tapas in a very Sevillian atmosphere. If you?re looking for something quieter in the area, a good option is <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#manololeonguadalquivir\\">Casa Manolo León (Guadalquivir)</a></strong>.</p>                	<p>To start the day off right, I recommend trying the typical Seville breakfast: a ?mollete? roll with olive oil, tomato, and ham, or some churros with chocolate. In the city center, you have several options like <a href=\\"#barelcomercio\\"><strong>Bar el Comercio</strong></a> in the Alfalfa area, or <a href=\\"#donacarmen\\"><strong>Doña Carmen</strong></a> near La Campana, which specializes in churros.</p><p>In the morning, you can visit the <a href=\\"#caac\\"><strong>Andalusian Center for Contemporary Art</strong></a>. This monastery, known as the Monastery of Santa María de las Cuevas, was founded in the 15th century as a community of Carthusian monks. Over the centuries, the monastery experienced periods of splendor and decline until it was abandoned in the 19th century. Today, it houses an impressive collection of Andalusian and Spanish contemporary art, spanning various disciplines such as painting, sculpture, photography, and video art.</p><p>If you prefer to stay in the city center, an option is the <a href=\\"#lebrija\\"><strong>Palace of the Countess of Lebrija</strong></a>. Its arches and courtyards will captivate you.</p><p>After this visit, we head to Triana, which, aside from its essential market, offers lesser-known spots for the general public. One such place is the secluded <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#plazuelasantaana\\">Plazuela de Santa Ana</a></strong>, where you can enjoy a drink at any of its terraces and visit its parish. Although it is well known, I cannot help but invite you to visit the <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#capilladelosmarineros\\">Capilla de los Marineros</a></strong> with the highly venerated image of the Esperanza de Triana.</p><p>For lunch in the area, I recommend <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#ruperto\\">Casa Ruperto</a></strong> where you can try their famous ?pajaritos? (fried quails) or their snails. Another option is the restaurant <a href=\\"#alfareria21\\"><strong>Alfarería 21</strong></a>, whose terrace is adorned with Triana pottery.</p><p>After lunch, you mustn?t miss trying the sweets from <a href=\\"#manujara\\"><strong>Manu Jara</strong></a> to bid farewell to Seville as it deserves. If, for some reason, you?re still here at dinner time, I recommend treating yourself at <a href=\\"#delao\\"><strong>Restaurante de la O</strong></a> and having a drink at <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#loladelosreyes\\"><strong>Lola de los Reyes</strong></a>, where the owner occasionally bursts into flamenco singing.</p><p>I recommend, as much as possible, making reservations in advance to ensure availability and checking opening hours and closing days so you don?t miss out on anything. You can find all the information at the points of interest.</p><p>Enjoy!</p>\t\t	381	cerveceria-giralda-sevilla.jpg	1225,1123,1113,1165,1112,1226,1227,1168,1228,1229,1230,1231	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	227,41,502,157,12,48,23,182,451,504,489,498,495,49,180,50,487,206,45,510,4,234,154,96,6,112,53,161,141,486,8	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=1yBPxNA1fCwLo13j3NwN1aoXIQ5KGJOA&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtJG4XfnFmIF	price_1Q2TJsAFILSEnUZXlx1usujY	1	N	N	Explore the corners that make Seville a fantastic city that never ceases to amaze you	\N	\N	Discover The Secret Seville	prod_Quos5a3EwU3PQj	price_1Q2zF4AFILSEnUZXwCsYaEFW		https://buy.stripe.com/test_28obLRf7D9K6e7m5n3		plink_1Q3AnpAFILSEnUZXahssKiA2	3Dias	18	N
382	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:12:06	2024-11-22 07:10:26	14299	2023-10-01 00:00:00	MAD09 FOTOGRAFIA	Explora, Captura y Comparte	explora-captura-y-comparte	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Un viaje fotográfico por el arte callejero y los rincones más fotogénicos</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nDescubre Madrid desde una perspectiva artística única, explorando conceptos digitales de vanguardia, lugares emblemáticos, saboreando restaurantes dignos de Instagram y sumergiéndote en el apasionante mundo del arte callejero. Una experiencia que recoge lo mejor de la ciudad en una aventura visual y gastronómica #MadridArtAndCulture	18	fotografomadrid2-2.jpg	2	<p>El primer día puedes empezar tomando un café en <a href=\\"#reina\\"><strong>El café de la reina</strong></a>, está en la plaza donde se encuentra el <a href=\\"#museosofia\\"><strong>Museo Reina Sofía</strong></a> es el lugar perfecto para tomar un café por la mañana o una copa por la tarde. Al lado tienes <a href=\\"#ikono\\"><strong>Ikono</strong></a>, un espacio donde tienes diferentes salas y escenarios creados por diferentes artistas locales, mezclando conceptos digitales y originales, perfectos para fotografiar y ser fotografiado en ellos.</p><p>Para comer podéis ir a <a href=\\"#ramses\\"><strong>Ramsés</strong></a> que está enfrente de la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#alcala\\"><strong>Puerta de Alcalá</strong></a> y el <a href=\\"#retiro\\"><strong>Parque del Retiro</strong></a>. Al terminar puedes dar un paseo por el parque o subir a la azotea del ayuntamiento y tomar algo.</p><p>Para tomar unas buenas fotos al atardecer os recomiendo ir al <a href=\\"#templodedebod\\"><strong>Templo de Debod,</strong></a> este lugar da mucho juego viendo el sol ponerse en el horizonte. También desde el mirador se puede ver el sol caer entre los edificios del templo. Después un paseo por la <a href=\\"#plazadeespana\\"><strong>Plaza de España</strong></a> y hasta <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#palacioreal\\"><strong>El Palacio Real</strong></a>.</p><p>Me encantan las ciudades de noche, si eres como yo coge tu cámara y pasea por la <a href=\\"#plazadelavilla\\"><strong>Plaza de la Villa</strong></a> (Pasadizo de la Plaza de la Villa).</p><p>Para cenar hay un lugar muy tradicional llamado <a href=\\"#casapipi\\"><strong>Casa Pipi</strong></a>, es un bar con tapas deliciosas (las albóndigas están riquísimas) otra opción es ir a <a href=\\"#lamayorcerveceria\\"><strong>La mayor cervecería</strong></a> (gran variedad de deliciosas cervezas de importación)</p>                	<p>Hoy puedes empezar el día tomando un café en el <a href=\\"#carmencitabrunch\\"><strong>brunch Carmencita</strong></a> en la c/ Doctor Fourquet o en la cafetería <a href=\\"#peyma\\"><strong>Peyma</strong></a> a 2 min de nuestro primer plan del día. En este último por la tarde es también un lugar donde se puede ir a tapear.</p><p>Para hoy os propongo un plan diferente dedicado al street art o fotografía callejera, la primera parada es en <a href=\\"#embaja\\"><strong>c/ embajadores</strong></a> 19, la siguiente parada será en la misma calle en el número 29, aquí hay un increíble graffiti en blanco y negro, después verás un increíble graffiti en 3D en el número 33.</p><p>De ahí podéis ir a comer al <a href=\\"#calcuta\\"><strong>Calcuta</strong></a> en la calle Lavapiés, se come genial y es comida 100% india.</p><p>Después de comer daremos un paseo hasta llegar a <a href=\\"#callao\\"><strong>Callao</strong></a>, si entras en el Corte Inglés tienes el gourmet en la última planta desde el que puedes hacer unas fotos preciosas de la Gran Vía.</p><p>Por la tarde, si quieres un plan diferente tienes que ir a <a href=\\"#wowconcept\\"><strong>Concepto Wow</strong></a> (dentro del centro comercial), es un lugar super llamativo perfecto para sesiones de fotos, lo mejor es solicitar vía mail el permiso para hacerlas.</p><p>Para cenar ir te recomiendo <a href=\\"#belmondo\\"><strong>Bel mondo</strong></a> en Velazquez y prueba sus deliciosas pizzas. Otra opción sería<strong> <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#tierraburritobar\\">Tierra Burrito bar</a> </strong>y comer comida típica mexicana.</p>                	<p>Para hoy te propongo desayunar en <a href=\\"#mur\\"><strong>Café Mur</strong></a>, cerca de la <a href=\\"#cubos\\"><strong>Plaza de los Cubos</strong></a> , bajar por la Gran Vía y subir al <a href=\\"#bellasartes\\"><strong>Círculo de Bellas Artes</strong></a>, con vistas panorámicas de 360 grados para mí las mejores de Madrid. En su terraza podrás tomar una copa o unas bravas, mientras disfrutas de las increíbles vistas y, por supuesto, hacer unas fotos espectaculares. Hay que pagar 5 euros para subir, pero merece la pena.</p><p>Puedes terminar en la nueva <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#plazaesp\\"><strong>Plaza España</strong></a> con las nuevas luces y el amplio espacio (perfecto para hacer fotos) y si te apetece subir al mirador del <a href=\\"#riu\\"><strong>H</strong><strong>otel Riu Plaza de España</strong> </a>(aunque es un poco caro subir merece la pena, cuesta 10 euros).</p><p>Si quieres salir de la capital te sugiero que cojas el tren de cercanías hasta Aranjuez, si es primavera u otoño los<a href=\\"#ara\\"> <strong>jardines del palacio de Aranjuez</strong></a> que son el escenario perfecto para unas buenas fotos, frente a los jardines tienes el ?<a href=\\"#mercado\\"><strong>Restaurante Patio del Mercado</strong></a>». También puedes coger el tren e ir al <a href=\\"#monasteriodelescorial\\"><strong>Monasterio del Escorial</strong></a>, la sierra de Madrid es muy bonita, si te quedas a comer allí hay un restaurante muy bueno que se llama <a href=\\"#llano\\"><strong>Bar Restaurante El Llano </strong></a>o si no en <a href=\\"#principe\\"><strong>Restaurante Parilla Principe</strong></a> buenas tapas, comida española, barata y con buen servicio.</p><p>De vuelta a Madrid terminamos con una copa en la azotea del hotel <a href=\\"#me\\"><strong>ME Madrid Reina Victoria</strong></a> en la Plaza Sta Ana, con unas preciosas vistas de la ciudad.</p><p>En Madrid cada rincón puede ser una fotografía para llevarse a casa, espero que te hayas quedado a gusto y por supuesto que vuelvas.</p>\t\t	382	fotografomadrid2-2.jpg	1232,1216,1233,1234,1235,1236,1237,1238,1213,1239,1137,1240	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	541,432,525,526,363,529,527,523,535,530,513,536,515,524,542,539,533,358,537,373,446,540,538,375,522,534,517,435,388,532	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=1aSyV5_BgdSXVuUbLY01Fltgx1NMtWR8&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtAC7zDapQOM	price_1Q2TJtAFILSEnUZXBgTOld7q	1	N	N	Un viaje fotográfico por el arte callejero y los rincones más fotogénicos	\N	\N	Explora, Captura y Comparte	prod_Quot9A09aTYKtO	price_1Q2zFRAFILSEnUZXMYXYfXCT		https://buy.stripe.com/test_aEU3fle3z6xU9R66r8		plink_1Q3AnqAFILSEnUZX8ebk6XY5	3Dias	19	N
383	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:12:20	2024-11-22 07:10:26	12715	2023-10-02 00:00:00	SV16 Glutenfree 3 days	Gluten Free	gluten-free	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Discover the city of Sevilla and savor its restaurants with gluten-free options</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nExperience an unforgettable adventure in Seville designed especially for travelers with celiac disease. Our exclusive gastronomic journey will lead you to discover carefully selected restaurants where you can savor delicious gluten-free options. Taste traditional Andalusian dishes and authentic tapas without worries. Seville awaits you with its charming streets, history, and gastronomy tailored to your needs. Turn your visit into a safe and delicious gastronomic journey, where every bite is a gluten-free adventure. Discover celiac-friendly Seville in a unique and flavorful way!	19	celiacos2.jpg	1	<p>We start our visit to Sevilla with a good breakfast at <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#alfonsito\\"><strong>Alfonsito Brunch café</strong></a> (where you can choose from a wide variety of gluten-free pastries and bread).</p><p>Or, if you prefer a 100% natural juice to take with you while you stroll, you have to stop by <a href=\\"#purafruta\\"><strong>Pura Fruta</strong></a>, in the Alfalfa district.</p><p>Our first day in Sevilla should be spent exploring its wonderful historic center. I recommend starting with the <a href=\\"#alcazar\\"><strong>Alcazar</strong></a>, then visiting the Cathedral, and taking a stroll through the Santa Cruz neighborhood.</p><p>For a gluten-free meal, I recommend: <a href=\\"#pasaje\\"><strong>El Pasaje de Santa María la Blanca</strong></a> (with a very nice inner courtyard and a menu that blends classic Sevillian and international tapas) or under the Metropol Parasol (las Setas), <a href=\\"#camballa\\"><strong>Camballá</strong></a>, which combines modernity with traditional cuisine.</p><p>If you&#8217;re looking for a more immersive experience, one option I recommend for dining today or any other day is to try <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#sazon\\">SAZÓN The Folk Cook</a></strong>, SAZON is the world\\ s first platform to provide Spanish food homely prepared by locals at their own houses, where you would taste it in complete privacy.</p><p>You can spend the afternoon shopping in the commercial area, on Tetuán Street and Sierpes Street (don&#8217;t miss <strong><a href=\\"#verbo\\">Verbo Bookstore</a></strong> on Sierpes Street, located in a former theater).</p><p>To end the day, I recommend going to the Arenal neighborhood and having dinner at <a href=\\"#postigo\\"><strong>Postigo 10</strong></a> (traditional Sevillian cuisine) or at <a href=\\"#petit\\"><strong>Petit Comité</strong></a> (creative cuisine inspired by French and Spanish influences), both with gluten-free options.</p><p>After dinner, you can enjoy an ice cream at <a href=\\"#mito\\"><strong>Gelateria Mito</strong></a>, authentic Italian ice cream that is 100% gluten-free. Or if you prefer, have a drink at <a href=\\"#maruja\\"><strong>Maruja Melón</strong></a>, on Paseo Colón.</p>                	<p>On our second day, we start at <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#orfeo\\"><strong>Orfeo Café</strong></a>, where they offer a wide variety of gluten-free cakes and breakfast options.</p><p>In the morning, we&#8217;re going to spend time exploring the second most important art gallery in the country, after the Prado Museum. We&#8217;re heading to the <a href=\\"#bellasartes\\"><strong>Fine Arts Museum of Sevilla</strong></a>, where you&#8217;ll find works by great painters like Murillo, Zurbarán, El Greco, and Velázquez, showcasing various artistic styles, including Sevillian Baroque. The building itself is a true work of art, once an ancient convent, and it features beautiful courtyards.</p><p>In the area, I recommend dining at <a href=\\"#tulipanes\\"><strong>Los Tulipanes</strong></a> (specializing in Dutch dishes, you&#8217;ll also find homemade Mediterranean tapas from our region) or at <a href=\\"#barra\\"><strong>Barra Baja</strong></a> (a market restaurant with fresh produce, seasonal vegetables, and fish from the Andalusian coast).</p><p>In the afternoon, I recommend going to <a href=\\"#setas\\"><strong>Metropol Parasol (Las Setas)</strong></a> or visiting the <a href=\\"#duenas\\"><strong>Dueñas Palace</strong></a>. You can stop for a coffee at <a href=\\"#mehl\\"><strong>Mehl café</strong></a> (they offer pastries and gluten-free bread) or at <a href=\\"#cremeria\\"><strong>Gioeila Cremería</strong></a> (they have various ice creams specifically marked as suitable for celiacs and others who can&#8217;t consume gluten).</p><p>I recommend spending the late afternoon in <a href=\\"#alameda\\"><strong>Alameda de Hércules</strong></a> and having dinner at <a href=\\"#grosso\\"><strong>Grosso Napoletano</strong></a> (spectacular and authentic Neapolitan pizza, 100% gluten-free) or at <a href=\\"#duo\\"><strong>Dúo Tapas</strong></a> (classic tapas in an informal yet chic bar with a menu for celiacs).</p>                	<p>On the last day, we&#8217;re going to explore the Nervión neighborhood. Start with a good breakfast at <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#ananas\\"><strong>Ananas Coffee Brunch</strong></a>. Then you can do some shopping at <a href=\\"#nervion\\"><strong>Nervión Plaza Shopping Center</strong></a>, or if you&#8217;re a football fan, swing by the <a href=\\"#futbol\\"><strong>Sevilla FC Stadium</strong></a>, the Sánchez Pizjuán. I also recommend taking a look at the <a href=\\"#buhaira\\"><strong>Buhaira Gardens</strong></a>, a garden next to the remains of an old Almohad palace and a large pool, now a civic center.</p><p>For gluten-free dining around here, you have <a href=\\"#gruta\\"><strong>Gruta Tapas</strong></a> (gluten-free, their menu is based on traditional Spanish meals) or <a href=\\"#chaparrita\\"><strong>La Chaparrita</strong></a> (authentic homemade Mexican cuisine, almost their entire menu is suitable for celiacs).</p><p>To spend the afternoon, you can take the metro and head to <a href=\\"#espana\\"><strong>Plaza de España</strong></a> (there are boats for a leisurely ride) and <a href=\\"#luisa\\"><strong>Maria Luisa Park</strong></a> (you can rent bicycles inside and tour the park).</p><p>Afterwards, I recommend crossing to the other side of the river to explore the neighborhoods of Los Remedios and Triana. If you&#8217;d like a snack, you have <a href=\\"#durazno\\"><strong>Durazno and Chajá</strong></a> pastry shop, specializing in gluten-free and lactose-free pastries.</p><p>In the Triana neighborhood, you can visit several churches like <a href=\\"#ana\\"><strong>Santa Ana</strong></a> or the <a href=\\"#marineros\\"><strong>Capilla de los Marineros</strong></a>, or explore the <a href=\\"#ceramica\\"><strong>Ceramics Center</strong></a>. For dinner, you have <a href=\\"#bahia\\"><strong>Freiduría Bahía</strong></a> (fried fish with gluten-free flour and seafood) or <a href=\\"#delao\\"><strong>Restaurante de la O</strong></a> (a magical place with a beautiful terrace by the Guadalquivir River).</p>\t\t	383	celiacos2.jpg	1241,1242,1226,1243,1244,1245,1246,1247,1248,1249	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	2,543,565,568,547,23,578,559,564,573,546,557,577,552,561,563,569,570,153,556,168,553,560,210,566,554,574,551,9,550,544,123,8,567,576,549	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=1NrDVPe_4DHKhh4xMuxxvc4JR5S3htT8&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHt8CzVapQb5k	price_1Q2TJtAFILSEnUZXI34ZBRAq	1	N	N	Discover the city of Sevilla and savor its restaurants with gluten-free options	\N	\N	Gluten Free	prod_QuoslzApvqkdEW	price_1Q2zF4AFILSEnUZXyOY7X8Yd	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_7sI2bhaRn6xUgfu16P	\N	plink_1Q3AnrAFILSEnUZXDfW0XJFX	3Dias	20	N
384	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:12:31	2024-11-22 07:10:26	12744	2023-10-02 00:00:00	SV17 Vintage 3 days	Vintage Seville	vintage-seville	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Enjoy the most vintage and retro side of Seville</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nGet ready for an exciting adventure in Sevilla as you uncover secondhand shops, collector\\ s spots, and charming markets. This experience will let you dive into the heart of Híspalis\\  capital from a unique perspective, where you\\ ll unearth hidden treasures, discover historical gems, and experience the city\\ s authentic charm. Join us on this journey filled with nostalgia and quirky finds as we explore the quirkiest corners of Sevilla. Perfect for travelers looking for a truly unique adventure!\\r\\n\\r\\n&nbsp;	20	flamingos-vintage-kilo.png	1	<p>The first day starts in the most alternative area of Sevilla, the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#setas\\"><strong>Metropol Parasol</strong></a> (Las Setas). A great place to begin the route is on <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#regina\\"><strong>Regina Street</strong></a>, a street reinvented in recent years, where you can find craft shops, clothing stores, cafes, restaurants&#8230; We recommend having a hearty breakfast to get your energy up at <a href=\\"#cacharreria\\"><strong>La Cacharrería</strong></a>, you&#8217;ll love its atmosphere, decoration, breakfasts, brunch, juices, and cakes?</p><p>We continue down the street and reach Feria Street, one of the liveliest streets in the city, where traditional neighborhood stores mix with modern shops. Moreover, if you come on a Thursday, you&#8217;ll experience the street in all its glory with the <a href=\\"#jueves\\"><strong>historic antique market &#8220;El Jueves</strong></a>.&#8221; Here&#8217;s a list of shops to visit: for clothing, there&#8217;s <a href=\\"#wonder\\"><strong>Wonder Vintage</strong></a>, Nonna´s Vintage,, Ropero, Antro Vintage, Pipa Vintage<b>?</b>; for books, there&#8217;s <a href=\\"#baena\\"><strong>Baena Bookstore</strong></a>&#8230; You can take your time and have a wonderful day in the area.</p><p>A must-visit is the <a href=\\"#feria\\"><strong>Mercado de Feria</strong></a>, where you&#8217;ll find a traditional market for fruits, vegetables, meat, and fish. You can also grab a bite at <a href=\\"#jaleo\\"><strong>Jaleo Guadalquibeer</strong></a>. Just behind here, you can visit the <a href=\\"#algaba\\"><strong>Marqueses de la Algaba Palace</strong></a> or the <a href=\\"#luis\\"><strong>Monumental Ensemble of Saint Louis of the French</strong></a>. For lunch in the area, I recommend &#8220;<a href=\\"#ambigu\\"><strong>El Ambigú</strong></a>.&#8221;</p><p>If you&#8217;re looking for a more immersive experience, one option I recommend for dining today or any other day is to try <a href=\\"#sazon\\"><b>SAZÓN The Folk Cook</b></a>, SAZON is the world\\ s first platform to provide Spanish food homely prepared by locals at their own houses, where you would taste it in complete privacy.</p><p>And for retro video game enthusiasts, you have to stop by <a href=\\"#arcade\\"><strong>Arcade Bar</strong></a>, where you can play arcade machines, board games, have snacks, and enjoy various types of beer. For dinner, I suggest heading to the Alameda. You can go to <a href=\\"#antojo\\"><strong>Bar Antojo</strong></a>. And for a drink, you can enjoy one of the terraces in the square, like <a href=\\"#azul\\"><strong>Casa Azul</strong></a>.</p>                	<p>Today, we start the day at the Cathedral. Right across from it, you have one of Sevilla&#8217;s hidden charming spots, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#cabildo\\"><strong>Plaza del Cabildo</strong></a>. In this beautiful semicircular square, you&#8217;ll find several interesting and curious shops like <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#ortega\\"><strong>Lola Ortega Antique Shop</strong></a> or <a href=\\"#felix\\"><strong>Poster Felix</strong></a>. Additionally, if you come on a Sunday, you can find a coin and <a href=\\"#stamp\\"><strong>stamp collecting market</strong></a>. </p><p>From here, we&#8217;ll head down Postigo del Aceite, towards the Arenal neighborhood. Here, I recommend checking out the <a href=\\"#postigo\\"><strong>El Postigo Crafts Market</strong></a>. Next, we&#8217;ll walk to Plaza del Salvador, where you can find the second-hand clothing stores <a href=\\"#moda\\"><strong>Moda-re</strong></a> and <a href=\\"#peninsula\\"><strong>Península Vintage</strong></a>. You can also visit the charming second-hand bookstore <a href=\\"#boteros\\"><strong>Boteros</strong></a>. For lunch in this area, I recommend the restaurant <a href=\\"#sal\\"><strong>Sal Gorda</strong></a>. </p><p>Then, we&#8217;ll walk down Sierpes Street to reach Amor de Dios Street, where you have the <a href=\\"#read\\"><strong>Re-Read bookstore</strong></a>, and the classic record stores <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#latimore\\"><strong>Latimore</strong></a> and Record Sevilla. We&#8217;ll conclude our shopping route on San Eloy Street to visit the clothing store <a href=\\"#mosaico\\"><strong>Mosaico</strong></a>, you&#8217;re sure to find a surprise or a bargain. You can end the day by having a drink or dinner on the terrace of <a href=\\"#justa\\"><strong>Justa y Rufina</strong></a>.</p>                	<p>Today, we&#8217;ll stay on the other side of the river, in Los Remedios and Triana. I recommend having breakfast at <a href=\\"#valle\\"><strong>Café del Valle</strong></a>.</p><p>You can visit the antique shop <a href=\\"#desvan\\"><strong>El Desván de Bartleby</strong></a> and stroll down the traditional Pagés del Corro street, and explore <a href=\\"#overtime\\"><strong>Overtime</strong></a>, which specializes in antiques and collectibles. If you come on the weekend, don&#8217;t miss the <a href=\\"#delao\\"><strong>Art Market on Paseo de la O</strong></a>. I would stop for a drink or have lunch at <a href=\\"#plazuela\\"><strong>Taberna la Plazuela</strong></a> or at the <a href=\\"#triana\\"><strong>Triana Market</strong></a>.</p><p>In the afternoon, you can visit the <a href=\\"#ceramica\\"><strong>Triana Ceramic Center</strong></a>. We&#8217;ll take Castilla Street, where you&#8217;ll find another spot for collectors, <a href=\\"#cecilio\\"><strong>Coleccionismo Don Cecilio</strong></a>. You can end the afternoon by grabbing a drink on Betis Street, for example at <a href=\\"#prensa\\"><strong>La Prensa de Triana</strong></a>, and have dinner on San Jacinto Street at <a href=\\"#valiente\\"><strong>La Valiente</strong></a>.</p>\t\t	384	flamingos-vintage-kilo.png	\N	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	592,591,584,601,594,607,614,589,608,598,585,582,586,606,233,593,611,615,616,153,604,595,587,599,4,605,609,610,600,596,603,580,602,8,597,576,612,583	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/6/embed?mid=1N6XK9QoureIbXOdjb40-BOl4MBUfAzg&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHt7VVQoV5pO7	price_1Q2TJuAFILSEnUZXROa1t83r	1	N	N	Enjoy the most vintage and retro side of Seville	\N	\N	Vintage Seville	prod_QuosyKKegTgQl7	price_1Q2zF5AFILSEnUZXWWVoJp2y	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_00g3fl0cJbSeaVaaHq	\N	plink_1Q3AnrAFILSEnUZXB5ph3TQB	3Dias	21	N
385	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:12:40	2024-11-22 07:10:26	14298	2023-09-29 00:00:00	MAD05 LGTBI	Una aventura llena de color en Chueca	una-aventura-llena-de-color-en-chueca	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Momentos de color en Chueca disfrutando de la comunidad LGTBIQ+ de la capital</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nSumérgete en Chueca, el corazón LGBTQ+ de la ciudad, en una experiencia llena de color y diversidad. Descubra tiendas únicas con productos que celebran la diversidad, desde la moda al arte. Deléitese con una gastronomía que refleja los sabores y colores de la comunidad. Sumérjase en la vida nocturna de emblemáticos locales y disfrute de emocionantes espectáculos. Una invitación a vivir plenamente la cultura LGBTQ+, donde el amor, la diversidad y la autenticidad se celebran a lo grande.	21	lgtbi-1.jpg	2	<p>Para empezar os propongo desayunar en <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#carmencitabar\\">Bar Carmencita</a></strong> una buena opción para un brunch por la mañana, también podéis visitar el <a href=\\"#mercadosananton\\"><strong>Mercado de San Antón</strong></a> donde se puede subir a la terraza a tomar algo y disfrutar de las bonitas vistas de la ciudad. Para comer, recomendamos el <a href=\\"#vivares\\"><strong>Restaurante Vivares</strong></a> un clásico de Chueca que no falla. Si quieres vivir el ambiente LGTBI, te sugiero que deis un paseo hasta la <a href=\\"#pedroz\\"><strong>Plaza Pedro Zerolo</strong>,</a> comer algo en &#8220;<strong><a href=\\"#polleria\\">La Pollería»</a></strong> allí venden unos dulces muy originales. Si os gusta el arte contemporáneo, ir a <a href=\\"#madismad\\"><strong>Mad is Mad </strong></a> y si os gusta más la fotografía, podéis ir a <a href=\\"#yellowkorner\\"><strong>Yellowkorner.</strong></a></p><p>Para cenar, sugiero <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#mordida\\">&#8220;La mordida»</a></strong>, este tiene comida mexicana super rica, el bar es muy agradable y colorido. Cerca teneis la opción de comer en <a href=\\"#economato\\"><strong>el Economato</strong></a> este último es una buena opción si quereis comer comida española. Después y para subir el tono del día puedes visitar algunos bares como <a href=\\"#mystic\\"><strong>D&#8217;Mystic </strong></a>o<strong><a href=\\"#kama\\"> La Kama</a>.</strong></p>                	<p>Para el segundo día os propongo comenzar con un desayuno brunch en <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#brunchqueen\\">Drag Queen Brunch &amp; Bingo </a></strong>es un lugar ideal. Se trata de un divertido brunch drag, para disfrutar de unas copas, varias actuaciones drag, bingo y, por supuesto, una deliciosa comida. Por la tarde te sugiero que vayas a <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#espaciodulce\\">Sweet Space</a></strong><strong> </strong>(es un museo interactivo donde vivir una experiencia diferente). Después puedes ir a tomar un café a <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#faraday\\"><strong>Faraday</strong></a> además de cafetería tienen discos de vinilo y un rollo muy hípster. Si te apetece un rollo más cultural, el <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#musroman\\">Museo del Romanticismo</a></strong> es genial. Para la noche os sugiero que comais algo en <a href=\\"#ficus\\"><strong>Bar Ficus</strong></a> y luego empecéis la fiesta. No dudéis y pasaros por <a href=\\"#whynot\\"><strong>Why not?</strong></a> o <a href=\\"#loca\\"><strong>Vuelvete Loca</strong></a></p>                	<p style=\\"text-align: left;\\">Para hoy te propongo una mañana de compras en el centro de Chueca. Podéis empezar en Berkana, Amantis, SR Leather Shop, City, Rotunda Warning, Socks Market. Después de una mañana de compras ir a tomar un brunch en &#8220;<a href=\\"#desayuneria\\"><strong>La desayuneria</strong></a>».<br />Por la tarde un café en &#8220;<a href=\\"#caracola\\"><strong>la caracola</strong></a>&#8221; imprescindible probar la tarta de pistacho.<br />Pero si buscáis algo más específico existe el <a href=\\"#llbar\\"><strong>Bar LL</strong></a> con un espectáculo drag o «<a href=\\"#cazador\\"><strong>El Cazador</strong></a>&#8221; que es un bar especial para hipsters gays.<br />¿Sois amantes de los clásicos? Entonces el lugar ideal para visitar es<a href=\\"#blackandwhite\\"><strong> Black &amp; White</strong></a>. Para terminar el plan LGBTI en Madrid ir a<a href=\\"#boyberry\\"><strong> Boyberry</strong> </a>uno de los bares de cruising gay más populares de la ciudad, que se divide en zona de juegos, Glory hole, spy holes, cabinas y hasta un cuarto oscuro. Y, por si fuera poco, tiene una tienda donde venden diferentes accesorios y material que os puede interesar.</p>\t\t	385	lgtbi-1.jpg	1250,1251,1252,1178,1253,1254,1255,1256,1257,1258	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	617,632,639,640,628,626,638,625,352,636,635,627,351,621,637,348,618,631,620,619,431,634,633,349	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=13JsyZsjHS1QQveg5GOEs2x6sn58nkis&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHt5GUR9Jw5Br	price_1Q2TJuAFILSEnUZXstqZsJcw	1	N	N	Momentos de color en Chueca disfrutando de la comunidad LGTBIQ+ de la capital	\N	\N	Una aventura llena de color en Chueca	prod_Quot9xroW1jWUy	price_1Q2zFRAFILSEnUZXRoRcVzmj	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_3csg270cJg8u2oEdTD	\N	plink_1Q3AnsAFILSEnUZXbB24SKY6	3Dias	22	N
386	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:12:50	2024-11-22 07:10:26	14529	2023-10-01 00:00:00	MAD13 - HEALTHYANDRUN	Zen y Salud	zen-y-salud	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Escapa del caos y sumérjete en una vida sana, relajación y delicias culinarias</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nDescubre en Madrid una experiencia centrada en el bienestar, la salud, el sabor y la relajación. Disfruta de opciones gastronómicas veganas y saludables en varios restaurantes. Relájate en los balnearios y participa en actividades como yoga y patinaje sobre ruedas. Explora experiencias creativas como Arte y Vino. Termina tus días con cenas gourmet. Madrid ofrece mucho más que bullicio y tráfico.	22	pexels-pixabay-235922.jpg	2	<p>Comenzaremos nuestra experiencia con un desayuno muy especial en <a href=\\"#frutasprohibidas\\"><strong>Frutas Prohibidas</strong></a> donde podrás encontrar una amplia oferta en desayunos y bruch para veganos. Prueba sus huevos Benedict en una de sus tres versiones. </p><p>Aproveche la oportunidad para visitar el <a href=\\"#cuartelcondeduque\\"><strong>Cuartel del Conde-Duque</strong></a> un imponente centro cultural, antiguo edificio militar, que acoge siempre una interesante oferta de danza, teatro, exposiciones y museos, hoy convertido en un referente de la cultura contemporánea en la capital.</p><p>Para comer <a href=\\"#sanissimo\\"><strong>Sanissimo Opera Vegan</strong></a> en el corazón del barrio de la Ópera y muy cerca del <a href=\\"#palacioreal\\"><strong>Palacio Real</strong></a> una bonita zona de la ciudad para pasear.</p><p>Dos opciones para esta tarde, una más zen que empezaría en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#eleggua\\"><strong>Eleggua</strong></a> Te fascinará esta tienda si te gusta el feng shui, la meditación, la aromaterapia o el poder de los minerales y luego el yoga en el<a href=\\"#retiro\\"> <strong>Retiro</strong></a> con <a href=\\"#buhozen\\"><strong>Buhozen</strong></a> asociación que practica el yoga y la meditación, donde todo el mundo es bienvenido y no es necesario reservar. Sólo tienes que consultar su página web para conocer los horarios exactos y la ubicación, http://www.buhozen.org/. Realmente una experiencia muy reparadora, en pleno centro de Madrid y en contacto con la naturaleza. Y otro ajuste en <a href=\\"#rollingdanceandburger\\"><strong>Rolling Dance and Burger</strong></a> una espectacular pista de patinaje al más puro estilo americano, con música y restaurante. </p><p>Si has ido a patinar y no has \\"pecado\\" con un hot dog, puedes cenar en <a href=\\"#honestgreen\\"><strong>Honest Green</strong></a> , donde su comida sin gluten es de origen local y responsable, acompaña tu plato con el hummus de la semana. </p>                	<p>Propongo para hoy una ruta en bicicleta por el <a href=\\"#anillo\\"><strong>Anillo Verde Ciclista</strong></a> una ruta circular de 65 km que bordea toda la zona urbana de la ciudad. Puedes alquilar una bicicleta en <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#rentandrollmadrid\\">Rent and Roll Madrid</a>, </strong><a href=\\"#mybikerio\\"><strong>Mi bici Río</strong></a> y hacer parte o toda la ruta dependiendo de tu forma física.</p><p>Después del paseo y para reponer fuerzas <a href=\\"#vegaalamo\\"><strong>Vega Álamo</strong></a> donde tiene su cocina ecológica-vegana abierto desde las 13.30 hasta las 00.00, ininterrumpidamente. No te pierdas los tacos heura, ¡seas vegano o no! o también puede optar por la comida italiana en <a href=\\"#nap\\"><strong>NAP</strong></a> para disfrutar de unas pizzas estupendas con una excelente relación calidad-precio.</p><p>Y es hora de cuidarse, de relajarse, ahora es el momento en <a href=\\"#hammanalandalus\\"><strong>Hammam Al Ándalus</strong></a> donde tienes multitud de masajes y baños, en pleno centro de Madrid o en <a href=\\"#spa\\"><strong>el Spa Eurostars Tower</strong></a> con circuitos termales, masajes y tratamientos con impresionantes vistas al Skyline de Madrid. En ambos debes echar un vistazo a su oferta y reservar, ¡tú decides!</p><p>En la cena, y para seguir en las nubes, tómese un pincho de salmón flambeado en <a href=\\"#healthypoke\\"><strong>Poke saludable</strong></a>, o cualquiera de sus pokes o ensaladas, además tienes varios locales así que tienes uno cerca seguro. También tienes <a href=\\"#revuelta\\"><strong>C</strong><strong>asa Revuelta</strong></a>, no es el sitio mas sano pero tienen una gran variedad de tapas y hacen un balacalo que esta delicioso. Es un sitio mitico en madrid que no te puedes perder.</p>                	<p>Para nuestro tercer día vamos a desayunar en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#brunch\\"><strong>Café Green Bakery y Brunch</strong></a>, un lugar precioso donde vivir una auténtica experiencia realfooder, con oferta vegana y deliciosos zumos.<br />Si te apetece caminar te sugiero<a href=\\"#centrodeocio\\"> <strong>Centro de Ocio y Deporte Tercer Depósito Canal de Isabel II</strong></a>.<br />Para comer tienes una opción cercana que es <a href=\\"#bio\\"><strong>Restaurante Ecocentro | Bio Vegetariano</strong></a> o también <a href=\\"#run\\"><strong>Cafe RUN RUN RUN</strong></a> (un lugar diseñado para corredores) si necesitas algún suplemento deportivo cerca tienes una tienda. Por la tarde te propongo una actividad diferente <a href=\\"#art\\"><strong>Arte y Vino</strong></a> en la que podrás pintar un cuadro y tomar una copa de vino, pasarás un rato divertido y entretenido, haciendo algo diferente. Consulte su propuesta aquí: https://artwine.es/calendario-de-reservas/madrid/<br />Para cenar propongo<a href=\\"#perrachica\\"><strong> Perrachica</strong></a> moderno restaurante industrial chic o <a href=\\"#sagaretxe\\"><strong>Sagaretxe</strong></a> pinchos vascos y platos de pescado con terraza a pie de calle.</p>\t\t	386	pexels-pixabay-235922.jpg	1259,1260,1261,1262,1263,1264,1265,1266,1267,1268	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	650,663,647,659,662,658,660,642,645,641,433,649,652,654,373,446,664,657,651,661,648,643,665,656,653	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=1OoNoT6ERBCFyRsdkxZPXKu5V3Gb5gFc&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtC9NBAf3uHj	price_1Q2TJvAFILSEnUZXE7bN1dzQ	1	N	N	Escapa del caos y sumérjete en una vida sana, relajación y delicias culinarias	\N	\N	Zen y Salud	prod_QuotBM4LpTNUIP	price_1Q2zFSAFILSEnUZXWIwbSWrR	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_4gw2bhe3z9K6d3i8zk	\N	plink_1Q3AnsAFILSEnUZXSV73FmB1	3Dias	23	N
387	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:12:59	2024-11-22 07:10:26	14297	2023-10-04 00:00:00	MAD10 OTAKU	Pasion Otaku	pasion-otaku	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Sumérgete en el mundo otaku de Madrid</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nExplore las librerías de manga, saboree los mejores sabores japoneses y descubra las tiendas de cosplay que encantan a los entusiastas del país del sol naciente	23	pexels-pushpendra-pal-15138928-1-1.jpg	2	<p>Empecemos nuestra experiencia yendo al <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#otaku\\"><strong>Centro Otaku</strong></a> un auténtico santuario del coleccionismo para los aficionados al manga, en pleno barrio de Malasaña y muy cerca de la Gran Vía madrileña. Allí podrás encontrar figuras, cómics, merchandising original y un sinfín de material procedente de Japón. Merece la pena ir con tiempo para perderse en sus estanterías, porque al principio puede parecer una tienda pequeña, pero verás que hay mucho que ver.</p><p>Tras el obligado paseo por la <a href=\\"#granvia\\"><strong>Gran Vía,</strong></a> os recomiendo comer en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sushi\\"><strong>Running Sushi en Akihabara</strong></a>, un restaurante con buffet en cinta transportadora y una decoración espectacular, que no te dejará indiferente, eso sí, debes reservar, ya que está bastante solicitado.</p><p>Después de comer y ya que estás por la zona, visita la<a href=\\"#espana\\"><strong> Plaza de España</strong></a> recientemente renovada, el Palacio Real y <a href=\\"#mayor\\"><strong>la Plaza Mayor,</strong></a> lugares emblemáticos de la ciudad. Junto a la Plaza Mayor se encuentra el <a href=\\"#cafe\\"><strong>Café Kawaii</strong></a> , un local dedicado a la cultura kawaii y donde podrás tomar un tentempié con un toque cosplay, ya que tienen diademas, varitas, gafas&#8230; y sentirte como un niño, muy recomendables sus tortitas decoradas.</p><p>Para el plan de tarde-noche, camine hasta <a href=\\"#sol\\"><strong>Puerta del Sol</strong></a> y toda la zona del km 0, con abundantes tiendas de todo tipo y cena en <a href=\\"#japan\\"><strong>Livin&#8217;Japan</strong></a>, cerca de la Plaza de Antón Martín, donde además de sentirte como en Japón, podrás cenar leyendo algún manga de su colección, a disposición de los clientes. Y no te pierdas las albóndigas y pasteles de pollo, ¡deliciosos!</p>                	<p>Para el segundo día, desayuno en <a href=\\"#hanabusa\\"><strong>Pastelería Hanabusa</strong></a>, en el mercado Antón Martín, prueba su té matcha y sus mochis de frutas, un 10.</p><p>Subiendo por la calle Atocha, pasado el hermoso Teatro Calderón, nos encontramos con la <a href=\\"#x\\"><strong>Generación X</strong></a> un espacio único dedicado no sólo al universo otaku, sino también al cómic en general y a los juegos de mesa. Allí seguro que encuentra ese regalo especial para alguien, ¡o para usted!</p><p><a href=\\"#mikado\\"><strong>Restaurante Mikado</strong></a> esa es mi propuesta para comer hoy, el primer restaurante japonés de la capital, abierto en 1968 y pionero en la cocina japonesa. Parada obligada si vienes a Madrid y te gusta la comida japonesa, es auténtica. Se puede llegar en metro, está a unos 30 minutos del centro y es aconsejable reservar. Una vez allí, déjese aconsejar, todo es exquisito.</p><p>Por la tarde, otro lugar que no debe perderse es <a href=\\"#gion\\"><strong>Gion</strong></a>, una tienda de moda, regalos y decoración, nueva y vintage, traída de Japón, en el <a href=\\"#chueca\\"><strong>Barrio de Chueca</strong></a>, donde un paseo por la calle Almirante, Fuencarral o la plaza de Chueca es más que necesario.Volviendo a la zona centro, en la misma calle Preciados encontramos un local, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#kon\\"><strong>Konnichiwa</strong></a>, donde podrás cenar como si estuvieras en una calle japonesa, con decoración Izakaya, muy lograda y con un ambiente agradable. Pida su takoyaki u okonomiyaki, este último para compartir.</p>                	<p>Mi recomendación para el tercer día es fuera de Madrid centro, a menos de media hora, pero merece mucho la pena. La primera parada es el <a href=\\"#bonsai\\"><strong>Museo del Bonsái</strong></a> . Allí encontrará una de las mejores colecciones de bonsáis fuera de Japón, cuidada al detalle, una experiencia zen.</p><p>Para comer, en la misma calle tienes <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#silk\\">Seda La Moraleja</a></strong>, un espacio multifuncional, con terraza, zona de tapas, copas, con decoración oriental y cocina de fusión, española y japonesa. Allí tienes que probar la tortilla de patata con trufa, habrás probado otras, pero no como esta. Si aún tienes tiempo, también puedes tomarte allí una copa después de cenar, como ya he dicho, es un lugar muy especial.</p><p>Si lo que quieres es volver a Madrid, te sugiero que comas en un restaurante que me encanta, es pequeño con una comida que te transporta al Japón más auténtico. Se llama <a href=\\"#naomi\\"><strong>Naomi</strong></a>. Ya tendrás casi todo el Madrid japonés así que si quieres puedes recorrer el Paseo de la Castellana y visitar el <a href=\\"#museo\\"><strong>Museo de Ciencia</strong><strong>s</strong></a><a href=\\"#museo\\"><strong> Naturales</strong></a>.</p><p>Estas son mis sugerencias para una escapada japonesa a Madrid. También te sugiero un par de sitios de té de burbujas, muy de moda ahora, para mi son los mejores, y que puedes ir tomando mientras paseas por la ciudad, son <br /><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#le\\"><strong>Le.cha</strong></a> y<a href=\\"#i\\"><strong> I Sweet</strong></a>.</p>\t\t	387	pexels-pushpendra-pal-15138928-1-1.jpg	1269,1270,1271,1272,1273,1274,1275,1276,1277,1278	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	678,671,666,675,677,667,685,679,684,673,683,680,682,674,375,670,672,676,681,668	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=1NRUlKtZCJDQIIpnGleNZb0muyN0PcXE&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtcX7OZ10nyu	price_1Q2TJvAFILSEnUZX66g2OE9z	1	N	N	Sumérgete en el mundo otaku de Madrid	\N	\N	Pasion Otaku	prod_QuotWrAKq3VfCw	price_1Q2zFSAFILSEnUZXqGYc1J1l	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_14k9DJ0cJbSebZe02P	\N	plink_1Q3AntAFILSEnUZX2mPnhT28	3Dias	24	N
388	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:13:08	2024-11-22 07:10:26	14296	2023-10-05 00:00:00	MAD04 CINE	Una aventura de cine	una-aventura-de-cine	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Disfruta del séptimo arte en madrid</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nVive una experiencia cinematográfica inolvidable en Madrid. El argumento de esta aventura le sumergirá en una emocionante película, todo ello mientras saborea deliciosas tapas en una acogedora sala de cine. La mezcla de cultura y entretenimiento hará que su estancia en Madrid sea absolutamente perfecta.	24	platea-1.jpg	2	<p>Comenzamos nuestra experiencia y qué mejor manera de hacerlo que en la mismísima Academia de las Artes y las Ciencias Cinematográficas, en su <a href=\\"#cafedelaacademia\\"><strong>Café de la Academia</strong></a>, donde podrás tomar un delicioso desayuno rodeado de un ambiente acogedor y multitud de guiños cinematográficos. Aproveche la oportunidad para conocer las actividades que allí se desarrollan.</p><p>Para continuar el día te propongo hacer la ruta Madrid de Almodóvar, nombrado hijo adoptivo de la ciudad en 2018, donde podrás visitar diferentes escenarios de sus películas y que, si eres fan de su cine, reconocerás perfectamente. Puedes encontrar toda la información en cualquier punto de información turística de la ciudad o descargarte el mapa de su página web; https://www.esmadrid.com/madrid-de-almodovar.También puedes entrar en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#carpetaniatour\\"><strong>Carpetania tour</strong></a> y apuntarte a tu tour Almodóvar.</p><p>Para comer dos propuestas diferentes, <a href=\\"#camerino\\"><strong>Camerino</strong></a>, un restaurante con aire cinematográfico donde la decoración e incluso la presentación de los platos están inspirados en películas, o <a href=\\"#comicplanet\\"><strong>Comic Planet</strong></a>, ambientado en el mundo del cómic. Si te apasionan los superhéroes, no te vayas sin visitarlo entero, es un auténtico museo. Es importante reservar porque suele estar muy concurrido.</p><p>Por la tarde también hay dos opciones, <strong><a href=\\"#autocinemadrid\\">Autocine Madrid</a></strong>, donde podrás disfrutar de una película como si fueras el protagonista de GREASE, podrás disfrutar de comida y bebida en sus gastrotetas y del espectacular skyline de Madrid, tan cinematográfico o <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#cineembajadores\\"><strong>Embajadores cine</strong></a>, una apuesta moderna de cine de barrio con una cartelera de películas muy variada.</p>                	<p style=\\"padding-left: 40px;\\">Para este segundo día, haga una primera parada en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#libreria8ymedio\\"><strong>Librería 8 y medio,</strong></a> situada muy cerca de Plaza España, rodeada por el <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#golem\\">Golem</a></strong> y <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#renoir\\"><strong>Cines Renoir</strong></a>, los mejores cines de Madrid con la mejor oferta de películas en V.O. y en pleno <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#paseodelafama\\"><strong>paseo de la fama</strong></a>. Es un lugar para hablar, pensar y leer sobre cine, mientras se toma un café. <br />Estando en Madrid y siendo amante del cine, no puedes perderte el <a href=\\"#cinedore\\"><strong>Cine Doré</strong></a> un precioso edificio modernista donde se proyectan películas de la Filmoteca Nacional y puedes comer justo al lado en el <a href=\\"#mercadoantonmartin\\"><strong>Mercado de Antón Martín</strong></a>, con una gran variedad de puestos de comida y comida internacional. Al lado se encuentra el <a href=\\"#cineideal\\"><strong>Cine Ideal</strong></a>, el cine más antiguo de Madrid.<br />Por la tarde, visitar la <a href=\\"#salaequis\\"><strong>Sala Equis</strong></a>, el último cine X de Madrid convertido en un lugar donde ver películas, comer algo o tomar una copa, en un ambiente urbano y cosmopolita. Puedes quedarte allí para la sobremesa o hacer el recorrido para ver Escenarios de series y cine.<br />Y si hablamos de lugares con historia los más emblemáticos de la capital, que han sido escenarios de películas, series y visitados por estrellas nacionales e internacionales, sin duda estamos hablando de <a href=\\"#museochicote\\"><strong>Museo Chicote</strong></a>, donde se puede cenar, tomar un cóctel antes o después de ir a ver un musical de toda la oferta que ofrece la Gran Vía madrileña, ya que está abierto hasta las 3.00.</p>                	<p style=\\"padding-left: 40px;\\">Seguro que hoy vas a necesitar empezar con energía después de 2 días intensos, The<a href=\\"#gardenbrunchcafe\\"> <strong>Garden Brunch Café</strong></a> es el lugar, parece sacado de BARBIE y tanto si eres de desayunos dulces como si eres más de salados, allí no tendrás excusa porque tienen de todo. Abierto a partir de las 9.30 h.<br />Si eres fan de Harry Potter no puedes perderte una tienda de más de 200m2, con ropa, libros o coleccionables, dedicada en exclusiva al mágico mundo de J.K. Rowling, <a href=\\"#callejonmondriagon\\"><strong>Callejón Madriagon</strong></a> que se encuentra a unos 30 minutos del centro de Madrid.<br />Otra experiencia cinematográfica, si tus gustos son más de clásicos italianos, es <a href=\\"#belmondo\\"><strong>Bel Mondo</strong></a> un restaurante italiano con una atmósfera de &#8220;dolce vita&#8221; total que te hará sentir como si estuvieras en la costa de Amalfi con Tom Ripley o en una película de Fellini. Prueba su tarta de queso, una de las mejores que hayas probado.Por la noche también te sugiero que vayais al <a href=\\"#circulobellasartes\\"><strong>Círculo de Bellas Artes</strong></a> la visita a este lugar es muy completa porque por un lado puedes descubrir exposiciones y una oferta cultural muy amplia y también puedes subir a la terraza, disfrutar de este lugar mágico con unas vistas de película. Si prefiere otro lugar también puede ir a <a href=\\"#platea\\"><strong>Platea</strong></a>, un antiguo teatro reconvertido en espacio gourmet donde comer, escuchar música y disfrutar situado en el centro de Madrid.</p>\t\t	388	platea-1.jpg	1279,1280,1281,1282,1283,1284,1285	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	690,432,686,702,688,687,696,691,698,693,535,370,701,692,697,700,695,705,694,699	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=1LXFx4LxW-Aw3BtecEKMWRZp6nWdA8eA&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtIKlZlnTVUr	price_1Q2TJwAFILSEnUZXfaRNzHVe	1	N	N	Disfruta del séptimo arte en madrid	\N	\N	Una aventura de cine	prod_QuotQbDQjwSx5r	price_1Q2zFTAFILSEnUZXYJopR91k	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_fZedTZ4sZf4qaVa7vi	\N	plink_1Q3AnuAFILSEnUZXaoz5pu00	3Dias	25	N
389	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:13:17	2024-11-22 07:10:26	13911	2023-10-03 00:00:00	MAD16 pets	Pets Lovers	pets-lovers	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Take your dog to the best places and enjoy your experience with him</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nDiscover pet-friendly places to have a great time together. With the host\\ s recommendations, you can spend a weekend in the capital and take your pet everywhere. They deserve a little getaway too!	25	WhatsApp-Image-2023-09-21-at-23.56.24-1.jpeg	2	<p>To start I suggest <a href=\\"#cafemur\\"><strong>Mür Café,</strong></a> coffee and cocktail bar, rustic and industrial aesthetics, with homemade cakes made with delicious natural products, there are also dog cookies available.near you have the country house that is also super good for your dog to play.then you can go to <a href=\\"#madridrio\\"><strong>Madrid Rio</strong></a>, there is an area enabled for dogs to play and have a great time. Nearby there is vaery nice dog groomer calles <a href=\\"#amable\\"><strong>Amable</strong></a>. <br />A good place to eat and petsfiendly is the <a href=\\"#bartoboggan\\"><strong>Toboggan bar,</strong></a> if you want to go back to the center you can go through the latina and stop for example at <a href=\\"#casalucas\\"><strong>Casa Lucas</strong></a>, <a href=\\"#lamiak\\"><strong>lamiak,</strong></a> <a href=\\"#lalina\\"><strong>lalina</strong></a> in the plaza de la cebada.</p><p>In the afternoon I suggest <a href=\\"#visti\\"><strong>the garden of the vistillas</strong></a> and the<strong><a href=\\"#jardinsanfrancisco\\"> gardens of San Francisco,</a></strong> very close is the Church of San Francisco is baroque and one of the most beautiful. A walk through the part of Madrid de los Austrias I recommend you to go to <a href=\\"#eljardindelconvento\\"><strong>the garden of the convent</strong></a> to buy sweets.<br />For dinner at night I suggest going to the area of Cuzco to dine at the restaurant <a href=\\"#donatecla\\"><strong>Doña Tecla</strong></a>, a restaurant in the center of the city with a large terrace.</p>                	<p>Today I propose that in the morning you go to <a href=\\"#goldacafe\\"><strong>Golda Café</strong></a> a coffee shop in Malasaña where dogs feel in paradise about 10 minutes walk is the bakery for dogs &#8220;<strong><a href=\\"#miguitas\\">Miguitas, </a></strong>you will love the cakes and treats they sell for dogs, mine is very happy when I take him there.<br />Then I suggest a walk through the <strong><a href=\\"#parquevilladeparis\\">parque Villa de Paris </a></strong> (a french-inspired park in the heart of madrid) and a stroll to the <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#plazadecolon\\">Plaza de Colon</a></strong> where the archaeological museum and the national library.<br />For lunch, I suggest you to go to<strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#rawcocogreenbar\\"> Rawcoco Green Bar,</a></strong> for the foodie lovers, it is an ideal place to take pictures with your pet, very nice atmosphere.<br />In the afternoon, after lunch I suggest you to go to one of the best viewpoints in Madrid to see the sunset which is the <a href=\\"#parktiernogalvan\\" data-wplink-edit=\\"true\\"><strong>park Tierno Galvan</strong></a> de Vallecas, it is huge and ideal to go with dogs. <br />For dinner you can go to <a href=\\"#pizeriacastelo\\"><strong>Pizzeria castelo</strong></a> in the Atocha area. <strong><a href=\\"#santaypura\\">Santa y pura</a></strong> in the Lavapiés area or <a href=\\"#labonita\\"><strong>La Bonita</strong></a>, in the area of Cuzco, with a menu of typical Mediterranean gastronomy.</p>                	<p>Today I propose you to go for a delicious brunch at <a href=\\"#elperroylagalleta\\"><strong>El perro y la galleta</strong></a>, which also specializes in brunch and homemade desserts (all with cookie). They have a terrace so you can enjoy the outdoors while you eat delicious food. The decoration is so cute.<br />Afterwards you can go to <a href=\\"#lobitos\\"><strong>Lobitos</strong></a>, a place where your dog will enjoy trying all the snacks, if you want your dog to feel like a king you have to take him to &#8220;<a href=\\"#manuelapets\\"><strong>Manuela Pets</strong></a>&#8220;, the best dog spa in town, they will treat him great and he will come out smelling great. You will go crazy looking at all the accessories.<br />&#8220;They will go crazy and love the place. Later a walk through the dog park in the &#8220;<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#parquedelretiro\\" data-wplink-edit=\\"true\\"><strong>Parque del Retiro&#8221;</strong></a> for them to enjoy and socialize.<br />For lunch go to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#fellinamadrid\\"><strong>Fellina Madrid</strong></a>, traditional Italian food, better known, but worth it because they have fresh pasta, risottos, a trattoria in the Chamberí neighborhood, delicious food, beautiful atmosphere and decor and of course all dogs welcome, if you already know you can go to eat at <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#lamorenilladelosantojos\\"><strong>La morenilla de los antojos</strong></a>, has a varied menu brunch type, and live music. <br />In the afternoon, after resting for a while you can take your dogs to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#parquejuancarlos\\"><strong>Parque Juan Carlos I</strong></a> (good views, a lake and an outdoor auditorium) and an exclusive area for dogs near the central square of the park, agility obstacles, benches and drinking fountains available.For dinner you can go to &#8220;<strong><a href=\\"#labicicleta\\">La Bicicleta&#8221;</a></strong> a restaurant in the park.</p>\t\t	389	WhatsApp-Image-2023-09-21-at-23.56.24-1.jpeg	1286,1287,1288,1289,1290,1291	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	708,709,710,716,726,730,717,733,725,731,712,711,727,707,728,718,706,729,732,722,719,723,720,721,724,715,714,713	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1dIGwMqoUW6VrVd9OoViUOD6ilIOEUgk&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtiaVbYw621b	price_1Q2TJwAFILSEnUZXAQSCqgtt	1	S	S	Take your dog to the best places and enjoy your experience with him	\N	\N	Pets Lovers	prod_QuotFF4LjGPQQY	price_1Q2zFTAFILSEnUZXcCIjzaG9	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_6oE8zF0cJ7BY4wMcPD	\N	plink_1Q3AnuAFILSEnUZXX4sEQSTs	3Dias	26	N
390	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:13:30	2024-11-22 07:10:26	14036	2023-10-03 00:00:00	SV18 Kids 3 days	KIDS	kids	<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\"><strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Seville\\ s Family Delights: Explore with Your Little Ones </span></strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Explore the magic of Madrid as a family while strolling through its beautiful parks, admiring its miniature cities and enjoying theatrical shows. Plus, don\\ t miss the opportunity to savor the delicious food at restaurants that will make every meal an unforgettable experience for young and old alike. Madrid has something for everyone in the family!</span>	26	salt-and-sugar-1.jpg	1	<p>To start getting to know the city, we&#8217;re going to one of its most famous spots, <a href=\\"#espana\\"><strong>Plaza de España</strong></a>. But first, to gather some energy, I suggest having breakfast in the surrounding area, for example at <a href=\\"#espana\\"><strong>Tarta Home Coffee and Cake</strong></a> (they have delicious pastries and an outdoor terrace). At Plaza de España, the kids will have a blast crossing its bridges and sailing little boats on the lake that you can rent. There&#8217;s usually a street performance with soap bubbles, which they love.</p><p>Right next to it, we have the spectacular <a href=\\"#luisa\\"><strong>Maria Luisa Park</strong></a>, with ample space for the kids to run around, there are swings inside, you can rest in the shade or have a picnic, or have a drink at the bars in Plaza de América, like <a href=\\"#bilindo\\"><strong>Terraza Bilindo</strong></a> (they also serve breakfast). To explore the park, you can rent bikes or a cyclobus (for 4 people) from the cyclotour company. Right in front of the park, you also have the <a href=\\"#ciencia\\"><strong>Casa de la Ciencia</strong></a>, if you feel like visiting. On weekends, they have a planetarium session.</p><p>For lunch, inside the park, you have <a href=\\"#abylio\\"><strong>Kiosco Abilio</strong></a> with classic tapas at a good price, or behind it, there are several restaurants like <a href=\\"#remate\\"><strong>El Remate</strong></a>.</p><p>If you&#8217;re looking for a more immersive experience, one option I recommend for dining today or any other day is to try <a href=\\"#sazon\\"><strong>SAZÓN The Folk Cook</strong></a>, SAZON is the world\\ s first platform to provide Spanish food homely prepared by locals at their own houses, where you would taste it in complete privacy.</p><p>After lunch, I recommend going to the <a href=\\"#acuario\\"><strong>Aquarium</strong></a>, the kids will really enjoy seeing the species that accompanied Magellan during his first circumnavigation of the world. You can end the afternoon relaxing by the Guadalquivir River and <a href=\\"#contadero\\"><strong>Paseo Marqués de Contadero</strong></a>, sit on a terrace to have a drink while watching the sunset, for example at <a href=\\"#agua\\"><strong>Kiosco del Agua</strong></a>, take a boat ride on the river&#8230; or see the replica of the <a href=\\"#nao\\"><strong>Nao Victoria</strong></a>, the kids will feel like true shipwreck survivors.</p><p>For dinner, you can stay in the Arenal area. There are places for tapas like <a href=\\"#arenal\\"><strong>Taberna el Arenal</strong></a>. Or if the kids prefer pizza, I recommend the Italian restaurant <a href=\\"#tesorero\\"><strong>La Casa del Tesorero</strong></a>, the historical building it&#8217;s located in is a marvel.</p>                	<p>First, a good breakfast, today in the historic center area, I invite you to enjoy the palace house where <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sugar\\"><strong>Salt &amp; Sugar café</strong></a> is located.</p><p>Nobody visiting Seville can miss seeing the Giralda, the Cathedral, or <a href=\\"#alcazar\\"><strong>the Alcazar</strong></a>&#8230; but since we&#8217;re with kids, why not turn it into an adventure? I recommend booking a theatrical visit or a family scavenger hunt with the company <a href=\\"#vivo\\"><strong>Sevilla Museo Vivo</strong></a>, the kids will have a lot of fun learning about the mysteries and legends of Seville.</p><p>You can have lunch in the Plaza Nueva area. If you&#8217;re in the mood for something exotic and want to feel like you&#8217;re in Japan, go to <a href=\\"#buga\\"><strong>Buga Ramen</strong></a>. The little ones will love its decor, and one of the waiters is a robot kitty! If you&#8217;re in the mood for tapas, you can go to the <a href=\\"#seis\\"><strong>Seis restaurant</strong></a>.</p><p>In the afternoon, we&#8217;re heading to the <a href=\\"#ilusion\\"><strong>Museum of Illusions</strong></a>! The kids are going to be amazed by the experience. Around here, you can have churros with chocolate at <a href=\\"#dona\\"><strong>Doña Carmen</strong></a>. And for the sunset, you have to go up to <a href=\\"#setas\\"><strong>Las Setas, the Metropol Parasol</strong></a>, to see the city from above, run along its walkways&#8230; Plus, you can enjoy the nighttime light and sound show. On the mezzanine, there are also swings for the kids to play on.</p><p>For dinner, you can go to Plaza de la Alfalfa, there are swings in the area as well. I recommend <a href=\\"#bodega\\"><strong>La Bodega de la Alfalfa</strong></a>.</p>                	<p>For day 3, if you&#8217;re in season (usually from April 15th to October 31st), you can have a very fun day at the <a href=\\"#magica\\"><strong>Isla Mágica theme park</strong></a>. Another year-round option on the <a href=\\"#bosque\\">outskirts</a> of Seville is <a href=\\"#bosque\\"><strong>El Bosque Suspendido Adventure Park</strong></a>(treetop adventure courses, climbing, paintball&#8230;). Alternatively, if you prefer to continue enjoying the city, you can visit the Cartuja area.or continue enjoying the city, this time in the Cartuja area. Around here, I recommend going to the <a href=\\"#torre\\"><strong>Torre Sevilla Shopping Center</strong></a>. It&#8217;s an open-air shopping center with a great playground area for the kids. Right next to it, you have <a href=\\"#caixa\\"><strong>Caixa Forum</strong></a> (with several family activities) and the <a href=\\"#navegacion\\"><strong>Pabellón de la Navegación</strong></a> and its lookout tower. You can have lunch at the shopping center or at the restaurant at Caixa Forum itself called Arcasa.</p><p>Would you like to have a coffee in an old monastery? I recommend going to the CAAC cafeteria (<a href=\\"#caac\\"><strong>Andalusian Center for Contemporary Art</strong></a>), its entrance is free, and there are garden areas for the little ones to run around. To end the afternoon, you can cross the footbridge and you&#8217;ll arrive at a paradise for the kids, the <a href=\\"#descubrimientos\\"><strong>Parque de los Descubrimientos</strong></a>. It&#8217;s a playground area shaped like a giant ship by the river. You can let them play and watch the sunset.</p><p>And to end the day, you have the San Lorenzo neighborhood nearby, where you can have dinner at <a href=\\"#taplato\\"><strong>Bodega San Lorenzo Ta Plato</strong></a>. If not, you also have the <a href=\\"#alameda\\"><strong>Alameda de Hércules</strong></a> area nearby, with outdoor terraces and a children&#8217;s playground area for them to play and enjoy. I recommend <a href=\\"#leones\\"><strong>Kiosco de los Leones</strong></a> and finishing with an ice cream at the <a href=\\"#freskura\\"><strong>Freskura ice cream parlor</strong></a>.</p><p>We recommend making reservations in advance for restaurants and events to ensure availability, as well as checking opening hours.</p><p>Enjoy!</p>\t\t	390	pexels-mark-neal-3365379.jpg	1087	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	2,737,36,758,751,760,738,504,754,740,767,757,766,744,739,756,747,153,763,168,753,745,761,331,9,749,748,8,752,742,750,746,77,759	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/6/embed?mid=1tf5JAyYewEOheP85-Lq2RMiBY6Nom2Q&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtPvSO6Agxng	price_1Q2TJxAFILSEnUZXHQH7K7KU	1	N	N	Seville\\ s Family Delights: Explore with Your Little Ones 	\N	\N	KIDS	prod_QuosgIG6hAsD0s	price_1Q2zF5AFILSEnUZXrwggf1R4	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_00geY3f7Dg8u9R6g1Q	\N	plink_1Q3AnvAFILSEnUZXlroVgFqL	3Dias	27	N
391	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:18:58	2024-11-22 07:10:26	14783	2023-10-06 00:00:00	MAD07 FOODIE	Siéntete un auténtico foodie	sientete-un-autentico-foodie	<p style=\\"text-align: center;\\"><span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\"><strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Saboree la creatividad culinaria y las recomendaciones de los expertos </span>\\r\\n</strong>\\r\\n</span></p>\\r\\n<p style=\\"text-align: left;\\">Embárquese en un delicioso viaje de innovación culinaria mientras deleita su paladar en los exquisitos paraísos gastronómicos de la ciudad. Sumérjase en una experiencia culinaria única donde la creatividad y el arte convergen en cada bocado. Nuestra ciudad es el epicentro de la cocina contemporánea y, con las recomendaciones de nuestros expertos locales, descubrirá joyas ocultas y los sabores más cautivadores</p>	27	amazonico.jpg	2	<p>Para empezar te sugiero que vayas a tomar un café a <a href=\\"#elcomercial\\">?<strong>El comercial?</strong> </a>no es el sitio más barato, pero es un lugar mítico de Madrid. Si quieres otra opción me gusta <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#faraday\\"><strong>Faraday</strong></a> en Chueca tiene una tarta de limón y lavanda deliciosa, allí puedes pasear por la <a href=\\"#pedrozerolo\\"><strong>C/ </strong><strong>Pedro Zerolo</strong></a> y vivir el ambiente hipster.</p><p>Para la hora del aperitivo os propongo seguir por Chueca y entrar en el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#mercadosananton\\"><strong>Mercado de San Antón</strong><strong>.</strong></a> Ahí tienes opciones que merecen la pena, mis favoritas ?Bodegón de Vinos? o ?Bodegón gourmet? otras que también merecen mucho la pena son, <a href=\\"#diurno\\"><strong>Diurno</strong> </a>comer solomillo con pasta, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#elcisneazul\\"><strong>El cisne azul </strong></a>si te gustan las setas. Para comer sugiero dos lugares legendarios, ?<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#casabotin\\"><strong>Casa Botín</strong></a>?, el restaurante más antiguo del mundo donde se puede degustar un espectacular cochinillo o el famoso ?cocido madrileño? en el <a href=\\"#lhardy\\"><strong>Lhardy</strong></a>.</p><p>Luego un gin tonic en el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#diana\\"><strong>Jardín de Diana</strong></a> y por la tarde un paseo hasta <a href=\\"#retiro\\"><strong>El Retiro</strong></a> para conocerlo o dar un paseo en barco.</p><p>Por la noche les sugiero cenar en el ?<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#lamaquina\\"><strong>Restaurante la Máquina</strong></a>? algo de marisco o si es temporada, unas angulas del Cantábrico. Si no, en la calle Jorge Juan tienes otras opciones como <a href=\\"#amazonico\\"><strong>Amazónico</strong></a>.</p>                	<p>Hoy puedes empezar con unos churros en <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#sangines\\">San Ginés</a></strong> , un paseo por el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#palacioreal\\"><strong>Palacio Real</strong></a> hasta llegar al <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#debod\\"><strong>Templo egipcio de Debod</strong></a> y la <a href=\\"#sanantonio\\"><strong>Parroquia de San Antonio de la Florida</strong></a> para descubrir las pinturas de Goya. Posteriormente merienda en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#casalabra\\"><strong>Casa Labra</strong></a> y luego ruta por la zona latina y la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#cebada\\"><strong>Plaza de la Cebada</strong></a>. Mis favoritos en <a href=\\"#lalatina\\"><strong>La Latina</strong></a> son: <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#lucio\\">Los huevos de lucio</a></strong>, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#lamiak\\"><strong>Lamiak</strong></a>, <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#concha\\">Taberna la Concha</a></strong>, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#lucas\\"><strong>Casa Lucas</strong></a>, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#vermuteria\\"><strong>Vermuteria la Bolita Negra</strong></a> y <a href=\\"#peztortilla\\"><strong>Pez tortilla</strong></a>. Recuerda que la tradición es pedir una cervecita, probar un pintxo o una tapa y cambiar de barra.</p><p>Por la noche, un bar típico de Madrid como <a href=\\"#elviajero\\"><strong>El viajero.</strong></a></p><p>Si te apetece hacer alguna opción cultural además de probar la gastronomía madrileña te sugiero el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#prado\\"><strong>Museo del Prado</strong></a> o <a href=\\"#museosorolla\\"><strong>Museo Sorolla</strong></a>. Y si quieres un plan divertido <a href=\\"#sweetspace\\"><strong>Sweet Space</strong></a>. Para cenar sin duda el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#zalacain\\"><strong>Zalacaín</strong></a> que ahora cuenta con Íñigo Pérez como chef, donde podrás probar su famoso baKalao tellagorri.</p>                	<p>Para empezar el día te propongo un clásico de Madrid que debes ir a desayunar a <a href=\\"#santateresa\\"><strong>Churrería Santa Teresa</strong></a>.</p><p>Para tomar un vermut o un aperitivo sugiero pasear por cualquiera de los mercados que tan de moda se están poniendo, como el de <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sanildefonso\\"><strong>San Ildefonso.</strong></a> (Tienes que probar las carrilleras Vermut Manuela comunas con curry en la Taberna Manuela).</p><p>Una visita obligada para comer al mediodía es <a href=\\"#mercadolapaz\\"><strong>mercado de la paz</strong></a>, el puesto de Casa Dani es estupendo y sus tortillas son una delicia (consultar horarios) o ir al restaurante ?<a href=\\"#losasturianos\\"><strong>Los Asturianos</strong></a>? increíble precio y comida.</p><p>Así como te recomiendo restaurantes, para bebidas un poco más gourmet, puedes ir al <a href=\\"#museochicote\\"><strong>Museo Chicote</strong></a> considerado el mejor bar de Europa, se dice que por allí pasaron Frank Sinatra o Ava Gardner.</p><p>También <a href=\\"#martini\\"><strong>DRY Martini Bar</strong></a> de Javier de las Muelas, que está dentro del hotel Gran Melia Fénix, y la coctelería <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#museobar\\"><strong>1912 Museo Bar</strong> </a>en el hotel The Westin Palace.</p><p>Creo que con todos estos lugares, puedes disfrutar de un fin de semana de lujo en Madrid, así que solo espero que lo disfrutes y sobre todo me cuentes que te parece.</p>\t\t	391	real-fabrica-de-tapices.jpg	1307,1308,1309,1310,1311,1312	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	804,429,803,774,784,790,798,772,773,768,445,364,352,786,428,788,775,801,787,800,618,799,700,794,795,373,446,783,792,785,620,371,431,789,388,791,797	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=12PKuxebHcEoxDzyVrYuyZ1uouNdbplw&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHt228QdORPOW	price_1Q2TJxAFILSEnUZXAFHqPv8G	1	N	N	Saboree la creatividad culinaria y las recomendaciones de los expertos 	\N	\N	Siéntete un auténtico foodie	prod_QuotYS5aMGDbjI	price_1Q2zFUAFILSEnUZXSW5mH6ae		https://buy.stripe.com/test_dR62bh0cJf4qaVa16X		plink_1Q3AnwAFILSEnUZX4lgm3xg7	3Dias	28	N
392	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:19:38	2024-11-22 07:10:26	16190	2023-10-27 00:00:00	MAD11-Experience origins	Origins of Madrid	origins-of-madrid	<p style=\\"text-align: center;\\"><strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">know the origins of Madrid</span></strong></p>\\r\\nIn this experience, you will discover places that have preserved their essence over time, including their architecture, culinary traditions and original recipes. These places will allow you to connect with the origins and authenticity of the local culture.	28	real-fabrica-de-tapices.jpg	2	<p>This first day of experience I suggest you spend it in the neighborhoods of Malasaña and Chueca, where you will see while strolling through the streets, the richness of the locals for their aesthetics and their different themes. </p><p>For a very special breakfast, <a href=\\"#pepinillosycafe\\"><b>Bread and pickles </b><b>coffee</b></a>,a charming place owned by two artisan artists, its aesthetics will not leave you indifferent. Then, on the same street you can visit the workshop of one of them, <a href=\\"#tallerartesano\\"><b>Javier S. Medina </b></a>who uses natural materials such as wicker or esparto grass to make his now famous ecological trophies, which even Sarah Jessica Parker herself has fallen in love with.</p><p>Another place to visit and not to be missed is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#tabernalacarmencita\\"><b>La Carmencita Tavern</b></a>. The second oldest tavern in the city, where since 1854 you can eat traditional recipes in the same place where Lorca, Neruda and Miguel Hernandez spent their days in endless gatherings.</p><p>In the afternoon <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#casacrespo\\"><b>Antigua Casa Crespo</b></a> very close to the Plaza del 2 de Mayo is this espadrille shop from 1863, where you can find classic models of espadrilles for men and women, as well as more modern models, all of them hand sewn. </p><p>For an afternoon you can go to the area of Chueca square and as a must visit the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#angelsierra\\"><b>Angel Sierra&#8217;s Tavern</b></a>. Don&#8217;t stay on the terrace and ask for a table inside, where you can have tapas and vermouth on tap surrounded by barrels, and which has been open since 1908. For dinner, you are in an area with a wide and varied offer, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#laformentera\\"><b>La Fermentera </b></a>with a lot of traditional cuisine in its menu.</p>                	<p>Today to start the day visit the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#fabricadetapices\\"><b>Royal Tapestry Factory</b></a> which can only be visited in the morning, where you can see not only the finished tapestries but also the whole process of elaboration, with a history of more than 300 years.</p><p>Then head for the antiques district par excellence, Lavapiés and its area of El Rastro, in Ribera de Curtidores. <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#galeriaspiquer\\"><b>Piquer Galleries </b></a>and the number of almonedas in the surrounding streets and on Ruda Street, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#eturel\\"><b>Eturel</b></a>, a shop-workshop where they make handmade decorative items and accessories using traditional fabrics from all over Spain.</p><p>If we talk about traditions and you are in Madrid you have to try the cocido madrileño, if you can, do it at <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#Lhardy\\"><b>Lardhy </b></a>opened in 1839 and famous precisely for its cocido.</p><p>If you want to have something to drink after lunch, a coffee, a cocktail or a drink, the place is the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#Granhotelingles\\"><b>Great</b> <b>English Hotel</b></a><br />The first hotel in Madrid and recently remodeled. It dates back to 1886 and has an impressive lobby where many Madrileños go for their after work.</p><p>Another emblematic place to visit in the area is the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#reinavictoria\\"><b>Queen Victoria Theater</b></a>. It was inaugurated in 1916 by Alfonso XIII and Queen Victoria Eugenia, hence its name, although from that day to the present it has changed its name several times due to different historical moments, at present it has its original name. Varied programming, with comedies and monologues and an impressive stained glass window protected by Heritage.</p><p>For dinner you have a multitude of options in the area, the neighborhood of Las Letras, but if you feel like something special go to <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#alimentacionquiroga\\">Quiroga Food</a>, </b>a traditional grocery store where you can taste their products, try their sausages and cheeses.</p>                	<p>You can&#8217;t leave the city without visiting the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#museodehistoria\\"><b>Madrid History Museum</b></a>The museum is a beautiful baroque building, the former hospice of San Fernando, and houses a multitude of models, objects, paintings, photographs &#8230; to give you an idea of the history of Madrid since its appointment as capital of Spain in 1561, take the time because it is worth it. </p><p>And if we talk about the history of Madrid, the calamari sandwich, try it at <a href=\\"#barpostas\\"><b>Bar Postas,</b></a> or the brewery <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#lacampana\\"><b>La Campana</b></a> in the surroundings of Plaza Mayor.</p><p>Also near the Plaza Mayor you have the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#mercadosanmiguel\\"><b>San Miguel Market</b></a>. If you want to eat something else, an ice cream&#8230; or have a snack, the best thing to do is to visit all the stalls to see all the variety before deciding!</p>\t\t	392	sol-y-luna-1.jpg	1313,1314,1315,1316,1317,1318	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	809,808,805,813,818,820,807,810,815,814,812,819,816,817,811,821,806	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=18tDRX1dILrQij4dpiV9f69-_G9Sxlgg&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHt4smVWW9gX2	price_1Q2TJyAFILSEnUZX1zSET4Hu	1	S	N	know the origins of Madrid	\N	\N	Origins of Madrid	prod_QuotxzaXZrdpj4	price_1Q2zFUAFILSEnUZXWhhXGUzv		https://buy.stripe.com/test_5kA17dbVr09w7IY9Du		plink_1Q3AnwAFILSEnUZXs4oWPj0a	3Dias	29	N
393	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:19:45	2024-11-22 07:10:27	16206	2023-10-30 00:00:00	MAD12- Interior Design and Architecture	Interior design and architecture	interior-design-and-architecture	<p style=\\"text-align: center;\\"><strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Get to know Madrid from the inside </span></strong></p>\\r\\nEnjoy an exciting plan that combines the exploration of modernist architecture with a wide range of culinary experiences, from gourmet haute cuisine to traditional dishes. It will be an unforgettable experience that will immerse you in the cultural richness of the region.	29	sol-y-luna-1.jpg	2	<p>This first day I suggest that you start with the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#cafecomercial\\"><b>Café Comercial</b></a>, an icon of the capital since 1887, where artists, writers, journalists, journalists, bullfighters? and has even been the inspiration for novels, recently restored respecting its bohemian spirit. </p><p>The next stop is the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#palaciodelongoria\\"><b>Longoria Palace</b></a>. The façade is very ornamented with artificial stone, really incredible. Inside, don?t miss the stained glass window and lobby, if you have the opportunity to visit it, as this is not possible at all times.</p><p>For lunch time I recommend a walk through the neighborhood of Las Letras to visit the <a href=\\"#casadeperezvillalmil\\"><b>House of Pérez Villaalmil</b></a>. Another modernist style building from the early twentieth century, originally conceived as a residential house and that today remains so for a few lucky ones. In the same building, on the first floor, there is the <a href=\\"#matute\\"><b>Matute</b></a>, where you can eat, have a drink, if you decide to stay try their croquettes.</p><p>Without leaving the neighborhood, another proposal is that you visit <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#casamira\\"><b>Casa Mira</b></a>, founded in 1842, and that maintains all the essence of the stores of that time, is a reference in sweets, especially its nougat, in the capital.</p><p>On the same street you can enjoy two buildings that seem to be one because of their great similarity and being united, the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#casadeallende\\"><b>Allende House</b></a> with its impressive tower and wooden belvedere, and the Meneses <a href=\\"#edificiomeneses\\"><b>Meneses building</b></a>. Just across the street are the<a href=\\"#galeriascanalejas\\"><b>Canalejas Galleries</b></a>The building complex, which after a thorough renovation, has now become an icon of luxury with the opening of important fashion brands. Downstairs you can dine with the great gastronomic offer of its 13 restaurants (my favorites are The Eight, Davvero or Salvaje).</p>                	<p>Today we will leave the downtown area to visit other places that are of great interest if you like interior design and architecture.</p><p>Breakfast at <a href=\\"#cristinaoria\\"><strong>Cristina Oria</strong></a> de Ortega y Gasset, a chef who has managed to create a perfect fusion of store and restaurant, where you can find decorative items, gifts or a drink, surrounded by an exquisite decoration. Without leaving the area and in the same block, you can find many and varied proposals of really interesting interior design firms and studios.<b>.</b> Natuzzi, Roche Bobois, Slou but the one you have to visit, if you have to, is <b><a href=\\"#solyluna\\">Sun and Moon</a>,</b>with its interesting and special proposals of furniture and articles covered in leather.</p><p>We left the Salamanca neighborhood to head to La Guindalera, to admire the Torres Blancas building, the <a href=\\"#edificiotorresblancas\\"><strong>White Towers Building</strong></a>, a symbol of brutalist architecture and widely used in films and series, undoubtedly an iconic image of Madrid. Without leaving the neighborhood and a little further south, we find the <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#coloniamodernista\\">Modernist Colony</a></strong> or what is left of it, since many of its houses were demolished to build blocks of apartments, but you can still admire some of them in very good condition in Roma street and Castelar street. Roma Street and Castelar Streetbuilt between 1890 and 1906.</p><p>Time for lunch and I recommend a couple of places near the Retiro, since the afternoon and evening plans will be around there.<b>. <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#ultramarinospirulo\\">Ultramarinos Pirulo</a></b> o<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#quintin\\"><b> Ultramarinos Quintín</b></a>, to eat in a traditional grocery store, brought to the 21st century.</p><p>Once in the Retiro, there is a lot to walk around and a lot to see; <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#casadelasfieras\\">House of the wild beasts, </a> <a href=\\"#lamonta%C3%B1adelosgatos\\">the mountain of the cats</a></b>, which has just reopened after decades of closure, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#monumentodealfonsoxii\\"><b>monument to Alfonso XII</b></a> and of course the <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#palaciodecristal\\">Crystal Palace</a>.</b></p><p>For dinner, and if you fancy a drink afterwards, it?s worth a visit to the reinvented and well-known Florida Park, where interior designers Pascua Ortega and Guillermo García-Hoz left their stamp in the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#floridaretiro\\"><b>Florida Retiro</b></a> .</p>                	<p>For this third day we will start in the area of Plaza de España, recently renovated and depending on the season you can see it converted into an ice rink, a real antique market or a space for a large concert, for its open and functional design. <a href=\\"#adoradobarferraz\\"><b>Adored Ferraz bar</b></a>, is the place if you are in the mood for a good breakfast or a delicious brunch, industrial style with a retro feel. </p><p>Then, cross Ferraz street and you will be able to admire at the end of the staircase of the park of the barracks of La Montaña the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#Templodedebod\\"><b>Temple of Debod</b></a>. The temple, an Egyptian temple of the second century BC and was brought stone by stone, keeping the orientation of its place of origin.</p><p>Another interesting visit very close to there and that you should make is to the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#museocerralbo\\"><strong>Cerralbo Museum</strong></a>, a small palace of the s. XVII that houses more than 50,000 pieces of great value, many of them from the collections of the Marquis of Cerralbo, its owner.</p><p>Walk along the Gran Via, to admire its atmosphere, its buildings, to go to the place you could visit to eat, at the beginning of the Chueca neighborhood, <b><a href=\\"#celsoymanolo\\">Celso and Manolo</a>,</b> for its particular interior design project, a reinvented tasca, you can?t miss it, nor its San Jacobos of eggplants!</p>\t\t	393	hotel-indigo-madrid.jpg	1319,1320,1321,1322,1323,1324	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	841,827,829,826,837,844,843,822,830,839,394,840,836,825,828,833,838,823,824,831,834,835,832	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=1H8TkZY_psoUjwBLQgxCXmTHPGrw4cV0&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtcUw2Peydbf	price_1Q2TJyAFILSEnUZXw6UkhspC	1	N	N	Get to know Madrid from the inside 	\N	\N	Interior design and architecture	prod_QuotRAyCMt1uWR	price_1Q2zFVAFILSEnUZXi7FASVox		https://buy.stripe.com/test_00gdTZcZv5tQbZe7vn		plink_1Q3AnxAFILSEnUZXJebEwVJT	3Dias	30	N
394	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:19:57	2024-11-18 21:05:30	28380	2023-10-06 00:00:00	MAD08 ROOFTOPS	From the heights	from-the-heights	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Get to know Madrid from above</strong> </span>\\r\\n\\r\\nEnjoy an unforgettable experience in Madrid, where you can enjoy the most exquisite brunches, immerse yourself in the exciting \\"tardeo\\" and end the day in the city\\ s modern \\"sky bars.\\" Discover the capital, its culture and its environment, and live an experience that will last in your memory.	30	pexels-athena-2972890.jpg	2	<p>I suggest you start having breakfast at the <a href=\\"#chocolateriasangines\\"><strong>San Ginés chocolate shop</strong></a>, then you can take a walk down the Carrera de San Jeronimo and see the fountains of Cibeles and Neptune until you reach the<a href=\\"#ayuntamientodemadrid\\"><strong> City Hall of Madrid.</strong></a> There you can go up to the terrace which has stunning views. To go up you have to pay 3? which is worth it, and there are also art exhibitions in the lower part of the building, for lunch I suggest <a href=\\"#ramses\\"><strong>Ramsés</strong></a> in the Plaza del Retiro or <a href=\\"#aarde\\"><strong>Aarde</strong></a> on the other side of the square. </p><p>For a coffee with great views you should go for a drink in the <a href=\\"#circulodebellasartes\\"><strong>circle of fine arts</strong></a>, 360 degree views, there are also options to eat something if you feel like bravas are very rich. In the lower part of the building there are sometimes exhibitions that are very interesting. </p><p>Then I recommend you to go up the Gran Via and go up to the terrace of the Hyatt Hotel, <a href=\\"#eljardindediana\\"><strong>the garden of Diana</strong></a>, here you will see the remains of bombs from the civil war. For dinner and to see the sunset I suggest the <a href=\\"#templodedebod\\"><strong>Temple of Debod</strong></a>. If you already know it you can go to the viewpoint of the Almudena and for dinner I propose several options, if I am more of a traditional restaurant I propose <a href=\\"#casamingo\\"><strong>Casa Mingo</strong></a>, if you like trendy places I propose <a href=\\"#bocanegra\\"><strong>Bocanegra</strong></a> or <strong><a href=\\"#arroceriadstapa\\">Arroceria D&#8217;stapa</a></strong> and if not a perfect plan, more economical and romantic is to buy some sandwiches and eat them watching the sunset.</p>                	<p>For today the first stop I propose is to have breakfast at the<a href=\\"#zapshop\\"> <strong>Zap Shop shoe</strong> </a>store in Puerta del Sol. From this secret shoe shop you will see beautiful views of the square. </p><p>Then go to the skybar of <a href=\\"#picalagartos\\"><strong>Picalagartos</strong></a>. It is located on the eighth floor of the NH Collection Gran Via, with a very top views, and with a very chic kitchen, this area is very commercial as you may have noticed so if you like shopping this is your place.</p><p>Nearby is also the rooftop of the <a href=\\"#hotelindigo\\"><strong>Hotel Indigo</strong></a>, which besides having a drink or a meal, has an infinity pool so it is one of the top terraces in Madrid.</p><p>The rooptof of the <a href=\\"#hotelgenerator\\"><strong>Generator Hotel </strong></a>is new, international atmosphere and live music. I love it, it is definitely my favorite. Nearby there is a Japanese that I love very small called <a href=\\"#musashi\\"><strong>Musashi</strong></a> I recommend it 100%.</p><p>For dinner go to the <a href=\\"#corteingles\\"><strong>&#8220;El corte ingles&#8221; of the Plaza Callao</strong></a>, on the ninth floor, they have the Gourmet area and views of a large part of the Gran Via, you can take something with high quality products. and have a privileged view of the Schweppes building.</p><p>The trendy terrace in Madrid is in the <a href=\\"#hotelriu\\"><strong>Riu hotel</strong></a>, with a very cool atmosphere and a varied cocktail menu. Take a picture on the glass walkway and tag Liiffe.com in networks.</p>                	<p>Today I suggest you to have brunch at &#8220;<a href=\\"#lamalaje\\"><strong>La Malaje</strong></a>&#8221; in the plaza de la paja it costs 15? and its terrace at street level is very good. Afterwards it is very good that you take a walk in that area of the latina. You have the &#8220;cava baja&#8221; where there are many restaurants to have an aperitif. </p><p>For lunch you can go to the <a href=\\"#onlyyou\\"><strong>Only You Hotel</strong> <strong>Boutique</strong></a> has a restaurant that I love, better to book.</p><p>In the afternoon I propose a different plan from the heights of the city you can go to the <a href=\\"#moncloa\\"><strong>Moncloa lighthouse</strong></a>, you will be 110 meters high seeing the whole city at your feet.</p><p>To finish the experience a different plan go to<strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#miradordelassietetas\\"> the viewpoint of the seven tits</a></strong> from which you will have a privileged view of the city. Then for dinner a very good Moroccan food bar called <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#restaurantezahara\\"><strong>Restaurante Zahara</strong></a> or <a href=\\"#restauranteelencuentro\\"><strong>Restaurante el Encuentro.</strong></a></p>\t\t	394	pexels-taryn-elliott-4457038.jpg	1395,1396,1397,1398,1399	14.9	15.65	70069.40	N	en	848,854,846,853,852,849,860,864,850,858,857,861,862,865,859,863,856,847,867,866,392,851,855	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=1jZkPwJKGFxr5a6TzcZjRF0LW69RU-HE&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtlpO2iH8Srk	price_1Q2TJzAFILSEnUZX6oqWIXqM	1	N	N	Get to know Madrid from above	\N	\N	From the heights	prod_QuotkRj00CcKAo	price_1Q2zFVAFILSEnUZX3jvSLab3	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_8wM3fl5x37BYbZeaHA	\N	plink_1Q3AnxAFILSEnUZXkCQQa56g	3Dias	31	N
395	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:20:09	2024-11-22 07:15:43	16362	2023-11-05 00:00:00	MAD15- RockandRoll	Feel the rock passion	feel-the-rock-passion	<p style=\\"text-align: left;\\"><strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\"><b>Rock & Roll por Madrid</b></span></strong></p>\\r\\nEnjoy this experience with the host\\ s recommendations of the best Rock&Roll places in the capital, meet the people and enjoy the music.	31	sala-el-grito2.jpg	2	<p>My plan for the first day is in the neighbourhoods of Madrid. In the morning the plan starts in Vallecas, I suggest you go to see the sculpture of Ángeles Rodríguez Hidalgo in<a href=\\"#c\\"> <strong>Calle de Peña Gorbea, 22</strong></a>, a grandmother from Vallecas who became a fan of heavy metal and won the affection of the public when she attended AC/DC concerts. Nearby there is a shop selling records, clothes and rock-themed accessories called <a href=\\"#hardcore\\"><strong>Potencial Hardcore</strong></a>. For lunch you have the <a href=\\"#tipika\\"><strong>Típika Restauran</strong>t</a> with Peruvian food which is super good, you also have the <a href=\\"#las\\"><strong>Las Costillas Restaurant</strong></a> with grilled meat, both are very good. In the afternoon, you can go to Usera and go to <a href=\\"#the\\"><strong>El Grito</strong></a> and spend an afternoon of rock, table football, darts and beer. For dinner I recommend a traditional bar called <a href=\\"#winery\\"><strong>Bodega Estebaranz</strong></a>, where you can eat some raciones and get to know the authentic Madrid. You can also go to <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#donde\\">Bar Donde Siempre</a>,</strong> where you can eat and talk to people, it?s a cool classic. At night you have to go to <a href=\\"#cocodrilo\\"><strong>Cocodrilo Rock Bar</strong></a>, its name is sealed to Johnny Cifuentes, pianist and only survivor of the original group of Burning, the legendary rock band in Spain formed in 1974.</p>                	<p>My route today starts in the morning with a visit to mythical places like <a href=\\"#la\\"><strong>La Metralleta</strong></a> or<strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#babel\\"> Discos Babel</a>,</strong> where you will discover authentic vinyl jewels. At midday for lunch you can go to <a href=\\"#dcorazon\\"><strong>DCorazon</strong></a>, a restaurant serving typical Spanish dishes, if you don?t like it you can also go to the restaurant <a href=\\"#mi\\"><strong>La Mi Venta</strong></a> (traditional cuisine), and in the afternoon if it?s your first time in Madrid I suggest a stroll around <a href=\\"#sol\\"><strong>Puerta del Sol</strong></a>, <a href=\\"#via\\"><strong>Gran Vía</strong></a> and <a href=\\"#mayor\\"><strong>P</strong><strong>laza Mayor</strong></a>. For dinner I have two options: <a href=\\"#rock\\"><strong>Flamingo Rock</strong></a> for tapas or <a href=\\"#bar\\"><strong>Bustock Rock Bar</strong>.</a> At night the plan is for the classics of the movida madrileña. You have to go to <a href=\\"#penta\\"><strong>El Penta</strong></a>, a historic bar in Malasaña, where artists like Alaska and Antonio Vega were born. <a href=\\"#barracuda\\"><strong>Barracudas Rock Bar</strong></a>, one of the city?s rock temples, close to Ventas, and <a href=\\"#lactea\\"><strong>La Vía Láctea</strong></a>, an eclectic venue with walls papered with posters of musicians, a pool table and eighties décor. <a href=\\"#way\\"><strong>Wrong Way</strong></a> is also very trendy: more recent, it is considered one of the best Punk Rock bars in the capital, although it also specialises in Hardcord, Reggae and Psychobilly.</p>                	<p>Today I have thought of a more traditional plan, for breakfast I suggest <a href=\\"#gines\\"><strong>the churrería San Ginés</strong></a>, then a stroll through Malasaña and for lunch go to <a href=\\"#latina\\"><strong>La Latina</strong></a> for tapas and go to the Cava Baja, a classic that never disappoints, there you have <a href=\\"#lucio\\"><strong>Los Huevos de Lucio</strong></a>,<a href=\\"#lamiak\\"> <strong>Lamiak</strong></a> or the classic <a href=\\"#cruz\\"><strong>Bar Cruz </strong></a>in the heart of the Madrid flea market. Afterwards, for a drink you can go to Plaza de la Cebada, which is close by and is a very traditional area.</p><p>In the afternoon I?ve thought of two different plans: do a bit of rock clothes shopping at <a href=\\"#metal\\"><strong>Aguja del Metal</strong></a> or at <a href=\\"#rocket\\"><strong>Punk Rocket Madrid</strong></a>. For dinner you can go to <a href=\\"#gerardo\\"><strong>Casa Gerardo</strong></a> or <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#bigots\\">Bigotes Rock Bar</a></strong><strong>,</strong> and then you can continue the night at <a href=\\"#astro\\"><strong>Astro Zombie Bar</strong></a>, one of the most legendary bars in Madrid.</p><p>You can also take the train and go to Getafe: there you have a mythical rock bar, <a href=\\"#garage\\"><strong>Bar Garaje</strong></a>, a place you will love. For dinner there you have<a href=\\"#laundry\\"><strong> Bar Lavadero</strong></a> and <a href=\\"#creek\\"><strong>Cervecería La Caleta</strong></a>, both are great and you can enjoy a more authentic experience.</p>\t\t	395	sala-el-grito2.jpg	1325,1326,1327,1328,1329,1330	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	898,877,893,886,884,868,901,875,878,880,873,883,896,881,869,890,876,711,871,891,894,879,882,895,897,392,899,900,885,872,870,887,874,888	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1eQEZZlpnv5ewFtg9JarwLUYZUlbxbGs&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHto2b4x4VAEH	price_1Q2TJzAFILSEnUZXXbq1bURj	1	N	N	Rock & Roll por Madrid	\N	\N	Feel the rock passion	prod_QuotmkpPO0ZTY4	price_1Q2zFWAFILSEnUZX3d66Qins		https://buy.stripe.com/test_28ocPV2kR8G2fbq5nh		plink_1Q3AnyAFILSEnUZXvawFTY5m	3Dias	32	N
396	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:20:13	2024-11-22 07:15:59	3971	2024-11-15 00:00:00	MED15_Medellin_es_Botero_1_Dia	Feel the rock passion	feel-the-rock-passion	<p style=\\"text-align: left;\\"><strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\"><b>Rock & Roll por Madrid</b></span></strong></p>\\r\\nEnjoy this experience with the host\\ s recommendations of the best Rock&Roll places in the capital, meet the people and enjoy the music.	304	sala-el-grito2.jpg	4	\N	\N	\N	396	Santafe-scaled-1.jpg	\N	14.9	16.55	68657.95	N	es	898,877,893,886,884,868,901,875,878,880,873,883,896,881,869,890,876,711,871,891,894,879,882,895,897,392,899,900,885,872,870,887,874,888	&lt;iframe&gt;	\N	\N	1	N	N	Rock & Roll por Madrid	\N	\N	Feel the rock passion							3Dias	33	N
397	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:21:32	2024-11-22 07:10:27	17612	2023-10-27 00:00:00	SV13 Casas Palacio 3 días	Ruta De Las Casas Palacio 3 Días	ruta-de-las-casas-palacio-3-dias	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Sumérgete en la majestuosidad del pasado sevillano con estas joyas arquitectónicas, llenas de historia y elegancia, que te transportarán a una época de esplendor.</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">A través de esta experiencia, tendrás la oportunidad de sentir la esencia de la vida aristocrática de Sevilla y conocer las historias fascinantes que se esconden entre sus muros centenarios. Una experiencia inolvidable que te conectará con la rica herencia cultural y gastronómica de esta encantadora ciudad.</span>	33	condesa-de-lebrija.png	1	<p>Comenzamos en el barrio de la macarena. Nuestra primera parada es la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#duenas\\"><b>casa Palacio de Dueñas</b></a> de la muy querida por los sevillanos difunta Duquesa de Alba. Aquí encontrarás, además del edificio, un museo de pertenencias de la difunta Duquesa.</p><p>Continuamos hacia la calle feria, para visitar el <a href=\\"#algaba\\"><b>Palacio de los Marqueses de la Algaba</b></a>, hoy edificio gubernamental, pero visitable.</p><p>Nos merecemos un descanso, os proponemos tapear en los distintos bares del <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#feria\\"><b>Mercado de abastos de la calle Feria</b></a>, frecuentado por locales. Si preferís sentaros a la mesa y sois más de viajar comiendo, os proponemos el libanés <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#fatouch\\"><b>Fatouch </b></a>y su hummus de remolacha o la pequeña <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#bottega\\"><b>Bottega Italia</b></a> y cualquiera de sus pastas, eso sí, deja hueco para su canollo o su tiramisú de postre. Si buscas una experiencia más inmersiva, una opción que te recomiendo para cenar hoy o cualquier otro día es probar <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#sazon\\">SAZÓN The Folk Cook</a></strong>, SAZON es la primera plataforma del mundo que ofrece comida española casera preparada por los lugareños en sus propias casas, donde la degustarás con total privacidad.</p><p>Con energías renovadas, pasearemos hasta la alameda de Hércules, aquí encontramos la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sirenas\\"><b>Casa de las Sirenas</b></a>, antigua casa palacio, hoy centro cívico, con visita gratuita y, posiblemente, alguna exposición.</p><p>Paseando por el Barrio de San Lorenzo, os proponemos recorrer la calle hombre de piedra donde se encuentra el busto <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#piedra\\"><b>Hombre de Piedra</b></a>, dice la leyenda que un pobre infeliz yace aquí empalado, continuando hasta llegar al <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#monsalves\\"><b>Palacio de Monsalves</b></a>, seguro que os suena, ya que aquí se grabó la famosa serie ?allí abajo?, este edificio está propuesto como ampliación para el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#bellasartes\\"><b>Museo de Bellas Artes</b></a> de Sevilla, que si está abierto recomendamos visitar porque sólo su edificio es un antiguo convento mercedario y alberga en su interior una colección de arte barroco, así como obras de Murillo, Velázquez o Zurbarán. Ya que estáis por la zona os propongo visitar el museo de Bellas Artes ya que es gratis para los ciudadanos de la UE y cuesta sólo 1,50 euros para el resto.</p><p>Para terminar el día volvemos nuestros pasos a la alameda.Os proponemos para cenar ?<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#arteysabor\\"><b>Arte y Sabor</b></a>? un restaurante de fusión andalusi, árabe y andaluza? decir que su pastela es una delicia (abre de viernes a domingo). Otra opción es tapear en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#lola\\"><b>Lola por Dios</b></a>. </p><p>Aquí ya os dejamos libertad, para comer un helado, tomar una copa o buscar un rincón donde bailar en esta plaza que es puro ambiente.</p>                	<p>La mañana la comenzamos visitando <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#salinas\\"><b>la casa Salinas </b></a>(atención abre de lunes a viernes de 10 a 14), que está muy bien conservada. </p><p>Seguiremos paseando por el Barrio de Santa Cruz, sus edificios son antiguas casas palacio hoy convertidas en apartamentos o casas de vecinos privadas, acércate a sus rejas y patios para descubrir pequeñas joyas escondidas, mientras llegas a la plaza de los Venerables, donde puedes visitar el antiguo <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#venerables\\"><b>Hospital de los Venerables</b></a>.</p><p>Tras la visita, nos acercaremos a la bulliciosa plaza de la alfalfa donde te damos dos opciones: tapear de pie en sus tascas típicas como<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#trastienda\\"><b> La Trastienda</b></a> o<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#alfalfa\\"><b> La Bodega de la Alfalfa</b></a>, o sentarnos a comer en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#escalona\\"><b>La Escaloná</b></a>, donde puedes probar sin miedo cualquiera de sus tapas, aunque las mas populares son la carrillá, sus croquetas o su tataki de atún. </p><p>Paseando para bajar el almuerzo, volveremos para conocer el palacio de mañara y visitaremos la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#pilatos\\"><b>Casa Pilatos</b></a>, una de las mejores conservadas de la ciudad, propiedad de los Duques de medinaceli, consultar si durante vuestra visita a la ciudad <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#engranajes\\"><b>Engranajes Culturales</b></a> hace visitas teatralizadas porque merece mucho la pena, es una visita a la que le dedicaras tiempo.</p><p>Si os apetece disfrutar de un buen espectáculo de flamenco por la zona, os recomiendo <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#flamenco\\"><b>La Casa del Flamenco</b></a>, es una casa-palacio del s. XV convertida en auditorio de flamenco, que ofrece espectáculos muy completos y tiene varios pases por las tardes. </p><p>Para cenar os proponemos <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#laurel\\"><b>la Hostería del Laurel</b></a>, donde te sentarás a la mesa que inspiró al personaje más literario sevillano más famoso: D. Juan Tenorio y de la que te recomendamos su popular rabo de toro. Si os apetece algo más informal podéis tapear en el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#columnas\\"><b>Bar Santa Cruz Las Columnas</b></a>.</p>                	<p>Empezamos el día en la calle cuna, en concreto en el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#lebrija\\"><b>Palacio de la Condesa de Lebrija</b></a>, una visita que no te puedes perder, tanto por el edificio como por las joyas que alberga en su interior provenientes de Itálica, incluidos enormes mosaicos enteros.</p><p>Tras esta visita, nos acercamos a la plaza del Salvador, donde nos sentaremos en los veladores de mesas altas del centro a disfrutar de la cerveza fría, las tapas más típicas de la ciudad como unas ricas papas aliñadas y las vistas de una de las plazas más bonitas y llenas de vida del centro de la ciudad (tienes <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#bodeguita\\"><b>La Antigua Bodeguita</b></a> o la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#salvador\\"><b>Freiduria Salvador</b></a>).</p><p>Por la tarde, continuamos paseando hasta la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#fabiola\\"><b>Casa Fabiola</b></a>, hoy convertida en una sala de exposiciones de arte costumbrista. Para terminar la tarde os recomiendo visitar el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#caridad\\"><b>Hospital de la Caridad</b></a> y tomar algo en la terraza del <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#donamaria\\"><b>Hotel Doña María</b></a> que tiene unas vistas espectaculares.</p><p>Para terminar esta ruta de casas palacios os proponemos cenar en un sofisticado restaurante con aires señoriales, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sanfernando\\"><strong>Restaurante San Fernando</strong></a>, que está dentro del conocido Hotel Alfonso XIII (recomiendo reservar con antelación para garantizar la disponibilidad).</p><p> Que disfrutéis!!</p>\t\t	397	La-pedrera.jpg	1577,1578,1579,1580,1581,1582,1583	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	912,906,909,908,927,919,914,920,905,926,928,915,929,925,917,921,918,922,916,923,913,904,911,902,924,903,910,930,907	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=1H4xN9MQrR70XpllM4plPywQfXHtBFog&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtrTc6rTW4z2	price_1Q2TK0AFILSEnUZXMQdUHTar	1	S	S	Sumérgete en la majestuosidad del pasado sevillano con estas joyas arquitectónicas, llenas de historia y elegancia, que te transportarán a una época de esplendor.	\N	\N	Ruta De Las Casas Palacio 3 Días	prod_Quos5PFHl3a6ht	price_1Q2zF6AFILSEnUZXqiJphQzA		https://buy.stripe.com/test_28o17d7Fb09wfbqeXS		plink_1Q3AnzAFILSEnUZX5SP9LKnq	3Dias	34	N
398	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:25:14	2024-11-18 21:05:30	24784	2024-02-09 00:00:00	BCN01 - Contemporary Art	Discover contemporary art 3 Days	discover-contemporary-art-3-days	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Barcelona where contemporary creativity breaks new ground and tradition is transformed into an explosion of artistic expression.</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"color: #000000;\\">Do you want to discover and enjoy all the contemporary art that Barcelona has to offer? This is your experience. Your host has prepared a weekend of plans for you to fully enjoy this art, the best gastronomic proposals and other activities. Are you up for it?</span>	34	La-pedrera.jpg	3	<p>Welcome to Barcelona! </p><p>My city is at the forefront of the artistic avant-garde and with this contemporary art route we immerse ourselves in the innovative creativity of local and international artists while exploring the galleries and cultural spaces that define the contemporary art scene in Barcelona. Let&#8217;s get started!</p><p>The first day we will move around the Raval neighborhood. Known for its multiculturalism and for hosting many studios, galleries and bookstores. </p><p>In order to awaken the senses and enjoy the experience with all the energy, I recommend you to have breakfast at <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#breik\\">Breik Cafeteria</a>. </b>You will find a wide variety of breakfasts to suit your palate. And in case you like to get up early, it is open from 6 am. ??</p><p>To start off on the right foot, we will visit the<strong><a href=\\"#macba\\"><br />MACBA</a></strong><b>. </b>  The general visit is well worth it, they also have other exhibitions and activities scheduled throughout the months that will surprise you. Every Saturday from 4 p.m. it is free of charge. </p><p>The square in front of MACBA is known for gathering many skaters from the city. A different way to see Barcelona and enjoy it. There you can see them doing tricks and it is a meeting point.</p><p>Next to MACBA you will also find the<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#cccb\\"> <b>Center of Contemporary Culture of Barcelona (CCCB)</b></a>as interesting as the previous one. They have creative art shows, a theater and several exhibitions per month. Nearby, a very nice place to eat is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#veggie\\"><b>Veggie Garden</b></a>a vegan space with a very good atmosphere. An alternative to this is <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#caravelle\\">Caravelle</a>, </b>a modern, lively and popular restaurant.</p><p>Then I would tell you to get lost in the streets of the city to finish enjoying the day. If you do not want to enter more museums, stroll through El Raval, I recommend you the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#tallers\\"><b>Tallers Street</b></a> one of the old medieval streets, full of vintage stores, second hand clothes, musical instruments stores&#8230; I also recommend to go to see <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#botero\\"><b>Botero&#8217;s Cat</b></a>The sculpture, created in 1989 by Fernando Botero, of large dimensions and the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#hospitalc\\"><b>Hospital Street</b></a> and visit the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#cruz\\"><b>Former Hospital de la Santa Cruz</b></a>.</p><p>In the afternoon we can visit the born and enter the <a href=\\"#museoeuropeo\\"><b>European Museum   </b><b>Museum of Modern Art</b></a> is an 18th century palace that displays 20th and 21st century works. On your way out you can have a drink at the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#bornet\\"><b>Bornet</b></a>The atmosphere and the background music make it stand out. In the area I recommend you to visit <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#maxo\\"><b>Maxó Gallery </b></a>Inside you can have your photo printed for 3? with the theme of the gallery.</p><p>For dinner I reccomend <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#musiu\\"><strong>M</strong><b>usiu</b></a> that is located in Passeig de Gràcia, its pastas stand out and it has a very good atmosphere to have a cocktail afterwards. </p>                	<p>For the second day I recommend visits to the main art galleries of the city. We will move around the Eixample and the Born.</p><p>A sophisticated choice for breakfast is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#migas\\"><b>Good Migas</b></a> the gastronomic offer is healthy. You will find breakfasts, vegan dishes and a wide variety of healthy options. It is one of my favorites, whenever I pass by one I go in either to telework while I have a coffee or to have a snack and enjoy their dishes. ??</p><p>In the morning we will focus on the galleries. For this I have planned a route that you should follow in this order for a better experience, we will start in the Eixample:</p><p>The starting location will be <a href=\\"#bombon\\"><b>Bombón Projects</b></a> awaits you with its diverse exhibitions of contemporary art. The next to visit is the <b><a href=\\"#chiqui\\">Chiquita Room</a>,</b> a center for contemporary art and creation that develops its activity as a gallery, artists&#8217; residence, producer and curator of projects, cultural mediator, publisher of artists&#8217; books and school of inspiration. Next and close to the previous one, we will go to the<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#joan\\"><b> Joan Gaspar Gallery</b></a><br />which is committed to avant-garde art. </p><p>We will continue with the <br /><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#angeles\\"><b>Àngels Barcelona Gallery</b></a><br /> focuses on contemporary culture and its different practices. To finish the tour I recommend <a style=\\"color: #f41f8c;\\" href=\\"#banksy\\"><strong style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Banksy Museum</strong></a> has a permanent exhibition of the author. </p><p>We will go to the born, to have lunch in the area you will find <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sagardi1\\"><b>Sagardi Argenteria </b></a>Basque style where you can taste the pinchos and its famous grill, the treatment is very good and a great experience.</p><p>After lunch, let yourself be surprised at the<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#moco\\"><b> Moco Museum</b></a> known for its immersive exhibitions and modern character. Ideal to enjoy the experience and take pictures for your memories.</p><p>We will continue on to the Eixample district to visit the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#punxes\\"><b>Casa de les punxes </b></a>work elaborated by Josep Puig i Cadafalch in modernist style&#8230;.a real highlight!!!!</p><p>To end the day we can have dinner at <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#junkfood\\"><b>Vegan Junk Food </b></a>a different vegetarian restaurant in a modern atmosphere or if you prefer something more informal you have <br /><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#parkingpizza\\"><b>Parking pizza</b></a> delicious!</p>                	<p>At the end of the experience we will walk around the city to admire the best modernist facades of the city by l&#8217;Eixample.</p><p>If we talk about modernism in Barcelona, the first thought that comes to anyone in the city is Gaudí, the most representative artist of the movement. So what better way to start than by looking at his great works. </p><p>We start the day in Plaza Catalunya, where you can find a very representative place for breakfast <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#zurich\\"><b>Café Zurich </b></a>present in the city for more than 100 years. </p><p>Once we have breathed the atmosphere of Barcelona in Café Zurich. We will start our tour by going to the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#palaumusica\\"><b>Palau de la Música Catalana</b></a>. It is an auditorium that stands out for its artistic beauty and was designed by Lluís Domènech i Montaner. It has a self-guided tour option, my recommendation is to buy the ticket and enjoy its interior. We then headed to Passeig de Gràcia to go to the<a href=\\"#casamorera\\"><b> Lleó Morera House </b></a>designed by the same author, one of the geniuses of Catalan modernism.</p><p>2 minutes away we find <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#amatller\\"><b>Amatller House</b></a> representative of Josep Puig i Cadafalch. It is a striking work of Catalan style. Full of history with the option of a guided tour. Next to him we find <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#batllo\\"><b>Batlló House</b></a> one of the most representative works of the Modernism movement and of course one of the most iconic places of the city designed by Gaudí. In case you want to access, you can buy tickets online.</p><p>Here I recommend you to stop for lunch or a drink at <br /><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#secrets\\"><b>Secrets Pau Claris</b></a>. A very TOP place to try light dishes. Or <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#doratapas\\"><b>Dora Tapas Bar </b></a>stands out for its atmosphere and facilities.</p><p>In the afternoon we will go to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#pedrera\\"><b>La Pedrera (Casa Milà) </b></a>UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1984. Another representative work of Gaudí and very criticized at the time. A 5-minute walk away we will find <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#comalat\\"><b>Comalat House</b></a><b> </b>is a block of apartments designed in 1911 under the influences of Gaudí. I emphasize its arches and facade. A few meters away we find <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#fuster\\"><b>Fuster House</b></a><b> </b>was the last work of the artist Lluís Domènech i Montaner, with French-style attics that were unusual at the time.</p><p>Finally, we will go to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#vicens\\"><b>Vicens House</b></a>. I recommend taking public transportation, there is a bus in front of the Hotel Majestic, when you are at the bus stop take number 24 or 22. </p><p>I highlight other points of interest that are known but you can not miss if you like the architecture of Gaudí as La Sagrada Familia, Park Güell, and the<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#calvet\\"><b>Calvet House</b></a>.</p><p>At the end of the tour I recommend dinner at <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#fred\\">Elsa and Fred</a>, </b> their patatas bravas are delicious!!! Another street option to try a different type of experience is the<b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#wok\\">Wok to Walk</a>. </b></p><p>As a final colophon and if you feel like some leisure time I recommend you <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#tavernabcn\\"><b>La Taverna de Barcelona </b></a>is a music bar with live music, you can eat and have a cocktail.</p><p>I hope you enjoyed the tours! Barcelona has endless plans. Remember that we have more experiences to recommend you around the city. </p><p>See you soon!!! ??</p>\t\t	398	La-pedrera.jpg	1577,1578,1579,1580,1491,1582,1583	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	958,949,945,937,931,955,966,935,959,933,946,963,961,967,940,939,964,948,944,938,947,962,969,957,932,942,951,943,956,954,952,950,960,936,941,953,934,965,968	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1fSHtj97xWMlK2YfPqKz06laHLHn2lOo&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHt265qets4xD	price_1Q2TK0AFILSEnUZXCyFkqLti	1	S	S	Barcelona where contemporary creativity breaks new ground and tradition is transformed into an explosion of artistic expression.	\N	\N	Discover contemporary art 3 Days	prod_QuotRcK2pmKvZ9	price_1Q2zFlAFILSEnUZXCkJdarxf	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_fZecPVaRn7BY7IY173	\N	plink_1Q3AnzAFILSEnUZXKceFwq22	3Dias	35	N
399	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:25:18	2024-11-18 21:05:30	23589	2024-02-21 00:00:00	BCN02 - Modernism	The secrets of modernism 3 Days	the-secrets-of-modernism-3-days	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Barcelona where contemporary creativity breaks new ground and tradition is transformed into an explosion of artistic expression.</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"color: #000000;\\">Do you want to discover and enjoy all the contemporary art that Barcelona has to offer? This is your experience. Your host has prepared a weekend of plans for you to fully enjoy this art, the best gastronomic proposals and other activities. Are you up for it?</span>	\N	La-pedrera.jpg	3	<p>For breakfast, I suggest you start at one of my favorite places in modernist Barcelona, ??which is <a href=\\"#chelo1\\"><b>Chelo Café.</b></a> If it&#8217;s sunny, don&#8217;t hesitate to go out to the terrace. Afterwards, and to get into the topic, I propose a walk along the ramblas, entering the <a href=\\"#boque1\\"><b>Boqueria Market</b></a><b> </b>and in the store Ale hop. This store would go unnoticed a priori, but it is a modernist palace with surprising ceilings.</p><p>Then I propose that you enter the bar association and (current Barcelona archive) it is officially called the <a href=\\"#arcadia1\\"><b>Arcadia Palace</b></a>, you can see the cloister and go have something to \\"<a href=\\"#gats4\\"><b>The four cats</b></a>\\" the bohemian place in the city where the geniuses of modernism met and where Picasso exhibited one of his works for the first time.</p><p>To eat I suggest <a href=\\"#soso1\\"><b>La Sosenga</b></a> it&#8217;s highly recommended. They are both very close to <a href=\\"#paau\\"><b>Palau de la Música</b></a> and the <a href=\\"#seda\\"><b>Silk Palace</b></a> building. You can go to these monuments and take a couple of photos or if you feel like visiting them.</p><p>For the afternoon, I suggest you go up Urquinaona to Paseo de Gracia, walk looking at the buildings and finish having a drink on the rooftop of the <a href=\\"#hcondes\\"><b>Hotel Condes de Barcelona</b></a> watching \\"La Pedrera\\" and \\"La Sagrada Familia\\" in the background.</p><p>If among your plans you want to visit one of Gaudí&#8217;s famous houses, this is the time for you to do it, my favorite is Casa <a href=\\"#llo1\\"><b>Batlló</b></a>If the price seems expensive to you, you can enter through the store and go to the typical modernist bathrooms or enter the building next door, go up to the highest floor and admire the terraces of Casa Batlló. For dinner you can go to <a href=\\"#meson1\\"><b>Meson Jesus</b></a><b> </b>or to <b>\\" <a href=\\"#vasca\\">La Penela</a></b> \\".</p>                	<p>Today my plan focuses on getting to know better the life of the geniuses of modernism, so I suggest you go to breakfast at the <b><a href=\\"#escri\\">Escriba Pastry Shop</a> ,</b>  one of the most important in the city with a façade of modernist volumes and finishes. Nearby is Plaza Catalunya from where you can go by train to  <a href=\\"#canet\\"><b>Canet de Mar</b></a>. There you will see the family pantheon of Doménech and Montaner. Another option is to go to the  <a href=\\"#colonia\\"><b>Colonia Güell</b></a> and see the place where Gaudí died.</p><p> Back in Barcelona to eat you can choose <a href=\\"#londonb\\"><b>London Bar</b></a> or <a href=\\"#tapes1\\"><b>Art i Tapes</b></a>. Afterwards a walk to admire modernist buildings such as La<b> </b><a href=\\"#ramona\\"><b>Casa Ramona</b> <b>factory</b></a>,  <a href=\\"#morera1\\"><b>Casa Lleó i Morera</b></a>,  <b><a href=\\"#calvet1\\">Calvet House</a> , <a href=\\"#llopis\\">Manuel Llopis Bofill House</a> , <a href=\\"#bruno\\">Bruno Cuadros House</a></b>. Afterwards you can go have a drink and watch the sunset  <b><a href=\\"#fuster1\\">Fuster House</a> .</b></p><p>For dinner I propose two options, both of which are in the modernist part and are called <a href=\\"#diaz\\"><b>Casa Diaz.</b></a><b> </b>or <b><a href=\\"#portoles1\\">Portoles Restaurant</a> .</b></p><p>Then I suggest you go to the <a href=\\"#ayre\\"><b>Ayre Hotel Rosellón</b></a> , the views are spectacular and worth it.</p>                	<p>You can start with breakfast at the Pedrera café and then head out to <a href=\\"#casabe\\"><b>Casa Bellesguard</b></a>, is less known but equally fascinating to know. There you can discover the secrets of the Horta area.</p><p>To eat I suggest you do it at <a href=\\"#disb\\"><b>Disbarat</b></a><b> </b>or in<b> </b>In both <a href=\\"#glop1\\"><b>Glop</b></a> you can eat typical Catalan food.</p><p>In the afternoon, visit <a href=\\"#vicens0\\"><b>Casa Vicens</b></a><b> </b>either<b> </b><a href=\\"#santpau\\"><b>Sant Pau</b></a><b> </b>or <a href=\\"#macaya\\"><b>the Palau Macaya</b></a> and then take the train and finish with a walk through the royal square.</p><p>For dinner, a classic like \\" <b><a href=\\"#mbuenas\\">Muya Buenas</a> \\"</b> or <b>\\" <a href=\\"#grillr\\">Grill Room</a> \\"</b>\\". Then I propose a drink in  <a href=\\"#confite\\"><b>The confectionery</b></a><b> </b>or <b><a href=\\"#coc\\">Tandem cocktail Bar</a> .</b></p>\t\t	399	1-casa-vicens-gaudi-fachada-1526894972.jpeg	1512,1513,1514,1515,1516,1517,1518	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	972,985,994,995,971,966,982,959,990,992,987,986,998,970,983,996,981,964,1002,977,984,989,979,956,993,999,976,1004,1003,973,997,1000,980,974,1001	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1pkI1W518KoMmwxEpQC1DEWMtPREW-LM&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtUrfTZ0H3rJ	price_1Q2TK1AFILSEnUZXd1vKdDE3	1	S	N	Barcelona where contemporary creativity breaks new ground and tradition is transformed into an explosion of artistic expression.	\N	\N	The secrets of modernism 3 Days	prod_QuotpBScrkoZKg	price_1Q2zFmAFILSEnUZXoOUorKir	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_28obLRaRnbSe6EUg1Y	\N	plink_1Q3Ao0AFILSEnUZXl7h6tfn5	3Dias	36	N
400	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:25:23	2024-11-18 21:05:30	24789	2024-02-22 00:00:00	BCN03 - Discover Gothic in Barcelona	Discover The Gothic In Barcelona	discover-the-gothic-in-barcelona	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Barcelona, a journey through time, immerse yourself in the history of the Gothic Quarter and enjoy the modern charm of the Ciutat Vella.</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\nStroll through the cobbled streets of the Gothic Quarter, where history comes alive at every turn. Admire the imposing architecture of Barcelona and let yourself be carried away by the charm of the Ciutat Vella, enjoying the gastronomic recommendations of your host. A three-day trip full of discoveries and emotions.	36	gotico-bcn.jpg	3	<p>Although the Gothic is the best known part of the city, this experience hides secrets that you will discover and that are outside the typical tourist plans.</p><p>The first day for breakfast I suggest you to have breakfast at the <a href=\\"#granja\\"><strong>Dulcinea Farm</strong></a> in the square of <a href=\\"#pi\\"><strong>Sta Maria del Pi</strong></a>. This square has a very nice painting market on weekends and the basilica is the stage for the Candelight concerts in the evenings. Those streets until you reach the <a href=\\"#veronica\\"><strong>Veronica Square</strong></a> I love them because of the weather and the little shops.</p><p>To continue I propose a walk through <a href=\\"#neri\\"><strong>Sant Felipe Neri</strong></a>El Call, (there is a coffee shop almost hidden where you can taste coffee from all over the world, it is called <a href=\\"#side\\"><strong>Right Side</strong></a>). The imposing<a href=\\"#augusto\\"><strong>Temple of Augustus</strong></a>, <a href=\\"#rei\\"><strong>the Plaza del Rei</strong></a>. In the middle of the morning if you feel like something fresh, I propose you <a href=\\"#ginger\\"><strong>Ginger</strong></a> in the <a href=\\"#ovisso\\"><strong>Sant Just square or Ovisso</strong></a> at Plaça George Orwell. To eat my choices are &#8220;<a href=\\"#pintor\\"><strong>El Pintor</strong></a>&#8220;, o <a href=\\"#andu1\\"><strong>Anduriña</strong></a> (an old-fashioned bar) or <a href=\\"#sal\\"><strong>Salterio</strong></a> in the Jewish quarter for a cup of tea after lunch.</p><p>For the afternoon my proposal is the <a href=\\"#historia\\"><strong>museum of History of Barcelona</strong></a> or a stroll through the <a href=\\"#miquel\\"><strong>Sant Miquel square</strong></a> to the beach.<br />In the evening, if you are into live music, without a doubt <a href=\\"#craft\\"><strong>Craft</strong></a>or if you are more into Jazz, for me the best option is <a href=\\"#harlem\\"><strong>Harlem Jazz bar</strong></a>.</p>                	<p>Today you can start by having breakfast at <a href=\\"#delicies\\"><b>Café de les Delicies</b></a>It is a place with a vintage touch. If you only want to taste a sweet <a href=\\"#ayub\\"><b>Ayub Cafeteria</b></a>Here they elaborate the best Arab sweets of the city. Afterwards, we went out to visit the Raval. </p><p>Strolling through the Raval and discovering its decadent touch by discovering unique places is worthwhile. A walk until you reach the Rambla del Raval and see <a href=\\"#gato\\"><b>the cat of &#8220;Botero</b></a>&#8220;or visit the nearby <a href=\\"#cruz\\"><b>Hospital de la Santa Cruz.</b></a></p><p>For lunch, my suggestion for the neighborhood is the <a href=\\"#augustin\\"><b>Bar Bodega Agustin</b></a><b> </b>y <a href=\\"#atlanta\\"><b>the Atlanta Bar</b></a>bars where time seems to have stopped. If you feel like a coffee in the sun afterwards, a good option is the Plaza Castella, I usually go there. <a href=\\"#shop\\"><b>SAVTA Sandwich Shop</b></a>. This square has many terraces to recharge your batteries and vitamin D.</p><p> Next to it is Tallers Street where there are plenty of vintage stores where you can spend hours, one that I love to visit is <a href=\\"#revolver\\"><b>Revolver</b></a> where you can find new and second hand records from all periods. For dinner<a href=\\"#3\\"><b> O toxo 3 brothers</b></a> in the Raval or<a href=\\"#morelia\\"> <b>Morelia </b></a>on the plaque of the Mercat del Born. To have a drink afterwards and unwind with a few drinks you can go to <a href=\\"#lon\\"><b>London Bar</b></a> a place with a curious aesthetic perfect to end the day or in the  evening. <a href=\\"#23\\"><b>23Robadors</b></a> if what you want is live music.</p>                	<p>For this day my option is to let yourself be fooled by the Born neighborhood. You can start by buying a croassant with mascarpone cheese from <a href=\\"#hoffman\\"><b>Hoffman</b></a> and sit to drink a coffee on the terrace of the Rec. Then I propose a walk through <b><a href=\\"#ciudadela\\">the citadel greenhouse</a>, <a href=\\"#moco\\">the MOCO museum in</a></b>Montcada Street or wander through the labyrinths of the Born. For lunch I propose <a href=\\"#convent\\"><b>the convent</b></a> in brosoli street, <a href=\\"#ciu\\"><b>the Ciudadela</b></a> if you want rice and if you are wine lovers my proposal is <a href=\\"#aguita\\"><b>Agüita</b></a> where you can also taste some delicious sausages.</p><p>For the coffee where you can taste the coffees of the world and in the afternoon a stroll through the mulberry grove. You can also participate in a pottery workshop, as the guild district preserves the medieval craft tradition.</p><p>Another option is to go to the <a href=\\"#francia\\"><b>France station, see its modernist architecture</b></a>to see its modernist architecture and take a stroll through the old port warehouses until you reach the beach area.</p><p>For the evening you have several options, if you want something with a veggie touch I propose you <a href=\\"#vegetalia\\"><b>Vegetalia</b></a> if you are more of a &#8220;usual &#8221; kind of person, I suggest <a href=\\"#can\\"><b>Can Culleretes</b></a>.</p><p>To end the day <a href=\\"#mamaine\\"><b>Mamainé </b></a>a small and very chic place or <a href=\\"#paraiso\\"><b>the Paradise </b></a>a clandestine cocktail bar that leaves no one indifferent.</p><p>I hope you enjoy very much this plan for the old part of the city and&#8230;. See you next time!</p>\t\t	400	gotico-bcn.jpg	1463,1464,1465,1466,1467,1468,1469,1470	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1032,1038,1015,1026,1022,1017,1025,937,1021,1041,1019,1005,1039,1012,1020,1033,1024,1034,984,1042,951,1030,1029,1013,1011,1028,1009,1016,1008,1018,1027,1006,1010,1037,1036,1014,1043,1040,1007	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1RCjqbRbts5-3ZWt2es4_Jj7Ywso2YNg&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHts7k0Y3ypYd	price_1Q2TK1AFILSEnUZXMuhJfNY7	1	N	N	Barcelona, a journey through time, immerse yourself in the history of the Gothic Quarter and enjoy the modern charm of the Ciutat Vella.	\N	\N	Discover The Gothic In Barcelona	prod_Qv1Hb05FKzQuFh	price_1Q3BEUAFILSEnUZXc8ubTeLE	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_8wM039e3z4pM1kAg3T	\N	plink_1Q3BIcAFILSEnUZXD8STAdO9	3Dias	37	N
401	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:25:37	2024-11-18 21:05:30	22251	2024-02-19 00:00:00	BCN06 - Relax & Gourmet	Relax & Gourmet 3 Dias	relax--gourmet-3-dias	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Vive la fusión perfecta de relajación y delicias gourmet en Barcelona, donde la serenidad se combina con experiencias culinarias irresistibles. ?????</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Disfruta de tratamientos rejuvenecedores, paisajes encantadores y momentos de tranquilidad en los lugares más exclusivos de la ciudad. Deja atrás el estrés y déjate llevar por una experiencia de bienestar única en Barcelona.</span>	37	relax-bcn-.png	3	<p>¡Hola! Bienvenidos a Barcelona! Mi ciudad puede ser un oasis de serenidad, os voy a recomendar mis sitios favoritos para que disfrutéis de unos días de relax, tranquilidad y buena comida que no olvidaréis? espero que os guste!! Recordad que para los spas y restaurantes es importante consultar horarios y reservar con antelación para aseguraros la disponibilidad.</p><p>Hoy nos moveremos por el Eixample y el Barrio Gótico. A modo de empezar el día os recomiendo <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#billy\\"><b>Billy Brunch </b></a>(calle Bailén). Sirven muy buen café con varias formas, pancakes, tostadas con varios toppings y mucha variedad.</p><p>Después de desayunar en este placentero lugar, nos dirigimos a <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#evasiom\\"><b>Evasiom Spa</b></a>, un spa con masaje tailandés. Se caracteriza por su especialidad en la aromaterapia, se basa en trabajar y usar aceites esenciales beneficiosos para nuestro cuerpo. Más allá de esto, de verdad logras desconectar con diferentes olores que te permiten entrar en una atmósfera relajante. </p><p>De camino a Evasiom Spa tienes la opción de observar las obras modernistas de la ciudad que están de paso como <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#punxes\\"><b>la Casa de les Punxes</b></a> y <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#comalat\\"><b>la Casa Comalat</b></a> y así evitarás la multitudes.</p><p>¿Qué os ha parecido Evasiom Spa? ¿Relajante verdad? muy bien, ahora tengo dos recomendaciones para activar un poco el cuerpo por ello os recomendare:</p><ol><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a href=\\"#ramonet\\"><b>Los Jardines de Muñoz Ramonet</b><b> </b></a>es un jardín histórico del siglo XX fue concebido para uso privado pero actualmente es de uso público y promueven respetar el ambiente del jardín. Ofrece reposo y evasión entre la urbe y el tráfico. Cuenta con un palacete y un estanco, por los alrededores abundan esculturas.</li><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\">La otra opción es más cultural y es <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#antoni\\"><b>el Museo de la Fundación Antoni Tàpies</b></a>, un edificio modernista con un museo contemporáneo en las que se exhiben pinturas y obras del autor. La entrada general cuesta 8 euros.</li></ol><p>Pienso que es hora de comer y para ello tengo un sitio que os hará mimar a vuestras papilas gustativas. La recomendación es <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#antigua\\"><b>Antigua </b></a>(Carrer de Marià Cubí), Antigua es un restaurante mediterráneo exclusivo donde se sirven vinos y exquisitos platos de carne y marisco.</p><p>Otra opción más casual es <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#saona\\"><b>Saona Travessera de Gràcia</b></a> con un servicio amable y un ambiente acogedor. Poseen un menú degustación de medio día con 5 platos y es la opción recomendable, en caso contrario elegir a la carta.</p><p>Por la tarde nos moveremos por el Barrio Gótico. Visitar el poco conocido <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#augusto\\"><b>MUHBA Templo de Augusto</b></a> (los lunes cierra a las 2), en su interior posee las columnas del templo de Augusto que han sido restauradas y datan del siglo I a. C. Otra opción acorde a la experiencia es visitar el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#frederic\\"><b>Museo Frederic Marès</b><b> </b></a>es un tesoro cultural en el corazón de Barcelona. Gracias a su majestuoso edificio y la colección de piezas expuestas te harán retroceder en el tiempo y sumergirte en la vida y creatividad de Frederic Marès. </p><p>Para relajarnos después de esta visita, un buen lugar de pausa y tranquilidad es <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#salteiro\\"><b>Salteiro</b></a>, muy top y su elemento principal es el té. En cuanto al ambiente está suavemente iluminado y encontrarás libros y objetos curiosos. </p><p>Si preferís tomar una copa y admirar la Catedral desde una terraza en las alturas, vuestro lugar es <a href=\\"#cola\\"><b>Hotel Colón</b></a> está delante de la Catedral. Una vez dentro, cuando estéis en la parte alta, tendréis una panorámica exclusiva y  un ambiente que dará paso a disfrutar de la experiencia. Si queréis tomar algo sugiero reservar antes de ir. </p><p>Para cenar y Por la noche te recomiendo <a href=\\"#disfru2\\"><b>Disfrutar</b></a> de la gastronomía mediterránea, ofrece menús experimentales muy top en el barrio de l\\ Eixample. Si preferís sushi el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#shunka\\"><b>Restaurante Shunka</b></a> es de los mejores de la ciudad. Ubicado en el barrio gótico.</p>                	<p>Seguimos con nuestra rutina de relajación y cuidados, lo primero de todo es desayunar  y por ello os recomiendo un lugar muy TOP, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#papa\\"><b>LA PAPA BARCELONA</b><b> </b></a>un sitio gourmet con elaboraciones más cuidadas. Tiene dos sedes en Barcelona, una en la calle Aribau, 92 y la otra en la calle Pau de Claris, 190. Todo está buenisimoooo</p><p>Tras salir con una sonrisa de LA PAPA BARCELONA? hora del spa! Aquí os dejo algunos de mis favoritos, no olvidéis reservar para no quedaros sin sitio!: </p><p>&#8211;<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#aire\\"><b>Spa Aire de Barcelona</b></a>, con una ubicación perfecta en el casco antiguo, ambientación en antiguos baños árabes para disfrutar al máximo baño caliente, el hamam, podéis reservar un masaje fantástico. </p><p>&#8211;<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sentits\\"><b>9 sentits</b></a>. Tienen diferentes servicios como los masajes para parejas con diferentes rituales y baños aromáticos, masajes de bienestar individuales, vinoterapia&#8230; </p><p>-Mi última recomendación es <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#isis\\"><b>Isis Spa</b></a>, delante del <b><a href=\\"#egipcio\\">Museo Egipcio de Barcelona</a> (</b>el que también vale la pena visitar si tenéis tiempo). Inspirado y ambientado en Egipto.</p><p>Después de esta sesión relajante, para comer podemos ir a <a href=\\"#xera\\"><b>Xera Restaurant</b><b> </b></a>ubicado en el raval ofrece una cocina catalana moderna. Es una gran experiencia, prueba de ello poseen otro restaurante pegado a ellos llamado <a href=\\"#rao\\"><b>RAÓ restaurant</b><b> </b></a> con una cocina vanguardista que cautiva a sus comensales con ceviches, pescados y platos innovadores.</p><p>Por la tarde nos dirigimos a Plaza España y nos situaremos delante de las imponentes Torres Venecianas que nos abrirá paso a contemplar por una parte la Fuente de Montjuic (ahora en desuso debido a la sequera en Barcelona) y por otra parte el imponente <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#art\\"><b>Museo Nacional d&#8217;Art de Barcelona</b></a>. En este punto solo os puedo recomendar que os dejéis llevar por la belleza del lugar. </p><p>Tras pasear y observar los alrededores nos dirigimos al <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#teatro\\"><b>Teatro Griego</b><b> </b></a>con una belleza sin igual, donde pasar la tarde. En sus alrededores hay un jardín e incluso un pequeño estanque. Te servirá para relajarte y cada cierto tiempo suelen hacer actuaciones culturales, te recomiendo entrar en su página web y mirar la programación.</p><p>Os recomiendo acabar la tarde en el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#olimpico\\"><b>Anillo Olímpico de Montjuic</b></a> donde se celebraron los juegos de 1992. Es una zona muy amplia, por lo tanto, tendrás intimidad y no habrá multitudes. </p><p>Para cenar e ir concluyendo vuestro lugar es<a href=\\"#amposta\\"><b> Bodega Amposta</b><b> </b></a>un lugar de tapas y platos principales con una ambientación elegante que nos preparará para nuestro último lugar. <a href=\\"#hcolon\\"><b>El Hotel Catalon</b><strong>ia</strong></a>, es muy poco conocido pero en la parte interior del hotel, en la planta baja hay una coctelería que está abierta las 24h del día e incluso puedes pedir comida.</p>                	<p>Hoy he pensado en algo diferente? pero tranquilos, antes de aventurarnos, será mejor desayunar y calmar los sentidos. Por ello, para un mayor deleite, he considerado que un lugar menos frecuentado será ideal para vosotros, ya que se encuentra en un rinconcito escondido en el Barrio Gótico. Este local se proclama como especialista en café y os sorprenderá con sus presentaciones y sus grandes ventanales exteriores. Os invito a empezar el día en<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#side\\"><b> </b><b>Right Side Coffee Bar</b></a>.</p><p>Anteriormente os comentaba que había pensado en algo diferente y por ello he decidido <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#tattva\\"><b>Tattva Yoga Studio</b><b> </b></a>a 500 metros de la Right Side Coffee Bar, nos espera un centro de yoga con un ambiente insuperable. El centro de yoga es super bonito, tiene una energía especial y los profesores también. </p><p>Simplemente ve allí y te lo agradecerás a ti mismo y a los increíbles maestros más tarde. Recomiendo llamar antes para informarse. Si no conseguís reservar aquí, otra opción por la zona es <a href=\\"#lotus\\"><b>Happy Lotus Massage Therapy &amp; Yoga Barcelona</b></a> que abre los fines de semana (hay que reservar cita).</p><p>Tras salir nos dirigimos al Born a pasear por la Plaça Comercial en ella encontrarás desde el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#born\\"><b>Centro Cultural del Born</b><b> </b></a>es un precioso edificio de finales del siglo XX. En su interior posee exposiciones y en él se encuentra el <a href=\\"#yacimiento\\"><b>Yacimiento del Born</b></a>, ruinas excavadas de la ciudad del siglo XVIII muy bien conservadas. </p><p>Por los alrededores hay muchos bares por si os apetece hacer un vermut. Mi recomendación personal es <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#drstra\\"><strong>Dr. Stravinsky</strong></a>, uno de los 50 mejores bares del mundo. Por ello os daré otra opción: <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#bubita\\"><b>Bubita Sangria Bar</b><b> </b></a>lugar un poco más discreto donde estaréis igual de bien.</p><p>Ya por último os recomiendo comer en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#buon\\"><b>Buon Appetito</b></a>, restaurante que sirve pizzas, pasta y ensaladas y ofrece un menú diaria que es la opción más asequible. Otra opción en la zona es <a href=\\"#san\\"><b>San Pedrito</b></a>, restaurante de gastronomía mexicana con ambientazo.</p><p>En la tarde aprovecha para dar un paseo por Passeig de Colom<b>. </b></p><p>Si queréis disfrutar la ciudad y el puerto de Barcelona con las mejores vistas os recomiendo <a href=\\"#sagardi\\"><b>Sagardi 1881</b></a>. Está en lo alto del Museo de Historia de Catalunya. Una vez arriba tendrás una vista exclusiva del puerto, con un DJ en vivo y con una oferta gastronómica mediterránea. </p><p>Luego dirígete a Passeig de Joan Borbó hasta llegar a la playa de la Barceloneta, este será nuestro nuevo destino. Caminad hasta el <a href=\\"#vela\\"><b>Hotel Vela (Hotel W)</b></a> y ubicaros en la parte trasera de él. Es una zona ideal para terminar la tarde viendo el atardecer. Además si os apetece a 5 minutos está <a href=\\"#velissima\\"><b>Velissima Barcelona</b><b> </b></a>restaurante italiano, donde podéis hacer una copa o comer. Otras recomendaciones están en la parte de delante del hotel donde hay numerosos restaurantes a elegir: Gallito, Wok Home, Pez Vela?.</p><p>¡A disfrutar!</p>\t\t	401	relax-bcn-.png	1488,1489,1490,1491,1492,1493,1494,1495	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	1060,1067,1050,1044,1068,1076,1077,1047,1046,1073,1056,1075,1069,1045,1072,1055,1080,1061,1058,1048,1052,1049,1062,1053,1065,1064,1057,1070,1079,1054,1078,1051,1059,1071,1066,1081,1063,1074	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=18FGazF_DO_-equdA4yx6Jltr23fn2hQ&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtqyh8WRDG9t	price_1Q2TK2AFILSEnUZXIGGTUadM	1	S	S	Vive la fusión perfecta de relajación y delicias gourmet en Barcelona, donde la serenidad se combina con experiencias culinarias irresistibles. ?????	\N	\N	Relax & Gourmet 3 Dias	prod_QuotuiLT4a68hX	price_1Q2zFnAFILSEnUZXGpGSnr28	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_fZeeY3aRn1dA5AQbLJ	\N	plink_1Q3Ao1AFILSEnUZX2ZcvuTss	3Dias	38	N
402	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:25:52	2024-11-22 07:10:27	22224	2024-02-16 00:00:00	BCN04 - Gluten Free	Gluten free	gluten-free	<strong><span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\">Disfruta de la gastronomía sin preocupaciones con las recomendaciones de los mejores sitios sin gluten de la ciudad.</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Sabemos lo que cuesta encontrar un sitio que ofrezca comida sin gluten y no preocuparte mientras comes tranquilamente. Tenemos las mejores recomendaciones de un local para que no te agobies pensando y buscando dónde comer. Disfruta además de algunas recomendaciones culturales de tu anfitrión por la misma zona de los restaurantes.</span>	38	foodie-bcn.jpg	3	<p>¡Hola! Bienvenidos/as a Barcelona. Estas son mis recomendaciones para que paséis unos días de lujo sin preocuparos por el gluten. Para todos los restaurantes recomiendo consultar horarios y reservar para aseguraros disponibilidad.</p><p>Empezamos el día en el barrio de el Eixample. Para desayunar os recomiendo <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#equilibrium\\">Equilibrium Café</a>, </b>un lugar vegano, con platos variados, sabrosos y energéticos. </p><p>Después de reponer fuerzas, una manera satisfactoria de empezar el día es adentrarnos en la Barcelona modernista. Por ello nos dirigiremos a un Palacio Modernista construido por el famoso arquitecto Catalán Josep Puig i Cadafalch. La obra se llama <a href=\\"#maca3\\"><b>Palau Macaya</b></a><b> </b>y actualmente es un centro de convenciones. Recomiendo observar el edificio o acceder y empaparse del arte modernista, no os dejará indiferentes. </p><p>Una vez concluida la visita, es hora de caminar hacia la <a href=\\"#fransales\\"><b>Parroquia de San Francisco de Sales</b></a><b> </b>una imponente iglesia de tendéncia neogótica. Pienso que son de esos edificios que en ocasiones pasan desapercibidos pero que son auténticas obras de arte.</p><p>Después os recomiendo ir a la <a href=\\"#purisima\\"><b>Basílica de la Purísima Concepción</b></a>. Una obra que da encanto al distrito del Eixample, posee un patio interior con un pequeño jardín. Ideal para estar tranquilo, ya que no es muy concurrido. También recomiendo pasar por Carrer Roger de Llúria 49, C/ del Consell de Cent, 340, 08009 donde encontraremos un edifico llamado <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#casacerda\\"><b>las Casas de Cerdà </b></a>con murales venecianos plasmados en todo el edificio. Una de las primeras viviendas unifamiliares que recuperó los dibujos originales de 1863 con una restauración que se hizo en 2013. Justo en frente del edificio de Consell de Cent 340 se encuentra el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#1864\\"><b>Hotel Catalonia Eixample 1864</b></a> que es la otra Casa Cerdà con murales. </p><p>Para los amantes de la arqueoligía y la historia, otra joya que podéis visitar por la zona del Eixample es el <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#egipcio\\">Museo Egipcio</a>.</b> </p><p>Por los alrededores os recomiendo comer en <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#malatxabar\\">Malatxa Bar</a>,</b> un restaurante con mucha oferta gastronómica sin gluten. Os recomiendo las croquetas?buenísimas!!</p><p>Después de comer os recomiendo dos opciones:</p><ol><li> El barrio de Gracia: Si cruzáis la Avenida Diagonal podéis ir a los <a href=\\"#munos1\\"><b>Jardines de Muñoz Ramonet</b></a>, más desconocidos pero muy bonitos. Os recomiendo pasear por Gracia tranquilamente, sigue manteniendo ese espíritu de barrio y podéis ir a ver la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#vicens\\"><b>Casa Vicens</b></a>. </li></ol><p>En Gracia para comer o cenar tenéis el <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#gut\\">Gut</a>,</b> un pequeño local de comida mediterránea. A unos 5 minutos el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#tag\\"><b>Obrador Gluten Tag</b></a>! dónde TODO es gluten free y es una opción más dulce. </p><ol start=\\"2\\"><li> El barrio gótico y pasear por el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#boqueria\\"><b>Mercado de la boqueria</b></a>, visitar el graffiti de la Plaza del guaje en homenaje a el dueño del bar Los Baskos, o acceder de manera gratuita a los<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#rubio\\"><b> Jardins de Rubió i Lluch</b></a>. Además cuenta con un bar y es un lugar escondido de Barcelona, un sitio de escape 100% recomendado.</li></ol><p>Aquí en la noche para una cena más formal <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#ville\\"><b>En Ville</b></a> es ideal. La temática del restaurante y sus platos marcan la diferencia. Os recomiendo el pulpo. </p>                	<p>Para este día he pensado algo diferente. Por ello conoceremos el distrito de Poblenou, conocido por tener identidad propia gracias a sus pequeños comercios, sus grandes edificios y por la playa de Bogatell. A modo de conocer el distrito y los puntos de interés más relevantes de su entorno. Empezaremos en Glòries, ubicada en la línea roja del metro L1. Cerca hay una pastelería llamada<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#lupita\\"><b> </b><b>Casa Lupita Gluten Free</b></a> dedicada al gluteen free con gran variedad de oferta, además de poseer hamburguesas o sandwich. Cuidan mucho la estética y al cliente. </p><p>Junto a la parada de metro encontraremos por un lado <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#agbar\\"><b>La Torre Agbar</b></a>, uno de los edificios más emblemáticos de Barcelona. Posee un mirador donde poder contemplar en su máximo esplendor el distrito de Poblenou, y el <b><a href=\\"#museoarte\\">Museo de Arte de Diseño</a>,</b> en su alrededor hay jardines y es ideal para comenzar la mañana y disfrutar de la mágica Barcelona.</p><p>Para comer por la zona podemos dar un paseo por la Rambla de Poblenou, lo ideal es ir observando y ser curioso. Hay muchos lugares para tapear, comer y se respira un buen ambiente. </p><p><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#apriboca\\"><b>ApriBoca</b></a>, es un restaurante italiano con opciones de pasta, pizzas y postres sin gluten. También el restaurante <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#quinto\\"><b>El Quinto</b></a> dónde la mayoría de la carta es sin gluten. Mi recomendación personal y que tiene que figurar en vuestra experiencia y más aún si disfrutais de una buenas tapas debeis ir al <a href=\\"#unio\\"><strong>Bar la Unió</strong></a></p><p>Después de comer si os apetece algo de cultura, os recomiendo varios museos: <a href=\\"#centroarte\\"><b>Ideal Centro de Artes Digitales De Barcelona</b></a>, con exposiciones temporales que varían según las fechas y el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#framis\\"><b>Museo Can Framis</b></a> con obras de arte contemporáneas catalanas. Y por supuesto deberéis pasear por los <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#ca\\"><b>Jardines de Ca l\\ Aranyó</b></a>, un lugar único en Barcelona.  Por este barrio podréis pasear hasta la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#bogatell\\"><b>Platja de Bogatell</b></a>.</p><p>Por la noche os recomiendo un <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#caber\\"><b>Cabernet Bar</b></a>. Una opción ideal si os apetece comer mientras os tomáis una copa y disfrutais de un ambiente más nocturno. Os recomiendo las gambas al ajillo.</p>                	<p>Hoy nos iremos al Barrio Gótico<b>,</b> concretamente en la Plaza Sant Jaume tenemos <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#conesa\\"><b>Conesa</b></a>, una de las mejores bocaterías de la ciudad, la opción sin gluten tendrá 1 euro añadido por el pan. Por la zona podéis visitar la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#neri\\"><b>Plaza Sant Felipe Neri</b></a>, es una pequeña plaza con una iglesia barroca deteriorada por las bombas de la Guerra Civil.</p><p>Luego bajaremos hasta la <a href=\\"#plor1\\"><strong>Plaza George Orwell</strong></a>  conocida como la \\"calle del tripi\\" y dedicada al novelista y periodista que vivió en Barcelona de 1936 a 1937. Por la zona encontrareis <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#vegee\\">Vegetalia</a>, </b>un restaurante con gran variedad sin gluten, recomendamos la paella vegetal y el wok tailandés con noodles de arroz. Otra opción es <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#voca\\"><b>A vocados</b></a> en la calle Ferran (si cenáis ahí os animo a probar los cócteles de <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#snoo\\"><b>Snooker</b></a>).</p><p>Para la tarde y a modo de conocer en profundidad el barrio visitaremos <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#mayorbcn\\"><b>La Sinagoga Mayor de Barcelona</b></a>, construida entre el siglo III y IV es una de las más antiguas de Europa conservando su arquitectura medieval. La entrada es gratuita y merece la pena ser visitada.</p><p>Una vez hayas visto esto subiremos por el barrio gótico para contemplar la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#arcediano\\"><b>Casa del Arcediano</b><b> </b></a>está cerca de La Catedral de Barcelona que también recomiendo visitar. La casa del Arcediano se caracteriza por ser una mansión renacentista del siglo XV con detalles góticos y un pequeño patio. La entrada es gratuita.</p><p>Llegada la hora de la cena os recomiendo un restaurante pasando Via Laietana, se llama <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#manduca\\"><b>Manduca Gluten Free</b></a>. Encontrareis gran variedad de comida con temática healthy. Probaría sus smoothies y la pasta con champiñones. </p><p>Las opciones Gluten free son muy diversas por ellos os dejaré varias recomendaciones:</p><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#fileruso\\"><b>El filete Ruso</b></a> unas carnes para chuparse los dedos).</li><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#nectari\\"><b>Nectari</b><b> </b></a>(estrella Michelín). </li></ul><p>Si queréis cenar a precios asequibles:</p><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#marius\\"><b>Cal Marius</b></a>: gastrotaberna sin gluten y cervezas aptas. Ubicado en Diagonal.</li><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#m2\\"><b>M2 Gluten Free</b></a>, variedad de cocina internacional y nacional. </li><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#martita\\"><b>La Martita</b></a>: cocina mediterránea con opciones veganas. </li></ul><p>Si os apetece dulce, podéis ir a:</p><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#jansana\\">Jansana</a>.</b> Te ofrece una amplia variedad de panes, pasteles, bollería y postres 100% libres de gluten. Elaborados con ingredientes frescos y siguiendo recetas tradicionales, sus productos satisfarán a los paladares más exigentes.</li><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#chock\\"><b>Chöck Barcelona</b></a>  Degusta sus famosos «krönuts», una reinterpretación del cruasán relleno de crema y cobertura de chocolate, o elige entre una gran variedad de donuts, tartas, helados y otras delicias elaboradas con el mejor cacao.</li></ul><p> ¡Que disfrutéis! </p>\t\t	402	foodie-bcn.jpg	1471,1473,1474,1475,1476,1478,1479	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	1112,1100,1102,1085,1107,1119,1115,1097,1091,1123,1108,1117,1101,1096,1082,1092,1087,1103,1122,1105,1090,1095,1121,1114,1098,1086,1120,1089,1116,1094,1104,1099,1062,1118,1093,1083,1084,1106,1110,1109,1113,1111	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1MRNoqax-WMq-Mc0WNoZpavf9QY1yhyA&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHt9oGvhBCohO	price_1Q2TK2AFILSEnUZXX7zUyxFs	1	S	N	Disfruta de la gastronomía sin preocupaciones con las recomendaciones de los mejores sitios sin gluten de la ciudad.	\N	\N	Gluten free	prod_QuotzCAjUrWw34	price_1Q2zFnAFILSEnUZXBzmgbUbv	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_8wM2bh3oV1dA7IYdTS	\N	plink_1Q3Ao2AFILSEnUZXxWua2aPm	3Dias	39	N
403	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:25:56	2024-11-22 07:10:27	24591	2024-03-27 00:00:00	BCN07 - Foodie &amp; Traveler - DEMO	Foodie & Traveler 3 Days	foodie--traveler-3-days	<strong><span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\">Disfruta de la gastronomía sin preocupaciones con las recomendaciones de los mejores sitios sin gluten de la ciudad.</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Sabemos lo que cuesta encontrar un sitio que ofrezca comida sin gluten y no preocuparte mientras comes tranquilamente. Tenemos las mejores recomendaciones de un local para que no te agobies pensando y buscando dónde comer. Disfruta además de algunas recomendaciones culturales de tu anfitrión por la misma zona de los restaurantes.</span>	\N	foodie-bcn.jpg	3	<p>Welcome to Barcelona! I am your host and in this experience I am going to recommend my favorite restaurants and places in the city so that you can get to know Barcelona. Before starting, I recommend that if the third day is a Sunday, you start with day three first and leave day one for the third day. This way you can visit all the planned places. :)</p><p>To maintain that traveler essence we will move away from that central and iconic part of Barcelona. Therefore, as a way to begin the experience, I recommend visiting the upper neighborhoods of the city, specifically we will move through the Les Corts district, it is the third smallest neighborhood in the city but it is charming.  </p><p>As a way to start the day by delighting our senses of sight and taste, I recommend having breakfast at <a href=\\"#mommy\\"><b>¡Oh Mommy</b></a>  a brunch restaurant located in the center of Les Corts. I could define this place with one word: delightful.  </p><p>After this feast, we begin our adventure and to do so we will move to the <a href=\\"#cervantes1\\"><b>Cervantes Park</b></a>  located in Pedralbes. It is synonymous with peace and beauty. In Cervantes Park you can breathe fresh air and in the company of its rose gardens, its grass areas and its vegetation it is like a green lung within the Pedralbes neighborhood.</p><p>I recommend spending the morning here, but if the traveler spirit drives you to do more, I have more recommendations for you :)  </p><p>On the one hand, the <a href=\\"#palacio1\\"><b>Gardens of the Pedralbes Palace</b></a><b> </b>a place with landscaped gardens and fountains, and the garden is crowned by a historic palace. This Garden will be an ideal place to end our tour by heading to the  <a href=\\"#nou1\\"><b>Camp Nou</b></a> , a great international symbol of the city of Barcelona. </p><p>I recommend going down Carrer de Marti i Franquès, to soak up the atmosphere that is lived and felt in Pedralbes, one of the best neighborhoods in Barcelona.  </p><p>I recommend you visit the field facilities and its surroundings. To finish, I recommend eating at<b> </b><a href=\\"#turuleca1\\"><b>The Turuleca</b></a>, a Peruvian gastronomy restaurant with dishes with a lot of color and a lot of flavor. A gastronomy very well criticized by the international media. Your essentials are the ceviche with the famous tiger&#8217;s milk and its sautéed loin ??</p><p>In the afternoon I recommend something more central and that is why you can take a walk along Passeig de Gracia and see its most iconic buildings, ( <a href=\\"#pedrera1\\"><b>La Pedrera</b></a><b> </b><b>and</b><b> </b><a href=\\"#batllo1\\"><b>Casa Batlló</b></a> ) with Casa Batlló I recommend looking at it from the <a href=\\"#estacion1\\"><b>Servicio Estación</b></a> building , where you can see the back of the building and it is a little-known place. </p><p>Near La Pedrera I recommend you go to the <a href=\\"#dutti1\\"><b>Massimo Dutti store</b></a>  which is located in a modernist building with a garden inside. Then go to Plaza Cataluña and finish walking along Las Ramblas. Over there eat at the restaurant  <a href=\\"#canaletas1\\"><b>gutters</b></a>. In the middle of Las Ramblas it is  Ale-Hop , entering is another modernist palace.</p><p>Now with a full belly you can go to <a href=\\"#catedral1\\"><b>the Cathedral Square</b></a>  and stop for a photo at the \\"The Kiss\\" mural. Continue along Via Laietana to the port and walk along the  <a href=\\"#fusta1\\"><b>Moll de Fusta</b></a>, just in front of the port. Walk until you reach the  Columbus Statue and from here go to the <a href=\\"#raval2\\"><b>Barceló Raval Hotel</b></a>, is 11 minutes walking. Its rooftop has spectacular 360º views where it is incredible to see the sunset, and this is where you can end the day, but if you prefer it to be a place of passage, you can end up in  <a href=\\"#nacional1\\"><b>El Nacional</b></a> with a glass of cava.</p>                	<p>Today we will start in Eixample, and we will go to the Urgell stop on L1 of the Barcelona metro. Once here we had breakfast at  <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#eixa1\\"><b>Eixampeling</b></a> is a happy and colorful cafe where we can surround ourselves with the best vibes, and then head to Plaza España and enjoy Montjuic.</p><p>Inside Montjuic there are too many things to see, so it will take us all morning. Some of my recommendations are the following:  <a href=\\"#historic1\\"><b>Historical Botanical Garden</b></a>, just behind the imposing National Museum of Art of Catalonia. Admission is free, I describe the place as one of those hidden corners in Barcelona, ??that little is known about and apart from the place itself which is super beautiful, the fact that it is little known gives it its charm.  </p><p>At the end we headed to the <a href=\\"#griego1\\"><b>Greek Theater Gardens</b></a> , an essential place where you will find a mini amphitheater worth visiting.</p><p>From here I recommend eating in a privileged place in Barcelona, ??little known if you don&#8217;t frequent the area, is the <a href=\\"#oleum1\\"><b>Restaurant Òleum</b></a>  located inside the Museum. From start to finish it is quite an experience. And the atmosphere lends itself to it, what better than eating inside a museum. In case you want to have another option, mine is  <a href=\\"#amposta1\\"><b>Bodega Amposta</b></a> , a little further away but excellent in terms of quality-price, it is also a cozy restaurant. </p><p>In the afternoon I propose the Gràcia neighborhood, a neighborhood with a special atmosphere with a much more rural past, breathing its Catalan spirit and its more street culture. It is considered a town within a city.  </p><p>The afternoon is focused on cultural elements and symbols of the Gràcia neighborhood. Our first point of reference will be the  <a href=\\"#nebot1\\"><b>Residential building by Mario Català Nebot</b></a> , in the beginning no one understood him, but with the passage of time his creations have become an object of worship with psychedelic windows and wavy shapes. Many Barcelonans call it the Barcelona pool. </p><p>Then we will go to Passeig de Sant Joan, here we will find two sculptures with symbolism, on the one hand the Little <a href=\\"#roja1\\"><b>Red Riding Hood Fountain</b></a>, is a curious bronze image from 1921. It shows an empowered Little Red Riding Hood as if she had subdued the Wolf. A few meters away we find  <a href=\\"#hercules1\\"><b>The Fountain of Hercules</b></a> , they say it is one of the oldest statues in Barcelona, ??it was inaugurated in 1802 and was built to celebrate the wedding and visit of King Charles IX.</p><p>And from here we head to <a href=\\"#sol1\\"><b>Plaza del Sol</b></a>  emblematic and meeting place of the Gràcia neighborhood, ideal for a place to pause while enjoying the sunrise of Barcelona. What better than to put yourself on the scene and go to  <a href=\\"#cafe1\\"><b>Coffee of the sun</b></a>, its most legendary bar. In addition, there are modernist style buildings in its surroundings.</p><p>To finish dinner in <a href=\\"#nua1\\"><b>Nüa</b></a>, a futuristic and healthy restaurant that I love. And to end the day a cocktail at  <a href=\\"#19681\\"><b>Marcelino 1968</b></a> .</p>                	<p>Good morning! For this day I have thought of something vintage&#8230; for them we will have to go to Glòries, this on L1 of the Barcelona metro. In the area have breakfast in  <a href=\\"#wapa1\\"><b>Wapa Barcelona Restaurant</b></a> , is next to the Agbar Tower and is a quiet place to start the day. </p><p> </p><p>Once ready we will go to one of the largest second-hand markets in Barcelona. Is he  <a href=\\"#dels1\\"><b>Mercat dels Encants</b></a>, it is very curious to see and you will find a lot of curiosities. There is always something good to see.</p><p>If you still want more, a little further away you will find <a href=\\"#encants1\\"><b>Petits Encants</b></a> , in Arc del Triomf, an antique store with a large number of curiosities.</p><p>And eat at <a href=\\"#elsa1\\"><b>Elsa and Fred</b></a><b> </b>where you can make the menu of the day for 15 euros or order à la carte. A cozy restaurant with grilled dishes.</p><p>In the afternoon our destination is Barcelona. A good morning starts with a delicious brunch facing the sea in  <a href=\\"#cala1\\"><b>The Cala</b></a>  (Barceloneta). After touring the  Maritime ride by bike, there is a place called Rent Bike BCN located in Barceloneta or Online Bike Rental located in El Born, where you can rent a bike to enjoy the experience and take a tour around El Born and discover its corners.</p><p>Another option is to go to <a href=\\"#puerto1\\"><b>Torre de Jaime I &#8211; Teleférico del Puerto de Barcelona</b></a><b> </b>and enjoy the views and good weather of Barcelona. </p><p>To eat, <a href=\\"#xampa\\"><b>Xampanyet</b></a> is one of the usual bars that I like, otherwise you can <a href=\\"#bubbles1\\"><b>Rooster &amp; Bubbles</b></a> with a more modern touch.</p><p>Enjoy Barcelona!</p>\t\t	403	pexels-nesrin-danan-3193818.jpg	1496,1497,1498,1499,1500,1501,1502,1584	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1142,1127,1133,959,1134,1125,1147,1138,967,1126,1140,1139,1136,1144,1149,1132,1151,1135,1148,1152,1143,1141,1157,1131,1146,1154,1145,1137,1129,1128,1156,1155,1150,1124	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1_gJsoEH6VZjUsFC97FxycsUE7TIW72E&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtAvml5vlEYl	price_1Q2TK3AFILSEnUZXXtJn2kwi	1	N	N	Disfruta de la gastronomía sin preocupaciones con las recomendaciones de los mejores sitios sin gluten de la ciudad.	\N	\N	Foodie & Traveler 3 Days	prod_QuotyizfBIOxer	price_1Q2zFoAFILSEnUZX0YiqJDqS	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_6oE17df7De0mfbq6rr	\N	plink_1Q3Ao2AFILSEnUZXp5YrpPmP	3Dias	40	N
404	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:26:00	2024-11-22 01:14:08	23117	2024-02-19 00:00:00	BCN05 - Parks and Gardens	Parks & Gardens 3 Days	parks--gardens-3-days	<b>Discover the city\\ s secret parks and gardens.</b> Would you like to discover secret gardens in the city? Immerse yourself in the urban nature of the city by visiting the city\\ s most beautiful parks and gardens, and enjoy the cultural and gastronomic recommendations of your local host for a very green day out!	\N	foodie-bcn.jpg	3	<p>Hello and welcome to Barcelona! In this experience we are going to visit my favorite parks and corners of Barcelona, from some of the best known to others more hidden and with a special charm?let?s start!</p><p>In the morning, we explore the charming neighborhood of Plaza España, one of the most emblematic places in the Catalan capital. To enhance our experience, we will start by recharging our batteries with two delicious breakfast suggestions.</p><p>On the one hand <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sand\\"><b>SandwiChez</b></a> <b> </b>(Gran Vía Street) with a coffee and some delicious chocolate muffins and as a second alternative <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#tartela\\"><b>Tartela BCN</b></a> with a healthier and more sophisticated option. </p><p>Once prepared, we get down to work to discover one of my favorite places where I go every weekend, the Jardins de Joan Maragall. <a href=\\"#joan\\"><b>Joan Maragall Gardens</b></a> (only open on Saturdays and Sundays) is an elegant garden with fountains and gardens. But don?t worry, I have more options for you if you don?t coincide on the days indicated.</p><p>And this recommendation is the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#botanic\\"><b>Historical Botanical Garden</b></a>located behind the great Museo Nacional d?Arts de Barcelona. This garden was a former quarry and you will find unusual plants from the Eurosiberian region. Admission is free and it is one of those places few frequented in Barcelona where I guarantee you will be able to disconnect.</p><p>Once we have finished contemplating the garden, in the area a 15 minute walk away we will find the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#botanico\\"><b>Botanical Garden of Barcelona</b></a> just behind the Olympic Stadium of Montjuic, emblematic place of Barcelona for hosting the Olympic Games in 1992. The entrance fee is 5 euros and inside you will find international flora chosen to grow in Mediterranean climate, also has views of the sea and the city.</p><p>To end the morning go for lunch at <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#xalet\\"><b>El Xalet de Montjuic</b></a> located in the surrounding area. This restaurant located on top of a hill with panoramic views of the city, is a gastronomic space that combines Mediterranean cuisine and signature cuisine. Another option is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#xemei\\"><b>Xemei</b></a>a Venetian restaurant offering pasta and seafood dishes.</p><p>In the afternoon we will move around the raval and born neighborhoods. Our first stop will be the Antiguo<a href=\\"#santa\\"><b> </b><b>Hospital de la Santa Cruz</b></a> 5 minutes from the L3 stop of the green line of the subway. This hospital is an ancient medieval complex that has a library inside, in addition to what we are interested in <a href=\\"#lluc\\"><b>The Rubió and Lluc Gardens</b></a> a little known place in the raval, where you can relax and get away from the hustle and bustle of the city. It also has a bar where you can have tapas or a drink. </p><p>And if you are in the mood for culture I recommend the <a href=\\"#pau\\"><br /><br /><b>Ancient monastery of Sant Pau del Campo</b><br /><br /></a>The building is a beautiful and secret building in Barcelona, many are satisfied with just seeing the outside of it. In my case, whenever I can, I am one of those people who go inside to enjoy this Romanesque monastery. Admission is free.</p><p>As a transition to the born we will go to the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#casaig\\"><b>Garden of the Ignacio de Puig House </b></a>is located near the Ramblas, 3 minutes from the Liceu metro station L3 and is an oasis of peace little known by the inhabitants of the city.</p><p>At this point and as a break there is a very top place that I usually frequent to finish the evening is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#taverna\\"><b>Irati Taverna Basca</b></a> is a restaurant with a charm of its own. It focuses on skewers and its strong point is the Basque grill. I recommend trying the cider and the skewers that are released from time to time. </p><p>To end this great day discovering the serenity of Barcelona we concluded by heading to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#ateneu\\"><b>El Jardí de l?Ateneu</b></a> is located in an emblematic building, outside you will find a sign with the following text ?Ateneu Barcelonès?. It has a beautiful garden and is also a restaurant in case you feel like having something to eat.</p><p>Finally, we went to the<b> <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#musica\\">Palau de la Música Catalana</a> </b>to observe the great work of Lluís Domènech i Montaner in modernist style. Inside it has a little known cafeteria frequented by residents of the area, also as a way to conclude the day you can have dinner at <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#pizzicato\\">PIZZICATO</a></b> the Palau?s restaurant. With great attention from the staff and an elegant atmosphere to enjoy the night.</p>                	<p>Ready for this new day? Today I have a different type of recommendations and we will be moving through different neighborhoods. I have been thinking about the District of Les Corts and the charming neighborhood of Gràcia.</p><p>Our first stop will be Pedralbes, here we will start the day with a delicious brunch at <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#salt\\"><b>Salt & Pepper ? Burger and Brunch </b></a>a place where they take care of the product and offer generous portions. Once ready, let?s get started! We turn to the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#pedralbes\\"><b>Pedralbes Palace Gardens</b></a>a beautiful place with landscaped gardens and fountains. The Royal Palace of Pedralbes is located inside the building. is a palace that in the past was used by royalty, is endowed with Mediterranean gardens and a fountain designed by Antonio Gaudi. </p><p>Believe me, they are worth it and you will spend a lot of time walking around and observing everything it contains. At the end of this tour, the<a href=\\"#william\\"><b> William Shakespeare Gardens </b></a>with a lake and several fountains, this garden is a little bit smaller than the previous one but it is a very quiet place and from this location we can go towards the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#pabellones\\"><b>Güell Pavilions </b></a>a complex in ruins that was commissioned to Antonio Gaudí at the end of the 19th century. It is full of mythological and aesthetic details. The entrance fee is 6 euros.</p><p>Finally, I recommend the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#amelia\\"><b>Villa Amelia Gardens </b></a>with a small pond in the middle of the garden crowned by a sculpture by Ricard Sala. It is farther away than the previous ones, but it could not be missed because of the peace it offers. </p><p>At this point I have a little surprise for your palate. Taking advantage of the area you can not miss for anything in the world and in my personal opinion a must of Pedralbes is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#abadessa\\"><b>El Jardí de l?Abadessa</b></a> is a restaurant with an elegant garden terrace. Taking advantage of the hour I recommend the daily menu, an excellent option, but you also have the option of a la carte. It is one of my favorite places in the upper part of Barcelona.</p><p>In the afternoon we will move around the neighborhood of Gràcia. I propose two alternatives. In case you want to move around the city and cover more areas, I recommend that before going to Gràcia, you go to the <a href=\\"#purissima\\"><b>Basilica of the Immaculate Conception</b><b> </b></a>built in the XIV century, it has very remarkable elements and is a place of peace and tranquility. Inside there is a beautiful garden. </p><p>Otherwise we head directly to Gràcia and our first stop will be<a href=\\"#silencio\\"><b> El Jardí del Silenci</b></a> which serves as an open-air civic center with workshops and exhibitions. Another interesting place to see that I recently discovered is <a href=\\"#olokuti\\"><b>Olokuti Grácia</b></a> is a store with household items and materials made by local people. </p><p>At this point I recommend a walk through the charming neighborhood of gracia with a much more rural past, in which many stand out as a village in the middle of the city. I recommend<a href=\\"#diamant\\"><b> the Plaça del diamant.</b></a>This square is named after a classic of Catalan literature, it is one of the most famous squares and there you will find a sculpture in honor of the book called ?La colometa?. </p><p>Finally and to end the afternoon I recommend the Plaça del Sol was built at the end of the 19th century when Gràcia was still a village. Around it are several modernist buildings. One of its most mythical places es <b><a href=\\"#sol\\">Cafè del Sol</a>,</b> inside you will find table games and an international tapas bar.</p><p>For dinner and to end another fantastic day, if you like pintxos I recommend you to visit<a href=\\"#gasterea\\"><b> Gasterea </b></a>Basque style. In case you want something more sophisticated and try modern Spanish gastronomy, your place is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#barra\\"><b>Barra Alta Restaurant</b></a>.</p>                	<p>For the third day I recommend you to leave the big parks. We will head to the Sant Gervasi neighborhood and have breakfast at the <a href=\\"#cafeteria\\"><b>Cafeteria</b></a> in the science square, located in an impotent modernist building, worthy of being contemplated. Before we head to our destination, you can access the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#cosmocaixa\\"><b>CosmoCaixa Observatory</b></a> located in the building. I suggest buying tickets online.</p><p>After filling your belly and enjoying the imposing modernist building. We headed to the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#tibidabo\\"><b>Tibidabo</b></a> It has one of the best viewpoints in Barcelona and several places of interest that I will mention later. It was inaugurated in 1905 and is the highest peak located in the Sierra de Collserola. </p><p>The ticket costs 35 euros and I recommend buying them online. The easiest way to access is to go to Estació inferior less than 10 minutes walk from the CosmoCaixa Observatory, the entrance fee is 12 euros round trip.</p><p>Once upstairs I encourage you to visit the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sagrados\\"><b>Temple of the Sacred Heart of Jesus </b></a>built in the 20th century, it stands out for its huge bronze sculpture at the top of the expiatory temple.</p><p>In the area I usually eat at <a href=\\"#tb\\"><b>The TB Bar </b></a>inside it has a gazebo and the dish I recommend is the paella with foie.</p><p>In the afternoon we will go to the emblematic <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#ciutadella\\"><b>Ciutadella Park </b></a>A MUST IN THE CITY created at the end of the 19th century. It is a meeting place where you can have a picnic and even rent a boat, in the area of the fountain, the heart of the Ciutadella. Prices are around 6 to 7 euros per person. </p><p>In the park you can find people doing yoga, taking dance classes, playing instruments, reading, relaxing and spending the day. When you enter you will realize that you can easily spend the whole afternoon exploring the park. Inside you will find bars in case you feel like having a drink while you relax.</p><p>Leaving the park you can visit the famous <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#arc\\"><b>Arc del Triomf </b></a>built as the main entrance to the Universal Exposition of 1888. In front of the Arc del Triomf metro station on the L1 is the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#electro\\"><b>Central Catalana de Electricidad</b></a>. It is a modernist building that goes unnoticed by the residents of Barcelona. It will serve as an element of passage to access to the <a href=\\"#norte\\"><b>North Station Park</b></a>. It is an urban park where you can end the day in the most relaxing way. </p><p>End up dining at <b><a href=\\"#fismuler\\">Fismuler</a>, </b> which has a wide gastronomic offer and sometimes there is live music. I recommend the razor clams au gratin. Another lesser-known and more international option is the restaurant <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#wen\\"><b>Wen Zhou Ramen II </b></a>They make a very good homemade ramen, they also have a great variety of dishes. </p>\t\t	404	jardines-bcn.jpeg	1480,1585,1586,1483,1587,1485,1588,1571	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1167,1192,1185,1179,1162,1183,1186,1193,1191,1187,1178,1170,1180,1195,1168,1184,1176,1139,1024,1169,1160,1194,1181,956,1174,1172,1166,1173,1158,1159,1189,1182,1190,1163,1188,1177,1196,1175,1164	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1aCNqelvh2twRMYS15_-rdeOIHxGVTOM&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtUxx5dVBPOY	price_1Q2TK3AFILSEnUZX9N3LusC9	1	N	N	Discover the city\\ s secret parks and gardens.	\N	\N	Parks & Gardens 3 Days	prod_Quotdor6NLX9AN	price_1Q2zFoAFILSEnUZXqNRiomRX		https://buy.stripe.com/test_aEU8zF8Jf4pM4wMdTU		plink_1Q3Ao3AFILSEnUZXjEosvZYF	3Dias	41	N
405	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:26:05	2024-11-22 02:08:36	24593	2024-03-27 00:00:00	BCN08 - Bohemian & Vintage - DEMO	Bohemian & Vintage 3 Days	bohemian--vintage-3-days	<p><strong>Ideal experience for lovers of vintage and second hand in which you will discover places you will fall in love with.&nbsp;</strong>Come and visit the best markets in the city, the most diverse stores, gastronomic recommendations where you can enjoy local and international cuisine, brunches, exhibitions and curious places that you will love. Explore its most authentic neighborhoods and discover hidden treasures in every corner.</p>\\r\\n	\N	foodie-bcn.jpg	3	<p>Welcome to Barcelona! I am Violeta and I am a lover of everything vintage, in this experience I leave you my favorite places that I hope you enjoy as much as I do.</p><p>For the first day we will tour the El Gotic neighborhood, if you want to have breakfast in the area my recommendation is <a href=\\"#brunch1\\"><b>The Benedict Brunch Barcelona</b></a> , ??they have a very varied menu with all kinds of breakfasts and sweets?to fill your stomach well! </p><p>Once we have a full stomach, we can walk towards the Gotic and get lost in its streets where we will find a very good variety of vintage stores, my favorites in this area are  <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#blue1\\"><strong>Blue Goose</strong></a> (opens at 12), Le Swing Vintage? and you can?t miss the wedding dresses from  <a href=\\"#arca1\\"><b>L?Arca</b></a>! Since you are in the area, I recommend visiting the  <a href=\\"#fun1\\"><b>Big Fun Museum</b></a><b> </b>(an original museum with optical illusions where you can take photos and portraits of famous people made with food <b>)</b> , or the <a href=\\"#puig1\\"><b>Casa Ignacio de Puig Garden</b></a> , a small secret oasis in the center of the city.</p><p>To eat in the area I recommend having tapas or having a vermouth at the <a href=\\"#porta\\"><b>El Portalón</b></a> tavern , or if you prefer something healthier although it is a better known option, I really like the <a href=\\"#greens1\\"><b>Honest Greens</b></a> which is next to Plaza Catalunya., </p><p>After eating you can tour the Workshops Street. On this street there are countless vintage stores to spend hours in, one that I love to visit is  <a href=\\"#revo\\"><b>Revolver</b></a> where you can find new and second-hand records from all eras, and of course <b><a href=\\"#kilo1\\">Flamingo?s Vintage Kilo</a> ,</b> where the price of clothing is determined by the weight of the garment! In this area I also recommend having a drink at the <a href=\\"#moritz1\\"><b>Moritz Brewery</b></a> .</p><p>To end the day you can go to the Eixample neighborhood and pay tribute to yourself at <a href=\\"#or1\\"><b>O ??Retorniño</b></a>, a Galician restaurant specializing in fish and seafood, is a little further away but it is well worth it! If you fancy a closer and more sophisticated bar, you have  <a href=\\"#loli1\\"><b>The Lolita Barcelona</b></a> .</p>                	<p>This morning is a good time to visit <a href=\\"#mercate1\\"><b>El Mercat dels Encants</b></a><b> </b>/ Carrer de los Castillejos, 158 (Monday, Wednesday, Friday and Saturday), a market where I would dare to say that you can find anything you are looking for. For breakfast in the area, I like it  <b><a href=\\"#guli1\\">Giulietta Cafe</a> .</b> </p><p>After visiting the market you can head towards Poblenou for a walk, here we can visit <a href=\\"#cartes1\\"><b>IDEAL the Barcelona Digital Arts Center</b></a><b> </b>It has 3D projections of Klimt or Monet and it?s really cool to see <b>.</b> Or if you want to continue shopping, my favorites in the area are <a href=\\"#vpoble1\\"><b>Vintage Poblenou</b></a> and the Scandinavian furniture store <a href=\\"#noak1\\"><b>NOAK Room</b></a> is also worth it .</p><p>To eat in the area I recommend <a href=\\"#tavernicola1\\"><b>La Tavernicola</b></a><b> </b>a restaurant with Argentine dishes that you will love, or if you prefer you can go for a walk on the Rambla de Poblenou and end up eating at <a href=\\"#can2\\"><b>Can Recasens</b></a><b> </b>which is a very original restaurant with a shop selling typical products at the entrance <b>,</b> You will love their charcuterie or cheese boards! At the end, if you continue straight along the Rambla del Poblenou, you will arrive at the promenade where I love to stop to read or sit and look at the sea while the sun shines on me.  </p><p>There is nothing better to spend the afternoon than traveling to the Gracia neighborhood, one of the most bohemian and charming neighborhoods in the city. Here the possibilities are endless, we can start by visiting my favorite stores like  <b><a href=\\"#100armarios\\">Rummaging 1000 closets</a></b> and <a href=\\"#leopardo1\\"><b>Leopardo Leopardi Concept Store</b></a> <b>.</b> If you have come to grace from Monday to Friday you can also visit the <a href=\\"#saturnalia1\\"><b>Saturnalia Bookstore</b></a> <b>.</b> You can end up having a drink in Plaza del Sol , which is one of the meeting points in the neighborhood and has a great atmosphere every afternoon. </p><p>To end the day I recommend having tapas and a drink at <a href=\\"#coco1\\"><strong>Coco?s Secrets</strong></a>, a very charming place in Barcelona. The decoration will not leave you indifferent, they have theme nights every week, some days shows and live music! Another option is the  <a href=\\"#cpages1\\"><b>Café Pagés</b></a> if you fancy something more traditional. </p>                	<p>For this last day we cannot forget the Born neighborhood, where you will find contemporary art galleries and independent designer shops. For breakfast in the area, my recommendation is  <a href=\\"#pic1\\"><b>Picnic</b></a>  (Carrer del Comerç), when you enter, you will find a small, very well-lit place where you will feel in a very pleasant and familiar atmosphere. They have a very varied brunch menu from Friday to Sunday, don?t miss it!!</p><p>Afterwards we can walk through the streets of El Born, what we find most in the shops of El Born is the figure of the independent artisan/designer/antique dealer, with his own very marked discourse and far from the imposed artistic and fashion canons. to visit some of their stores like  <a href=\\"#ziggy1\\"><b>Ziggy Vintage</b> , <b>Carlos Segura</b></a> ? since you are in the area, I recommend visiting the Maxó Gallery or, if you feel like something sweet, the <a href=\\"#choco1\\"><b>Chocolate Museum</b></a>. To have tapas you can have something on one of the terraces of the Mercat de Santa Caterina.</p><p>If today were Sunday (a day when you can find many stores closed), don?t worry, I have a great alternative plan! He  <a href=\\"#antoni1\\"><b>Sant Antoni Sunday Market</b></a>, the best book market in Barcelona, ??old books, collector?s books, out-of-print books, postcard collecting, historical documents, comics, posters, movies, trading cards, video games, used and second-hand books? a real gem! If you are here at lunchtime you can have tapas at  <a href=\\"#tombs1\\"><b>The Three Tombs</b></a> . </p><p>If you still have energy in the afternoon, you can take a walk through the Raval, the bohemian neighborhood par excellence of Barcelona, ??visit the <a href=\\"#monica1\\"><b>Santa Mónica art center</b></a>  which is full of talented and upcoming artists. Here the street par excellence for vintage shops is Carrer de la  Riera Baixa (closed on Sundays), where you will find some that I usually frequent like <a href=\\"#80s\\"><b>Club 80?s</b></a> or the record store <a href=\\"#wah1\\"><b>Wah Wah Records</b></a>. In the area if you want to have a drink you have a bar with authentic Catalan tradition, the  <a href=\\"#marsella1\\"><b>Marseille bar</b></a> .</p><p>End of our route, I hope you enjoy Barcelona and come back soon to see more of this beautiful city?see you soon!!</p>\t\t	405	pexels-burst-374677.jpg	1505,1506,1551,1500,1508,1553,1589,1511	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1228,1200,1198,1220,1215,1223,1224,1219,1226,1205,1168,1210,1203,1211,1199,1217,1230,1206,1213,1207,1221,1028,1216,1225,1227,1218,1197,1208,1209,1202,1214,1212,1229,1222	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1bE0yPBWbP4bxkgme2fWAiH4uciDNl8w&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtNMOQSMTcya	price_1Q2TK4AFILSEnUZXzDwj0lT4	1	N	N	Ideal experience for lovers of vintage and second hand in which you will discover places you will fall in love with.	\N	\N	Bohemian & Vintage 3 Days	prod_Qv1Hpp7k7dVOg4	price_1Q3BEUAFILSEnUZXtfWlKSGD		https://buy.stripe.com/test_8wM039e3zf4qfbq4lc		plink_1Q3BIcAFILSEnUZXzHY5hRuT	3Dias	42	N
406	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:26:18	2024-11-18 21:05:30	22185	2024-02-22 00:00:00	BCN10 - Book Lovers	Book Lovers	book-lovers	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Experiencia ideal para amantes de los libros en la que descubriréis librerías con mucha personalidad, agradables cafeterías dónde relajarse y planes de lo más culturetas.</span>	42	young-woman-sitting-blanket-reading-book.jpg	3	<p>¡Bienvenidos! Soy vuestra anfitriona, si os gusta leer tanto cómo a mí seguro que disfrutaréis de esta experiencia. Os recomendare Bibliotecas, librerías ocultas de la ciudad y lugares que pocos conocen a modo de que conozcáis aquel lado oculto que pocos conocen. </p><p>Hola Book Lovers ??</p><p>¿Preparados para la travesía? En la mañana nos moveremos por la zona de Arc de Triomf, monumento construido como entrada principal en la Exposición Universal que se celebró en la ciudad en el año 1888. </p><p>Os sugiero desayunar en <a href=\\"#sand\\"><b>SandwiChez</b></a>, cafetería elegante y tranquila donde por una parte comenzar el día sin estrés y por si os apetece leer un poco. De todas maneras en caso que os apetezca desayunar en una terraza, esta <a href=\\"#granja\\"><b>Granja Cafeteria</b></a>, algo más alejado pero donde estaréis super comodos.</p><p>En este punto book lovers nos adentramos en nuestro viaje por ellos os recomiendo nuestro primer lugar,<b> </b><a href=\\"#arus\\"><b>Biblioteca Arús</b></a> biblioteca del pretérito con olor a madera vieja, su estatua de mármol impresiona. Es una biblioteca de barrio inaugurada el 1895. Es toda una joya antigua. Guarda libros y colecciones antiguas principalmente. Hay la posibilidad de hacer una visita guiada en sus dos plantas superiores y ver una de las colecciones de Sherlorc Holmes de Joan Proubasta, una de las colecciones privadas más importantes de España y unas de las 10 más importantes del mundo. La entrada general cuesta 16 euros.</p><p>Os recomiendo mirar los horarios de apertura. Los sábados y domingos está cerrada. Los jueves y viernes abren a las 15:30 h.</p><p>En caso contrario y a modo de entender otro tipo de lectura os recomiendo visitar <a href=\\"#comics\\"><b>Norma Comics</b></a> es el paraíso del mundo del manga. El edificio cuenta con dos plantas y te encontrarás miles de cosas por ver. Seas amante o no es una visita que vale la pena y más aún sabiendo que cuenta con 13.612 reseñas web y tiene aún un escalofriante 4,7 en estrellas. Y es algo muy difícil de conseguir. </p><p>En la parte posterior del edificio está la Librería<b> </b><a href=\\"#gigamesh\\"><b>Gigamesh</b></a><b> </b>especializada en literatura fantástica y de terror. Con muy buenas reseñas web. Y además una de mis favoritas por mi afición al terror.</p><p>Por  último, os recomiendo ir al<b> </b><a href=\\"#ciutadella\\"><b>Parc de la Ciutadella</b></a> y visitar la Biblioteca del Parlamento de Cataluña<b>,</b> un edificio histórico interesante de ver. Os sugiero relajaros por la zona. </p><p>Ahora vamos con la joya de la corona, si os digo que conozco un sitio que es un restaurante, una cafetería y una librería a la vez? ¿Sorprendente? Esta es mi recomendación book lovers, es lugar se llama <a href=\\"#laie\\"><b>Laie Librería Café</b></a> y aunque esté un poco más alejado en caso de querer pasar la mañana-tarde aquí os recomiendo saltaros el Parc de la Ciutadella e ir directamente. Además cuenta con una terraza donde se puede estar al aire libre. Mi definición es que es un lugar ideal para los amantes de los libros :)</p><p>Por la tarde iremos por lugares históricos y no precisamente por su contexto. Si no porque son lugares que aparecen en el libro de \\"<i>La sombra del viento de Carlos Ruiz Zafón</i>\\" Para quien no conozca el libro ni el autor os explico? prometo ser breve.</p><p>Fue un novelista español famoso por su obra más emblemática <i>La sombra del viento</i>. Con más de 15 millones de ejemplares vendidos se considera una de las 100 obras más importantes escritas en español de los últimos 25 años.</p><p>Por ello os sugiero hacer este recorrido por el born y el gótico a modo de finalizar la tarde. Que aproveche.</p><p>Comenzaremos en el Centro Cultural de Born<b> </b>esto te hará entrar en ambiente, pasea por los alrededores y dirígete a la <a href=\\"#maria\\"><b>Basílica de Santa María del Mar</b></a>, en esta basílica un personaje de la obra va día tras día a confesarse, imaginate? El personaje se llama Bernarda. Subir por el Carrer Montcada y entrar en la Librería<b><a href=\\"#picasso\\"> Laie Museo Picasso</a>,</b> un lugar que en toda su esencia es arte. A Partir de aquí nos dirigimos a C. de l\\ Argenteria y de aquí a Plaça Sant Jaume descrita por el protagonista de la novela. A partir de aquí recomiendo pasar por el Pont del Bisbe y dirigirnos a <a href=\\"#llibres\\"><b>Stock Llibres</b></a><b> </b>un pequeño tesoro que nos ofrece Barcelona, librería pequeña pero muy bien surtida.</p><p>A partir de aquí os recomiendo descansar y acabar el día en <a href=\\"#antic\\"><b>Antic Teatre</b></a>. Un lugar animado en el cual despejar la mente.</p>                	<p>Para este día podéis empezar el día desayunando en la cafetería de la <a href=\\"#byron\\"><b>Librería Byron</b></a><b> </b>ubicada en el barrio de l\\ Eixample, en donde podéis teletrabajar si os hace falta. Cerca se encuentran dos de mis librerías favoritas. <a href=\\"#finestres\\"><b>La Librería Finestres</b></a>, muy agradable y acogedora y<a href=\\"#altair\\"><b> </b><b>La Librería Altair</b></a> en la que disfrutarás mucho si te gusta viajar, porque está especializada en guías y mapas.</p><p>Después el plan que os recomiendo es recorrer el Raval, si os apetece puede estar muy guay descubrir las exposiciones del <a href=\\"#cccb\\"><b>CCCB</b></a> o el<a href=\\"#macba\\"><b> MACBA</b></a>. Parada para comer en el <a href=\\"#central\\"><b>Bar Central</b></a>, tiene un pequeño patio ideal si hace buen tiempo. Una opción vegetariana es <a href=\\"#biocenter\\"><b>Biocenter</b></a>, un restaurante amplio y vistoso con tapas vegetarianas muy ricas.</p><p>Por la tarde me parece el momento ideal para ir al teatro. Podéis mirar la programación en el <a href=\\"#poliorama\\"><b>Teatre Poliorama</b></a>, el <a href=\\"#biblioteca\\"><b>Teatre La Biblioteca</b></a> o disfrutar de una actuación musical en el <a href=\\"#liceu\\"><b>Gran Teatre del Liceu</b></a> o el espectacular <a href=\\"#palau\\"><b>Palau de la Música</b></a><b> </b>dentro hay una cafetería oculta que pocos conocen donde podrás tomar un café mientras lees un libro. O ir a Antic Teatre con un patio interior ideal para tomar algo mientras lees.</p><p>Otra opción es ir al  barrio de Gracia y pasarse por algunas de sus tiendas más pintorescas cómo la <a href=\\"#saturnalia\\"><b>Librería Saturnalia</b></a>, en la misma plaza dónde se encuentra podéis tomar algo o cenar en el <a href=\\"#teatreneu\\"><b>Bar Teatreneu</b></a> o en <a href=\\"#gracia\\"><b>Jardinet de Gràcia</b></a> un restaurante top con una decoración floral en el centro. No os olvidéis de probar la burrata. </p>                	<p>Para este día os propongo dos planes. Una buena opción es ir al <a href=\\"#sant\\"><b>Mercado Dominical de Sant Antoni</b></a> dónde encontraréis libros, vinilos y más en el que pasar la mañana. Espero que esteis de suerte book lovers, porque solo abren los domingos de 8:30 a 14:00. En caso de no coincidir en la fecha indicada, no os preocupeis tengo una alternativa. </p><p>Pero si coincidis os recomiendo varios opciones gastronómicas:</p><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\">Para desayunar: <a href=\\"#desa\\"><b>La Desayuneria</b></a>, desayunos creativos.</li><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\">Para comer: <a href=\\"#tombs\\"><b>Els tres Tombs</b></a> por si os apetece tomar algo mientras leeis o os relajéis</li></ul><p>En caso que os falle el plan nos dirigimos al Barrio de Gràcia. Y como en el primer día, este bello barrio ha sido descrito en un clásico de la literatura catalana. En honor a ello tiene una plaça con su nombre, ah y se me olvidaba? también una escultura. El libro en cuestión se llama <i>La plaça del diamant. </i></p><p>Por ello tengo varias ideas en mente. Una vez en Gràcia, disfrutaremos del barrio mientras caminamos hacia nuestro destino, como era de esperar <a href=\\"#diamant\\"><b>la Plaça del Diamant</b></a>, un lugar histórico y conocido por la famosa novela. En ella encontraremos una escultura en honor a <i>la Colometa</i>, la protagonista de la novela. </p><p>Una vez hayas concluido te recomiendo hacer un taller de cerámica. Está por la zona y se llama <a href=\\"#ceramica\\"><b>La Ceramicaria Gràcia</b></a><b> </b>recomiendo llamar y reservar. Una experiencia enriquecedora donde poder elevar tu imaginación.</p><p>Luego acabar en<a href=\\"#sol\\"><b> </b><b>Plaza del Sol</b></a> y comer en un restaurante de la zona.</p><p>En la tarde y como dato curioso en agosto del año 2023 la <a href=\\"#marquez\\"><b>Biblioteca Gabriel García Márquez</b></a> ganó el premio internacional de la mejor biblioteca pública nueva. Ubicada en el barrio de Sant Martí. Es toda una experiencia donde podréis leer vuestro libro favorito en una hamaca, además también posee una zona exterior por si os apetece leer al aire libre.</p><p>Por la zona si os apetece comer está el <a href=\\"#verneda\\"><b>Restaurante La Verneda</b></a>, donde elaboran platos caseros.</p><p>¡A disfrutar! Y recordar que tenéis más experiencias en la web.</p>\t\t	406	young-woman-sitting-blanket-reading-book.jpg	1454,1455,1456,1590,1458,1459,1591,1582,1557	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	1241,1247,1254,1085,1233,1262,1248,1245,1258,1235,1251,1232,1255,1260,1257,1244,1243,1259,1237,1239,1242,1253,1246,1256,1234,1252,1236,1261,1263,1231,1240,1250,1249	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1Ec4ArI9K5yw-XQJCdWaR0jBfaGL-NkM&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtvxeqJLBdGP	price_1Q2TK4AFILSEnUZXE4Dxu02O	1	N	N	Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.	\N	\N	Book Lovers	prod_QuotunOLmsYpyB	price_1Q2zFpAFILSEnUZX0EfGCG3A	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_aEUdTZ1gNg8ubZe5np	\N	plink_1Q3Ao4AFILSEnUZXPH1D08Zz	3Dias	43	N
407	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:26:22	2024-11-22 02:10:36	24775	2024-03-14 00:00:00	BCN11 - Contemporary Art	Contemporary art, culture & gastronomy 1 Day	contemporary-art-culture--gastronomy-1-day	<p><strong>Sensory Awakening in Barcelona: A Day of Cultural and Gastronomic Experiences&nbsp;</strong>Embark on a fascinating journey through our local recommendations, where art and culture intertwine in an enchanted dance. From contemporary galleries to themed bars, every step you take will reveal a magical Barcelona, tinged with contemporary touches that awaken the senses and feed the adventurous soul. Discover the city from a unique perspective and be amazed by its boundless creativity!</p>\\r\\n	\N	young-woman-sitting-blanket-reading-book.jpg	3	<p>In the morning, as a way to awaken your senses and enjoy the experience with all the energy, I recommend having breakfast at <a href=\\"#caravelle\\"><b>Caravelle</b></a> . You will find a wide variety of breakfasts that adapt to your palate. </p><p>To get off to a good start we will visit the gallery  <a href=\\"#angels\\"><b>angels barcelona</b></a>  which focuses on contemporary culture and the different practices of this and also  <a href=\\"#chiquita\\"><b>Chiquita Room  </b></a>is a center for contemporary art and creation that carries out its activity as a gallery, artist residence, producer and curator of projects, cultural mediator, publisher of artist books and school of inspiration.</p><p>Then I suggest going through Calle Tallers and visiting: <a href=\\"#nevermind\\"><b>Nevermind</b></a>, an ideal bar for rock and punk lovers. With an underground aesthetic, at the end of the bar you will find a skatepark where you can watch others practicing on their skateboards. Another option would be  <a href=\\"#la\\"><b>The Llibertària</b></a> <b>,</b> will take you on a walk through the most anarchist history of Barcelona. In a cozy atmosphere, you will find tributes to the city?s revolutionaries and different objects that are already living history of the city, such as the first piano that was played in El Molino, a mythical venue on Barcelona?s Paral·lel.</p><p>Next and close to the previous one we will go to the <a href=\\"#joan\\"><b>Joan Gaspar Gallery</b></a> , which is committed to avant-garde art. </p><p>To eat there is a very cool place called <a href=\\"#veggie\\"><b>Veggie Garden.</b></a>a vegan space with a very good atmosphere. An alternative to this is  <a href=\\"#musiu\\"><b>Musiu</b></a> modern, lively and popular Italian restaurant.</p><p>In the afternoon visit the born and enter the <a href=\\"#arte\\"><b>European Museum of Modern Art</b></a>, is an 18th century palace that displays works from the 20th and 21st centuries. On your way out you can have a drink at the  <a href=\\"#bornet\\"><b>Bornet</b></a>The atmosphere and the background music make it stand out. In the area I recommend you to visit  <a href=\\"#maxo\\"><b>Maxó Gallery</b></a> , inside you can take a printed photo for ?3 with the gallery theme.</p><p>To end the day we can have dinner at <a href=\\"#fa\\"><b>Fa Patxoca</b></a> , a tapas restaurant in a modern atmosphere or if you prefer something more informal, you have <a href=\\"#parkingpizza\\"><b>Parking pizza</b></a> , delicious!</p><p>As a final culmination and if you fancy some entertainment, I recommend <a href=\\"#taverna\\"><b>La Taverna de Barcelona</b></a> , ??it is a music bar with live music, you can eat and have a cocktail.</p><p>I hope you enjoyed the tours! Barcelona has endless plans. Remember that we have more experiences to recommend you around the city.  </p><p>See you soon!!! ??</p>\t\t	\N	\N	407	museo-europeo.jpeg	1519,1520,1521,1522,1523,1524	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	935,946,940,1275,948,947,969,942,943,1267,954,941,1268,934	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1r6l2hxVNvQjKKg7PfzgtFt4X5ahZJt4&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtJx7GxM9mLI	price_1Q2TK5AFILSEnUZXdkmxxI2B	1	N	N	Sensory Awakening in Barcelona: A Day of Cultural and Gastronomic Experiences	\N	\N	Contemporary art, culture & gastronomy 1 Day	prod_QuotH7EvUOFmEB	price_1Q2zFqAFILSEnUZXwgtn4T1Z		https://buy.stripe.com/test_dR6cPV1gNf4q0gw17a		plink_1Q3Ao4AFILSEnUZXNRXxDp7K	1Dia	44	N
408	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:26:26	2024-11-18 21:05:30	24742	2024-03-18 00:00:00	BCN12 - Modernism	Modernism tour 1 Day	modernism-tour-1-day	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Experiencia ideal para amantes de los libros en la que descubriréis librerías con mucha personalidad, agradables cafeterías dónde relajarse y planes de lo más culturetas.</span>	\N	young-woman-sitting-blanket-reading-book.jpg	3	<p>For breakfast, I suggest you start at one of my favorite places in modernist Barcelona, ??which is <a href=\\"#chelo1\\"><b>Chelo Café.</b></a>  If it?s sunny, don?t hesitate to go out to the terrace. Afterwards, and to get into the topic, I propose a walk along the ramblas, entering the  <a href=\\"#boque1\\"><b>Boqueria Market</b></a><b> </b>and in the store Ale hop. This store would go unnoticed a priori, but it is a modernist palace with surprising ceilings.</p><p>Afterwards I suggest you enter the bar association and (current Barcelona archive) it is officially called the <a href=\\"#arcadia\\"><b>Palacio de l?Arcadia</b></a> , you can see the cloister and go for a drink at \\" <a href=\\"#gats4\\"><b>Els cuatre gats\\"</b></a>\\" the bohemian place in the city where the geniuses of modernism met and where Picasso exhibited one of his works for the first time. Since you are in the area we cannot ignore the  <a href=\\"#paau\\"><b>Palau de la Música</b></a> and the <a href=\\"#seda\\"><b>Silk Palace</b></a> building. You can go to these monuments and take a couple of photos or if you feel like visiting them.</p><p>To eat, I suggest <a href=\\"#sk2\\"><b>Restaurante Sk</b></a> to have a traditional menu at an affordable price or <a href=\\"#soso1\\"><b>La Sosenga</b></a> with a slightly higher price, but also highly recommended. </p><p>After regaining your strength, if you want to visit one of Gaudí?s famous houses, this is the time for you to do it, my favorite is the  <a href=\\"#llo1\\"><b>Batlló House</b></a>If the price seems expensive to you, you can enter through the store and go to the typical modernist bathrooms or enter the building next door called Servicio Estación and go up to the highest floor and admire the terraces of Casa Batlló.</p><p>In the afternoon we will go for a walk through the Montjuic area to admire modernist buildings such as <a href=\\"#ramona\\"><b>the</b> <b>CasaRamona</b> factory.</a>  Built between 1909 and 1912. Since 2002 it has been the headquarters of CaixaForum.  </p><p>Or take a tour of Eixample and visit the following not-so-known houses: <a href=\\"#morera1\\"><b>Casa Lleó i Morera</b></a> , <b><a href=\\"#calvet1\\">Casa Calvet</a> , <a href=\\"#llopis\\">Casa Manuel Llopis Bofill</a> , <a href=\\"#bruno\\">Casa Bruno Cuadros</a></b>. Afterwards you can go have a drink and watch the sunset in  <a href=\\"#fuster1\\"><b>Fuster House</b></a>, currently a hotel. Built by Lluís Domènech i Montaner, a world leader in Catalan modernism.</p><p>For dinner I propose two options, both of which are in the modernist part and are called <a href=\\"#diaz\\"><b>Casa Diaz.</b></a><b> </b>or <b><a href=\\"#portoles1\\">Portoles Restaurant</a> .</b></p><p>Then I suggest you go to the <a href=\\"#ayre\\"><b>Ayre Hotel Rosellón</b></a> , the views are spectacular and you will have the best views to observe the Sagrada Familia, I recommend booking. </p>\t\t	\N	\N	408	Casa-Lleo-Morera1.jpg	1525,1577,1527,1528,1529,1530,1531	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	972,994,971,966,959,990,987,986,970,1293,964,989,956,993,976,1282,973,974	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1B0-jnpErRlHkQ79sfs96piCCfP4h6TQ&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtifdWjHmsvY	price_1Q2TK5AFILSEnUZXEp711x1a	1	N	N	Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.	\N	\N	Modernism tour 1 Day	prod_Qv1HZ5U2aNkQqI	price_1Q3BEVAFILSEnUZXflnnMxJs	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_00g3fl7Fb8G23sI4ld	\N	plink_1Q3BIdAFILSEnUZXVM6MktxM	1Dia	45	N
409	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:26:30	2024-11-18 21:05:30	24758	2024-03-14 00:00:00	BCN13 - Discover Gothic in Barcelona	Discover the gothic 1 Day	discover-the-gothic-1-day	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Experiencia ideal para amantes de los libros en la que descubriréis librerías con mucha personalidad, agradables cafeterías dónde relajarse y planes de lo más culturetas.</span>	\N	young-woman-sitting-blanket-reading-book.jpg	3	<p>Although the Gothic is the best known part of the city, this experience hides secrets that you will discover and that are outside the typical tourist plans.</p><p>I suggest you have breakfast at the <a href=\\"#granja\\"><b>Granja Dulcinea</b></a> in the Plaza de <a href=\\"#pi\\"><b>Sta Maria del Pi.</b></a>. This square has a very nice painting market on weekends and the basilica at night is the scene of Candlelight concerts. Those streets until you reach the <a href=\\"#veronica\\"><b>Verónica Square</b></a> , I love it for the climate and the little shops there.</p><p>To continue, I propose a walk through <b><a href=\\"#neri\\">Sant Felipe Neri</a> ,</b> El Call, (there is an almost hidden cafeteria where you can try coffee from all over the world, it is called <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#side\\">Right Side</a> .</b> The imposing<b> <a href=\\"#augusto\\">Temple of Augustus</a> , <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#rei\\">Plaza del Rei</a> </b>.At mid-morning, if you fancy something cool, I suggest <a href=\\"#ginger\\"><b>Ginge</b></a>r in Plaça de Sant Just. u <a href=\\"#ovisso\\"><b>Ovisso</b></a> in George Orwell Square. To eat my options are <b>\\" <a href=\\"#pintor\\">El Pintor</a> \\",</b> or <a href=\\"#andu\\"><b>Anduriña</b></a> (a traditional bar) or <a href=\\"#sal\\"><b>Salterio</b></a> in the Jewish quarter to have tea after eating.</p><p>Then in the afternoon you can sit and drink a coffee on the terrace of the Rec plate. Then I propose a walk through <b><a href=\\"#ciudadela\\">the greenhouse of the citadel</a> , <a href=\\"#moco\\">the MOCO museum</a></b> on Montcada street or wander through the labyrinths of Born, a short walk through the mulberry pit ? You can also participate in a ceramics workshop, as a guild neighborhood preserves the medieval craft tradition.</p><p>Another option is to go to the <a href=\\"#francia\\"><b>France station, see its modernist architecture</b></a>to see its modernist architecture and take a stroll through the old port warehouses until you reach the beach area.</p><p>For the night you have several options, if you want something with an Italian and elegant touch I suggest <a href=\\"#restaurant\\"><strong>Cachaca Restaurant</strong></a> <b>,</b> if you are more of the ?always? <a href=\\"#can\\"><b>Can Culleretes</b></a> .</p><p>To end the day, <a href=\\"#mamaine\\"><b>Mamainé is</b></a> a small and very chic place or <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#paraiso\\"><b>El Paraiso</b></a> , a clandestine cocktail bar that leaves no one indifferent.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	409	santa-maria-del-pi.jpeg	1537,1538,1539,1466,1467,1542,1543,1544	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1015,1311,1041,1308,1005,1039,1012,1042,951,1013,1011,1307,1009,1008,1006,1010,1014,1043,1007	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1ez5ZNhYLvfZkhfW9Oiu37gErCFbEz5I&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHt9vNn8dC4Ar	price_1Q2TK6AFILSEnUZXRi32LSTW	1	N	N	Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.	\N	\N	Discover the gothic 1 Day	prod_Qv1H5kWQ83V9ln	price_1Q3BEVAFILSEnUZXX8LN18II	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_6oEdTZcZvbSee7mbNG	\N	plink_1Q3BIdAFILSEnUZX3eE0EkDP	1Dia	46	N
410	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:26:38	2024-11-22 06:38:43	25956	2024-03-14 00:00:00	BCN14 - Gluten Free	Gluten Free 1 Día	gluten-free-1-dia	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><b><strong>Destinos sin gluten:</strong></b> <b><strong>recomendaciones seleccionadas para una experiencia sin preocupaciones</strong></b></span>\\r\\n\\r\\nSumamos dos ingredientes esenciales para crear una experiencia sin preocupaciones: la comodidad y la recomendación exclusiva de nuestros anfitriones locales. Te invitamos a explorar la Barcelona menos transitada del Eixample y el fascinante barrio de Poblenou, donde la belleza se fusiona con la tranquilidad y las espectaculares vistas de la costa mediterránea.	46	bristol-.jpeg	3	<p>¡Descubre Barcelona en un día lleno de historia, arte y delicias culinarias!</p><p>Comienza tu día en Barcelona con un delicioso desayuno en el acogedor <a href=\\"#bristol1\\"><b>Bristol Café</b></a>. Disfruta de su ambiente relajado y saborea exquisitos cafés y pasteles antes de comenzar tu aventura.</p><p>Después de recargar energías, dirígete al impresionante<b> </b><a href=\\"#maca3\\"><b>Palau Macaya</b></a>, una joya arquitectónica que te dejará maravillado con su diseño modernista. Continúa tu recorrido cultural visitando la encantadora <a href=\\"#fransales\\"><b>Parroquia de San Francisco de Sales</b></a> y la majestuosa<b> </b><a href=\\"#purisima\\"><b>Basílica de la Purísima Concepción</b></a>, donde podrás admirar la magnificencia de la arquitectura sacra.</p><p>Para el almuerzo, te recomendamos dos opciones irresistibles. Dirígete al <a href=\\"#malatxabar\\"><b>Malatxa Bar</b></a> para disfrutar de tapas creativas y sabores auténticos en un ambiente vibrante, o visita <a href=\\"#naturpi\\"><b>Pizza Natura</b></a> para deleitarte con sus pizzas saludables y sin gluten, una opción perfecta para todos los gustos y necesidades dietéticas.</p><p>En la tarde, sumérgete en el mundo del diseño en <a href=\\"#museoarte\\"><b>Design Museum of Barcelona</b></a>, donde encontrarás exposiciones fascinantes que celebran la creatividad y la innovación. Después, relájate en los hermosos <a href=\\"#ca\\"><b>Jardins de Ca l\\ Aranyó</b></a>, un remanso de tranquilidad en medio de la ciudad. Continúa tu paseo por la animada<b> </b><a href=\\"#poblenou2\\"><b>Rambla del Poblenou</b></a> llena de vida y puntos locales de interés. Para finalizar disfruta del atardecer y la brisa marina en la<b> </b><a href=\\"#bogatell\\"><b>Playa Bogatell</b></a>.</p><p>Para la cena, te espera una experiencia culinaria única en Barcelona. Dirígete al <a href=\\"#caber\\"><b>CABERNET BAR TAPES COPES I VINS</b></a> para disfrutar de una selección de tapas y vinos en un ambiente acogedor y sofisticado, o prueba la auténtica cocina catalana en <a href=\\"#polmo\\"><b>Monopol</b></a>, donde cada plato es una obra maestra gastronómica.</p><p>¡Disfruta de un día inolvidable explorando los tesoros de Barcelona y deleitándome con su deliciosa gastronomía!</p><p><br style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" /><br style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" /></p>\t\t	\N	\N	410	bristol-.jpeg	1563,1564,1473,1566,1567,1568,1569,1570	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	1085,1315,1107,1322,1089,1326,1099,1083,1084,1320,1106,1323	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=15I5MEMog_cmhvK884Zm_WtnmXXlBd3k&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtwCxGwlFcSz	price_1Q2TK6AFILSEnUZXAnr5rCmp	1	N	N	Destinos sin gluten: recomendaciones seleccionadas para una experiencia sin preocupaciones 	\N	\N	Gluten Free 1 Dí­a	prod_Quot7rrg7wohiW	price_1Q2zFrAFILSEnUZXIB0gHZOV		https://buy.stripe.com/test_aEU4jpbVr6xU4wMeY1		plink_1Q3Ao6AFILSEnUZX1S0R3sP4	1Dia	47	N
411	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:26:41	2024-11-18 21:05:31	24749	2024-03-14 00:00:00	BCN15 - Parks and Gardens	Gardens & Parks 1 Day	gardens--parks-1-day	<b>Discover the city\\ s secret parks and gardens.</b> Would you like to discover secret gardens in the city? Immerse yourself in the urban nature of the city by visiting the city\\ s most beautiful parks and gardens, and enjoy the cultural and gastronomic recommendations of your local host for a very green day out!	\N	bristol-.jpeg	3	<p>Hello and welcome to Barcelona! In this experience we are going to visit my favorite parks and corners of Barcelona, from some of the best known to others more hidden and with a special charm&#8230;let&#8217;s start!</p><p>In the morning, we explore the charming neighborhood of Plaza España, one of the most emblematic places in the Catalan capital. To enhance our experience, we will start by recharging our batteries with two delicious breakfast suggestions.</p><p><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#tartela\\"><b>Tartela BCN</b></a> is a brunch with a product and a photo presentation, and incredible flavors. Will not leave you indifferent.</p><p>Once prepared, we get down to work to discover one of my favorite places where I go every weekend, the Jardins de Joan Maragall. <a href=\\"#joan\\"><b>Joan Maragall Gardens</b></a> (only open on Saturdays and Sundays) is an elegant garden with fountains and gardens. But don&#8217;t worry, I have more options for you if you don&#8217;t coincide on the days indicated.</p><p>And this recommendation is the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#botanic\\"><b>Historical Botanical Garden</b></a>located behind the great Museo Nacional d&#8217;Arts de Barcelona. This garden was a former quarry and you will find unusual plants from the Eurosiberian region. Admission is free and it is one of those places few frequented in Barcelona where I guarantee you will be able to disconnect.</p><p>Once we have finished contemplating the garden, in the area a 15 minute walk away we will find the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#botanico\\"><b>Botanical Garden of Barcelona</b></a> just behind the Olympic Stadium of Montjuic, emblematic place of Barcelona for hosting the Olympic Games in 1992. The entrance fee is 5 euros and inside you will find international flora chosen to grow in Mediterranean climate, also has views of the sea and the city.</p><p>To end the morning go for lunch at <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#xalet\\"><b>El Xalet de Montjuic</b></a> located in the surrounding area. This restaurant located on top of a hill with panoramic views of the city, is a gastronomic space that combines Mediterranean cuisine and signature cuisine. Another option is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#xemei\\"><b>Xemei</b></a>a Venetian restaurant offering pasta and seafood dishes.</p><p>These are my recommendations for the morning, in the afternoon we will focus on Gothic and Born.</p><p>Let&#8217;s get started ??</p><p>Our first stop will be the Old<a href=\\"#santa\\"><b> </b><b>Holy Cross Hospital</b></a> 5 minutes from the L3 stop of the green line of the subway. This hospital is an ancient medieval complex that has a library inside, in addition to what we are interested in <a href=\\"#lluc\\"><b>Rubió i Lluc Gardens</b></a> a little known place in the raval, where you can relax and get away from the hustle and bustle of the city. It also has a bar where you can have tapas or a drink. </p><p>And if you are in the mood for culture I recommend the <a href=\\"#pau\\"><b>Ancient monastery of Sant Pau del Camo. </b></a>The building is a beautiful and secret building in Barcelona, many are satisfied with just seeing the outside of it. In my case, whenever I can, I am one of those people who go inside to enjoy this Romanesque monastery. Admission is free.</p><p>As a transition to the born we will go to the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#casaig\\"><b>Garden of the Ignacio de Puig House</b></a> is located near the Ramblas, 3 minutes from the Liceu metro station L3 and is an oasis of peace little known by the inhabitants of the city.</p><p>At this point and as a break there is a very top place that I usually frequent to finish the evening is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#taverna\\"><b>Irati Taverna Basca</b></a> is a restaurant with a charm of its own. It focuses on skewers and its strong point is the Basque grill. I recommend trying the cider and the skewers that are released from time to time. </p><p>To end this great day discovering the serenity of Barcelona we concluded by heading to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#ateneu\\"><b>El Jardí de l&#8217;Ateneu</b></a> is located in an emblematic building, outside you will find a sign with the following text &#8220;Ateneu Barcelonès&#8221;. It has a beautiful garden and is also a restaurant in case you feel like having something to eat.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	411	Jardins-de-Joan-Maragall.jpeg	1571,1572,1573,1546,1574,1575,1576	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1167,1162,1170,1168,1139,1024,1169,1160,1166,1159,1163,1164	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1EsTdCpBj26ozo28tsW4cOKmEajRFx1U&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtFJSw1ufwvQ	price_1Q2TK7AFILSEnUZXK3SVn8sL	1	N	N	Discover the city\\ s secret parks and gardens.	\N	\N	Gardens & Parks 1 Day	prod_QuotBWfDijXRrT	price_1Q2zFsAFILSEnUZX1nzNmGGt	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_5kAcPV0cJ9K61kAdTY	\N	plink_1Q3Ao7AFILSEnUZX0fI3lMBt	1Dia	48	N
412	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:26:48	2024-11-22 07:10:27	23954	2024-03-14 00:00:00	BCN16 - Relax & Gourmet	Relax y Gourmet 1 Dia	relax-y-gourmet-1-dia	<strong><span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\">Vive la fusión perfecta de relajación y delicias gourmet en Barcelona, donde la serenidad se combina con experiencias culinarias irresistibles. ?????</span></strong>\\r\\n<p style=\\"text-align: center;\\"><span style=\\"color: #000000;\\">Sumérgete en un oasis de serenidad y indulgencia gourmet en el corazón de Barcelona. Descubre un mundo de tranquilidad mientras te deleitas con las delicias gastronómicas más irresistibles que Barcelona tiene para ofrecer, cada momento está diseñado para nutrir cuerpo y alma. ¡Deja que tus sentidos se eleven en este viaje de relajación incomparable!\\"</span></p>	48	relax-2-bcn.png	3	<p>¡Buenos días! Os invito a entrar en ambiente e iniciar el día de la mejor manera en <a href=\\"#tartela\\"><b>Tartela</b></a>, con productos espectaculares de foto.</p><p>Después de desayunar nos dirigimos a Plaza España y nos situaremos delante de las imponentes <a href=\\"#torres\\"><b>Torres Venecianas</b></a> que nos abrirá paso a contemplar por una parte la Fuente de Montjuic (ahora en desuso debido a la sequera en Barcelona) y por otra parte el imponente <a href=\\"#art\\"><b>Museo Nacional d&#8217;Art de Barcelona</b></a>. En este punto solo os puedo recomendar que os dejéis llevar por la belleza del lugar. </p><p>Tras pasear y observar los alrededores nos dirigimos al <a href=\\"#teatro\\"><b>Teatro Griego </b></a>con una belleza sin igual, donde pasar la mañana. En sus alrededores hay un jardín e incluso un pequeño estanque. Te servirá para relajarte y cada cierto tiempo suelen hacer actuaciones culturales, te recomiendo entrar en su página web y mirar la programación.</p><p>Una vez hayas terminado y concluido, vuestro lugar es<a href=\\"#amposta\\"><b> Bodega Amposta</b></a> un restaurante de tapas y platos principales con una ambientación elegante que nos preparará para nuestro último lugar. </p><p>Ya es hora de mimar un poco nuestro cuerpo y sentidos, por ello una temática egipcia os hará entrar en situación, <a href=\\"#isis\\"><strong>Isis Spa</strong></a>, desde baños egipcios a tratamientos faciales. Un lugar para relajar tu mente y cuerpo.</p><p>Por la tarde visitar <a href=\\"#bossvi\\"><strong>Bossvi</strong></a> una tienda de decoración de interiores enfocada en las plantas artificiales. Dejaros llevar por su ambiente único en Barcelona, donde solo admirar es un deleite.</p><p>Además podéis ir a <a href=\\"#ramonet\\"><b>Los Jardines de Muñoz Ramonet </b></a>es un jardín histórico del siglo XX fue concebido para uso privado pero actualmente es de uso público y promueven respetar el ambiente del jardín. Ofrece reposo y evasión entre la urbe y el tráfico. Cuenta con un palacete y un estanco, por los alrededores abundan esculturas.</p><p>La otra opción es más cultural y es <a href=\\"#tapies\\"><b>el Museo de la Fundación Antoni Tàpies</b></a>, un edificio modernista con un museo contemporáneo en las que se exhiben pinturas y obras del autor. La entrada general cuesta 8 euros.</p><p>A modo de terminar el día os recomiendo cenar en dos lugares, por una parte <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#antigua\\">Antigua</a> </strong>un restaurante con comida mediterránea muy buena, rica y con buenas cantidades. Destaca por sus instalaciones y sus emplatados. La otra opción algo más desenfadada es <a href=\\"#saona\\"><strong>Saona Travessera de Gràcia</strong></a> A diferencia del restaurante anterior el local es más luminoso y está centrado en pequeñas tapas. Són dos conceptos totalmente distintos, pero igual de buenos. A vuestro criterio. </p><p>Para finalizar cerca esta <a href=\\"#solange\\"><strong>Solange Cocktail Bar</strong></a> Coctelería tranquila con un ambientazo para concluir el día de la manera más elegante. Un trato muy profesional y os ofreceran la mejor opción.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	412	relax-2-bcn.png	1532,1489,1533,1534,1535,1479,1536	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	1050,1068,1345,1347,1061,1048,1065,1051,1350,1339,1066,1340	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1PkzvNCQEaGyss8uuPUiqYnJ79jPPFx4&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtVEFLnhOTMi	price_1Q2TK7AFILSEnUZXuNvOr3DU	1	N	N	Vive la fusión perfecta de relajación y delicias gourmet en Barcelona, donde la serenidad se combina con experiencias culinarias irresistibles. ?????	\N	\N	Relax y Gourmet 1 Dia	prod_Quot4Ui4RB4H8M	price_1Q2zFsAFILSEnUZXHwgqrjC6	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_9AQbLR7Fb6xUgfug27	\N	plink_1Q3Ao7AFILSEnUZXuHDFfjN3	1Dia	49	N
413	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:26:56	2024-11-18 21:05:31	25959	2024-03-15 00:00:00	BCN17 - Foodie & Traveler	Foodie & Traveler 1 Dia	foodie--traveler-1-dia	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><b><strong>Discover the gastronomic treasures hidden in Barcelona, from its traditional tapas to its most avant-garde restaurants.</strong></b></span>\\r\\n\\r\\nStart the day in the vibrant Eixample neighborhood and tour the most emblematic corners of Montjuic, from the historic botanical gardens to the panoramic views from the Castle. Explore the bohemian charm of Gràcia, marveling at the architectural creations of Mario Català Nebot and the symbolic sculptures of Passeig de Sant Joan. Let Barcelona seduce you with its unparalleled magic and immerse yourself in the cultural richness of the city.	49	gluten.jpeg	3	<p>Hoy empezaremos en el Eixample, y nos dirigiremos a la parada de Urgell en la L1 del metro de Barcelona. Una vez aquí desayunamos en <a href=\\"#eixa1\\"><b>Eixampeling</b></a>, es una cafetería alegre y colorida donde rodearnos de las mejores vibras, para luego dirigirnos a Plaza España y disfrutar de Montjuic.</p><p>Dentro de Montjuic hay demasiadas cosas por ver, por lo tanto nos ocupará toda la mañana. Algunas de mis recomendaciones son las siguientes: <a href=\\"#historic1\\"><b>Jardí Botànic Històric</b></a>, justo detrás del imponente Museo Nacional de Arte de Cataluña. La entrada es gratuita, describo el lugar como uno de esos rincones ocultas en Barcelona, que poco conocen y aparte de el lugar en sí que es super bonito, el hecho de ser poco conocido le da su encanto. </p><p>Al terminar nos dirigimos  a los <a href=\\"#griego1\\"><b>Jardines del Teatro Griego</b></a>, un indispensable en él encontrarás un mini anfiteatro digno de ser visitado.</p><p>Otra alternativa es el <a href=\\"#casti\\"><b>Castillo de Montjuic</b></a><b> </b>que se construyó originalmente en el siglo XVII como fortaleza militar, y ha sido escenario de importantes acontecimientos históricos, como el bombardeo de Barcelona en 1842 y la Guerra Civil Española. Se encuentra en una colina que domina la ciudad de Barcelona, por lo que ofrece unas vistas panorámicas impresionantes. Desde las almenas del castillo, puedes ver toda la ciudad, el puerto y el mar Mediterráneo.</p><p>A Partir de aquí te recomiendo comer en un lugar privilegiado de Barcelona, poco conocido si no frecuentas la zona es el <a href=\\"#oleum1\\"><b>Restaurant Òleum</b></a> ubicado dentro del Museo. De principio a fin es toda una experiencia. Y es que el ambiente da a ello, qué mejor que comer dentro de un museo. En caso de querer tener otra opción la mía es <a href=\\"#amposta1\\"><b>Bodega Amposta</b></a>, algo más alejado pero excelente en cuanto a calidad-precio, además es un restaurante acogedor. </p><p>Por la tarde propongo el barrio de Gràcia, un barrio con un ambiente especial con un pasado mucho más rural, respira su espíritu catalanista y su cultura más callejera. Es considerado un pueblo dentro de una ciudad. </p><p>La tarde está enfocada en elementos culturales y símbolos del barrio de Gràcia. Nuestro primer punto de referencia será el <a href=\\"#nebot1\\"><b>Edificio de viviendas de Mario Català Nebot</b></a>, en sus inicios nadie le entendía, pero con el paso del tiempo sus creaciones se han convertido en objeto de culto con ventanas psicodélicas y formas onduladas. Muchos barceloneses la llaman la piscina de Barcelona. </p><p>Luego iremos al Passeig de Sant Joan, aquí encontraremos dos esculturas con simbolismos por un lado la <a href=\\"#roja1\\"><b>Fuente de Caperucita Roja</b></a>, es una curiosa imagen de bronce de 1921. Muestra una caperucita Roja empoderada como si hubiese sometido al Lobo. A unos metros encontramos <a href=\\"#hercules1\\"><b>La Fuente de Hércules</b></a>, dicen que es unas de las estatuas más antiguas de Barcelona, se inauguró en 1802 se construyó para celebrar la boda y la visita del rey Carlos IX.</p><p>Por último y no por ello menos especial <a href=\\"#plgitano\\"><strong>Plaça del Poble Gitano</strong></a> es historia de Gràcia y un homenaje al corazón gitano del barrio.</p><p>Y de aquí nos dirigimos a <a href=\\"#sol1\\"><b>Plaza del Sol</b></a> emblemática y lugar de encuentro del barrio de Gràcia ideal para tomar algo en un ambiente único. Qué mejor que ponerte en escena e ir a <a href=\\"#cafe1\\"><b>Cafè del sol</b></a>, su bar más mítico. Además por sus alrededores hay edificios de estilo modernista.</p><p>Para finalizar cena en <a href=\\"#nua1\\"><b>Nüa</b></a>, un restaurante futurista y healthy que me encanta. Y para terminar el día un cóctel en <b><a href=\\"#19681\\">Marcelino 1968</a>.</b></p>\t\t	\N	\N	413	gluten.jpeg	1545,1547,1548,1549,1550,1592	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	1068,1362,1354,1357,1351,1358,1352,1353,1359,1364,1363,1360,1261,1355	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1b6lCIDOaUh0wmRcIu6kaeP-8FIwEGz8&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtkFAM5jL7l2	price_1Q2TK8AFILSEnUZXnsYVhYQ5	1	N	N	Discover the gastronomic treasures hidden in Barcelona, from its traditional tapas to its most avant-garde restaurants.	\N	\N	Foodie & Traveler 1 Dia	prod_QuotFAKSd7OZyZ	price_1Q2zFtAFILSEnUZXmfj0vCoW	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_6oE6rx0cJ7BY4wMdU0	\N	plink_1Q3Ao8AFILSEnUZXEOsOfr0R	1Dia	50	N
414	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:27:05	2024-11-22 07:10:27	23965	2024-03-15 00:00:00	BCN18 - Bohemian & Vintage	Bohemian & Vintage 1 Dia	bohemian--vintage-1-dia	<strong><span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\">Experiencia ideal para amantes de lo vintage y el second hand en la que descubriréis lugares que os enamorarán.</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"color: #000000;\\">¡Embárcate en una aventura bohemia y vintage por las calles encantadas de Barcelona! Descubre joyas ocultas en El Gòtic y El Born, donde cada rincón es un tesoro esperando ser encontrado. Desde desayunos reconfortantes  hasta paseos entre boutiques únicas, cada momento está impregnado de nostalgia y estilo. Luego, sumérgete en el alma creativa de Gràcia, explorando sus tiendas vintage y disfrutando de la vida en la Plaza del Sol. Termina tu día con delicias culinarias viviendo Barcelona con un toque retro y una pizca de magia.</span>	50	vintage-bcn.png	3	<p>¡Bienvenidos a Barcelona! Soy Violeta y soy amante de todo lo vintage, en esta experiencia os dejo mis lugares favoritos que espero que disfrutéis tanto cómo lo hago yo.</p><p>Empezaremos el día recorriendo el barrio de El Gotic y el barrio del Born, si queréis desayunar por la zona mi recomendación es <a href=\\"#brunch1\\"><b>The Benedict Brunch Barcelona</b></a>, tienen una carta muy variada con todo tipo de desayunos y dulces? para llenar bien el estómago! Otra opción es <a href=\\"#pic1\\"><b>Picnic</b></a> (Carrer del Comerç), cuando entres, te encontrarás con un local pequeñito, muy bien iluminado en el que te sentirás en un ambiente muy agradable y familiar, tienen menú brunch muy variado de viernes a domingo, no te lo pierdas!!</p><p>Born: En el barrio del Born, donde encontraréis galerías de arte contemporáneo y tiendas de diseñadores independientes, Después podemos pasear por las calles de el born, lo que más encontramos en las tiendas del Born es la figura del artesano/diseñador/anticuario independiente, con un discurso propio muy marcado y alejado de los cánones artísticos y de moda impuestos. para visitar algunas de sus tiendas como <a href=\\"#ziggy1\\"><b>Ziggy Vintage</b></a>, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#segura1\\"><b>Carlos</b><b> </b><b>Segura</b></a>? ya que estáis por la zona os recomiendo visitar la Galería Maxó o, si os apetece dulce, el <a href=\\"#choco1\\"><b>Museo del Chocolate</b></a>.</p><p>Gotic: Una vez tenemos el estómago lleno, podemos pasear hacia el Gotic y perdernos por sus calles donde encontraremos una muy buena variedad de tiendas vintage, mis favoritas en esta zona son <a href=\\"#blue1\\"><strong>Blue Goose </strong></a><b></b>(abre a las 12), Le Swing Vintage? y no os podéis perder los vestidos de novia de <a href=\\"#arca1\\"><b>L´Arca</b></a>! Ya que estáis por la zona, os recomiendo visitar el <a href=\\"#fun1\\"><b>Big Fun Museum</b></a><b> </b>(un original museo con ilusiones ópticas donde hacerse fotos y retratos de personajes famosos hechos con comida<b>)</b>, o el <a href=\\"#puig1\\"><b>Jardín de la Casa Ignacio de Puig</b></a>, un pequeño oasis secreto en el centro de la ciudad.</p><p>Para comer por la zona os recomiendo tapear o tomar un vermut en la taberna <a href=\\"#porta\\"><b>El Portalón</b></a>. Otra opcion es <a href=\\"#gallo\\"><strong>Gallo Nero</strong></a>, un restaurante italiano ofrece una variedad de opciones para todos los gustos, desde pizzas clásicas hasta platos más elaborados como la bistecca alla fiorentina (filete a la parrilla) o el ragù alla toscana (estofado de carne). Además, tiene sus postres caseros como el tiramisú o la panna cotta.</p><p>Nada mejor para pasar la tarde que desplazarnos al barrio de Gracia, uno de los barrios más bohemios y con más encanto de la ciudad. Aquí las posibilidades son infinitas, podemos empezar visitando mis tiendas favoritas como <b><a href=\\"#100armarios\\">Revolviendo 1000 armarios</a>  </b>y <a href=\\"#leopardo1\\"><b>Leopardo Leopardi Concept Store</b></a>. Otras opciones son  <a href=\\"#rev\\"><strong>Revolution Vintage Clothing</strong></a> y en la iconica Plaza del diamant en honor al clasico libro catalan, encontramos <a href=\\"#mah\\"><strong>Mahalo Vintage Gracia</strong></a>.</p><p>Si habéis venido a gracia de lunes a viernes también podéis visitar la <b><a href=\\"#saturnalia1\\">Librería Saturnalia</a>. </b>Podéis acabar tomando algo en la plaza del sol que es uno de los puntos de encuentro en el barrio y tiene ambientazo todas las tardes. Os recomiendo cenar en <a href=\\"#nina\\"><strong>Nina</strong></a> con tapas excelentes y un trato muy profesional. </p><p>Por si os apetece tomar algo hay un lugar muy top en la plaza de la revolución, se llama <a href=\\"#cani\\"><strong>Bar Canigó</strong></a> </p><p>Otra opción es tapear y tomar algo en <a href=\\"#coco1\\"><b>Coco &#8216;s Secrets</b></a>, un lugar con mucho encanto en Barcelona. La decoración no te dejará indiferente, tienen noches temáticas cada semana, algunos días espectáculos y música en directo! </p>\t\t	\N	\N	414	vintage-bcn.png	1551,1552,1553,1554,1555,1556	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	1382,1372,1370,1368,1383,1374,1375,1373,1377,1253,1371,1379,1369,1381,1366,1378,1376,1365,1367	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1lDyLE8_N8mEDAuqHIJ-7bYucc8k_tc0&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHthjUSbekBBP	price_1Q2TK8AFILSEnUZXijk7T6BJ	1	N	N	Experiencia ideal para amantes de lo vintage y el second hand en la que descubriréis lugares que os enamorarán.	\N	\N	Bohemian & Vintage 1 Dia	prod_QuotLQlBgh4ERJ	price_1Q2zFtAFILSEnUZXJPrS91cJ	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_aEU8zFbVr9K66EUbLT	\N	plink_1Q3Ao8AFILSEnUZX2REzQkSe	1Dia	51	N
415	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:27:13	2024-11-22 07:10:27	23967	2024-03-15 00:00:00	BCN20 - Book Lovers	Book Lovers 1 Dia	book-lovers-1-dia	<strong><span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\">Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"color: #000000;\\">¡Adéntrate en un mundo de aventura y magia entre páginas! Únete a nosotros, apasionados de los libros, en un recorrido por los rincones más encantadores y librerias de Barcelona. Descubre rincones históricos inspirados en obras como \\"La sombra del viento\\" de Carlos Ruiz Zafón y déjate llevar por el encanto literario del barrio de Gràcia. Termina el día con una cena en un restaurante con un jardín mágico y alarga la noche en un teatro lleno de diversión , donde el arte y el entretenimiento se fusionan. ¡Déjate envolver por las historias que Barcelona tiene para ofrecer!.</span>	51	Llibreriacafee-Laie.jpg	3	<p>Buenos días Book lovers,</p><p>Comenzamos con la joya de la corona, si os digo que conozco un sitio que es un restaurante, una cafetería y una librería a la vez? ¿Sorprendente? Esta es mi recomendación para vosotros. Se llama <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#laie\\">Laie Librería Café</a> </b>y cuenta con una terraza donde se puede estar al aire libre. Mi definición es que es un lugar ideal para los amantes de los libros :) Además por si os apetece luego también hacen menús diarios. </p><p><a href=\\"#comics\\"><b>Norma Comics</b></a> es el paraíso del mundo del manga y nuestra siguiente visita. El edificio cuenta con dos plantas y te encontrarás miles de cosas por ver. Seas amante o no es una visita que vale la pena y más aún sabiendo que cuenta con 13.612 reseñas web y tiene un escalofriante 4,7 en estrellas. Es algo muy difícil de conseguir. </p><p>En la parte posterior del edificio está la Librería<a href=\\"#gigamesh\\"><b> Gigamesh </b></a>especializada en literatura fantástica y de terror. Con muy buenas reseñas web. Y además una de mis favoritas por mi afición al terror.</p><p>Nos dirigimos al born para adentrarnos en un lugar histórico y no precisamente por su contexto. Si no porque es un lugar que aparece en el libro de \\"<i>La sombra del viento de Carlos Ruiz Zafón</i>\\" Para quien no conozca el libro ni el autor os explico? prometo ser breve.</p><p>Fue un novelista español famoso por su obra más emblemática <i>La sombra del viento</i>. Con más de 15 millones de ejemplares vendidos se considera una de las 100 obras más importantes escritas en español de los últimos 25 años. Por ello os sugiero hacer este recorrido por el born.</p><p>Comenzaremos en el Centro Cultural de Born esto te hará entrar en ambiente, pasea por los alrededores y dirígete a la <a href=\\"#maria\\"><b>Basílica de Santa María del Mar</b></a>, en esta basílica un personaje de la obra va día tras día a confesarse, imaginate? El personaje se llama Bernarda. Luego subir por el Carrer Montcada y entrar en la Librería<b><a href=\\"#picasso\\"> Laie Museo Picasso</a>,</b> un lugar que en toda su esencia es arte. Y hablando de arte acabar en la <a href=\\"#maxo\\"><b>Galería Maxó</b></a> para inmortalizar la mañana. En su interior hay una máquina de hacer fotos con la temática de la galería por un precio de 3?, así os llevaréis un pequeño recuerdo.</p><p>Para comer os doy dos opciones, <a href=\\"#nou\\"><strong>Nou Celler</strong></a> un restaurante de comida catalana con menú diario muy rico o <a href=\\"#pedrito\\"><strong>San Pedrito Restaurante Y Licoreria</strong></a> un restaurante de comida mexicana con una temática y un ambiente muy agradable.</p><p>Por la tarde nos dirigimos al Barrio de Gràcia. Este bello barrio ha sido descrito en un clásico de la literatura catalana. En honor a ello tiene una plaça con su nombre, ah y se me olvidaba? también una escultura. El libro en cuestión se llama <i>La plaça del diamant. </i></p><p>Disfrutaremos del barrio mientras caminamos hacia nuestro destino, como era de esperar <a href=\\"#diamant\\"><b>la Plaça del Diamant</b></a>, un lugar histórico y conocido por la famosa novela. En ella encontraremos una escultura en honor a <i>la Colometa</i>, la protagonista de la novela. </p><p>Seguimos con la siguiente plaza es <a href=\\"#la\\"><strong>Plaça de la Virreina</strong></a> es una zona concurrida llena de vida, contemplar la <a href=\\"#joan\\"><strong>Parròquia de Sant Joan de Gràcia</strong></a> y luego visitar <a href=\\"#haiku\\"><strong>Haiku Barcelona &#8211; Librería y tienda japonesa</strong></a> antes de ir a nuestro siguiente destino. Haiku tiene muchas curiosidad, donde seguro os comprareis algo al entrar. </p><p>Al terminar id a la <a href=\\"#sol\\"><strong>Plaça del Sol</strong></a> y contemplar los edificios modernistas además de <a href=\\"#saturnalia\\"><strong>Llibreria Saturnàlia</strong></a> una librería local peculiar. Os invito a tomar algo por los alrededores o cenar en <a href=\\"#gracia\\"><strong>Jardinet de Gràcia</strong></a> un restaurante top con una decoración floral en el centro. No os olvidéis de probar la burrata. Para finalizar el día con un ambiente de ocio vuestro lugar es <a href=\\"#teatreneu\\"><strong>Teatreneu </strong></a>dentro de un Teatro muy popular en Gràcia. </p><p>Buena suerte!!!</p>\t\t	\N	\N	415	Edificio-de-San-Ignacio-Universidad-de-Antioquia-1024x574-1.png	1611,1612,1613,1449,1614,1615	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	1254,1085,1389,1235,1395,1255,1393,1259,1237,1239,1253,1234,1390,1394,1261,1078	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1_K3zv9M89Zw_BBfM9Apv5amvxElRA-E&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHt318g0wR2ND	price_1Q2TK9AFILSEnUZXWwqByWQl	1	N	N	Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.	\N	\N	Book Lovers 1 Dia	prod_QuotmE9aF6xPdT	price_1Q2zFuAFILSEnUZXpjWq3Bmm	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_4gw17d6B709w8N25nw	\N	plink_1Q3Ao9AFILSEnUZXWxbGLKS1	1Dia	52	N
416	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:28:17	2024-11-22 07:12:57	26146	2024-04-10 00:00:00	SV21 Cofrade 1 Día	Sumérgete en el ambiente de Semana Santa 1 Día	sumergete-en-el-ambiente-de-semana-santa-1-dia	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Cultura, tapas y devoción en Sevilla</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nExplora la vibrante cultura cofrade de Sevilla mientras visitas sus lugares más emblemáticos. Desde la iglesia de la Macarena hasta la evocadora Este itinerario te sumerge en la devoción y el fervor que definen a la ciudad. Además, saborea la auténtica cocina local en los lugares frecuentados por los cofrades sevillanos. Esta experiencia única te conectará con la historia, la tradición, la cultura y los sabores de Sevilla, llevándote a la esencia de esta ciudad inolvidable.	52	Cofrade-2.jpeg	1	<p>Bienvenidos a Sevilla! Hoy comenzamos el día en uno de los barrios más cofrades de Sevilla: ¡Triana!</p><p>Comenzaremos desayunando en el bar <a href=\\"#baronesa\\"><b>La Baronesa</b></a>, después visitaremos la<a href=\\"#santaana\\"><b> Real Parroquia Señora Santa Ana</b></a>, conocida por su arquitectura barroca y su devoción a Santa Ana, la madre de la Virgen María, para posteriormente seguir hacía la <a href=\\"#capilladelosmarineros\\"><b>Capilla de los Marineros</b></a>, que alberga la imagen de la Esperanza de Triana, una de las imágenes más veneradas en Sevilla. Tampoco puede perderse la <a href=\\"#cristoexpiracion\\"><strong>Basilica del Stmo. Cristo de la Expiración.</strong></a></p><p>Después cruzaremos el icónico <b><a href=\\"#puentedetriana\\">puente de Isabel II</a>,</b> que conecta el barrio de Triana con el centro histórico de Sevilla. Al cruzar, propongo poner rumbo hacia la <a href=\\"#magdalena\\"><b>Parroquia de Santa María Magdalena. </b></a>Si se os hace tarde por la zona y queréis tapear algo, os recomiendo la <a href=\\"#matacandela\\"><b>Taberna Cofrade Matacandela</b></a>.</p><p>Después de almorzar, no olvides visitar la <a href=\\"#catedral\\"><strong>Catedral de Sevilla</strong></a>, para luego dirigirte a la <a href=\\"#lablanca\\"><strong>Iglesia de Santa María la Blanca</strong></a>. </p><p> </p><p>Ya que estáis por el centro otras parroquias menos conocidas pero dignas de ver por la zona de las Setas son la de <b><a href=\\"#sanpedroapostol\\">San Pedro Apóstol</a>, <a href=\\"#santacatalina\\">Santa Catalina</a> o la <a href=\\"#buensuceso\\">iglesia del buen Suceso</a></b><b>. </b>Si queréis tapear algo por la zona en un ambiente totalmente cofrade, no dejéis de ir a <b><a href=\\"#losclaveles\\">Los Claveles</a> o a <a href=\\"#elrinconcillo\\">el Rinconcillo</a>, </b>o si queréis cenar en un lugar muy conocido por sus \\"piripis\\", <a href=\\"#bodeguitaromeroymejias\\"><strong>Bodeguita Romero & Mejía</strong></a><strong>s</strong>. Y, para finalizar el día, no podéis perderos en el bar de copas <a href=\\"#garlochi\\"><b>Garlochí </b></a>con temática pintoresca y cofrade.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	416	Cofrade-2.jpeg	1089,1090,1091,1092,1093,1094,1095,1096,1097,1098,1099	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	es	1403,1414,1402,1407,1413,1415,1410,1408,1411,1409,1400,1412,1406,1405,1404,1401	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=16QkCEh0W5Va2avofHBPcv2c5v_ZB2FY&ehbc=2E312F\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtmoHuMNxFm4	price_1Q2TKAAFILSEnUZXwufTfuZI	1	S	N	Cultura, tapas y devoción en Sevilla	\N	\N	Sumérgete en el ambiente de Semana Santa 1 Dí­a	prod_Quosx4I3rKAD4f	price_1Q2zF6AFILSEnUZXYmuGwLAt		https://buy.stripe.com/test_dR69DJ3oV2hE2oE03d		plink_1Q3AoAAFILSEnUZX5NaLMtDH	1Dia	53	N
417	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:28:34	2024-11-22 07:10:27	26195	2024-04-10 00:00:00	SV22 Flamenco 1 Day	Art, Dance & Flamenco in 1 Day	art-dance--flamenco-in-1-day	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">The essence of flamenco music and dance in Seville</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nImmerse yourself in the captivating world of flamenco in Sevilla as you explore its most iconic corners. From historic neighborhoods to the most authentic tablao venues, this experience will take you to the heart of flamenco music and dance. Plus, savor authentic local cuisine at spots frequented by flamenco enthusiasts. Let the passion, music, and flavors of Sevilla sweep you away.	53	La-casa-del-flamenco.jpg	1	<p>Welcome to Seville! The cradle of flamenco, here history, culture and art intertwine in every corner. Discover the soul of Andalusia through this flamenco experience, an artistic expression that excites and enriches the senses. From the royal palaces to the intimate tablaos, Seville invites you to live a unique experience where flamenco comes to life and becomes an unforgettable passion. Let yourself be carried away by the passionate rhythm of Seville and its unmatched flamenco art&#8230;let&#8217;s get started!!</p><p>Morning in Triana: In the Plaza del Altozano, you will find a sculpture of a woman with a guitar in front of the Capilla del Carmen (<a href=\\"#monumentotrianaalarteflamenco\\"><strong>monument &#8220;Triana to Flamenco Art&#8221;</strong></a> created by Jesús Gavira), which is a symbol of Triana. If you are a fan of Holy Week, in Triana you have two chapels that are a must-see: the <a href=\\"#capilladelosmarineros\\"><strong>Capilla de los Marineros</strong></a> with the venerated image of the Esperanza de Triana, and that of the <a href=\\"#hermandaddelaestrella\\"><strong>Cofradía de la Estrella</strong> </a>on San Jacinto Street.<br />Don&#8217;t forget to visit the <a href=\\"#mercadodetriana\\"><strong>Triana Market</strong></a> where there are many stalls of all kinds in case you want to snack or have a gin and tonic at the Juan Carlos Kiosk (position 37). If you haven&#8217;t eaten at the market, another option is <a href=\\"#plazadeelsalvador\\"><strong>Las Golondrinas Pagés del Corro</strong> </a>or across the bridge to the historic center, the <a href=\\"#tabernacasasarmiento\\"><strong>Casa Sarmiento</strong>.</a></p><p>In the afternoon I recommend visiting the Macarena area, take the opportunity to visit the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"##monumentalensembleofsaintlouisofthefrench\\"><b>Conjunto Monumental de San Luis de los Franceses</b></a> (until 5 p.m.), the great jewel of Sevillian baroque architecture, which every year serves as the stage for the Biennale of Flamenco, a unique show.</p><p>Afterwards, don&#8217;t forget to visit the arch and the <a href=\\"#basilica\\"><strong>Basilica </strong></a>as well as the brotherhood museum. Also explore the famous <a href=\\"#alamedadehercules\\"><strong>Alameda de Hércules</strong></a>, which was the heart of bohemian flamenco for much of the 20th century. In the Alameda, you can visit the <a href=\\"#monumenttoniñadelospeines\\"><strong>Monumento de la Niña de los Peines</strong></a> (Pastora Pavón), one of the greatest flamenco singers of all time, and that of the guitarist Manolo Caracol.</p><p>For dinner, I recommend going to the <a href=\\"#penaculturalflamencatorresmacarena\\"><strong>Peña Cultural Flamenca Torres Macarena</strong></a>, an intimate flamenco center with live performances in its patio, where tapas and cold beer are served along with the show. They also have a charming terrace in a very Sevillian atmosphere (normally closed Monday and Tuesday and the show starts after 8 p.m.). If you prefer a quieter option, try <a href=\\"#alaljiberestaurant\\"><strong>Restaurante Al Aljibe</strong></a> in the heart of Alameda.</p><p>If La peña was not available and you fancy a flamenco tablao, in the famous Santa Cruz neighborhood you have <a href=\\"#lacasadelflamenco\\"><strong>La Casa del Flamenco</strong></a>, with several shows every night and a very complete performance. For dinner in this area, you can go to <a href=\\"#loscoloniales\\"><strong>Los Coloniales</strong></a>, a typical Andalusian tavern with painted tiles. The whiskey sirloin is delicious! If you want to have a drink afterwards, you can go to <a href=\\"#lacarboneria\\"><strong>La Carbonería</strong></a>.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	417	La-casa-del-flamenco.jpg	1087,1616,1617,1618,1619,1620,1621,1622	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	7,2,1,23,24,16,14,21,15,20,3,4,19,6,18,26	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=1CZ5DgQ1c57CkhPTadktgxWwxMwYiseg&ehbc=2E312F\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHtW2bGlWKUBO	price_1Q2TKAAFILSEnUZXrLi0wGyK	1	N	N	The essence of flamenco music and dance in Seville	\N	\N	Art, Dance & Flamenco in 1 Day	prod_QuosL7kUVxoCfV	price_1Q2zF7AFILSEnUZXxHWrBIF4	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_14keY37Fb1dAfbqbLW	\N	plink_1Q3AoAAFILSEnUZXt8IAwmq9	1Dia	54	N
418	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:28:49	2024-11-22 07:10:27	26197	2024-04-10 00:00:00	SV24 Barroco 1 Day	Splendor Baroque in 1 day	splendor-baroque-in-1-day	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Following the indelible trail of Seville\\ s architectural and artistic wonders</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nDiscover Seville\\ s Baroque, a blend of art, architecture, and cuisine. Explore hidden historical gems, from lesser-known majestic palaces to the Cathedral and the Royal Alcazar. Savor authentic tapas and relish nights on scenic terraces. An experience to uncover the cultural richness of churches and convents in this city.	54	Catedral-de-Sevilla.jpg	1	<p>Experiencing the Baroque in Seville is a journey that transports visitors to an era of artistic splendor and religious fervor. It&#8217;s like strolling through an open-air museum where every street, square, and church tells a story of grandeur and devotion. </p><p>Today, we&#8217;ll begin by visiting the <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#palaciodesantelmo\\">Palace of San Telmo</a></strong>, a magnificent example of Baroque architecture that has witnessed various significant events over the centuries. We&#8217;ll then head to the old <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#rectorado\\">Royal Tobacco Factory of Seville</a></strong>, now known as &#8220;El Rectorado.&#8221; The building is a prominent example of Baroque architecture that has witnessed important events over the centuries. </p><p>Next, we&#8217;ll visit the <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#palacioarzobispal\\">Archbishop&#8217;s Palace</a></strong>, which was the residence of bishops and archbishops of episcopal sees, as well as military and nobles. </p><p>We certainly can&#8217;t ignore the <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#catedral\\">Seville Cathedral</a></strong>, one of the most impressive Baroque constructions in Spain. Its grandiose facade and majestic interior merge Baroque opulence with Gothic grandeur. And of course, La Giralda, the Cathedral&#8217;s bell tower, is an icon of the city. Its design, a fusion of Islamic, Gothic, and Renaissance styles, is a testament to the artistic transition that marked the Baroque era. </p><p>We&#8217;ll take a break for lunch. Although it has become somewhat touristy lately, it&#8217;s worth having some tapas at <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#bargiralda\\">Bar Giralda</a></strong>, which coexists with a 12th-century hammam and is simply spectacular. Or if tapas are your thing, the <strong>Bar Santa Cruz \\"Las Columnas\\"</strong> is also recommended.</p><p>After lunch, we are going to visit the <a href=\\"#hospitalcaridad\\"><strong>Hospital de la Caridad</strong></a>, a prominent example of Baroque architecture. It was founded in the 17th century by the pious Sevillian Miguel de Mañara, who transformed an old chapel into a hospital to care for the sick and needy. </p><p>We&#8217;ll then head to the <a href=\\"#iglesiaelsalvador\\"><strong>Church of El Salvador</strong></a>. It&#8217;s the largest church in Seville after the Cathedral. It&#8217;s a Baroque temple that was built where the Ibn Adabbas mosque used to be, of which the prayer courtyard and the base of the minaret tower are preserved.</p><p>Moreove, we&#8217;ll venture into the Santa Cruz Neighborhood, with its cobbled streets and whitewashed courtyards, also reflecting the influence of Baroque on local architecture. Here, the wrought-iron balconies and ornate grilles are a testimony to the artistic richness of the era. Apart from wandering through its Jewish quarter streets and enjoying its orange tree courtyards, in this area, we have one mandatory stop: The <a href=\\"#venerables\\"><strong>Hospital de los Venerables</strong></a>: with its Baroque-style church and orange tree courtyard, it&#8217;s another testament to the opulence of the era. Its decorative details, such as plasterwork and tiles, bear witness to the artistic ingenuity of the time.</p><p>For the night, after such an eventful day, you deserve a treat at the <a href=\\"#restaurantesanfernando\\"><strong>San Fernando Restaurant</strong></a>. Another more budget-friendly option is <a href=\\"#ovejasnegras\\"><strong>Ovejas Negras</strong></a>. Afterwards, you can grab a drink at the charismatic <a href=\\"#garlochi\\"><strong>Garlochí</strong></a> (you have to try  their &#8216;Sangre de Cristo&#8217; cocktail, is quite an experience).</p>\t\t	\N	\N	418	Catedral-de-Sevilla.jpg	1118,1119,1120,1121,1122,1123,1124,1125	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	118,120,122,133,126,49,127,132,119,117,131	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=1uYXYDlaaA6_J0WJp0-nuwmUglUoRCH4&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHte8rNBMDWvU	price_1Q2TKBAFILSEnUZXyX8Y1ldi	1	N	N	Following the indelible trail of Seville\\ s architectural and artistic wonders	\N	\N	Splendor Baroque in 1 day	prod_QuosOFnpr9IRpb	price_1Q2zF7AFILSEnUZXRltgcf8C	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_9AQeY30cJ3lI2oE8zL	\N	plink_1Q3AoBAFILSEnUZXOzsz8ib4	1Dia	55	N
419	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:29:04	2024-11-22 07:10:27	26199	2024-04-11 00:00:00	SV25 Gourmet & Relax 1 Day	Gourmet & Relax in 1 day	gourmet--relax-in-1-day	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Take a break and treat yourself with your partner in Seville</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nSet off on a journey through Seville where history and culture intertwine. Explore the city, unwind at spas, savor local cuisine, and enjoy magical sunsets while cruising the Guadalquivir River. Immerse yourself in a unique experience full of discoveries and flavors in this charming city.	55	relaxgourmet3.jpg	1	<p>We start our first day by leisurely enjoying a coffee and breakfast at <a href=\\"#mokambo\\"><strong>Mokambo café</strong></a>. This café offers healthy breakfasts and brunches with fresh, organic products ? a true celebration of real food. The owners&#8217; hospitality is excellent, and you can tell they prepare everything with care.</p><p>From here, we head to our first relaxation experience in the city. <a href=\\"#aire\\"><strong>Aire de Sevilla Arab Baths</strong></a>: The place is stunning. They offer a thermal circuit with various massage options, treatments, and experiences, both for individuals and couples. The terrace with a jacuzzi is absolutely enchanting. The service is fantastic, and I always leave feeling incredibly relaxed.</p><p>Once thoroughly relaxed at the spa, I suggest taking a leisurely stroll and exploring some of the gourmet shops in the city center, where you can buy (and taste) some delicacies of the city, such as:</p><ul><li><a href=\\"#sabor\\"><strong>Sabor a España</strong></a>: A unique shop that will enchant you with its aroma, which you&#8217;ll recognize from afar. It&#8217;s a traditional gourmet shop; nougat, dried fruits, marzipan, and many more that will transport you back in time.</li></ul><ul><li><a href=\\"#sierra\\"><strong>Productos de la Sierra</strong></a>: A rustic shop with high-quality regional gourmet products like wine, cheese, and olive oil.</li></ul><ul><li><a href=\\"#oleoteca\\"><strong>La Oleoteca</strong></a>: A haven for Extra Virgin Olive Oil enthusiasts. They have the best EVOOs in the world. They also offer olive oil tastings.</li></ul><p>For lunch, I recommend <a href=\\"#disparate\\"><strong>El Disparate</strong></a>, a gastrobar with a pleasant and beautiful atmosphere, featuring a charming and tranquil terrace overlooking Alameda de Hércules. The service is top-notch. If not, right across, you have the <a href=\\"#aljibe\\"><strong>Al &#8211; Aljibe</strong></a> restaurant with exquisite Mediterranean tapas. It&#8217;s located in a lovely house and has a delightful terrace upstairs.</p><p>In the afternoon, we recommend getting a massage at the <a href=\\"#koru\\"><strong>Koru Massage Center</strong></a>. They offer a wide range of massages, facial treatments, body treatments, and well-being experiences designed to help you relax and unwind from your daily routine. Moreover, I recommend taking a leisurely stroll through Maria Luisa Park, getting lost in its gardens, lying on the grass to read a good book, heading up <a href=\\"#gurugu\\"><strong>Mount Gurugú</strong></a>, and sitting down for a coffee on the terrace of <a href=\\"#bilindo\\"><strong>Bilindo</strong></a>. Right next door, you also have the <a href=\\"#espana\\"><strong>Plaza de España</strong></a>.</p><p>An activity that we can recommend for tonight are the <a href=\\"#candlelight\\"><strong>Candlelight </strong></a>concerts, concerts illuminated by candlelight and performed by live musicians in some of the most emblematic places in Seville. For lunch, now completely relaxed from the massage, you have these options:</p><ul><li><a href=\\"#estraperlo\\"><strong>Estraperlo</strong></a>: A fantastic experience, delicious food, and excellent service.</li></ul><ul><li><a href=\\"#fiaca\\"><strong>La Fiaca Tapas y Vinos</strong></a>: A cozy bar for enjoying tasty tapas. Their potato salad and croquettes are famous, but everything is incredible.</li></ul><p>By the way, we have a very special plan. How about having dinner while sailing along the Guadalquivir? It&#8217;s spectacular. I advise you to book one of the experiences offered by Andaluza de Barcos or <a href=\\"#esturion\\"><strong>Esturión Tours</strong></a> to enjoy a private boat ride on the river with dinner included.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	419	relaxgourmet3.jpg	1100,1101,1102,1103,1104,1105,1106,1107,1108	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	67,7,89,75,79,84,85,80,73,66,81,9,72,71,82	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=1yN6lxgbvV7Njwwgxyom98M7BySWFSO0&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHt0eK5IiZrUT	price_1Q2TKBAFILSEnUZXvwpGDcqk	1	N	N	Take a break and treat yourself with your partner in Seville	\N	\N	Gourmet & Relax in 1 day	prod_QuossG3tOs2ycn	price_1Q2zF8AFILSEnUZXXxhgnsvY	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_6oE4jp2kR9K68N22bo	\N	plink_1Q3AoCAFILSEnUZXuzeF2lJV	1Dia	56	N
420	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:29:22	2024-11-22 07:10:27	26203	2024-04-11 00:00:00	SV26 Sevilla Secreta 1 day	Discover The Secret Seville in 1 day	discover-the-secret-seville-in-1-day	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Explore the corners that make Seville a fantastic city that never ceases to amaze you</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nEmbark on a unique adventure to uncover the hidden treasures of Seville. During this experience, you\\ ll dive into the city\\ s rich history as you explore stunning buildings with centuries of intertwined stories, stroll through streets steeped in secrets and legends, and savor meals at one-of-a-kind restaurants that will take your taste buds on an unforgettable journey. Get ready for an experience that will leave you in awe of the authenticity and charm of Seville like never before.	56	familiasevilla.jpg	1	<p>In this experience, in addition to visiting the essential places of the Andalusian capital, I will share some lesser-known corners that will allow you to discover another side of Seville. I also recommend some of my favorite bars and restaurants for tapas and drinks. I hope you enjoy it!</p><p>I recommend trying the typical Seville breakfast: a &#8220;mollete&#8221; roll with olive oil, tomato, and ham, or some churros with chocolate. In the city center, you have several options like <a href=\\"#barelcomercio\\"><strong>Bar el Comercio</strong></a> in the Alfalfa area, or <a href=\\"#donacarmen\\"><strong>Doña Carmen</strong></a> near La Campana, which specializes in churros.</p><p>In the morning, you can visit the <a href=\\"#lebrija\\"><strong>Palace of the Countess of Lebrija</strong></a>. Its arches and courtyards will captivate you.</p><p>We&#8217;ll continue in the city center as there are many things to see. We&#8217;ll head to the <a href=\\"#algaba\\"><strong>Palace of the Marquises of Algaba</strong></a> (it&#8217;s free and closes at 2 pm), and then proceed to the <a href=\\"#sanluisdelosfranceses\\"><strong>Church of San Luis de los Franceses</strong></a> (closes at 5 pm), a lesser-known architectural gem.</p><p>For lunch in the area, I recommend grabbing something at <a href=\\"#losclaveles\\"><strong>Los Claveles</strong></a> (a local Sevillian place with Holy Week decor and a variety of tapas).</p><p>If you&#8217;re looking for a more immersive experience, one option I recommend for dining today or any other day is to try <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sazon\\"><b>SAZÓN The Folk Cook</b></a>, SAZON is the world\\ s first platform to provide Spanish food homely prepared by locals at their own houses, where you would taste it in complete privacy.</p><p>After lunch, we can visit the <a href=\\"#palaciodeduenas\\"><strong>Dueñas Palace</strong></a> (open from 10 am to 8 pm), which is sure to captivate you, a beautiful place with a lot of history. Another unknown place is <a href=\\"#venerables\\"><strong>The Hospital de los Venerables, </strong></a>located right in the heart of the Santa Cruz neighborhood, its history dates back to the 17th century and is closely linked to charity and social assistance in the city. It was founded in 1675 by Archbishop Manuel Arias y Porres, with the purpose of housing and caring for older priests and needy elders. The name &#8220;Venerables&#8221; refers to the priests who, due to their advanced age or economic difficulties, needed special care and attention.</p><p>Other secret points are:</p><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a href=\\"#plazadelcabildo\\"><strong>Plaza del Cabildo</strong></a>, undoubtedly my favorite square in the city. The tragic event known as &#8220;El Motín del Trigo&#8221; took place in 1587 right here. Popular discontent over the high cost of wheat triggered a revolt that left a deep mark on the city&#8217;s memory.</li></ul><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a href=\\"#calleverde\\"><strong>Calle Verde</strong></a>, a street that holds many stories and legends where you can admire the beautiful courtyard of &#8216;El secreto de la calle Verde&#8217; from the window.</li></ul><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\">The charming <a href=\\"#plazasantamarta\\"><strong>Plaza de Santa Marta</strong></a>, which you access through a discreet street in Virgen de los Reyes square. In this tiny square, you&#8217;ll find a 16th-century cruise from the San Lázaro hospital. Its beauty lies in the fact that it has a crucifix carved on one side and a piety on the other.</li></ul><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\">The <a href=\\"#libreriaverbo\\"><strong>Verbo bookstore</strong></a> located in the building where the old Imperial Theater was.</li></ul><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a href=\\"#santamarialablanca\\"><strong>The Church of Santa María la Blanca</strong></a>, a jewel of the Baroque in the heart of the history of this church dates back to the 13th century when a synagogue was erected in the same place. This synagogue, known as the Major Synagogue of Seville, was one of the most important in the city&#8217;s Jewish community. However, with the expulsion of the Jews from Spain in 1492, the synagogue was converted into a Catholic church.</li></ul><p>For dinner in the area, I recommend the <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#elpatiodelpali\\">El Patio del Pali</a></strong> Restaurant (closed on Mondays and Tuesdays, I recommend making a reservation) or if you want something less formal, <a href=\\"#lasteresas\\"><strong>Las Teresas</strong></a> is a very authentic and local option.</p><p>Enjoy!</p>\t\t	\N	\N	420	familiasevilla.jpg	1225,1123,1113,1165,1112,1226,1227,1168,1228,1229,1230,1231	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	41,502,12,48,489,49,50,487,45,4,234,154,96,112,53,8	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=1TIz9B5_Ap-EPQPY9XirCfFQQr54wBMM&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuN7r1G8ujVy	price_1Q2TKCAFILSEnUZXhBtRYgJO	1	N	N	Explore the corners that make Seville a fantastic city that never ceases to amaze you	\N	\N	Discover The Secret Seville in 1 day	prod_QuosqBQ138WOd6	price_1Q2zF8AFILSEnUZXk10FUaSD	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_eVa3fle3zf4q6EU8zN	\N	plink_1Q3AoCAFILSEnUZXUTp3RmgH	1Dia	57	N
421	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:29:39	2024-11-22 07:10:27	26205	2024-04-11 00:00:00	SV29 Budget 1 day	Seville on a Budget in 1 day	seville-on-a-budget-in-1-day	<div><strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Explore the City Authentically on a Budget</span></strong></div>\\r\\n<div></div>\\r\\n<div>Discover Sevilla without breaking the bank. Dive into its charming neighborhoods, squares, museums, and iconic spots. Don\\ t miss our recommendations for savoring authentic local cuisine at wallet-friendly prices. Immerse yourself in the rich Sevillian culture with this experience.</div>	57	Patio-de-Banderas.jpg	1	<p>We&#8217;ll start in the bustling area of Avenida de la Constitución. For breakfast, you can head to <a href=\\"#ninos\\"><strong>Bar Los Niños</strong></a>, where you can enjoy a very affordable breakfast. Afterwards, take a look at <a href=\\"#postigo\\"><strong>El Postigo Market</strong></a> and continue our route by visiting the beautiful <a href=\\"#cabildo\\"><strong>Plaza del Cabildo</strong></a>, a hidden gem right in the heart of Seville.</p><p>Afterwards, you can visit the <a href=\\"#archivo\\"><strong>Archivo de Indias</strong></a>, which has free entry. This archive is a treasure trove of documents that narrate the golden age of exploration and colonization of America. Founded in 1785, it houses an impressive collection of historical documents, including maps, letters, and administrative records, which bear witness to the cultural richness and legacy of the Spanish colonial period.</p><p>If you want to visit the <a href=\\"#catedral\\"><strong>Cathedral</strong></a> and the Giralda, free visits take place from Monday to Friday (except holidays) with an entry time from 2:00 pm to 3:00 pm. Due to organization reasons, the daily capacity is limited, and the acquisition of this type of ticket can only be done through the monument&#8217;s website. Another option is if you arrive early, take advantage of free entry during worship hours.</p><p>Furthermore, if you come to this area on a Monday, you can also visit the <a href=\\"#alcazar\\"><strong>Alcázar of Seville</strong></a>  for free: On Mondays from October to March from 4:00 p.m. to 5:00 p.m. and from April to September from 6:00 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. there is no charge nothing. Reservations usually sell out well in advance and are made on the website.</p><p>For lunch, we&#8217;ll stop at <a href=\\"#chari\\"><strong>Bar Kiko de la Chari</strong></a>, offering very cheap daily menus and combined dishes?a literal taste of grandma&#8217;s homemade cooking. If you fancy hamburgers, <a href=\\"#toby\\"><strong>Toby Eats the World</strong></a> is an option with a terrace and views of the Torre del Oro, offering burger menus at 16.50 euros and salad menus at 17.50 euros.</p><p>In the afternoon, we&#8217;ll visit the <a href=\\"#bellasartes\\"><strong>Museum of Fine Arts</strong></a>, which is also free for EU citizens (1.50 euros for those outside the EU), and we&#8217;ll take the opportunity to visit some of Seville&#8217;s most well-known churches, such as the <a href=\\"#magdalena\\"><strong>Royal Parish of Santa María Magdalena de Sevilla</strong></a>, or the <a href=\\"#suceso\\"><strong>Church of El Buen Suceso</strong></a>.</p><p>Later,  we can visit the <a href=\\"#artesycostumbres\\"><strong>Museum of Arts and Popular Customs of Seville</strong></a>, which is free for EU citizens, and for those who aren&#8217;t, it only costs 1.50 euros. Since we&#8217;re in the area, we can&#8217;t miss the Maria Luisa Park and its gardens, and the essential <a href=\\"#espana\\"><strong>Plaza de España</strong></a>. In this square, there are often street flamenco performances under some of its arches. I hope you&#8217;re lucky enough to catch one!</p><p>For dinner, I&#8217;ll give you two options: <a href=\\"#claveles\\"><strong>Los Claveles</strong></a>, or if you&#8217;d like to experience a flamenco show at affordable prices, you can visit the <a href=\\"#torresmacarena\\"><strong>Torres Macarena Flamenco Club</strong></a>, an intimate flamenco venue with a live show in its courtyard where they serve tapas and chilled beer, along with a charming terrace in a very Sevillian atmosphere.</p><p>Enjoy!</p>\t\t	\N	\N	421	dorne-got.jpg	1147,1148,1149,1150,1151,1152,1153,1154,1155	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	151,188,183,122,44,45,184,210,169,40,6,9,53,123,189	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=1DdU_-UBRfcUq0IFTCxH0U-UgoBmK8f8&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHukqCxmC7PkL	price_1Q2TKCAFILSEnUZXymIVC2O8	1	N	N	Explore the City Authentically on a Budget	\N	\N	Seville on a Budget in 1 day	prod_Quos8z41rHqXRb	price_1Q2zF9AFILSEnUZXyubkPEgO	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_14kbLRcZve0m7IY03i	\N	plink_1Q3AoDAFILSEnUZXCno8AsNh	1Dia	58	N
422	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:30:02	2024-11-22 07:10:27	26210	2024-04-18 00:00:00	SV31 Movie 1 day	Movie Sets in 1 day	movie-sets-in-1-day	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Discover Seville as if you were in a movie</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Explore Seville through this exciting route that will take you to the movie settings of the city. From the charm of Triana to the grandeur of Plaza de España, you can experience the scenes from your favorite movies. We also have some recommendations for you to enjoy the vibrant nightlife in Seville.</span>	58	dorne-got.jpg	1	<p>On the first day, if you arrive early, you can start at <a href=\\"#luisa\\"><strong>María Luisa Park</strong></a>, not only one of the most beautiful parks in the city, but also the location of Plaza América and <a href=\\"#espana\\"><strong>Plaza España</strong></a>, which has been the backdrop for great films like Star Wars, The Dictator, and Lawrence of Arabia. Plaza de España is a dreamlike setting, a place where dreams take shape in bright tiles and water that reflects the faces of those who walk through it. In every corner, in every architectural detail, you can breathe in the art and history of the city.</p><p>Then, you can stroll along the river to the <a href=\\"#oro\\"><strong>Torre del Oro</strong></a> (see if you can spot a pirate ship :). From here you can see Triana, the picturesque neighborhood where films such as the Spanish film \\"Your Son\\" were filmed. Triana is like a canvas where tradition, history and Andalusian culture are intertwined. Its narrow, cobblestone streets open to cozy squares and vibrant, colorful patios and the Triana Bridge in pure &#8220;8 Basque Surnames&#8221; movie style.  </p><p>Continue towards the center, where you&#8217;ll find <a href=\\"#constitucion\\"><strong>Avenida de la Constitución</strong></a>, the location where the movie &#8220;Knight and Day&#8221; with Tom Cruise and Cameron Diaz was filmed. However, unlike the movie, don&#8217;t expect to find bulls roaming the streets; for that, it&#8217;s better to head to Pamplona.</p><p>Next, you can head towards the area where &#8220;Carmen,&#8221; the quintessential literary work &#8220;Carmen the Cigar Maker,&#8221; was filmed, telling the story of 19th-century Seville. To do this, you should visit the old Tobacco Factory, now known as &#8220;<a href=\\"#rectorado\\"><strong>El Rectorado</strong></a>.&#8221; El Rectorado was built in the 18th century and originally served as the headquarters of the Royal Seminary College of San Telmo, an educational institution for priestly formation. Later, in 1845, after Mendizábal&#8217;s disentailment, the building passed into the hands of the state and became the headquarters of the University of Seville. Today, it is a public building, but it&#8217;s worth exploring the surroundings and admire the famous <a href=\\"#alfonso\\"><strong>Alfonso XIII Hotel</strong></a>, several times set of the well-known series &#8216;The Crown&#8217;.</p><p>After this eventful morning, you can take a break and grab a bite to eat at <a href=\\"#teresas\\"><strong>Las Teresas</strong></a>, which is a classic spot in the area, or at the bar <a href=\\"#ovejas\\"><strong>Ovejas Negras</strong></a>.</p><p>After lunch, we can&#8217;t miss the obligatory visit to the <a href=\\"#alcazar\\"><strong>Real Alcázar</strong></a>, known as the &#8220;Palace of the Kingdom of Dorne&#8221; in Game of Thrones. A visit to the Alcázar of Seville is like stepping into a period film, where architecture, lush gardens, and history converge into a visually stunning experience.</p><p>The camera starts rolling in the Courtyard of the Maidens, where Moorish-style tiles tell a tale of Islamic and Mudéjar influences. The intricately carved columns and delicately adorned arches are like the stars of this opening scene. Every corner is a work of art in itself, where light filters through the lattice work. The sound of water in the fountains and ponds adds a serene soundtrack to the scene. The Gardens of Mercury and the Ladies are like natural sets that frame this film.</p><p>Later, we&#8217;ll head to <a href=\\"#pilatos\\"><strong>Casa Pilatos</strong></a> (closes at 6 PM), set of the films &#8216;Kingdom of Heaven&#8217; starring Orlando Bloom or &#8216;1492: The Conquest of Paradise&#8217;, by the same director, Ridley Scott, and afterwards, you can stay in the Santa Cruz neighborhood, where you&#8217;ll find remnants of medieval Seville. It&#8217;s a place filled with legends and mysteries. Its narrow, dark alleyways have been the backdrop for stories intertwined with Sevillian folklore. The streets even served as the setting for the film &#8220;Nobody Knows Anybody&#8221; with Eduardo Noriega, set against the backdrop of Seville&#8217;s Holy Week. In this area, if you&#8217;re in the mood for a flamenco show, I recommend <a href=\\"#flamenco\\"><strong>La Casa del Flamenco</strong></a> for a very comprehensive performance.</p><p>For dinner time, we head over to the area of the <a href=\\"#setas\\"><strong>Metropol Parasol (Las Setas)</strong></a>, where the movie &#8220;The Motive&#8221; was filmed. In this area, you can enjoy some tapas at <a href=\\"#palo\\"><strong>Palo Cortao</strong></a>, or if you&#8217;re looking for something more chic, you can visit the terrace of the <a href=\\"#unuk\\"><strong>Unuk Hotel</strong></a>, where you can stay for a drink afterwards with incredible views.</p><p>If you want to extend the night, you can end up at the <a href=\\"#koko\\"><strong>Koko</strong></a> nightclub. </p>\t\t	\N	\N	422	dorne-got.jpg	1147,1148,1149,1150,1151,1152,1153,1154,1155	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	92,12,260,257,138,250,14,153,168,132,69,9,123,256,166	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=1aYsM9SKkg9cYnZxoyWqaCyG2hQADplM&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuU1qGZ5IWmJ	price_1Q2TKDAFILSEnUZXUL95c0sL	1	N	N	Discover Seville as if you were in a movie	\N	\N	Movie Sets in 1 day	prod_Qv1H5aylHCBUCC	price_1Q3BESAFILSEnUZXjkmXbtxF	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_dR617d8Jf2hE6EUg3X	\N	plink_1Q3BIeAFILSEnUZXx59W4WzD	1Dia	59	N
423	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:30:06	2024-11-22 07:10:27	26211	2024-04-18 00:00:00	SV33 Casas Palacio 1 day	Route Of The Palace Houses in 1 day	route-of-the-palace-houses-in-1-day	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Immerse yourself in the majesty of Seville?s past with these architectural gems, full of history and elegance, which will transport you to an era of splendor.</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nThrough this experience, you will have the opportunity to feel the essence of aristocratic life in Seville and learn about the fascinating stories hidden within its centuries-old walls. An unforgettable experience that will connect you with the rich cultural and gastronomic heritage of this charming city.	59	duenas.jpg	1	<p>We start in the Macarena neighborhood, having  a breakfast in <a href=\\"#feria\\"><strong>Feria83</strong></a>. Our first stop is the palace of the<a href=\\"#algaba\\"><b> Palacio de los Marqueses de la Algaba.</b></a> Today it is a government building, but it can be visited. Then, the next stop is the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#duenas\\"><b>Casa Palacio de Dueñas</b></a> of the much loved by the Sevillians deceased Duchess of Alba. Here you will find, in addition to the building, a museum of belongings of the late Duchess. We continue towards the Calle Cuna, specifically at the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#lebrija\\"><b>Palacio de la Condesa de Lebrija.</b></a> A visit you can not miss, both for the building and for the jewels it houses inside from Italica, including huge entire mosaics.</p><p>We continue to the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#monsalves\\"><b>Palacio de los Monsalves.</b></a>This building is proposed as an extension for the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#bellasartes\\"><b>Museo de Bellas Artes</b></a> of Seville, which if it is open we recommend visiting because only its building is a former Mercedarian convent and houses inside a collection of Baroque art, as well as works by Murillo, Velázquez and Zurbarán. Since you are in the area I suggest you visit the Museum of Fine Arts as it is free for EU citizens and costs only 1.50 euros for the rest.</p><p>We deserve a break for lunch, we will go to the bustling Alfalfa square where we give you two options: tapas standing in its typical tascas such as<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#trastienda\\"><b> la Trastienda </b></a>o <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#alfalfa\\"><b>la Bodega de la Alfalfa</b></a> or sit down to eat at <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#escalona\\"><b>la Escaloná</b></a> where you can try without fear any of their tapas, although the most popular are the carrillá, their croquettes or their tuna tataki.</p><p>With renewed energy, we will continue walking through the Barrio de Santa Cruz, its buildings are old palace houses now converted into apartments or private tenement houses, get close to their railings and courtyards to discover small hidden gems, while you get to the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#pilatos\\"><b>Casa Pilatos</b></a> one of the best preserved in the city, owned by the Dukes of Medinaceli.</p><p>Later, we continue our walk to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#fabiola\\"><b>Fabiola House.</b></a> Today it has been converted into an exhibition hall of traditional art. To end the afternoon I recommend a visit to the ancient <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#venerables\\"><b>Hospital de los Venerables</b></a> and the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#caridad\\"><b>Hospital de la Caridad</b></a> and have a drink on the terrace of the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#donamaria\\"><b>Hotel Doña María</b></a> which has spectacular views.</p><p>To end this experience, we will have dinner at Plaza del Salvador, where we will sit at the high tables in the center to enjoy a cold beer, the most typical tapas of the city as some delicious potatoes and the views of one of the most beautiful and full of life squares in the city center (you have the opportunity to enjoy the best tapas in town). <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#bodeguita\\"><b>La Antigua Bodeguita</b></a> or the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#salvador\\"><b>Freiduría Salvador</b></a>.</p><p>By the way, for dinner we recommend you a more sophisticated restaurant, be sure to visit the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sanfernando\\"><strong>San Fernando restaurant</strong></a> and get into the Alfonso XIII Hotel (I recommend making a reservation in advance to ensure availability).</p><p>Enjoy!</p>\t\t	\N	\N	423	duenas.jpg	1225,1227,1451,1452,1152,1453	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1514,260,1504,1519,126,49,111,1518,756,1512,1510,1509,154,1507,96,1508,131	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=1LgB-md4uRlIQPtGRTrHeoKocdgWVmIM&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuQeoFGYh5j5	price_1Q2TKDAFILSEnUZX5rywvp7q	1	N	N	Immerse yourself in the majesty of Seville?s past with these architectural gems, full of history and elegance, which will transport you to an era of splendor.	\N	\N	Route Of The Palace Houses in 1 day	prod_Qv1H8JA8crrNnG	price_1Q3BESAFILSEnUZXBJLcFVV4	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_9AQ2bh1gN4pM1kAeZU	\N	plink_1Q3BIfAFILSEnUZX6L3ryBVs	1Dia	60	N
424	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:30:18	2024-11-22 07:10:27	26213	2024-04-19 00:00:00	SV37 Vintage 1 day	Vintage Seville in 1 day	vintage-seville-in-1-day	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Enjoy the most vintage and retro side of Seville</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nGet ready for an exciting adventure in Sevilla as you uncover secondhand shops, collector\\ s spots, and charming markets. This experience will let you dive into the heart of Híspalis\\  capital from a unique perspective, where you\\ ll unearth hidden treasures, discover historical gems, and experience the city\\ s authentic charm. Join us on this journey filled with nostalgia and quirky finds as we explore the quirkiest corners of Sevilla. Perfect for travelers looking for a truly unique adventure!\\r\\n\\r\\n&nbsp;	60	sevilla-vintage-1-dia.jpg	1	<p>The first day starts in the most alternative area of Sevilla, the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#setas\\"><strong>Metropol Parasol</strong></a> (Las Setas). A great place to begin the route is on <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#regina\\"><strong>Regina Street</strong></a>, a street reinvented in recent years, where you can find craft shops, clothing stores, cafes, restaurants&#8230; We recommend having a hearty breakfast to get your energy up at <a href=\\"#cacharreria\\"><strong>La Cacharrería</strong></a>, you&#8217;ll love its atmosphere, decoration, breakfasts, brunch, juices, and cakes?</p><p>We continue down the street and reach Feria Street, one of the liveliest streets in the city, where traditional neighborhood stores mix with modern shops. Moreover, if you come on a Thursday, you&#8217;ll experience the street in all its glory with the <a href=\\"#jueves\\"><strong>historic antique market &#8220;El Jueves</strong></a>.&#8221; Here&#8217;s a list of shops to visit: for clothing, there&#8217;s <a href=\\"#wonder\\"><strong>Wonder Vintage</strong></a>, Nonna´s Vintage,, Ropero, Antro Vintage, Pipa Vintage<b>?</b>; for books, there&#8217;s <a href=\\"#baena\\"><strong>Baena Bookstore</strong></a>&#8230; You can take your time and have a wonderful day in the area.</p><p>A must-visit is the <a href=\\"#feria\\"><strong>Mercado de Feria</strong></a>, where you&#8217;ll find a traditional market for fruits, vegetables, meat, and fish. You can also grab a bite at <a href=\\"#jaleo\\"><strong>Jaleo Guadalquibeer</strong></a>. Just behind here, you can visit the <a href=\\"#algaba\\"><strong>Marqueses de la Algaba Palace</strong></a> or the <a href=\\"#luis\\"><strong>Monumental Ensemble of Saint Louis of the French</strong></a>. For lunch in the area, I recommend &#8220;<a href=\\"#ambigu\\"><strong>El Ambigú</strong></a>.&#8221;</p><p>In the afternoon, we start at the Cathedral. Right across from it, you have one of Sevilla&#8217;s hidden charming spots, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#cabildo\\"><strong>Plaza del Cabildo</strong></a>. In this beautiful semicircular square, you&#8217;ll find several interesting and curious shops like <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#ortega\\"><strong>Lola Ortega Antique Shop</strong></a> or <a href=\\"#felix\\"><strong>Poster Felix</strong></a>. Additionally, if you come on a Sunday, you can find a coin and <a href=\\"#stamp\\"><strong>stamp collecting market</strong></a>. </p><p>From here, we&#8217;ll head down Postigo del Aceite, towards the Arenal neighborhood. Here, I recommend checking out the <a href=\\"#postigo\\"><strong>El Postigo Crafts Market</strong></a>. Next, we&#8217;ll walk to Plaza del Salvador, where you can find the second-hand clothing stores <a href=\\"#moda\\"><strong>Moda-re</strong></a> and <a href=\\"#peninsula\\"><strong>Península Vintage</strong></a>. You can also visit the charming second-hand bookstore <a href=\\"#boteros\\"><strong>Boteros</strong></a>. For lunch in this area, I recommend the restaurant <a href=\\"#sal\\"><strong>Sal Gorda</strong></a>. </p><p>Then, we&#8217;ll walk down Sierpes Street to reach Amor de Dios Street, where you have the <a href=\\"#read\\"><strong>Re-Read bookstore</strong></a>, and the classic record stores <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#latimore\\"><strong>Latimore</strong></a> and Record Sevilla. We&#8217;ll conclude our shopping route on San Eloy Street to visit the clothing store <a href=\\"#mosaico\\"><strong>Mosaico</strong></a>, you&#8217;re sure to find a surprise or a bargain. You can end the day by having a drink or dinner on the terrace of <a href=\\"#justa\\"><strong>Justa y Rufina</strong></a>.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	424	sevilla-vintage-1-dia.jpg	1624,1625,1626,1627,1628	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	584,601,594,589,598,585,582,586,606,233,153,604,595,587,599,4,605,600,596,603,580,602,597,583	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=1xbIGb9o9_8M2n-k2n7PNg-sv1YVMcz4&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuAlOMsgbd4O	price_1Q2TKEAFILSEnUZXWnWvcNhe	1	N	N	Enjoy the most vintage and retro side of Seville	\N	\N	Vintage Seville in 1 day	prod_QuoscdZhGqmT9O	price_1Q2zFAAFILSEnUZXmVowbDC9	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_3cs2bh7Fb4pM8N2cQ5	\N	plink_1Q3AoEAFILSEnUZXlPe6LBkr	1Dia	61	N
425	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:30:35	2024-11-22 07:10:27	26215	2024-04-19 00:00:00	SV38 Kids 1 day	Enjoy Sevilla with your kids 1 day	enjoy-sevilla-with-your-kids-1-day	<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\"><strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Seville\\ s Family Delights: Explore with Your Little Ones </span></strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Explore the magic of Seville as a family while strolling through its beautiful parks, admiring its miniature cities and enjoying theatrical shows. Plus, don\\ t miss the opportunity to savor the delicious food at restaurants that will make every meal an unforgettable experience for young and old alike. Seville has something for everyone in the family!</span>	61	Acuario_Sevilla.jpg	1	<p>To start getting to know the city, we&#8217;re going to one of its most famous spots, <a href=\\"#espana\\"><strong>Plaza de España</strong></a>. But first, to gather some energy, I suggest having breakfast in the surrounding area, for example at <a href=\\"#espana\\"><strong>Tarta Home Coffee and Cake</strong></a> (they have delicious pastries and an outdoor terrace). At Plaza de España, the kids will have a blast crossing its bridges and sailing little boats on the lake that you can rent. There&#8217;s usually a street performance with soap bubbles, which they love.</p><p>Right next to it, we have the spectacular <a href=\\"#luisa\\"><strong>Maria Luisa Park</strong></a>, with ample space for the kids to run around, there are swings inside, you can rest in the shade or have a picnic, or have a drink at the bars in Plaza de América, like <a href=\\"#bilindo\\"><strong>Terraza Bilindo</strong></a> (they also serve breakfast). To explore the park, you can rent bikes or a cyclobus (for 4 people) from the cyclotour company. Right in front of the park, you also have the <a href=\\"#ciencia\\"><strong>Casa de la Ciencia</strong></a>, if you feel like visiting. On weekends, they have a planetarium session.</p><p>For lunch, inside the park, you have <a href=\\"#abylio\\"><strong>Kiosco Abilio</strong></a> with classic tapas at a good price, or behind it, there are several restaurants like <a href=\\"#remate\\"><strong>El Remate</strong></a>.</p><p>After lunch, I recommend going to the <a href=\\"#acuario\\"><strong>Aquarium</strong></a>, the kids will really enjoy seeing the species that accompanied Magellan during his first circumnavigation of the world. You can end the afternoon relaxing by the Guadalquivir River and <a href=\\"#contadero\\"><strong>Paseo Marqués de Contadero</strong></a>, sit on a terrace to have a drink while watching the sunset, for example at <a href=\\"#agua\\"><strong>Kiosco del Agua</strong></a>, take a boat ride on the river&#8230; or see the replica of the <a href=\\"#nao\\"><strong>Nao Victoria</strong></a>, the kids will feel like true shipwreck survivors.</p><p>Nobody visiting Seville can miss seeing the Giralda, the Cathedral, or <a href=\\"#alcazar\\"><strong>the Alcazar</strong></a>&#8230; but since we&#8217;re with kids, why not turn it into an adventure? I recommend booking a theatrical visit or a family scavenger hunt with the company <a href=\\"#vivo\\"><strong>Sevilla Museo Vivo</strong></a>, the kids will have a lot of fun learning about the mysteries and legends of Seville.</p><p>Another option is the <a href=\\"#ilusion\\"><strong>Museum of Illusions</strong></a>! The kids are going to be amazed by the experience. Around here, you can have churros with chocolate at <a href=\\"#dona\\"><strong>Doña Carmen</strong></a>. And for the sunset, you have to go up to <a href=\\"#setas\\"><strong>Las Setas, the Metropol Parasol</strong></a>, to see the city from above, run along its walkways&#8230; Plus, you can enjoy the nighttime light and sound show. On the mezzanine, there are also swings for the kids to play on.</p><p>You can have dinner in the Plaza Nueva area. If you&#8217;re in the mood for something exotic and want to feel like you&#8217;re in Japan, go to <a href=\\"#buga\\"><strong>Buga Ramen</strong></a>. The little ones will love its decor, and one of the waiters is a robot kitty! If you&#8217;re in the mood for tapas, you can go to the <a href=\\"#seis\\"><strong>Seis restaurant</strong></a>.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	425	pexels-padrinan-932261.jpg	1270,1271,1275,1671,1672,1673	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	737,751,738,754,740,744,739,153,168,753,745,331,9,749,752,742,750,77	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=1QftBrmUNxGKrgZc5xAbp3jpMYDXt63g&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHu8kaWFrZy9W	price_1Q2TKEAFILSEnUZX4of4ydEV	1	N	N	Seville\\ s Family Delights: Explore with Your Little Ones 	\N	\N	Enjoy Sevilla with your kids 1 day	prod_QuosoaL4n9F0Kl	price_1Q2zFBAFILSEnUZX0h8rmu7J	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_6oE7vB4sZ4pM4wMbM2	\N	plink_1Q3AoFAFILSEnUZXs53fN9R9	1Dia	62	N
426	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:32:15	2024-11-22 06:39:44	26362	2024-02-03 00:00:00	MED09 Saddlebag	Tradición silletera 3 Días	tradicion-silletera-3-dias	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Cuando pasa un silletero es Antioquia la que pasa</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"color: #000000;\\"><span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\"> A través de esta experiencia, tendrás la oportunidad de sumergirte en un mundo plasmado de sabiduría ancestral, cultura, colores y hermosos aromas.  </span><span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Nuestros silleteros nos abren sus casas y con ellas el alma de la historia familiar representada en años de tradición que se ha ido pasando de generación en generación y que hoy llena de orgullo a los Antioqueños. Conecta con nuestra historia y disfruta de tres días de hermosos jardines y flores.</span></span>	62	finca-reserva-del-silletero.png	4	<p>Among flowers and beautiful gardens, the Paisa idiosyncrasy is adorned, one that tells the stories of the long walks that our ancestors made from the mountains to the city carrying a chair (silleta) with countless beautiful flowers on their backs. Let?s start learning about this great history and tradition that today is the intangible heritage of the nation!</p><p>Let?s start this trip through the Antioquia tradition, taking a bus to the town of Santa Elena in the traditional <a href=\\"#florez\\"><b>Plaza de Florez</b></a>  In the center of the city of Medellín, there on one side of the square you take bus 098 or 097 that goes to the El Placer village of the town, make sure that the bus sign specifies its passage through the village. On the way is the  <a href=\\"#elena\\"><b>Santa Elena Gardens Nursery</b></a>, there will be our first stop, where we will begin to learn about the different types of flowers that are in the territory. Admission is free and this is an ornamental garden where they grow all types of flowers, plants, fruit trees and ecological fertilizers; Here you will undoubtedly also be able to enjoy an immersion in nature and the variety of flora of the Santa Elena district.</p><p>In this sector of the district, very close to the road, there are several nurseries that you can visit, in some of them you can interact with their crops and learn about cultivation techniques, for example, a couple of streets away is the <b><a href=\\"#nato\\">La Granja del Ñato</a></b> nursery. <b>,</b> a place where you can strengthen your knowledge of the flora of Antioquia, which is lovingly organized for one of the most important events in the region: The silleteros parade. Near the nursery is <b><a href=\\"#samaria\\">La Samaria</a> ,</b>  a beautiful coffee surrounded by color. It is unmistakable, because the house is full of colors on its façade and interior; This is a good place to eat something delicious and have a coffee that combines with the cold climate of the town.</p><p>When you leave there you give back a little and you can share at the <b><a href=\\"#escuela\\">Santa Elena School Nursery</a> ,</b>  a magical place where they plant different types of plants and flowers that allow you to see the different tones of paisa nature and enjoy its special aromas.  If you want to buy flowers and also share with inhabitants of the sector, you can walk a little and be surprised by the beauty of the business.  <b>\\" <a href=\\"#don\\">Don Lucho</a> \\".</b>  The attention and kindness of ?don lucho? are undoubtedly the added values ??of the flower stand; With a big smile, thank them for the purchase. Without a doubt, if you want to inject yourself with color and rural joy, you should stop by Don Lucho?s stand, see their flowers, please them, and let yourself fall in love with the kindness of the peasants of the district of Santa Elena in Medellín.  You can have lunch at <a href=\\"#asados\\"><b>Asados ??el Placer</b></a>, a place of typical food highly recommended by the inhabitants of Santa Elena, because here you can live the tradition, eat the typical food of the region, among the dishes that I like the most is the posta sudada and the typical montañero, accompanied by a delicious \\"of course\\" with a sandwich, dishes representative of our tradition.  </p><p>At the end of lunch, and late in the afternoon, how delicious a hot chocolate is, that is why I invite you to visit <b><a href=\\"#kakaw\\">kakaw</a> ,</b>  a quite famous chocolate shop, where they not only sell the traditional cup of coffee, but they also sell vegan dishes for those who enjoy this type of cuisine.  It is a beautiful place, which has outdoor seating, where the attention of its staff is warm and special; It is undoubtedly a very good space to spend the afternoon and share delicious cuisine talking with the locals.  After the chocolate, I recommend you visit  <b>\\" <a href=\\"#artesano\\">Artisan</a> \\"</b>  a place where you can enjoy different workshops such as making candles, natural soaps, among others; It is important that when you get there you ask about the plan they have for that day; Additionally, there you can eat delicious artisan dishes, such as hamburgers, medallions or delicious desserts. On weekends, in the evening they also offer live music, making it a great plan to end the day in the town. You can?t miss it.  </p><p>However, if you want another type of food, to finish our tour of the town, and at night, we invite you to enjoy a delicious Pizza in  <a href=\\"#sapore\\"><b>The Sapore</b></a>, a pizzeria that is in front of the township police command, which is very famous for its artisanal pizzas and its good service, without a doubt it is a very good local \\"feeder\\" to finish the tour of this first day of the itinerary .</p>                	<p>We started the morning by entering one of the stations of our integrated Metro transportation system, taking the metrocable to Parque Arví. Our system is very well signposted, so you get on at the station closest to where you are and on the map you can guide yourself to get to the station called Parque Arví. When you get there, I recommend you enjoy the <b><a href=\\"#arvi\\">Arví Market</a> , </b>a space where you will find a sample of transformed crafts, gastronomic and agricultural products with which you can have breakfast, enjoy and support the local economy. Eating some chicken patties and some stuffed potatoes is my recommendation, a great choice to start the day. In this natural reserve of more than 16,000 hectares of nature, you can find countless experiences that you will live as a family and that will allow you to learn much more about our Silletera tradition. The silletera cycle, the orchid workshop, bird watching, among many others, are those experiences that you cannot miss. I recommend you ask at the ticket office for those that are available during your visit and let yourself be surprised by the nature, flowers and tradition of the place.</p><p>Admission to the park has no price, it is free, however some of the experiences and attractions may have a price, which is why it is important to ask about those that are available and if they have an additional cost. Being in Santa Elena you cannot miss having a coffee at <b>? <a href=\\"#panchocha\\">Panchocha</a> ?</b> and enjoy eating this traditional \\"panchocha\\" bread that has three types of cheese, it is located on the path of El Plecer, 200 meters from the school, there you can rest and talk for a while, enjoying the landscape and the delicious climate that this district offers you. ; However, if you want to enjoy a more traditional mecateadero, I invite you to buy empanadas, buñuelos and chorizos in <a href=\\"#pescadero\\"><b>the \\"Fishmonger\\"</b></a> a traditional fried food place owned by Luz Elena Londoño Alzate, a woman who has been a participant in the silleteros parade for years and mother of Maria Carolina Atehortúa Londoño, absolute winner of the parade in its 2023 version. However, if you like desserts more and are craving something sweet, <a href=\\"#kumini\\"><b>Kumini Cafe Bistro</b></a>, is the best choice. After the silletera cycle, you can take a bus and head towards the Piedra Gorda path where the cafe is located. When you arrive, you will find a very cozy, beautiful and nature-filled environment. </p><p>To end the afternoon, I recommend going down to the <a href=\\"#bendicion\\"><b>Silletero farm La Benddiciones</b></a> , where you can enjoy a tour that shows you the history of the Silletero parade. Additionally, you will share with various species of butterflies that they have in the beautiful Mariposario.; If you want to sleep among nature, you can also find accommodation there, with mountain chalet-type rooms. Before arriving at the place, I recommend you reserve the space and the tour in Whatsapp 320 7957392.</p><p>Before going down to Medellín, I suggest you have dinner at the restaurant <a href=\\"#bici\\"><b>Pizza Bike</b></a> and enjoy one of the 30 pizza specialties they have in the place, all conceptualized by the sport of cycling in the world, a sport that has given Colombia many victories. Within the menu, I recommend starting with the Pinarello starter which are pieces of cheese with olive oil and delicious French bread, then for the main course I would order a pizza cyclobiIn it you will find ingredients such as olives and mushrooms; Finally, I would accompany this delicious dinner with a coconut lemonade.</p><p>I sincerely hope you are enjoying this great journey through tradition.</p>                	<p>A good plan to start the day is to ride the <b>\\" <a href=\\"#bus\\">BUS DE LAS FLORES</a> \\"</b> , a tour full of magic, ideal to enjoy with the family and enjoy all the Silletera tradition of the city.</p><p>Pandora, is the tour operator that has this proposal, they give you an immersion in the Paisa tradition, visiting one of the <b>\\" <a href=\\"#reserva\\">reserva del silletero</a> \\"</b> farms. or <b>\\"</b> flower path\\"<b>\\"</b> where they have a number of cultural, recreational and gastronomic activities prepared for you, in addition, you can enjoy the visit and interaction of other places full of tradition that Pandora has contemplated in your tour.</p><p>To book it is very easy, you write to WhatsApp +57 301 7686327 and ask about the availability of the experience for that day. Already being in Santa Elena, why not enjoy a good mecatico paisa at the restaurant ? <a href=\\"#cafeteria\\"><b>cafeteria</b> <b>\\"El Silletero\\"</b></a> This is a traditional stopping place for all those going up or in Santa Elena. The delicious arepas de mote, the empanadas, the chicken pies, the warmed ones are many of the things they sell there and that you can enjoy.  Continuing with our immersion in the Silletera culture in the town of Santa Elena, I invite you this time to the Barro Blanco path to the  <a href=\\"#londono\\"><b>Londono family estate</b></a>, who are one of the most traditional families in the region, co-founders of the silleteros parade and winners for years in various categories.</p><p>Visiting the Londoño family at their farm in Santa Elena allows you to discover the Silletero tradition immersed in modernity. In the front garden you can enjoy a craft fair organized by the community; a kiosk for food consumption and also a small natural forest called the Tesoro del Arví, in which you can find different species of Orchids, Bromeliads, Mosses and Anthuriums.</p><p>To get there, you must take bus 098 or 097, which is based in the little square of Flórez located in the center of the city. It is important to note that the bus sign must say white mud or mud.  To continue our tour and if you like relaxation experiences, I recommend you visit the  <a href=\\"#hotel\\"><b>Hotel Entre Bosques </b></a>from Arví<b>,  </b>There you can have lunch with a menu prepared and designed by the chef for international visitors. In addition, in the same hotel you can enjoy a great spa afternoon with massages, jacuzzi and ecological walks in the middle of the wonderful forest of the district of Medellín, Santa Elena. .</p><p>As an alternative option, near the Londoño farm, in the El Rosario neighborhood, is the <b>\\"</b> Don José <b>\\"</b> farm , which is called <a href=\\"#pensamiento\\"><b>El Pensamiento</b></a> , it is the place that perhaps has one of the most beautiful gardens in the township, in addition , has a house museum \\"El Rincón Silletero\\"  that you can visit and that contains articles that tell the history of the silleteros.</p><p>For dinner, if it is Saturday or Sunday I recommend you go to <b>Cheo?s Barbecue ,</b>  a place located in the Central Park of Santa Elena, where they prepare delicious grilled meat and chicken dishes; They also have vegetarian dish options for those companions who do not like meat. Without a doubt it is an excellent place to share.</p>\t\t	426	finca-reserva-del-silletero.png	1629,1630,1631,1632,1633,1634	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1573,1581,1571,1568,1577,1584,1563,1579,1583,1570,1576,1565,1582,1574,1578,1569,1566,1564,1567,1580,1575,1572	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1E0Fd4F25MScai_WW6mi17JcLXO4iMrA&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuAJYnUxVLBE	price_1Q2TKFAFILSEnUZXrAfmClhA	1	S	S	Cuando pasa un silletero es Antioquia la que pasa	\N	\N	Tradición silletera 3 Dí­as	prod_QuotQX6HA1OoXc	price_1Q2zG0AFILSEnUZXZGLF6R2P		https://buy.stripe.com/test_9AQ9DJgbHf4qbZedUb		plink_1Q3AoGAFILSEnUZXxjl4GOUN	3Dias	63	N
427	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:32:19	2024-11-18 21:05:31	27430	2024-04-16 00:00:00	MAD001 MODERNART 1 Day	Modern Art 1 day	modern-art-1-day	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>An unforgettable experience of contemporary art</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\nExplore the world of contemporary art in the vibrant neighborhoods of Chueca, Las Letras and Lavapiés. Discover cozy galleries, captivating exhibitions and enjoy the unique essence of these places. Relax in cafes and bars with distinctive ambiance and create lasting memories by immersing yourself in Madrid\\ s contemporary art scene!	63	pexels-unalaurencic-20967.jpg	2	<p>Good morning art lovers! Today we wandered through my favorite areas of Madrid ??</p><p>I suggest you start on <a href=\\"#four\\"><b>Fourquet Street</b></a> , which is our reference street, since it has the most galleries per square km.</p><p>In the points of interest I detail the ones we like the most. They are all very small galleries and the treatment is almost personalized. You can always find sculptures, photography, contemporary or avant-garde art. Every so often they change.</p><p>The atmosphere on Fourquet Street is quite special, in all the bars very interesting conversations can arise about the works in the galleries.</p><p>In the area I recommend that you eat or have a brunch at <b>\\" <a href=\\"#carme\\">Carmencita Brunch Lavapiés</a> \\"</b>. To have a beer you have <b><a href=\\"#taber\\">La chulapa tavern in mayrit</a> , </b>Here they make a potato omelet and some delicious torreznos. The area of Lavapiés is special so just walking around is interesting.</p><p>There is a park <b>\\" <a href=\\"#esto\\">This is a plaza</a> \\"</b> where you can walk or read, an oasis in the middle of the chaos of the capital. You have several places on the same street to have a coffee, the ones we like the most are: for a coffee <b>\\"<a href=\\"#hello\\">Hello coffee Fouquet</a>\\"</b>.</p><p>Afterwards we can walk through the orchard area and visit some of its modern art galleries such as <a href=\\"#the\\"><b>The Goma</b></a> or <b><a href=\\"#mal\\">Malvín Gallery</a> .</b> Strolling through the orchard area we will find the <a href=\\"#gull\\"><b>Gulliver bookstore</b></a> .<b> </b>from León Street. Another interesting plan is to visit the <b><a href=\\"#rei\\">Reina Sofía</a> ,</b> the entire back part of the museum is a very multicultural and very cool area.</p><p>We can end up having a beer at <b>\\" <a href=\\"#tab\\">La tavern al sur de huertas</a> \\"</b> (where you can also have dinner), another option is the <a href=\\"#ori\\"><b>Orishas Restaurant</b></a><b> </b>or, if you like Indian food, <b><a href=\\"#cal\\">Calcutta</a> .</b></p><p>Enjoy!</p>\t\t	\N	\N	427	pexels-unalaurencic-20967.jpg	1180,1174,1638,1639,1640,1641	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1596,1586,1585,1589,1592,1591,1595,1588,1593,1587,1594,1590	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1b1F9SHtnr8FoR_Lv-l343QZyJ1Eyjv8&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuqppxv2bsIc	price_1Q2TKFAFILSEnUZXuzxzyUSi	1	N	N	An unforgettable experience of contemporary art	\N	\N	Modern Art 1 day	prod_QuotSYrYAUPzAE	price_1Q2zFWAFILSEnUZXXambO2Mq	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_7sI0395x309wbZe7vO	\N	plink_1Q3AoGAFILSEnUZXRV27xoJV	1Dia	64	N
428	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:32:22	2024-11-18 21:05:31	26975	2024-04-17 00:00:00	MAD002Children 1 Day	An unforgettable family adventure 1 Day	an-unforgettable-family-adventure-1-day	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>An unforgettable experience of contemporary art</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\nExplore the world of contemporary art in the vibrant neighborhoods of Chueca, Las Letras and Lavapiés. Discover cozy galleries, captivating exhibitions and enjoy the unique essence of these places. Relax in cafes and bars with distinctive ambiance and create lasting memories by immersing yourself in Madrid\\ s contemporary art scene!	\N	pexels-unalaurencic-20967.jpg	2	<p>Good morning, I&#8217;m Rafa, your host, and I propose:</p><p>In the morning, we will start with breakfast at the <a href=\\"#choc\\"><strong>Chocolatería San Ginés</strong></a> and then we will visit a very special place, the <a href=\\"#casamuseodelratonperez\\"><strong>House-Museum of the Ratón Pérez</strong></a> . Both adults and children will like it. Since you are in the center, I recommend a walk through the <a href=\\"#palacioreal\\"><strong>Royal Palace</strong></a> , <a href=\\"#jardinesdesabatini\\"><strong>the Sabatini Gardens</strong></a> , and <a href=\\"#plazadeespana\\"><strong>the Plaza de España</strong></a> where you will see Don Quixote and Sancho. If you fancy an outdoor plan you can go to the Casa de Campo and walk to the lake. To eat, you can opt for something more traditional like a Madrid stew at La Bola or something oriental like at Mercado Yatai.</p><p>Another option to spend the morning is to take a walk through Madrid Río, there are 17 children&#8217;s leisure areas and children will have a lot of fun. If you decide on this option, I recommend you to eat here nearby. <a href=\\"#costellorio\\"><strong>Costello Rio</strong></a> , the desserts are a delight, nearby you also have <a href=\\"#bartoboggan\\"><strong>Bar Toboggan</strong></a> and then a coffee at <a href=\\"#bitesmecafe\\"><strong>Bite me cafe</strong></a> .</p><p>In the afternoon I suggest some cultural visits, we will start by visiting <a href=\\"#elmuseodelasilusiones\\"><strong>The Museum of Illusions</strong></a> , where the children will have a lot of fun and you can take some great photos!</p><p>We will continue with a walk through the orchard neighborhood and if you like theater, I suggest you go to the <a href=\\"#teatroluchana\\"><strong>Luchana Theater</strong></a> , it has a very fun children&#8217;s billboard.</p><p>If you prefer to take a walk to the <a href=\\"#templodedebod\\"><strong>Temple of Debod</strong></a> to see the sunset, you can end up having dinner in a place that we love in the center is <a href=\\"#laexcentrica\\"><strong>La Excentric.</strong></a> You also have a mythical Madrid restaurant very close called <a href=\\"#casamingo\\"><strong>Casa Mingo</strong></a> .</p><p>Enjoy!</p>\t\t	\N	\N	428	pexels-pixabay-39691.jpg	1642,1193,1643,1644,1645,1646	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1604,852,1602,1605,1598,1599,393,392,1603,1601,1607,1608,1606	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1oUYDr7-43IZsmg5qsYWM1pu3W3SdNEY&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHunjyYzMHiEi	price_1Q2TKGAFILSEnUZXbkPHJyjM	1	N	N	An unforgettable experience of contemporary art	\N	\N	An unforgettable family adventure 1 Day	prod_QuotRP6lH1TySg	price_1Q2zFXAFILSEnUZXrntOeFY1	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_6oE0398Jf3lI3sI6rL	\N	plink_1Q3AoHAFILSEnUZXKEoImpnm	1Dia	65	N
429	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:32:25	2024-11-18 21:05:31	27432	2024-04-17 00:00:00	MAD004 CINEMA 1 Day	A 1 Day Movie Adventure	a-1-day-movie-adventure	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Enjoy the seventh art in madrid</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\nImmerse yourself in an unforgettable movie experience in Madrid. The script of this adventure will transport you through an exciting movie, while enjoying delicious tapas in a cozy movie theater. The combination of culture and entertainment guarantees that your stay in Madrid will be simply perfect.	65	pexels-conojeghuo-375885.jpg	2	<p>Good morning, I?m your host Marco, welcome to Madrid!</p><p>Today to get off to a good start I suggest <a href=\\"#garden\\"><strong>Garden Brunch Café</strong></a>, this place looks like something out of the movie BARBIE and whether you like sweet breakfasts or salty ones, you will have no excuse there because they have everything. Open from 9:30 a.m.</p><p>Then, if you are a Harry Potter fan, you cannot miss a store of more than 200m2, with clothing, books or collectibles, dedicated exclusively to the magical world of JK Rowling, <a href=\\"#callejonmondriagon\\"><b>Callejón Madriagon</b></a> , which is located about 30 minutes from the center of Madrid.</p><p>Another cinematic experience, if your tastes are more Italian classics, is <a href=\\"#belmondo\\"><b>Bel Mondo</b></a> an Italian restaurant with a total \\"dolce vita\\" atmosphere that will make you feel like you are on the Amalfi Coast with Tom Ripley or in a Fellini film. Try their cheesecake, one of the best you?ve ever had.</p><p>Being in Madrid and being a cinema lover, you cannot miss the <a href=\\"#cinedore\\"><b>Cine Doré,</b></a> a beautiful modernist building where films from the National Film Library are projected and you can eat right next door at the <a href=\\"#mercadoantonmartin\\"><b>Antón Martín Market</b></a>, with a wide variety of food stalls and international food. Next to it is the <a href=\\"#salaideal\\"><b>Cine Ideal</b></a> , the oldest cinema in Madrid.</p><p>In the afternoon, visit the <a href=\\"#salaequis\\"><b>Sala Equis</b></a>, the last X cinema in Madrid converted into a place to watch movies, eat something or have a drink, in an urban and cosmopolitan atmosphere. You can stay there for an after-dinner meal or take the tour to see scenes from series and movies.</p><p>And if we talk about places with history that are the most emblematic of the capital, which have been settings for movies, series and visited by national and international stars, we are undoubtedly talking about <a href=\\"#museochicote\\"><b>Chicote Museum</b></a>, where you can dine, have a cocktail before or after going to see a musical of all the offerings that Madrid?s Gran Vía has to offer, since it is open until 3:00.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	429	pexels-conojeghuo-375885.jpg	1279,1284,1647,1648,1649,1674	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1614,1612,1617,1613,1615,1611,1610,1616	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1W-c85dYd2ZqED_9JgWgvWzx9yqi5WNA&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHubBpxIKgpY9	price_1Q2TKGAFILSEnUZX2CPFqxM3	1	N	N	Enjoy the seventh art in madrid	\N	\N	A 1 Day Movie Adventure	prod_QuotcOHZi7qEo3	price_1Q2zFXAFILSEnUZXPjE9P3YU		https://buy.stripe.com/test_28o9DJ0cJ9K6bZebM6		plink_1Q3AoHAFILSEnUZXNZ0hl5my	1Dia	66	N
430	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:32:29	2024-11-22 22:04:37	27433	2024-04-17 00:00:00	MAD005 LGTBI 1 Day	A colorful adventure in Chueca 1 Day	a-colorful-adventure-in-chueca-1-day	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Colorful moments in Chueca enjoying the LGTBIQ+ community of the capital city</strong></span> Venture into Chueca, the vibrant LGBTQ+ heart of the city, and immerse yourself in a colorful and diverse experience. Discover unique stores with products that celebrate diversity in areas ranging from fashion to art. Indulge in cuisine that reflects the flavors and colors of the community. Immerse yourself in the nightlife of iconic venues and enjoy exciting shows. It\\ s an invitation to fully immerse yourself in LGBTQ+ culture, where love, diversity and authenticity are celebrated in a big way.	66	pexels-lucaspezeta-3358299.jpg	2	<p>Hello!</p><p>We have prepared some plans for you and we hope you enjoy a weekend full of color and atmosphere in the capital. The truth is that Madrid has neighborhoods, art, and nightlife to have a great time, so we leave you this little guide that will fit you like a glove.</p><p>To start, I suggest you have breakfast at <a href=\\"#lug16189\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Brunch Bingo Drag Queen</a><a href=\\"#brudra\\"><strong>,</strong></a> a good option for a brunch in the morning, you can also visit the <a href=\\"#lug36239\\">San Antón Market</a>&nbsp;<a href=\\"#merca2\\"><b></b></a>where you can go up to the terrace to have a drink and enjoy the beautiful views of the city. To eat, we recommend the <a href=\\"#viva\\"><b>Vivares Restaurant</b></a> a Chueca classic that does not fail. If you want to experience the LGTBI environment, I suggest you take a walk to the <a href=\\"#pedri\\"><b>Pedro Zerolo Square</b></a> .</p><p>But if you are looking for something more specific, there is <a href=\\"#LL\\"><b>Bar LL</b></a> with a drag show or ? <a href=\\"#caza\\"><b>El Cazador</b></a> ? which is a special bar for gay hipsters.</p><p>Are you lovers of the classics? Then the ideal place to visit is<b> </b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#ww\\"><b>Black &amp; White</b></a> . To finish the LGBTI plan in Madrid go to<b> </b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#boy\\"><b>boyberry</b></a> one of the most popular gay cruising bars in the city, which is divided into a games area, Glory hole, spy holes, cabins and even a dark room. And, if that were not enough, it has a store where they sell different accessories and materials that may interest you.</p><p>For dinner, I suggest&lt;&lt; <a href=\\"#mordi\\"><b>The bite</b></a>&gt;&gt;, this one has super delicious Mexican food, the bar is very nice and colorful. Nearby you have the option of eating at <a href=\\"#eco\\"><b>The Commissary</b></a> , the latter is a good option if you want to eat Spanish food. </p>	\N	\N	430	tmplw91srz4LKF00tDi	1251,1178,1651,1652,1653,1654	6.9	7.19	31514.35	S	EN	1624,1625,1618,3623,1622,1621,1626,1627,1623,1620	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1pKtyi-Fl4yMqxeGYolkL31VmfwsM6Bc&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuO2PGugYb5c	price_1Q2TKHAFILSEnUZXhEtLEZOd	1	N	S	Colorful moments in Chueca enjoying the LGTBIQ+ community of the capital city	\N	\N	A colorful adventure in Chueca 1 Day	prod_QuotSEjKXipeqZ	price_1Q2zFYAFILSEnUZX0yvrmqx6		https://buy.stripe.com/test_cN26rxgbH09w8N2g2n		plink_1Q3AoIAFILSEnUZX5By0Mc3B	1Dia	67	N
431	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:32:32	2024-11-18 21:05:31	27434	2024-04-17 00:00:00	MAD006 - SEXANDCITY 1 Day	Shopping and afternoon 1 Day	shopping-and-afternoon-1-day	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>A luxury shopping experience in Spain\\ s capital city</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\nLet yourself be carried away by the most exclusive and modern areas of the capital, where you can enjoy the latest trends in fashion and style. Experience the thrill of a \\"tardeo\\" in the most fashionable places and savor exquisite delicacies in the most popular restaurants in social networks.	67	pexels-markusspiske-210892.jpg	2	<p>Good morning, I&#8217;m Paula, your host. Do you dare to go shopping, what are you waiting for! COME ON !</p><p>We start the plan in the luxury area of ??Madrid. You can have breakfast at <b>\\"</b><a href=\\"#dolor\\"><b>Le Pain Quotidien</b></a>\\" on Serrano Street. In this part there are not only the big brands, but also very cute stores where you can find interesting things. These are my essentials in the area: <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#monisqui\\"><strong>Monisqui</strong></a>, <a href=\\"#brownie\\"><strong>Brownie</strong></a>, <strong><a href=\\"#renatta\\">Renatta&amp;go</a></strong> or <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#bimani\\"><strong>Bimani</strong></a>. The area is full of shops so you will have a lot of fun. To eat, you have to go to Jorge Juan street. There you have the restaurant <b>&#8220;</b> <a href=\\"#maqui\\"><b>Machine</b></a>\\" (a sure success), you can order the potato omelette which is a delight or the tomato with belly belly. You also have <a href=\\"#amaz\\"><b>Amazónico</b></a> , a trendy place with Brazilian food (the picaña and sirloin are highly recommended).</p><p>Then I propose a spa &amp; wellness plan, pampering yourself a little is always good. You can book an appointment at <a href=\\"#ham\\"><b>Hammam al andalus</b></a> if it is very crowded you can go to the <a href=\\"#well\\"><b>Wellness Boutique Experience</b></a><b> </b>Here they do massages, facial and body treatments.</p><p>After disconnection and relaxation, a walk through the Puerta del Sol and the Gran Vía, there you have <a href=\\"#zap\\"><b>Zap Shop</b></a> , a fun coffee shop-shoe store to have a drink. For the afternoon I recommend <a href=\\"#aur\\"><b>Aurora</b></a><b> </b>(it is usually very popular to book as soon as possible) and if you want to stay on Gran Via, you can go up to the terrace of <a href=\\"#dia\\"><b></b><b>the Diana garden</b></a> (you will see remains of the bombs from the civil war).</p><p>Another option is to have a drink on the roof of <a href=\\"#ay\\"><b>Madrid City Hall</b></a> , it costs ?3 but it is worth it, for dinner I suggest <a href=\\"#fon\\"><b>La fonda Lironda</b></a> in Chueca or you can also eat at<b> </b><a href=\\"#zest\\"><b>Zest</b></a> , where I recommend the delicious cheese risotto!</p><p>At night I suggest a few drinks at <a href=\\"#jazz\\"><b>jungle jazz</b></a> or at the <a href=\\"#azz\\"><b>Amazónico Distillery</b></a> .</p><p>Enjoy!</p>\t\t	\N	\N	431	pexels-markusspiske-210892.jpg	1206,1211,1215,1655,1656,1657	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1644,1634,1638,1632,1636,1630,1639,1635,1643,1641,1640,1629,1631,1628,1633,855,1642	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1dNz2yskawlBPG0Vni5sVwutuXxvc_R4&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHudOS7C6XZjx	price_1Q2TKHAFILSEnUZXohaan5M5	1	N	N	A luxury shopping experience in Spain\\ s capital city	\N	\N	Shopping and afternoon 1 Day	prod_Quot4P7q11nXtC	price_1Q2zFZAFILSEnUZXExcSkIbA	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_14k6rxcZvbSe5AQ3fC	\N	plink_1Q3AoJAFILSEnUZX8mRxuAyJ	1Dia	68	N
432	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:32:36	2024-11-18 21:05:31	27435	2024-04-17 00:00:00	MAD007 FOODIE 1 Day	Feel like a real foodie 1 Day	feel-like-a-real-foodie-1-day	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Taste culinary creativity and expert recommendations</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\nTake a delicious journey of culinary innovation as you indulge your palate in the city\\ s exquisite gastronomic paradises. Immerse yourself in a unique culinary experience where creativity and art merge in every bite. Our city is the epicenter of contemporary cuisine, and with the recommendations of our local experts, you will discover hidden gems and the most captivating flavors.	68	pexels-d-ng-nhan-324384-1624383.jpg	2	<p>To start, I suggest you go have a coffee at « <b><a href=\\"#elcomercial\\">El comercial</a> »</b> It is not the cheapest place, but it is a mythical place in Madrid. If you want another option I like it <a href=\\"#faraday\\"><b>Faraday</b></a> in Chueca has a delicious lemon and lavender cake, there you can walk along <a href=\\"#plazapedrozerolo\\"><b>C/ Pedro Zerolo</b></a> and experience the hipster atmosphere.</p><p>For aperitif time, I suggest you continue through Chueca and enter the <a href=\\"#mercadosananton\\"><b>San Antón Market</b></a> . There you have options that are worth it, my favorites &#8220;Bodegón de Vinos&#8221; or &#8220;Bodegón gourmet&#8221; others that are also very worthwhile are, <a href=\\"#diurno\\"><b>Daytime</b></a> eating sirloin with pasta, <a href=\\"#elcisneazul\\"><b>The blue cine</b></a><b> </b>if you like mushrooms. </p><p>To eat I suggest two legendary places, &#8220; <a href=\\"#bocaito\\"><b>Casa Botín</b></a> &#8220;, the oldest restaurant in the world where you can taste a spectacular suckling pig or the famous &#8220;Madrid stew&#8221; at <a href=\\"#lhardy\\"><b>Lhardy</b></a> .</p><p>In the afternoon I suggest a walk to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#retiro\\"><strong>El Retiro</strong></a> to see it or take a boat ride.</p><p>If you want to do some cultural option in addition to trying Madrid gastronomy, I suggest the <a href=\\"#mus1\\"><b>Prado Museum</b></a> or <a href=\\"#mus2\\"><b>Sorolla Museum</b></a> .</p><p>And if you want a fun plan, Dulce Espacio. For dinner without a doubt <a href=\\"#salada\\"><b>Zalacaín</b></a> , which now has Íñigo Pérez as chef, where you can try its famous baKalao tellagorri.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	432	pexels-d-ng-nhan-324384-1624383.jpg	1658,1304,1659,1660,1661,1662	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	414,1649,1646,814,1619,729,1621,418,404,1650,1645,1656	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1fHY7kVmWP9xzUAWPY33ib8RDyU-h76A&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuypbyr9O8Qn	price_1Q2TKIAFILSEnUZXozAm08qA	1	N	N	Taste culinary creativity and expert recommendations	\N	\N	Feel like a real foodie 1 Day	prod_Quot0JenkM8IIx	price_1Q2zFZAFILSEnUZXYdxITmwa	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_6oE6rx7Fbg8u7IY5nL	\N	plink_1Q3AoJAFILSEnUZXYCpY6kQW	1Dia	69	N
433	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:32:39	2024-11-18 21:05:31	27436	2024-04-17 00:00:00	MAD008 Rooftops 1 Day	From the heights 1 Day	from-the-heights-1-day	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Get to know Madrid from the heights</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\nEnjoy an unforgettable experience in Madrid, where you can delight yourself with the most exquisite brunch, immerse yourself in the exciting \\"tardeo\\" and end the day in the modern \\"sky bars\\" of the city. Discover the capital, its culture and atmosphere, and live an experience that will last in your memory.	69	pexels-athena-2972890.jpg	2	<p>Let&#8217;s start the day with a delicious breakfast at <a href=\\"#zap\\"><b>Zap Shop</b></a>, a unique shoe store located in the heart of Puerta del Sol. From here, you can take in the beautiful views of the square while you enjoy your breakfast.</p><p>Afterwards, I suggest you go to the <a href=\\"#picalagartos\\"><b>Picalagartos Skybar</b></a>, located on the eighth floor of the NH Collection Gran Vía. With stunning views and elegant cuisine, this place is ideal for enjoying a sophisticated atmosphere. Also, since the area is very commercial, if you like shopping, this is definitely your destination!</p><p>If you want a more cultural recommendation close to the Skybar, I recommend without a doubt the <a href=\\"#circulodebellasartes\\"><b>Royal Academy of Fine Arts of San Fernando art museum</b></a> .</p><p>Not far away, you will find the rooftop of the <a href=\\"#hotelindigo\\"><b>Hotel Índigo</b></a> , which in addition to offering options for drinks or eating, has an infinity pool, making it one of the best terraces in Madrid to relax and enjoy the atmosphere.</p><p>If you are looking for an international atmosphere and live music, I recommend the <a href=\\"#lalatina\\"><b>Hotel Generator</b></a> rooptof. I love this place, it is without a doubt my favorite. Also, nearby, you will find a lovely Japanese restaurant called <a href=\\"#musashi\\"><b>Musashi</b></a>. I recommend it 100%.</p><p>To continue an exciting afternoon from the heights of the city, I suggest a visit to the <a href=\\"#moncloa\\"><b>Moncloa Lighthouse</b></a> , where you will be 110 meters high, enjoying a panoramic view of the entire city.</p><p>And to conclude the experience in a unique way, I recommend you go to the <a href=\\"#siete\\"><b>seven tits viewpoint</b></a>, from where you will have a privileged view of the city. Then, for dinner, what better way to end than with a delicious Moroccan meal at the <a href=\\"#zahara\\"><b>Zahara Restaurant</b></a> or <a href=\\"#encuentro\\"><b>El Encuentro Restaurant</b></a> .</p>\t\t	\N	\N	433	pexels-athena-2972890.jpg	1663,1322,1664,1665,1666,1667	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1659,858,1660,1663,859,856,1666,1664,1665,855	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1TubFX_8_pLHLu6f2_X9Yqv1htnhg6G4&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuhYPcSxJnRL	price_1Q2TKIAFILSEnUZXduJq0P5h	1	N	N	Get to know Madrid from the heights	\N	\N	From the heights 1 Day	prod_QuotdKetN4b1RJ	price_1Q2zFaAFILSEnUZXi8TdNs1e	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_8wMdTZ7Fbe0m2oE2bA	\N	plink_1Q3AoKAFILSEnUZXXhlUF4GD	1Dia	70	N
434	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:32:43	2024-11-18 21:05:32	27437	2024-04-17 00:00:00	MAD009 PHOTOGRAPHY 1 Day	Explore, Capture and Share 1 Day	explore-capture-and-share-1-day	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>A photographic journey through street art and the most photogenic corners of the city</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\nExplore Madrid from a unique artistic perspective, delving into cutting-edge digital concepts, visiting emblematic places, tasting Instagram-worthy dishes and immersing yourself in the fascinating world of street art. An experience that captures the best of the city in a visual and gastronomic adventure. #MadridArtAndCulture\\r\\n\\r\\n&nbsp;	70	pexels-egorghetto-19829606.jpg	2	<p>Today you can start by having a coffee at <a href=\\"#reina\\"><b>El café de la Reina</b></a>, is in the square where <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sofia\\"><strong>the Reina Sofía Museum</strong></a> is located, it is the perfect place to have a coffee in the morning or a drink in the afternoon. Next to it you have <a href=\\"#icono\\"><b>Ikono</b></a> , a space where you have different rooms and scenarios created by different local artists, mixing digital and original concepts, perfect for photographing and being photographed in.</p><p>A different plan dedicated to street art or street photography, the first stop is at <a href=\\"#embaja\\"><strong>c/ambassadors</strong></a> <strong>19</strong> , the next stop will be on the same street at number 29, here there is an incredible graffiti in black and white, then you will see an incredible graffiti in 3D in number 33.</p><p>From there you can go to eat at <a href=\\"#calcu\\"><b>Calcutta</b></a> on Lavapiés Street, the food is great and it&#8217;s 100% Indian food, or you can go to <a href=\\"#ramses\\"><b>Ramsés</b></a> which is in front of the <a href=\\"#alcala\\"><strong>Puerta de Alcalá</strong></a> and <a href=\\"#retiro\\"><strong>the Retiro Park</strong></a>. When you finish you can take a walk in the park or go up to the roof of the town hall and have a drink.</p><p>To take some good photos at sunset I recommend going to the <a href=\\"#debido\\"><b>Temple of Debod</b></a> , This place gives a lot of fun watching the sun set on the horizon. Also from the viewpoint you can see the sun falling between the temple buildings. After a walk through the <a href=\\"#espana\\"><b>Plaza de España</b></a> and even <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#palacioreal\\"><strong>The Royal Palace</strong></a>.</p><p>I love cities at night, if you&#8217;re like me, take your camera and walk through the <a href=\\"#villa\\"><b>Plaza de la Villa</b></a> (Pasadizo de la Plaza de la Villa).</p><p>For dinner there is a very traditional place called <a href=\\"#pip\\"><b>Casa Pipi</b></a> , it is a bar with delicious tapas (the meatballs are delicious) another option is to go to <a href=\\"#cerv\\"><b>La Mayor Brewery</b></a> (great variety of delicious imported beers)</p>\t\t	\N	\N	434	pexels-egorghetto-19829606.jpg	1232,1235,1237,1668,1669,1670	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1670,1596,1669,729,1679,847,1593,1599,1601,851,1673,1680,1667,1678	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=13ui3Ud195mDifPrT3w7sd4dqP84c3rY&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuVmEiKpoBNd	price_1Q2TKJAFILSEnUZXXjNn0cTV	1	N	N	A photographic journey through street art and the most photogenic corners of the city	\N	\N	Explore, Capture and Share 1 Day	prod_QuotKhLo4DB7PX	price_1Q2zFaAFILSEnUZXNs6PUe91	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_7sIcPVf7DcWi5AQbMb	\N	plink_1Q3AoLAFILSEnUZXUYstklWt	1Dia	71	N
435	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:32:47	2024-11-18 21:05:32	27438	2024-04-17 00:00:00	MAD010 OTAKU 1 Day	Otaku Passion 1 Day	otaku-passion-1-day	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Dive into the otaku world of Madrid</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\nDive into manga bookstores, savor authentic Japanese flavors and explore the cosplay stores that captivate fans of the land of the rising sun.	71	pexels-padrinan-932261.jpg	2	<p>Today I suggest you have breakfast at the <b><a href=\\"#pastry\\">Hanabusa pastry shop</a> ,</b> in the Antón Martín market, try their matcha tea and their fruit mochis, a 10.</p><p>Let&#8217;s start our experience by going to the <a href=\\"#otaku\\"><b>Otaku Center</b></a> , an authentic sanctuary of collecting for manga fans, in the heart of the Malasaña neighborhood and very close to Madrid&#8217;s Gran Vía. There you can find figures, comics, original merchandising and endless material from Japan. It is worth going early to get lost in its shelves, because at first it may seem like a small store, but you will see that there is a lot to see.</p><p>Going up Atocha Street, past the beautiful Calderón Theater, we meet <a href=\\"#x\\"><b>Generation X</b></a> a unique space dedicated not only to the otaku universe, but also to comics in general and board games. There you are sure to find that special gift for someone, or for yourself!</p><p>Then I recommend eating at <a href=\\"#sushi\\"><b>Running Sushi in Akihabara</b></a> , a restaurant with a conveyor belt buffet and spectacular decoration, which will not leave you indifferent. However, you must make a reservation, since it is quite in demand.</p><p>Next to the Plaza Mayor is the <a href=\\"#cafe\\"><b>Café Kawaii</b></a> , a place dedicated to kawaii culture and where you can have a snack with a cosplay touch, since they have headbands, wands, glasses&#8230; and feel like a child, their decorated pancakes are highly recommended.</p><p>In the afternoon, another place not to be missed is <a href=\\"#gion\\"><b>Gion</b></a>, a new and vintage fashion, gift and decoration store, brought from Japan, in the Chueca neighborhood, where a walk along Almirante Street, Fuencarral or Chueca Square is more than necessary. Returning to the downtown area, in On the same Preciados street we found a place, <a href=\\"#kon\\"><b>Konnichiwa</b></a>, where you can dine as if you were on a Japanese street, with very successful Izakaya decoration and a pleasant atmosphere. Order your takoyaki or okonomiyaki, the latter to share.</p><p>I also suggest a couple of bubble tea places, very trendy now, for me they are the best, and that you can have while walking around the city, they are <a href=\\"#le\\"><b>Le.cha</b></a> and<b> </b><a href=\\"#i\\"><b>I Sweet</b></a> .</p>\t\t	\N	\N	435	pexels-padrinan-932261.jpg	1270,1271,1275,1671,1672,1673	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1683,1686,1681,1689,1685,1687,1688,1682,1684	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1o7AAqqQW3UwLCqpQaLfoEJNtT9XOpYo&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHupJpd13pKTs	price_1Q2TKJAFILSEnUZXpv1Yu8EL	1	N	N	Dive into the otaku world of Madrid	\N	\N	Otaku Passion 1 Day	prod_QuotOkl8sAu34t	price_1Q2zFbAFILSEnUZXrgxvDvAl	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_6oE6rx0cJg8ugfudUk	\N	plink_1Q3AoLAFILSEnUZXXmvhRi12	1Dia	72	N
436	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:32:49	2024-11-22 06:40:18	26089	2024-04-12 00:00:00	MED MEDELLIN iS TANGO 1 DIA (MEDELLIN)	Es tango 1 Día	es-tango-1-dia	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Medellín es la ciudad que naturalizó y reinterpretó el tango en Colombia. Te invito a que conozcas los lugares más emblemáticos de la ciudad que bailan al compás de este ritmo musical.</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\"> Mucha es la historia que se cuenta en Medellín sobre el tango. El paso de artistas internacionales muy importantes de este género, el suceso de varios hechos históricos, la composición de discos que enamoran, entre otras cosas más, hicieron que Medellín se conociera como una de las capitales del tango en el mundo fuera del cono sur. Te invito a que recorras las calles de mi ciudad conociendo los lugares donde se transpira este ritmo musical.</span>	72	Zelebre-azotea.jpg	4	<p>To talk about the history of tango is to go back to the 19th century, where different African-American and Creole rhythms, among others, merged in Europe, many of which allowed the birth of this rhythm so recognized worldwide.</p><p>It is said that the first songs of this musical genre were heard in Medellín in 1911 by Alfredo Diestro, and with him different movements, collectors and lovers of this genre began to be born. My grandfather, for example, loved to listen to the songs of Carlos Gardel, Óscar Agudelo, Alberto Rossi, among other artists, on his record player in the living room of his house with a cigar and a good drink; Like him, many inhabitants of Medellín let themselves be delighted by the musical notes of this artistic manifestation, which led them to find themselves in bars, discos and places where only this genre is danced and where they themselves honor the musical rhythm with dresses of sequins and shoes appropriate for dancing.</p><p>This is why our first stop is in Manrique , on 45th Street, at the <a href=\\"#casa\\"><b>Casa Gardeliana.</b></a>. A magical place, a house museum that is responsible for exhibiting the main objects of Carlos Gardel, an Argentine artist well known in Colombia and the world; Thanks to the love that Carlos Gardel had for Medellín and thanks to the history he has with the city, the Gardeliana House was declared Cultural Heritage of Medellín.</p><p>There you will not only learn the history, but you will have a drink and enjoy activities that are on the agenda for the day you chose to visit.</p><p>To get there it is very easy, take the metro to the university station, there you get off and take bus route 022 or 023 and either of the two will leave you at the door of the house museum.</p><p>Near the Gardeliana House is <a href=\\"#sazon\\"><b>Sazón al Carbón</b></a>, a place where you can have delicious barbecue lunches in the heart of this neighborhood, what I like most is their mixed grill, combined with the delicious chimichurri that they prepare; In addition, you can have a delicious cocktail from the menu, to cool off in the heat of Medellín. This restaurant is located on Carrera 44 # 78 ? 70, you can walk there.</p><p>Next stop, <a href=\\"#cafe\\"><b>Café Alaska</b></a>, a bohemian and tango corner that opened in 1937, two years after the plane crash in Medellín in which Carlos Gardel died. This is a place located on the second floor, on a corner just a few blocks from the Casa Gardeliana. Gustavo Rojas, its owner, is perhaps one of the people who knows the most about tango in Medellín, and he also has a collection of more than 200 thousand records that you will want to listen to. For lovers of this musical genre, this is a must-see stop, because whatever song comes to mind, Oscar is sure to have it in his collection.</p><p>Among the friendly, cordial and historical atmosphere, you will be able to talk with locals, learn family stories about tango and the transformation of the Manrique neighborhood, a place that was hit by the drug war in Colombia. Definitely, to chat and learn the Café Alaska is the best choice.</p><p>Being in the Manrique neighborhood, in commune 3 of Medellín, you will not be able to miss the cultural and community tourism proposal that the <a href=\\"#artistas\\"><b>Balcón de los Artistas</b></a> has.; This is perhaps one of the most representative social projects in the city, which frames and commemorates music, with incredible dances and touches that will make you enjoy Medellín Musical. As a corporation they have a wide agenda, there you can access dance classes, various shows and much more; You can consult all this on their website (<a href=\\"https://www.elbalcon.org/index.php/linea-comercial/\\">https://www.elbalcon.org/index.php/linea-comercial/</a> ) and book according to the day you decide to attend. </p><p>Finally, when night comes, if you want to enjoy the wonderful view that the Manrique neighborhood offers, I invite you to have dinner and have a couple of drinks at <a href=\\"#azotea\\"><b>Zelebre Azotea</b></a>, located on Carrera 45 # 69 ? 41, right in the sector where we have lived this entire adventure of musical experience. Here the menu is varied, you can eat a delicious hamburger, or for lovers of oriental food you can also order the sushi rolls of your choice; In addition, while you have a drink, you can enjoy the wonderful view of the city and the nightly musical show that they have as a surprise for you.  </p><p>But if what you want is to dance, I invite you to take a taxi towards San Juan Street, there before the 80th street break you will find <a href=\\"#ritmo\\"><b>Rhythms and Tangos</b></a>, which is a famous dance academy in the city, which at night offers a fairly extensive musical proposal to the beat of the best tango and pasodoble songs that can be known. It is an excellent place to learn to dance and continue enjoying this musical genre that graces the city so much.</p><p>It?s going to be a wonderful day, I know you?ll like it.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	436	Zelebre-azotea.jpg	1593,1594,1595,1596	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1692,1693,1690,1695,1691,1694	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1UhrXopSmiS6We303TPkALRB7lUIB08g&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	1	N	N	Medellín es la ciudad que naturalizó y reinterpretó el tango en Colombia. Te invito a que conozcas los lugares más emblemáticos de la ciudad que bailan al compás de este ritmo musical.	\N	\N	Es tango 1 Dí­a							1Dia	73	N
437	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:32:52	2024-11-18 21:05:32	27559	2024-04-12 00:00:00	MED PAISALANDIA LAND OF ADVENTURES 1 DAY (MEDELLIN)	Paisalandia, A Land Of Adventure And Magic 1 day	paisalandia-a-land-of-adventure-and-magic-1-day	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\">\\r\\n<strong> Among the mountains of the Aburrá Valley we also have fun for the little ones, enjoy with your family the places that Medellín has that are full of games, color and adventures.</strong>\\r\\n</span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400; color: #000000;\\"> Once upon a time there was a city full of flowers, colors and adventures. A magical city that offers joy and fun, with places that allow you to explore the world on ATVs, horses and long walks; playing with water, bounce houses, science and experimentation; In addition, share with animals in aquariums and other spaces full of nature, forests and mountains. In this experience we want to show you three days of pure fun so that you can enjoy with your children, the city of eternal spring. Medellin.</span>	73	Parque-norte-1.jpeg	4	<p>To start the day, we will enter the world of science, experimentation and aquariums <b>,</b> which is why I invite you to visit <a href=\\"#explore\\"><b>Parque Explora</b></a> of the city, located in the northern area. Getting there is very easy, enter the metro system towards Niquía and get off at the Universidad station, close to this metro station is this wonderful place.</p><p>The Park has more than 300 interactive experiences for the appropriation of scientific and technological knowledge, many of them related to music, where they will learn to play Colombian rhythms<b>; </b>he time, where they can test their reaction by capturing lights with their hands; the physical, where they will test their aim by throwing a ball on the spinning wheel in the open physics room, among many others. </p><p>Additionally, in this park, you will find a beautiful <a href=\\"#acqua\\"><b>aquarium</b> </a>with an emphasis on the Amazon, where you will discover more than 250 species of fish such as: arawanas, tucunarés, cachamas, pirarucús, among others.</p><p>This aquarium allows you to feel the life of freshwater animals in all its splendor, where many of them are on the verge of extinction. </p><p>After living all the experiences, I suggest you go to the dining area of ??the Park and visit \\"<a href=\\"#caserito\\"><b>Caserito Express</b></a>\\" a place where you can have lunch with typical dishes of the city such as: tumba paisa, sancocho, cazuelas, ajiaco and many other traditional delicacies; and additionally if you want to sweeten the day, how delicious an ice cream<b> \\" <a href=\\"#mimos\\">MIMOS </a>\\" </b>I recommend the mime with chocolate and peanuts. They will surely like it.</p><p>If you don&#8217;t like typical food, next to the exploratory is the <a href=\\"#brasa\\"><b>Brasa Roja </b></a>restaurant<b>,</b> where you can have lunch with a delicious roast chicken.</p><p>Go and visit this place, you are going to love it!</p><p>At the end of the tour in Parque Explora, I invite you to go to <a href=\\"#north\\"><b>Parque Norte</b></a>, which is located just a few steps from the Explora. This place is full of fun, mechanical games, jungles that you can explore in little wooden boats, and attractions for children and adults.</p><p>For the kids, this place has balloons, mechanical rabbits, mini crashes, among other adventures; The older ones will be able to enjoy attractions such as the Morgan, the Kamikaze, the trip to the center of the earth, the roller coasters and many more; And to live as a family, you can take the tour of the mythical train, the iguana train, the prehistoric jungle and many others.</p><p>Inside the park there are different options for food stalls to pick and eat, there are fast food restaurants, sweets, crisps, cotton candy, among others. Depending on the extraction you are in, you can choose the closest one. </p><p>At the end of the day and if you still have energy, take the metro at the Universidad station heading south to the Poblado station, there you can walk to Ciudad del Rio where you will find <b><a href=\\"#summit\\">SummitMedellín</a> ,</b> A very fun play place, here your children will be able to enjoy attractions such as bounce houses for adults and children, basketball lines, soft play for children, climbing towers and walls with harness, giant air mattress, among other attractions. Without a doubt, it is a great plan to end a day full of fun and adventure with the family. It is open every day until 9 pm.</p><p>For dinner, while in the park, head to the fast food area where you are sure to find something that you and your children will love.</p><p>Dare to live these moments of fun, joy and smiles as a family. You will create some wonderful memories together in my hometown.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	437	Parque-norte-1.jpeg	1597,1598,1599,1600,1601,1442	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1697,1700,1698,1696,1699,1701,1702	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1rAIcLheFAOA1ZpEldq1xArxGlL-sug0&amp;ehbc=2E312F&amp;noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuGbsO1cdKTn	price_1Q2TKKAFILSEnUZXrOP0yZHQ	1	S	N	Among the mountains of the Aburrá Valley we also have fun for the little ones, enjoy with your family the places that Medellín has that are full of games, color and adventures.	\N	\N	Paisalandia, A Land Of Adventure And Magic 1 day	prod_Quot12jkgMe8yh	price_1Q2zG0AFILSEnUZXFedI2TYa	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_00geY3aRng8u1kA2bD	\N	plink_1Q3AoMAFILSEnUZXMtn9zpEv	1Dia	74	N
438	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:32:55	2024-12-01 16:46:04	27561	2024-04-12 00:00:00	MED PATCH AFTER WORK 1 DAY (MEDELLIN)	Patch after work 1 Day	patch-after-work-1-day	<strong> <span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"> How about we talk, walk, have something delicious for dinner or, as we say in Medellín, ?patch? for a while after work. </span> </strong> <span style=\\"color: #000000;\\">Through this experience you will get to know different ?patches? of the city, where you can spend the evening and welcome the night enjoying a delicious beer, wine, or maybe painting, attending theater or some stand up comedy.<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">These recommendations are ideal for digital nomads who are in Medellín and for those who visit us at a fair or event, who after their workday want to enjoy and get to know the city.</span></span>	74	Milnueve32-2.jpg	4	<p>The Manila neighborhood of the city of Medellín is characterized by being the home of many artists, restaurants and independent businesses. As you walk the streets of this sector of the city you can find various craft and local markets where you can eat and buy travel souvenirs.</p><p>A place in this sector that immerses us in art and shopping is <a href=\\"#32\\"><b>Milnueve 32</b></a>, a place where you can breathe art in every corner and which is named after the year of birth of the famous Colombian sculptor Fernando Botero. At Milnueve 32 you can buy all kinds of materials for the work of art you want to create, access painting classes, buy second-hand clothes and jewelry, have a coffee, eat a small brunch, read a book, among others. It is a place that you do not want to miss visiting in Medellín.</p><p>Walking through the sector, what a pleasure to visit a couple of art galleries that fill visitors with magic with their works, paintings and exhibitions. </p><p><a href=\\"#molina\\"><b>Molina Gallery</b></a> is one of them, its founder has more than 30 years of experience in the marketing and dissemination of art. Within this gallery they support all emerging artists who love contemporary art, it is undoubtedly a place you can visit.</p><p>If you walk a couple of streets, you can also visit <b><a href=\\"#amarte\\">Amarte Galería</a> ,</b> a place where you can create and enjoy; There you will undoubtedly be able to have an immersion in art that will make you feel art firsthand.</p><p>To continue, I invite you to have a coffee at <b>\\" <a href=\\"#zorba\\">Zorba</a> \\",</b> a very bohemian place where you can enjoy different options of pizza, ice cream and desserts; while you listen to live music with different artists who can perform anything from a tango to a Latin American music song, jazz, soul or play percussion. It is the perfect \\"patch\\" to chat with friends and spend an afternoon. </p><p>For dinner, you must go to <b>\\" <a href=\\"#lavocaderia\\">Lavocadería</a> \\"</b> It is perhaps one of my favorite restaurants. The main color of this place is the variety of dishes prepared with avocado; a quite different and innovative gastronomy option for the palate. My favorites are the stuffed sirloin or the avoburger. When you see the menu, you will have excellent options to taste delicious dishes. Without a doubt, it is an unmissable place to visit.</p><p>This restaurant also offers you the opportunity to take travel souvenirs, go to the <a href=\\"#avo\\"><strong>A</strong><strong>v</strong></a><b>o Regalos</b> store and choose the one you like the most; Also, I recommend asking about <a href=\\"#tour\\"><b>the tour ? avocado course</b></a> that they do on a farm in eastern Antioquia. You will see that it is a great patch to do during your stay in Medellín.</p><p>To end the night, I would walk to <b><a href=\\"#masaya\\">Masaya</a> ,</b> a rooftop very close to the Manila neighborhood, where you can see the city, enjoy the pool and have a delicious cocktail with your travel companions. The perfect ending to a great night.</p><p>Walking through this neighborhood of the city is enjoying the wonderful climate of Medellín and the kindness of its people. Enjoy your adventure!</p>	\N	\N	438	Milnueve32-2.jpg	1602,1603,1604,1605	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	EN	1708,1707,1705,1710,1704,1703,1709,1706	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1r3bGuNJrBUSDDyDP-nKONQpuBY4ukek&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuI0biCYeHBI	price_1Q2TKKAFILSEnUZXnwxMgnLs	1	N	N	How about we talk, walk, have something delicious for dinner or, as we say in Medellín, ?patch? for a while after work.	\N	\N	Patch after work 1 Day	prod_Quot1Emtkiapo5	price_1Q2zG1AFILSEnUZXdLyxlt7R	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_9AQ17d2kR09w5AQaIa	\N	plink_1Q3AoNAFILSEnUZXo3JnPTzp	1Dia	75	N
439	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:32:58	2024-11-22 06:50:39	26135	2024-04-12 00:00:00	MED CUP OF COFFEE IN THE VALLEY 1 DAY (MEDELLIN)	Taza de café en valle de Aburrá	taza-de-cafe-en-valle-de-aburra	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Llegar a Medellín y sentir el aroma a café que sudan sus montañas es una de las experiencias únicas que vivirás en mi ciudad. Sumérgete en el sabor, el color y el aroma del reconocido fruto de color rojo intenso.</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Medellín, la segunda ciudad de Colombia, cuenta con una gran escena de café. Sus grandes montañas y la proximidad a los cafetales antioqueños hacen que la cultura cafetera en la ciudad vaya en aumento. A través de esta experiencia, tendrás la oportunidad de conocer, vivir y probar el proceso de café que se vive en las montañas de Medellín; además de conocer diferentes métodos de preparación y degustar increíbles maridajes. </span>	75	rosa-de-los-vientos.png	4	<p>On this day I propose that you live <b><a href=\\"#salsa\\">the experience of \\"Salsa and Coffee\\"</a> ,</b> a coffee tour through the streets of the Laureles sector, where one of its main attractions is a dance class in a professional academy, where rhythms such as: salsa, meringue and vallenato.</p><p>This tour also includes coffee pairings in different places in the sector, where accompanied by a guide they tell you the history of the fruit, the neighborhood and its importance for the city of Medellín. It is a plan with a lot of aroma of coffee and fun carried out by \\"Click Urbano\\", an unconventional tour operator, which specializes in urban tours, loaded with a lot of history, landscaping and coffee.</p><p>To access this experience you just have to contact them and ask about their availability.</p><p>However, if you want to make a calmer plan and do a coffee tasting in a good place and with spouses who know the history of the red fruit, I recommend starting the day with breakfast, tasting and pairing at <a href=\\"#rosa\\"><b>\\"Café Compass Rose?</b></a> Located in the Laureles neighborhood of Medellín. This is a very good option and by talking with Cata and Carlos you will surely spend an immersive and very interesting morning learning about the origins and processes of the drink and the most famous fruit in Colombia.</p><p>Finishing this plan, you can stay in this wonderful neighborhood and eat brunch or lunch at <b><a href=\\"#primavera\\">\\"Café Primavera\\"</a> ,</b> a place where you are immersed in a gastronomic experience with signature cuisine, which contains ingredients such as flowers and coffee <b>.</b> You will surely love the different dish options that the place has.</p><p>In the afternoon you can visit the cultural house <a href=\\"#tinto\\"><b>\\"Tinto de Verano\\"</b></a> a wonderful place where you can enjoy different art demonstrations, located on the corner of circular 5 #70-127 in the Laureles neighborhood in the west of the city, with its blue color and its plants fill the sector with light, upon entering you must let yourself permeate its magic with its different art workshops, drawing, painting, self-makeup, writing on social networks, among others. It is surely a great place to spend the afternoon, share with friends and get to know the soul of the residents of Medellín.</p><p>On the other hand, also in the afternoon, you could have another coffee experience, but this time focused on health and virtual reality and immersion in the Metaverse , where you can demystify many of the taboos that exist about this drink, all from the hand of <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#metaverso\\">Doc koffee</a> (we aredockoffe</strong> <b>e)</b>, an experience created by doctor friends who dedicated themselves to studying coffee, is something you really can?t miss. To book, it is important that you write to them on WhatsApp +57 300 4705079 and also, you can experience it at their headquarters in Laureles, so you will be in the area and you can continue enjoying this rich experience.</p><p>To end the day, I recommend having dinner at <b>\\" <a href=\\"#fidelina\\">Fidelina</a> \\"</b>  a beautiful restaurant that adorns one of the corners of the first Laureles park with its architectural tradition. This restaurant has an interior design that resembles the houses of Paisa grandmothers, in addition to serving a wide variety of dishes, cocktails and drinks. Its terrace is very special to enjoy the fresh air and the spring climate of Medellín.  </p>\t\t	\N	\N	439	rosa-de-los-vientos.png	1606,1607,1608,1609,1610	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1712,1716,1711,1713,1714,1715	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1kY7YS7KIdFnMnTd8qPg78acpIPnyuZ4&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHutjEAftXB5e	price_1Q2TKLAFILSEnUZXK3WtecJ8	1	N	N	Llegar a Medellín y sentir el aroma a café que sudan sus montañas es una de las experiencias únicas que vivirás en mi ciudad. Sumérgete en el sabor, el color y el aroma del reconocido fruto de color rojo intenso.	\N	\N	Taza de café en valle de Aburrá	prod_Qv1HUUj2n11FaU	price_1Q3BEWAFILSEnUZXcnXkzgTZ		https://buy.stripe.com/test_fZeeY33oVg8u1kA2d9		plink_1Q3BIgAFILSEnUZXE2nG2HOx	1Dia	76	N
440	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:33:02	2024-11-22 07:10:27	27764	2024-04-22 00:00:00	MED TRADITION SILLETERA 1 DAY (MEDELLIN)	Tradicion silletera 1 Day	tradicion-silletera-1-day	<strong><span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\">When a silletero passes by, it is Antioquia that passes by. A tradition that is cultural heritage.</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"color: #000000;\\">A través de esta experiencia, tendrás la oportunidad de sumergirte en un mundo plasmado de sabiduría ancestral, cultura, colores y hermosos aromas.  Nuestros silleteros nos abren sus casas y con ellas el alma de la historia familiar representada en años de tradición que se ha ido pasando de generación en generación y que hoy llena de orgullo a los Antioqueños. Conecta con nuestra historia y disfruta de tres días de hermosos jardines y flores.</span>	76	bus-de-las-flores-1024x614-2.png	4	<p>Among flowers and beautiful gardens, the Paisa idiosyncrasy is adorned, one that tells the stories of the long walks that our ancestors made from the mountains to the city carrying a chair (silleta) with countless beautiful flowers on their backs. Let?s start learning about this great history and tradition that today is the intangible heritage of the nation!</p><p>A good plan to start the day is to ride the <b>\\" <a href=\\"#bus\\">BUS DE LAS FLORES</a> \\"</b> , a tour full of magic, ideal to enjoy with the family and enjoy all the Silletera tradition of the city.</p><p>Pandora, is the tour operator that has this proposal, they give you an immersion in the Paisa tradition, visiting one of the farms <b>\\" <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#silletero\\">reserva del silletero</a> \\"</b> or \\"sendero de las flores\\"  where they have a number of cultural, recreational and gastronomic activities prepared for you, in addition, you can enjoy the visit and interaction of other places full of tradition that Pandora has contemplated in your tour.</p><p>To book it is very easy, you write to WhatsApp +57 301 7686327 and ask about the availability of the experience for that day.</p><p>Being in Santa Elena you cannot miss having a coffee at <b>? <a href=\\"#panchocha\\">Panchocha</a> ?</b> and enjoy eating this traditional \\"panchocha\\" bread that has three types of cheese, it is located on the path of El Plecer, 200 meters from the school, there you can rest and talk for a while, enjoying the landscape and the delicious climate that this district offers you. ; However, if you want to enjoy a more traditional mecateadero, I invite you to buy empanadas, buñuelos and chorizos in  <a href=\\"#el\\"><b>the \\"Pescadero\\",</b></a> a traditional fried food place owned by Luz Elena Londoño Alzate, a woman who has been a participant in the silleteros parade for years and mother of Maria Carolina Atehortúa Londoño, absolute winner of the parade in its 2023 version.</p><p>Continuing with our immersion in the Silletera culture in the town of Santa Elena, I invite you this time to the Barro Blanco path to the  <a href=\\"#familia\\"><b>Londono family estate</b></a>, who are one of the most traditional families in the region, co-founders of the silleteros parade and winners for years in various categories.</p><p>Visiting the Londoño family at their farm in Santa Elena allows you to discover the Silletero tradition immersed in modernity. In the front garden you can enjoy a craft fair organized by the community; a kiosk for food consumption and also a small natural forest called the Tesoro del Arví, in which you can find different species of Orchids, Bromeliads, Mosses and Anthuriums.</p><p>To continue our tour and if you like relaxation experiences, I recommend you visit the  <a href=\\"#hotel\\"><b>Hotel Entre Bosques  </b></a>from Arví<b>,  </b>There you can have lunch with a menu prepared and designed by the chef for international visitors. In addition, in the same hotel you can enjoy a great spa afternoon with massages, jacuzzi and ecological walks in the middle of the wonderful forest of the district of Medellín, Santa Elena. .</p><p>As an alternative option, near the Londoño farm, in the El Rosario neighborhood, is the <b>\\"</b> Don José <b>\\"</b> farm , which is called <a href=\\"#pensa\\"><b>El Pensamiento</b></a> , it is the place that perhaps has one of the most beautiful gardens in the township, in addition , has a house museum \\"El Rincón Silletero\\"  that you can visit and that contains articles that tell the history of the silleteros.</p><p>Late in the afternoon, how delicious a hot chocolate is, that is why I invite you to visit <b><a href=\\"#kakaw\\">kakaw</a> ,</b> a quite famous chocolate shop, where they not only sell the traditional cup of coffee, but they also sell vegan dishes for those who enjoy this type of gastronomy.</p><p>It is a beautiful place, which has outdoor seating, where the attention of its staff is warm and special; It is undoubtedly a very good space to spend the afternoon and share delicious cuisine talking with the locals.</p><p>After the chocolate, I recommend you visit <b>\\" <a href=\\"#artesano\\">Artesano</a> \\"</b>  a place where you can enjoy different workshops such as making candles, natural soaps, among others; It is important that when you get there you ask about the plan they have for that day; Additionally, there you can eat delicious artisan dishes, such as hamburgers, medallions or delicious desserts. On weekends, in the evening they also offer live music, making it a great plan to end the day in the town. You can?t miss it.</p><p>Enjoy and live Medellín and its tradition!</p>\t\t	\N	\N	440	bus-de-las-flores-1024x614-2.png	1633,1635,1675,1631,1636	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1571,1723,1721,1579,1722,1570,1574,1580,1720	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1Y43sczZUNs33kPGm_EG4-vJrrERlxA8&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuDinQsYXuP0	price_1Q2TKLAFILSEnUZXTR1D9h8u	1	N	N	When a silletero passes by, it is Antioquia that passes by. A tradition that is cultural heritage.	\N	\N	Tradicion silletera 1 Day	prod_Qv1HdYv5gyHqUb	price_1Q3BEXAFILSEnUZXIIWho3Eh		https://buy.stripe.com/test_bIYg27cZvf4q2oE196		plink_1Q3BIgAFILSEnUZX1Bi1lfcX	1Dia	77	N
441	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:33:06	2024-11-22 07:10:28	17542	2023-12-09 00:00:00	MED02 Queer Getaway	Movida Queer & Diversa 3 Dias	movida-queer--diversa-3-dias	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Descubre la vibrante escena LGBTQ+ de Medellín</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nExplora las zonas seguras y exclusivas de la Ciudad de la Eterna Primavera con nuestra propuesta Queer. Disfruta de rumba, cafés y hoteles LGBTIQ+ friendly. Medellín, cuna de la amabilidad, te espera con alegría. ¡Vive una experiencia inclusiva única!	77	hombre-vestido-cosmeticos-maquillaje-primer-plano-esmalte-2.jpg	4	<p>Welcome!! For your first day in the city, I propose a calmer plan to acclimatize. You can stop by for a good local coffee to recharge your batteries. I recommend <b><a href=\\"#pergamino\\">Parchment</a> , </b>where they connect the countryside with the city, through coffee produced by allied producers from all over the country. They have several locations in El Poblado, my favorite is the one on Vía Primavera, there is also a very nice one in Laureles. Of the coffee methods they brew, my favorite is the French press, but you can also find V60 Chemex, Aeropress, Moka, and Kyoto.</p><p>If you like shopping and supporting local brands from people in the community, you can take advantage of the morning and go to the <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#dolca\\">Dolca</a> </b>store<b>,</b> There are clothes for tasty people <b>,</b> there they dress you in SAFETY and they put all the TASTE into the clothes ?? They are located in Medellín in the charming Laureles neighborhood.</p><p>Stop by before leaving the place and have something delicious at <a href=\\"#chiringuito\\"><b>CHIRINguito</b></a> tastiest in Medallo, located in the same Rosada house in Dolca. Ah! And if you like karaoke here you will find the most chimba in the city. ????????????<br /><br />For lunch I recommend you stay exploring the Laureles area, they have a varied gastronomic offer, from typical, signature cuisine and international cuisine. If you have an appetite <a href=\\"#voraz\\"><b>Voracious </b></a>This is the place, suitable for carnivores. Laureles is so varied that here I leave you a must-see <a href=\\"#ina\\"><b>Ina Restaurant</b></a> Food that heals, inspires and transforms?They create and share magic in thousands of details in this place. Winners of the city?s revelation chef award. <br /><br />In the afternoon, you can continue enjoying Laureles, and this quiet neighborhood has such a varied offering that you can even find theaters, reserve a place in the play of your choice at <a href=\\"#teatrico\\"><b>El Teatrico</b></a> of Medellín, where art and entertainment are experienced as an intimate and uncomplicated experience. They are happy, curious and sensitive to all artistic expression and creation. They like people who laugh, who vibrate, who allow themselves to be surprised and surrender their emotions to the power of a gesture, a word, a sound, a song. People who know how to unplug their daily stress to live in spirit ?mode?.? I recommend the local coffee, it?s called el maromero.</p><p>And if you want to party at night, I recommend going to <a href=\\"#happy\\"><b>Happy House</b></a> , the happiest house in Medellín. On Fridays and Saturdays the hours are from 6pm to 4am, and the other days they also have service, but different hours so you keep in mind. If you are going to celebrate something special, it is best to contact them and book in advance, the place is very popular, mostly by local lbtq+ women, and the atmosphere is very cool. Thinking of everyone, I recommend visiting <b><a href=\\"#purple\\">Purple Gay Club </a></b>right there in Laureles<b>,</b> the place has an urban electro atmosphere and Lupe, a crossover restaurant that will surely make you sing your lungs out. Open Fridays and Saturdays.</p>                	<p>For today I recommend that we start the day in the center of Medellín. The tour through the center of Medellín surprises with the historical architecture of its constructions, making the buildings become the main character of the walk. Places like the  <a href=\\"#luces\\"><b>Park of Lights</b></a> , Berrío Park, Botero Park and the <a href=\\"#antioquia\\"><b>Museum of Antioquia</b></a>  (a museum characterized by the collection of drawings, paintings and sculptures of local master Fernando Botero) are emblematic sites of Antioquians that promote art and culture. During the tour, it is possible to purchase objects and  crafts of singular beauty to take as souvenirs, you could stop by the <a href=\\"#junin\\"><b>Junín</b></a> pedestrian street and there find a varied offer.  </p><p>To finish the tour, the LGBT community has access to the different records of the city?s historical memory, which are found in the <a href=\\"#memoria\\"><b>Casa de la Memoria Museum</b></a>. Created in 2006 in order to carry out an exercise in critical and comprehensive dialogue of the reality that was experienced in Medellín, it is a symbolic setting that calls for hope, inclusion, diversity and that is worth visiting.<br /><br />Taking advantage of the fact that you are in the center of Medellín, my favorite places to have lunch are <b><a href=\\"#hacienda\\">La Hacienda</a> ,</b> they rescue our origin, make it delicious and serve it at your table. <b><a href=\\"#astor\\">The Astor</a> :</b>  For dessert you can stop by and buy a morito del astor, they are shaped like a chick, a frog and a pig. You will love them!  <br /><br />We recommend that at night so as not to leave the center, visit <a href=\\"#barbacoas\\"><b>Barbacoas</b></a> , it is a fragmented street, the street above is Calle del Calzoncillo, known as the place of diverse rumba in Medellín, Here you can have a few drinks at <b><a href=\\"#kanahan\\">Kanahan Bar Since 2004</a> .</b>  The street below, or as it is known locally, the street of sin, below Bolívar Park, is a wilder area. A small corner, but full of party and diversity. Barbacoas is a small revolution for the more traditional Medellín, it occupies an intimate urban space, but beats strongly like the Queer heart of the city. Those who live in this block take care of it like a house is taken care of: it is swept, cleaned, painted, patched, strangers are avoided at the door, but visitors are welcomed. Currently, public space has been recovered for social appropriation, diversity and active and sustainable mobility.  </p><p>Tonight for dinner, you can come from the center to El Poblado or Laureles and enter <a href=\\"#rio\\"><b>Parques del Río</b></a> , there you can eat at <b><a href=\\"#lucho\\">Aqui paró Lucho</a> .</b> A restaurant with typical but gourmet food, which was born in one of the city?s market squares. This venue is on the way back to your hotel.  </p>                	<p>For those who want a more nature, romantic or luxury plan, the adventure through Medellín continues with a panoramic helicopter flight , the company <a href=\\"#fly\\"><b>Fly Colombia</b></a>, offers destinations for an exciting experience that changes the perspective of the city and its surroundings and also includes a themed celebration, accompanied by a glass of wine and an exquisite cheese board. In the \\"City of Flowers\\", do not forget to contact the specialized Agency<a href=\\"#woot\\"><b>  Woot Women Travel</b></a>, with local hosts part of the lgbtiq+ population. who are responsible for organizing queer tours, weddings, celebrations, anniversaries and romantic evenings for LGBTQ+ couples, in places of unexpected natural beauty and romantic atmosphere that promise fantastic events that will be remembered for a lifetime.</p><p>If you chose to tour Medellín by helicopter you can include El <a href=\\"#marmoleo\\"><b>Restaurante Marmoleo</b></a>  It is a gastronomic icon of the city, and arriving there in a powerful helicopter is the best way to serve your guests or celebrate that special moment, an exclusive plan that the city of Medellín offers you; an experience of the highest level and in the best style. You can also travel by land by private transportation from Medellín to Guatapé, for a full day full of activities such as climbing the Peñol stone, getting to know and exploring its colorful town and its architecture with skirting boards on the facades of the houses, going to the squares and parks to go down to the boardwalk where they have a wide range of water sports for rent, such as Jetskis, private boats, party boards, luxury catamarans, hotels and glamping-type Airbnbs on the islands of the Guatape dam, or if you prefer to do all this faster and from the heights, you can hire a helicopter flight to fly over the town, the stone and the dam, lasting from 6 minutes onwards, and there is a really economical option that is a shared flight, you can contact  <a href=\\"#helitours\\"><b>Helitours</b></a> and they will give you instructions for the flight.<br /><br />If heights are not your thing, but you still went on a tour to Guatapé, I recommend having lunch at the <a href=\\"#ancla\\"><b>Ancla Mare and Terra</b></a> restaurant, They are a restaurant Over The Water, The gastronomy of the sea and the land come together and inspire them. Located on the boardwalk of the Guatapé dam.</p><p><br /><br />At night after returning to Medellín and having rested in your hotel from your daytime tour, you cannot miss the <a href=\\"#chiquita\\"><b>Chiquita bar</b></a>, fun, kitsch and diverse; located on Vía Primavera, on Saturdays at 10pm they have a Drag show: Vibrate to the rhythm of good music, discover the extravagant, exotic and colorful worlds. Enjoy an unprecedented show, stand up comedy, karaoke, concerts and much more talent.  </p><p>On Sundays and holidays it vibrates with the Sungays, you can?t leave without knowing them <b>.</b>  A space to live a crazy experience, the perfect terrace to share with friends during the afternoon, have a drink and start a night full of color and fun. Here I leave you an extra patch, the friends bar,  <a href=\\"#aquellos\\"><b>Where those</b></a> located in Parque Lleras, on Mondays they have 3×2 mojitos, Wednesdays 3×2 in the entire cocktail bar, Thursdays 3×2 margaritas, you should check their networks, because certain hours apply.</p><p>If you still have energy to finish the party, you have to go to <b><a href=\\"#oraculo\\">Club Oracle</a> ,</b> it is a disco and nightclub, ??????They have the coolest DIVERSA rumba in Medellín, it has 3 environments to live the fantasy POPerreo/Electrónica/Crossover</p><p>In Medellín it is also possible to organize private cooking experiences that revolve around classes with <a href=\\"#chef\\"><b>LGBTIQ+ chefs</b></a> in which good conversation and knowledge of the local culture are guaranteed, ideal for a dinner with friends and local guests to socialize. </p>\t\t	441	hombre-vestido-cosmeticos-maquillaje-primer-plano-esmalte-2.jpg	1400,1401,1402,1403,1404,1405,1406,1407	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1735,1740,1752,1744,1732,1747,1743,1737,1730,1736,1741,1748,1746,1751,1726,1734,1733,1742,1749,1727,1739,1728,1738,1731,1729,1750,1745	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1RorPdkX5TzXjjdlJ--Nxcqka9UPoUx4&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuPW5jRfi74K	price_1Q2TKMAFILSEnUZXj3sEhPtz	1	N	N	Descubre la vibrante escena LGBTQ+ de Medellín	\N	\N	Movida Queer & Diversa 3 Dí­as	prod_QuotZIP79zDXVA	price_1Q2zG2AFILSEnUZXLv7iBHAn		https://buy.stripe.com/test_5kAdTZaRn3lI1kAbMf		plink_1Q3AoOAFILSEnUZXXX9U0QkB	3Dias	78	N
442	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:33:10	2024-11-22 07:10:28	17557	2023-12-07 00:00:00	MED03 Pet friendly	Experiencia pet friendly 3 Dias	experiencia-pet-friendly-3-dias	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Recorre las zonas más exclusivas y Pet Friendly de Medellín</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Ven a descubrir los destinos y lugares Pet Friendly preferidos por los antioqueños. No los dejes en casa tristes y aburridos, aquí en Medellín estamos locos por los peluditos y todos son bienvenidos en muchos lugares.</span>	78	pexels-samson-katt-5256146.jpg	4	<p>Welcome!! Yes with your pet   In the Metro Transportation System you want to travel, you must carry it in a guacal and you must present the current vaccination card.</p><p>Hours: Monday to Friday, 9:00 am to 3:00 pm Saturdays, Sundays and holidays, from 9:00 am to 12:00 pm.  </p><p>Our must-haves to share with our pets during the trip through Medellín if they are in El Sur, I recommend in the morning for breakfast, immersing yourself in the vibrant culinary experience of <a href=\\"#betty\\"><b>Betty?s Bowls</b></a>  Poblado, where they await you with delicious bowls full of freshness and irresistible flavors in a pet-friendly, energetic and lively environment. To be late you can go to  <b><a href=\\"#santa\\">Santa Leña</a> :</b> Coffee and artisanal bakery in Laureles, their breads are made with sourdough, conscious raw materials and a lot of love, and in the afternoons if you are in Envigado, you can stop by <b><a href=\\"#alfamore\\">Alfamore</a> ,</b> a flavor boutique, here I recommend the desserts in verrine.</p><p> </p><p>If what you want is to go for a walk and be in contact with nature, I recommend visiting <a href=\\"#piedras\\"><b>Piedras Blancas Park</b></a> , located in Medellín, more specifically in the district of Santa Elena, is a natural treasure that offers a unique experience for nature lovers and their pets. Known for its scenic beauty and abundant biodiversity, this park is the perfect destination for those looking to escape the bustle of the city and immerse themselves in a tranquil, natural environment.<br /><br />To spend an afternoon with your furry friends, what better than a pet-friendly park, and in Medellín and surrounding areas we have many of these, so as not to leave the town in the southern part of the city, you can go to UVA <b><a href=\\"#uva\\">el Tesoro</a> ,</b>  This public park located under the El Tesoro shopping center is the perfect place to walk with your dog, take a quiet walk, sit and read or play a sport. It has shops, lounges, a public library, a multipurpose court and others.</p><p><br />For dinner in El Poblado I recommend <a href=\\"#matriarca\\"><b>La Matriarch</b></a> , Colombian identity cuisine. For dinner you can try the matriarch?s chicharronería, the bacon in a box my favorite, and pets are welcome here.</p>                	<p>Today I propose a mixed plan, in the morning if you need a quiet space to work that allows you to bring your pet, you can go to <a href=\\"#cafe\\"><b>the cafe somewhere else</b></a> ,  With all its green and fresh silence, it was once the small house of Fernando Gonzales, writer and philosopher from Envigado, a place where he kept his books, his homeopathic bottles, his words, his conversations with friends. Now there are many visitors who come to enjoy this ideal space for reading, enjoying alone or in the company of other locals, teleworking and having a good coffee. Surrounded by underground waters, and fountains that sing in the sun, by trees and by literary presences.</p><p>If you want to leave the town, you can go through Oriente Antioquia to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#indiana\\"><b>Mall Indiana</b></a> to go to a unique restaurant or visit its Poblado headquarters to meet Aunt Grazia ?? , who reminds us of the joy of going to <a href=\\"#maga\\"><b>La Maga</b></a>  It also lives on four legs. They are pet friendly! Enjoy a MAGICAL Brunch  ???? The secret is to love the meetings? the company and good food? you can go to brunch, afternoon, breakfast or do coworking with your furry friend ??</p><p>In the afternoon, you can go have a beer accompanied by your pet at <b><a href=\\"#barrio\\">Barrio Sur Bar</a> ,</b> go and enjoy its indoor/outdoor garden, with a relaxed atmosphere, in the Buena Mesa sector, Envigado.<br /><br />If at night you want to go out partying and leave your furry friends resting in a safe and fun place for them, I recommend <b><a href=\\"#canis\\">La Mansión Canis</a> ,</b>  in Sabaneta. And you take advantage of the fact that you are in the area and go down to the park to see what is on offer and see the quality of life in this beautiful municipality, the smallest in Colombia, which is very close to Medellín. The three places that cannot be missed there in Sabaneta for the evening are,  <b>? <a href=\\"#romera\\">The Romera</a> ?  </b>ideal for walks in a nature reserve, the level is medium so you require prior preparation and bring plenty of water and food for you and your furry friends, along the way there are no shops or anything where you can buy something, and try to walk in large groups through the reserves of Medellín and request accompaniment from a professional tourism guide expert in hiking <b>? <a href=\\"#barquerena\\">The House of Culture: La Barquereña</a> ?</b> is the center par excellence of art and culture in Sabaneta, it is a true architectural jewel built  and are living culture <b>? <a href=\\"#sabaneta\\">El Parque de Sabaneta</a> ?,</b> <b> </b>where visitors can enjoy a morning, afternoon or evening accompanied by a good coffee, excellent service and the harmony offered by the trees and flowers that accompany the place.</p><p>What to eat in Sabaneta? If you took your furry friend to the nursery at the Canis mansion in Sabaneta, you can go up a few more meters and you will reach it.<a href=\\"#octava\\"><b>  eighth wonder viewpoint</b></a>, a place that has an incredible view of Medellín and have a guarito (paisa liquor) to start the night and order the local snack (grilled meats, arepas, potatoes), highly recommended. Or if you are in the main park of Sabaneta, be sure to try the chorimorcilla and the largest buñuelo in the world, in the middle of the park you will find the offer of this local cuisine.</p>                	<p>Today I have several options for plans in nature, so you can choose. Currently there are various places where your furry friend will have the opportunity to interact with other animals, enjoy games, run, stay active and, above all, have a different time. But first, if you need somewhere to have breakfast, another of my recommendations in Medellín is  <b><a href=\\"#selva\\">Azul Selva</a> :</b> Ideal for Brunch & Coffee, on Vía Primavera.</p><p>On the outskirts of Medellín is the <a href=\\"#salado\\"><b>El Salado Ecotourism Park</b></a>, an ideal green area to walk and enjoy with your pet. This ecotourism park offers a unique experience where your faithful companion can explore and have fun. With refreshing lakes and waterfalls, diverse flora and a tranquil atmosphere. If you have time, I recommend visiting the beloved Envigadeña Marta and her tourist farm.  <a href=\\"#mandalaire\\"><b>Mandalaire</b></a>, a few meters from El Salado Park. There you can enjoy nature, delicious garden-to-table dishes for breakfast or lunch, workshops and memorable experiences. Go and disconnect in that charming and cozy space. Don?t forget to make a reservation in advance!</p><p>The variety of places to walk pets continues to grow, and this place is an example of that. <b><a href=\\"#ciudad\\">Ciudad del Río park</a> ,</b> located near the Museum of Modern Art  in Medellín, it is a family space where pets can enjoy walks, games and socialize with other pets. In addition, it has training circuits specially designed for your fun and exercise. If you are here, do not hesitate to cross the avenue and go to Lunch at  <b><a href=\\"#mercado\\">River markets</a> .</b></p><p><a href=\\"#escobero\\"><b>PAE El Escobero Adventure Park</b></a>, in Envigado, adventure park and extreme moments to share with friends and family, obviously your pets are welcome, they are also part of the family! There you can do dog walks on the last Sunday of the month, hiking, polygon, motocross, ATVs, 4×4, picnic, there is restaurant service and it is close to Medellín, but you should preferably go in a truck with 4×4 traction through the terrain of the place. There is nothing to eat here, but at the entrance it is  <b><a href=\\"#tiki\\">Tiki Bar</a> ,</b> ideal to enjoy a good trout in different preparations and other dishes. <br /><br />For dinner you can go to <b><a href=\\"#gracia\\">La Gracia in the park</a> ,</b> taking advantage of the fact that to leave the PAE you have to go through Envigado, my favorite here is the thanks burger, to share you can order a funny Guacamole, loaded with pieces of chicharrón, pieces of ripe banana and nachos.</p><p>And what are you waiting for to come with your pets to discover Medellín Pet Friendly in nature?</p>\t\t	442	pexels-samson-katt-5256146-e1708333856238.jpg	1414,1413,1412,1411,1410,1409,1408	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1755,1753,1759,1767,1769,1774,1754,1768,1765,1760,1770,1772,1756,1775,1771,1766,1762,1763,1761,1758,1764,1773,1757	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1XDonxLV7mqVJRmiwAvxB1PrZkE-FHVk&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuu4shitwwRV	price_1Q2TKMAFILSEnUZX1Y9g2rtX	1	N	N	Recorre las zonas más exclusivas y Pet Friendly de Medellín	\N	\N	Experiencia pet friendly 3 Dí­as	prod_Quotle88v8MYtz	price_1Q2zG3AFILSEnUZXzjBCOmIC		https://buy.stripe.com/test_eVa7vBcZv8G29R6dUo		plink_1Q3AoPAFILSEnUZXAe5Sy6fR	3Dias	79	N
443	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:33:14	2024-11-22 07:10:28	17562	2023-12-06 00:00:00	MED04 Viewpoints	Top 10 miradores y parches 3 Dias	top-10-miradores-y-parches-3-dias	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Recorre los miradores más top de Medellín y descubre lugares para disfrutar desde las alturas</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Recorran el top 10 de miradores y parches en Medellín y disfruten de unas vistas que podrán dejarlos sin aliento!</span><span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">! Disfrute también de las recomendaciones gastronómicas de nuestros anfitriones locales!</span>	79	miradores-2.png	4	<p>When they talk to you about Medellín, you think of eternal spring, flowers, friendly people, innovation, transformation and endless adventures.  From the viewpoints you can admire different landscapes such as urban, industrial, rural environments, natural or geographical landscapes, etc., and also for bird watching, some have a wide range of gastrobars and other activities of interest?come on, let?s get started!</p><p>To begin, I recommend that when you are getting off or on the José María Córdova International Airport, located in Rionegro, that you tell your driver to take you through the Palmas variant and before taking you to the hotel, he will pass you through the <b><a href=\\"#laspalmas\\">Mirador las Palmas</a> .</b>  Here are two of the most popular public viewing points in the city. Its strategic location allows you to contemplate the entire extension of the Aburra Valley and have beautiful panoramic views, especially in the evening, with a frontal sunset, or at dusk, when it mixes with the lights and forms a luminous carpet that unfolds to the green mountains, some say that Medellín looks like a Christmas manger, full of twinkling lights.  <br /><br />I recommend having paisa style breakfast at <b><a href=\\"#rosa\\">Asados ??Doña Rosa</a></b> or <b><a href=\\"#sancho\\">Sancho Paisa</a></b>, located on the MDE Airport road that comes to the city. Both ideal for trying local cuisine. I recommend chicharrón, chorizos and blood sausages.</p><p>If you prefer a more intimate, diverse and inclusive space and taking advantage of the fact that you are in the Las Palmas sector, be sure to go to <b><a href=\\"#os\\">Os mirador</a> .</b> There you don?t need reservations, you just arrive and park at the place. It is located before the Oriente tunnel, towards Medellín ? Rionegro, and the entry of minors is prohibited.  </p><p>And if your schedule only allows you the morning free, I recommend that you put on a comfortable outfit and tennis shoes and go through the <a href=\\"#nutibara\\"><b>Cerro Nutibara Ecological Park</b></a>. There you can walk several of the ecological trails of this natural park, you can also observe +95 different species of migratory birds, enjoy several modern art sculptures that are on the slopes of the hill to end up in one of the greatest tourist attractions in Medellín, he  <b><a href=\\"#pueblito\\">Paisa town</a> .</b>  Keep in mind that this hill has two entrances, one on Av. 33 and the second on 30th Street. You can go by Metro to the industrial station and walk 10 minutes to its base, or get off at the Nutibara station of the Metroplús system. Even an Uber can take you, if you don?t want or can?t walk to the top, tell it to take you to the top so you can walk around it yourself and go down. In the place you find restaurants, my favorite is called  <a href=\\"#tradicion\\"><b>Paisa tradition</b></a> of typical food, museum, viewpoint, souvenir shops, ecological trails, a Bancolombia at hand and they exchange dollars there.</p>                	<p>For today I propose to mix two plans, one in the morning in which you can travel to the place in private transportation <b>,</b> offered by some tourism companies, such as <b><a href=\\"#vans\\">White Vans</a> ,</b>  It is located 1 hour from Medellín in San Félix, ideal for a more extreme walk through the clouds, here you can practice paragliding.<b>,  </b>I recommend contacting  <a href=\\"#xplore\\"><b>Xplore colombia Tours</b></a>  They have the best pilots certified to fly, is another option that you could consider including in your itinerary, since the sunsets from the<a href=\\"#felix\\"><b>  San Felix viewpoint</b></a> They are truly unique, on site there are gastronomic services in restaurants, camping, bakeries with very local products; such as the famous chocha bread with hot chocolate with cheese and rest areas.<br /><br />Personally, since I don?t like such popular places, I can recommend <a href=\\"#waira\\"><b>Waira restaurant bar picnic</b></a>, km 5 via Medellín San Félix. You can appreciate the view of the city, bring your pet, enjoy the bonfire and there are cabins. If you like animal protein, be sure to try the barrel pork rinds, it is a local classic.  <br /><br />After returning to Medellín. At night, the plan can be complemented with a visit to <a href=\\"#sabaneta\\"><strong>Sabaneta</strong></a> , this little corner of the Aburra Valley is currently an attractive place for visitors from the region, the country and abroad, due to the different places they have to visit. Today I want to highlight two of its viewpoints,  <b><a href=\\"#octava\\">The eighth wonder</a> ,  </b>¡Live the experience and don?t let them tell it to you <b>!</b> They open every day and <b><a href=\\"#oskar\\">Oskar?s viewpoint</a></b> ,  It is an ideal place to share with the family and enjoy exquisite dishes for dinner. They have a country headquarters (viewpoint) in the Las Lomitas sector and a Sabaneta Park headquarters (restaurant in the town).  </p>                	<p>For this last day, I recommend that you give yourself the opportunity to get to know other sectors of Medellín, other than the south of the city. As most of the viewpoints open from noon onwards, so you can take advantage of the morning and the location in  Belen , you can go shopping or have breakfast at the <a href=\\"#molinos\\"><b>Los Molino shopping center</b></a> <strong>,</strong> they have a varied offering, my recommended one there for breakfast is <b><a href=\\"#migueria\\">La Migueria</a> ,</b> every morning they turn on their ovens to delight us with every bite.<br /><br />If you want to go after 2pm to a viewpoint that has a broader offer to hang out, be sure to go to <b><a href=\\"#cielo\\">the Cielo viewpoint</a></b> , located in the commune of Belén. They have paintball, attractions, food and a mini farm. They have several instagrammable spots there! It has a spectacular view of the city.</p><p><br />or if you prefer another area different from the popular and touristy neighborhoods in the south of the city, you can go and visit <a href=\\"#hangar\\"><b>Hangar M45</b></a>, the eccentric themed restaurant that offers helicopter trips for dinner, is the place where a small plane landed on its terrace in December 2020 in the heart of the Manrique neighborhood of Medellín. You can enter the interior of the plane, enjoy a panoramic view of commune 3, feel the breeze and learn a little about the history, these are part of what you can experience here.  </p><p>A landing strip on the roof, chairs, a propeller converted into a fan, on the right wing its windows with a privileged view of Medallo. They are part of this experience of eating in the heights. There are no chefs here but pilots; that take you on a journey through all the senses, you can enjoy desserts, cakes, a coffee brought from Jericho, a varied menu with signature food and don?t forget to try their cocktails, with sensory experiences.  <br /><br />Some Tour Operator Agencies such as <b><a href=\\"#woot\\">Woot Women Travel</a></b> ,  They offer the experience of flying and getting to know the city from Manrique. The place has gone viral on TikTok for its particular industrial setting, which simulates a real hangar. And walking around the city for 20 minutes by helicopter costs no more than $300 Cop per person. This apart from consumption on site.</p>\t\t	443	miradores.png	1399,1417,1397,1396,1415,1398,1676	14.9	15.65	70069.40	S	en	1780,1793,1776,1790,1789,1781,1782,1777,1766,1785,1778,1788,1791,1792,1779,1786,1783,1745,1784	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1tBLzmKgsgnM4biNUPFsHn_ERroJdnkg&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuwiRZ61A7vK	price_1Q2TKNAFILSEnUZXflB8waKH	1	N	N	Recorre los miradores más top de Medellín y descubre lugares para disfrutar desde las alturas	\N	\N	Top 10 miradores y parches 3 Dí­as	prod_QuotZ4AyASeasp	price_1Q2zG3AFILSEnUZXI6z2wUPc		https://buy.stripe.com/test_14k8zF7FbaOa9R68A5		plink_1Q3AoQAFILSEnUZX0FCPxo9s	3Dias	80	N
444	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:33:17	2024-12-01 16:42:52	27778	2024-04-12 00:00:00	MED A MUSICAL MELODRAMA 1 DAY (MEDELLIN)	A musical melodrama 1 day	a-musical-melodrama-1-day	<p><br></p>	80	Edificio-de-San-Ignacio-Universidad-de-Antioquia-1024x574-1.png	4	<p>Medellín is porro, cumbia, tango, bagpipes and music of yesteryear.</p><p>Porro is a Colombian musical genre, born in the Atlantic region, but which for years has marked the musical history of Medellín. The famous porro vias, for example, were free performances that took place in the neighborhoods of the different communes of Medellín, where locals danced to the rhythm of songs such as Tolú by Lucho Bermúdez, Cumbia del Caribe by Edmundo Arias and many more.</p><p>To learn about these musical rhythms, especially their history and the impact they had on the social and nightlife of Medellín, I invite you to go to the Robledo neighborhood in the north of the city to the <b><a href=\\"#jordan\\">El Jordan Musical Documentation Center</a> ,</b> This is a house with more than 130 years of musical history, all kinds of events are held here and today it is part of the city?s public library network, where you can undoubtedly have an immersion in the musical history of Medellín. You can?t leave without visiting this magical place.</p><p>When you leave there, I invite you to visit the center of the city, a place full of history, including the musical history of Medellín, much of which remains alive to this day in every heartbeat, in every breath of this land surrounded by mountains. In each of the places we will visit today, various artists have performed, important musical performances have been performed, and there have been countless events that you will want to know about.</p><p>The first stop is the <a href=\\"#san\\"><b>San Ignacio Building and the Paraninfo of the University of Antioquia</b></a>, two adjacent buildings declared a national monument since 1982, two buildings that are located a few blocks from the Málaga Hall, there you can admire the theaters where countless concerts have been held, presentations by the most significant artists in the country. They are magical places, where you can enjoy historical tours that you can consult on the website that I indicate at the point of interest. As a recommendation there is a corporation called <b><a href=\\"#district\\">San Ignacio District</a> ,</b> which has experiences very focused on historical knowledge, with them you can also schedule the tour.</p><p>Then you can visit the traditional <b><a href=\\"#colon\\">Bar Colón</a> ,</b> There you can have lunch and listen to traditional Colombian music, it is a place with a lot of history that has been in the city for more than 20 years. Its cuisine is varied, and you can also have a good drink while listening to traditional rhythms such as porro, cumbia, old music, and much more.</p><p>You will find this place on the entire Ayacucho street, in the center of the city, just a few blocks from the San Ignacio building.</p><p>Being in the center, I invite you to take a tour of the <a href=\\"#homero\\"><b>Homero Manzi</b></a> house , a place that, although its main rhythm is tango, is loaded with musical history, live shows, dance and flavor. It is located in Calle 48 #41-3, La Candelaria, on one of the most famous corners in the city center. Here tribute is paid to the Argentine poet and composer Homero Manzi, which is why the space is loaded with photographs, posters and countless objects that take us to the most iconic years of tango in Medellín, without a doubt, you will like it and in a good place to spend the afternoon.</p><p>At the end and to experience these rhythms that are so representative of Antioquia folklore in a more intense way, I invite you to walk towards the <a href=\\"#malaga\\"><b>Salón Málaga</b></a> located a couple of blocks from Bar Colón. This is a place that is considered the sanctuary of traditional music. The Salón Málaga is absolutely essential in the city of Medellín, it includes exhibitions, a restaurant, dancing and its photographs, from more than 50 years of tradition, commemorate the musical history of my hometown. A place that opens from Monday to Saturday from 8 in the morning, and that has on its walls so many stories of the music of yesteryear, that of the 50s back in the 20th century. It is without a doubt the first place to visit on this third day of discovery of musical Medellín. Tango, Porro, Música Vieja, Cumbias, are some of the rhythms that you can enjoy in this wonderful place, don?t forget to try their empanadas!</p><p>After leaving there, and if you want to continue dancing, it is worth changing areas and taking a taxi to take you to San Juan Avenue before the famous Carrera 70 to visit <b><a href=\\"#palko\\">Palko Discoteca</a> ,</b> a place where you can take a joint class, have a few drinks, eat and dance until dawn. It is an excellent place to finish the night to the rhythm of the most local musical sounds of Medellín.</p>	\N	\N	444	Edificio-de-San-Ignacio-Universidad-de-Antioquia-1024x574-1.png	1612,1614,1449,1613,1611,1615	6.9	15.65	70069.40	S	ES	1799,1798,1795,1800,1801,1796,1797	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=15fE4DafgaENkaf8oQkn_2ZzFxfLo9e4&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	prod_QuHuN4Bs0BFpTD	price_1Q2TKNAFILSEnUZXrthyBs1X	1	N	N	Medellín dances to the sound of different tropical and Latin American rhythms that you will love to know, feel, dance and live. I invite you to move your body to the beat of our musical history. I invite you to get to know the historical musical melodrama of my city, Medellín.	\N	\N	A musical melodrama 1 Day	prod_Quotfxr253TLTU	price_1Q2zG4AFILSEnUZXzQ29qvtR	\N	https://buy.stripe.com/test_00g3flbVraOa8N24jQ	\N	plink_1Q3AoQAFILSEnUZXwv5E4PE5	1Dia	81	N
445	S	anonimo	2024-09-23 17:33:21	2024-11-22 07:10:28	17597	2024-02-04 00:00:00	MED10 Music	Bohemia, salsa y tango 3 Dias	bohemia-salsa-y-tango-3-dias	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">¡Vibra con los diferentes ritmos musicales Medellín y atrévete a bailar en los sitios más representativos!</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Déjate seducir por la salsa, el tango, los boleros, la cumbia y el porro, fusionando la tradición paisa con la pasión latina. Embárcate en un viaje sonoro con icónicos artistas como Fruko y sus Tesos, Grupo Galé, Edmundo Arias y más. Desde locales de moda hasta acogedores restaurantes, la ciudad te invita a explorar su rica herencia musical a través del baile y la melodía.</span>	81	musica-02.jpg	4	<p><strong>Medellín is tango!</strong> To talk about the history of tango is to go back to the 19th century, where different African-American and Creole rhythms, among others, merged in Europe, many of which allowed the birth of this rhythm so recognized worldwide.</p><p>It is said that the first songs of this musical genre were heard in Medellín in 1911 by Alfredo Diestro, and with him different movements, collectors and lovers of this genre began to be born. My grandfather, for example, loved to listen to the songs of Carlos Gardel, Óscar Agudelo, Alberto Rossi, among other artists, on his record player in the living room of his house with a cigar and a good drink; Like him, many inhabitants of Medellín let themselves be delighted by the musical notes of this artistic manifestation, which led them to find themselves in bars, discos and places where only this genre is danced and where they themselves honor the musical rhythm with dresses of sequins and shoes appropriate for dancing.</p><p>This is why our first stop is in Manrique , on 45th Street, at the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#gardeliana\\"><b>Casa Gardeliana.</b></a>. A magical place, a house museum that is responsible for exhibiting the main objects of Carlos Gardel, an Argentine artist well known in Colombia and the world; thanks to the love that Carlos Gardel loved Medellín and thanks to the history he has with the city, the Gardeliana House was declared Cultural Heritage of Medellín.</p><p>There you will not only learn the history, but you will have a drink and enjoy activities that are on the agenda for the day you chose to visit.</p><p>To get there it is very easy, take the metro to the university station, there you get off and take bus route 022 or 023 and either of the two will leave you at the door of the house museum.</p><p>Near the Gardeliana House is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sazon\\"><b>Sazón al Carbón</b></a>, a place where you can have delicious barbecue lunches in the heart of this neighborhood, what I like most is their mixed grill, combined with the delicious chimichurri that they prepare; In addition, you can have a delicious cocktail from the menu, to cool off in the heat of Medellín. This restaurant is located on Carrera 44 # 78 ? 70, you can walk there.</p><p>Next stop, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#cafealaska\\"><b>Café Alaska</b></a>, a bohemian and tango corner that opened in 1937, two years after the plane crash in Medellín in which Carlos Gardel died. This is a place located on the second floor, on a corner just a few blocks from the Casa Gardeliana. Gustavo Rojas, its owner, is perhaps one of the people who knows the most about tango in Medellín, and he also has a collection of more than 200 thousand records that you will want to listen to. For lovers of this musical genre, this is a must-see stop, because whatever song comes to mind, Oscar is sure to have it in his collection.</p><p>Among the friendly, cordial and historical atmosphere, you will be able to talk with locals, learn family stories about tango and the transformation of the Manrique neighborhood, a place that was hit by the drug war in Colombia. Definitely, to chat and learn the Café Alaska is the best choice.</p><p>Being in the Manrique neighborhood, in commune 3 of Medellín, you will not be able to miss the cultural and community tourism proposal that the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#balcon\\"><b>Balcón de los Artistas</b></a> has.; This is perhaps one of the most representative social projects in the city, which frames and commemorates music, with incredible dances and touches that will make you enjoy Medellín Musical. As a corporation they have a wide agenda, there you can access dance classes, various shows and much more; You can consult all this on their website (<a href=\\"https://www.elbalcon.org/index.php/linea-comercial/\\">https://www.elbalcon.org/index.php/linea-comercial/</a> ) and book according to the day you decide to attend.</p><p>Finally, when night comes, if you want to enjoy the wonderful view that the Manrique neighborhood offers, I invite you to have dinner and have a couple of drinks at <a href=\\"#zelebre\\"><b>Zelebre Azotea</b></a>, located on Carrera 45 # 69 ? 41, right in the sector where we have lived this entire adventure of musical experience. Here the menu is varied, you can eat a delicious hamburger, or for lovers of oriental food you can also order the sushi rolls of your choice; In addition, while you have a drink, you can enjoy the wonderful view of the city and the nightly musical show that they have as a surprise for you. </p><p>It?s going to be a wonderful day, I know you?ll like it. </p>                	<p><b>Medellín is salsa!</b></p><p>It was the 70s. There were no recognized stations and the Internet did not exist, salsa lovers had two options to enjoy good tunes; bars or music collectors. From there began a great love affair, which led to salsa in all the neighborhoods of Medellín and which takes us to visit iconic places in the city, where you will enjoy great songs and legendary salsa artists.</p><p>Let?s start by having a dance class in <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#timbale\\"><b>Timbalé.</b></a></p><p>This place is a house of music, dance and rhythm located in the La Floresta neighborhood of Medellín, where different events and activities are held around rhythms as important in the city as salsa; The magic of that place makes it very special, in addition, it tells the story of the most notable steps of the hard and romantic salsa that is heard to this day in Medellín.</p><p>Schedule yourself, check the personalized class of the day on their website and schedule your salsa experience <a href=\\"https://www.timbale.com.co/nosotros\\">https://www.timbale.com.co/nosotros</a></p><p>After leaving your class, what a delicious lunch at <a href=\\"#animal\\"><b>Animal Cocina</b></a>, a restaurant distinguished for its good hamburgers, in my case for example I love the Philadelphia combo, it is a delicious combination of meats, vegetables and soft cheeses. Surely when you see the menu you will find one that you will love. This restaurant is a few steps from Timbalé, so you can walk there and enjoy the tranquility of the area.</p><p>Another option for lunch and a pleasant afternoon is <a href=\\"#lavocaderia\\"><b>Lavocadería de la Floresta</b></a> , there you will find a wide variety of dishes made from avocado, a fruit very typical of the Andean region.</p><p>If you want something much more relaxing, you can stay late in the <a href=\\"#parquefloresta\\"><b>Parque de la Floresta</b></a> , where you will have walking trails and an offer of coffees, cocktail bars, ice cream parlors, among others; one of my favorite places to be there is <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#percimon\\">Percimón</a> ,</b> an ice cream parlor that offers balanced products to taste; the pistachio, passion fruit and red fruit ice cream are my favorites, in addition to the delicious alfajores and the red velvet cake which are delicious; Percimon It has a terrace where you can sit and chat and enjoy the climate of Medellín, without a doubt being there will be pleasant for you.</p><p>When night comes, to have dinner and then prepare for the city?s salsa party, I recommend having dinner at <a href=\\"#bodeguitahavanera\\"><b>La Bodeguita Havanera</b></a>, a delicious Cuban food restaurant that offers live music so you can enjoy its dishes and cocktails. A wonderful atmosphere to start the night in Medellín</p><p>When I leave here, I have two emblematic places to enjoy the rhythms and sounds of salsa and dance until dawn.</p><p>The first is <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#sonhavana\\">Son Havana</a> ,</b> a renowned salsa venue in the city, it was born in 2010 with a salsa band that plays live music; the best rhythms in the history of this musical genre. It is the ideal place to dance, enjoy and feel the warmth of the steps that make you have the sound of a good timpani. It is without a doubt one of my favorite places in Medellín to dance. IsIt is located in San Juan with 73, very close to the area where we spent the day. You can get there walking or taking a taxi that will charge you the minimum, more or less about 1.75 dollars. </p><p>My second recommendation is a traditional place ideal for dancing salsa, not suitable for quiet people, a place that keeps history, I?m talking about <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#tibiri\\">Al Tíbiri Tábara</a> ,</b> a bar where you don?t arrive, you descend. It is an old and mysterious basement, framed by the heat of the agitated steps of visitors dancing to the rhythm of musical instruments; a place to listen to and dance to the most representative salsa dura songs in history. Here you can undoubtedly hear the music of Joe Arroyo, Fruko y sus Tesos, the Latin Brothers, Hector Lavoe and many more. If you want to vibrate to the sound of these great artists, without a doubt the stop after 10 at night should be at the Tibiri.</p><p>This bar ? nightclub is very close to Son Havana, right on the corner of Carrera 70 and Calle 43 San Juan, a few blocks from my first recommendation. What you can do is spend some time at Son Havana and then visit the Tibiri, it will surely be a night full of musical flavor.</p>                	<p><b>Medellín is porro, cumbia, bagpipes and music of yesteryear.</b></p><p>Porro is a Colombian musical genre, born in the Atlantic region, but which for years has marked the musical history of Medellín. The famous porro vias, for example, were free performances that took place in the neighborhoods of the different communes of Medellín, where locals danced to the rhythm of songs such as Tolú by Lucho Bermúdez, Cumbia del Caribe by Edmundo Arias and many more.</p><p>To learn about these musical rhythms, especially their history and the impact they had on the social and nightlife of Medellín, I invite you to go to the Robledo neighborhood in the north of the city to the <b><a href=\\"#eljordan\\">El Jordan Musical Documentation Center</a> ,</b> This is a house with more than 130 years of musical history, all kinds of events are held here and today it is part of the city?s public library network, where you can undoubtedly have an immersion in the musical history of Medellín. You can?t leave without visiting this magical place.</p><p>When you leave there, I invite you to visit the center of the city, a place full of history, including the musical history of Medellín, much of which remains alive to this day in every heartbeat, in every breath of this land surrounded by mountains. In each of the places we will visit today, various artists have performed, important musical performances have been performed, and there have been countless events that you will want to know about.</p><p>The first stop is the <a href=\\"#san\\"><b>San Ignacio Building and the Paraninfo of the University of Antioquia</b></a>, two adjacent buildings declared a national monument since 1982, two buildings that are located a few blocks from the Málaga Hall, there you can admire the theaters where countless concerts have been held, presentations by the most significant artists in the country. They are magical places, where you can enjoy historical tours that you can consult on the website that I indicate at the point of interest. As a recommendation there is a corporation called San Ignacio District <b>,</b> which has experiences very focused on historical knowledge, with them you can also schedule the tour.</p><p>Then you can visit the traditional <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#barcolon\\">Bar Colón</a> ,</b> There you can have lunch and listen to traditional Colombian music, it is a place with a lot of history that has been in the city for more than 20 years. Its cuisine is varied, and you can also have a good drink while listening to traditional rhythms such as porro, cumbia, old music, and much more.</p><p>You will find this place on the entire Ayacucho street, in the center of the city, just a few blocks from the San Ignacio building.</p><p>Being in the center, I invite you to take a tour of the <a href=\\"#homeromanzi\\"><b>Homero Manzi</b></a> house , a place that, although its main rhythm is tango, is loaded with musical history, live shows, dance and flavor. It is located in Calle 48 #41-3, La Candelaria, on one of the most famous corners in the city center. Here tribute is paid to the Argentine poet and composer Homero Manzi, which is why the space is loaded with photographs, posters and countless objects that take us to the most iconic years of tango in Medellín, without a doubt, you will like it and in a good place to spend the afternoon.</p><p>At the end and to experience these rhythms that are so representative of Antioquia folklore in a more intense way, I invite you to walk towards the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#salonmalaga\\"><b>Salón Málaga</b></a> located a couple of blocks from Bar Colón. This is a place that is considered the sanctuary of traditional music. The Salón M