553	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-22 07:10:32	22828	2024-11-15 00:00:00	BCN04 - Gluten Free	Gluten free in Barcelona	gluten-free-in-barcelona	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Un paseo por los mejores rooftops de Medellín</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Llamada la ?Ciudad de la Eterna Primavera?, gracias a su agradable clima primaveral durante todo el año, Medellín es una gran ciudad para los placeres a cielo abierto. En la ciudad, se valora el aire libre y mejor si es con una vista privilegiada en altura. Las terrazas son entonces ese espacio con potencial para múltiples propósitos, ideal (para bares, restaurantes, piscinas infinitas, zonas de asados y BBQ); hasta rooftops verdes con huertos y jardines.</span>	\N	pexels-taryn-elliott-4457038.jpg	3	<p>Hello! Welcome to Barcelona. These are my recommendations for you to spend a few days of luxury without worrying about gluten. For all restaurants I recommend checking schedules and making reservations to ensure availability.</p><p>We started the day in the Eixample neighborhood. For breakfast I recommend <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#equilibrium\\">Equilibrium Café</a>, </b>a vegan place, with varied, tasty and energetic dishes. </p><p>After regaining strength, a satisfying way to start the day is to go into the modernist Barcelona. Therefore we will go to a Modernist Palace built by the famous Catalan architect Josep Puig i Cadafalch. The work is called <a href=\\"#maca3\\"><b>Palau Macaya</b></a><b> </b>and is currently a convention center. I recommend observing the building or access and soak up the modernist art, it will not leave you indifferent. </p><p>Once the visit is over, it is time to walk to the Parish of San Francisco de Sales.<a href=\\"#fransales\\"><b>St. Francis de Sales Parish </b></a>an imposing neo-Gothic church. I think they are one of those buildings that sometimes go unnoticed but are true works of art.</p><p>Then I recommend you to go to the<a href=\\"#purisima\\"><b> Basilica of the Immaculate Conception</b></a>. A work that gives charm to the Eixample district, it has an inner courtyard with a small garden. Ideal to be quiet, since it is not very crowded. I also recommend going to Carrer Roger de Llúria 49, C/ del Consell de Cent, 340, 08009 where you will find a building called <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#casacerda\\"><b>the Cerdà Houses </b></a>with Venetian murals painted throughout the building. One of the first single-family homes to recover the original 1863 drawings with a restoration that was done in 2013. Right in front of the building at Consell de Cent 340 is the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#1864\\"><b>Hotel Catalonia Eixample 1864</b></a> which is the other Casa Cerdà with murals. </p><p>For lovers of archaeology and history, another gem that you can visit in the Eixample area is the <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#egipcio\\">Egyptian Museum</a>.</b></p><p>In the surroundings I recommend eating at <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#malatxabar\\">Malatxa Bar</a>,</b> a restaurant with a wide range of gluten-free cuisine. I recommend the croquettes?delicious!</p><p>After lunch I recommend two options:</p><ol><li> The district of Gracia: If you cross the Diagonal Avenue you can go to the<a href=\\"#munos1\\"><b> Muñoz Ramonet Gardens </b></a>more unknown but very beautiful. I recommend you to stroll around Gracia quietly, it still keeps that neighborhood spirit and you can go to see the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#vicens\\"><b>Vicens House</b></a>. </li></ol><p>In Gracia for lunch or dinner you have the <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#gut\\">Gut</a>,</b> a small Mediterranean food place. About 5 minutes from the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#tag\\"><b>Obrador Gluten Tag</b></a>! where EVERYTHING is gluten free and is a sweeter option. </p><ol start=\\"2\\"><li> The gothic quarter and stroll through the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#boqueria\\"><b>Boqueria Market </b></a>visit the graffiti of the Plaza del guaje in homage to the owner of the bar Los Baskos, or access for free to the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#rubio\\"><b>Rubió i Lluch Gardens.</b></a> It also has a bar and is a hidden place in Barcelona, a 100% recommended getaway.</li></ol><p>Here in the evening for a more formal dinner <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#ville\\"><b>In Ville</b></a> is ideal. The theme of the restaurant and its dishes make the difference. I recommend the octopus. </p>                	<p>For this day I have thought of something different. We will visit the Poblenou district, known for having its own identity thanks to its small stores, its large buildings and the Bogatell beach. To get to know the district and the most relevant points of interest in the surrounding area. We will start at Glòries, located on the red line of the metro L1. Nearby there is a bakery called<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#lupita\\"><b> </b><b>Casa Lupita Gluten Free</b></a> dedicated to gluteen free with a wide variety of offerings, besides having hamburgers or sandwiches. They take great care of the aesthetics and the customer. </p><p>Next to the subway stop we will find on one side <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#agbar\\"><b>The Agbar Tower</b></a> one of the most emblematic buildings in Barcelona. It has a viewpoint where you can contemplate in its maximum splendor the district of Poblenou, and the <b><a href=\\"#museoarte\\">Museum of Design Art</a>,</b> The surrounding gardens are ideal to start the morning and enjoy the magic of Barcelona.</p><p>To eat in the area we can take a walk along the Rambla de Poblenou, the ideal is to go observing and be curious. There are many places for tapas, food and a good atmosphere. </p><p><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#apriboca\\"><b>ApriBoca</b></a> is an Italian restaurant with gluten-free pasta, pizza and dessert options. Also the restaurant <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#quinto\\"><b>El Quinto</b></a> where most of the menu is gluten-free. My personal recommendation that has to be included in your experience and even more so if you enjoy good tapas you should go to <a href=\\"#unio\\"><strong>Bar la Unió</strong></a></p><p>After lunch if you feel like some culture, I recommend several museums:<a href=\\"#centroarte\\"><b>Ideal Centro de Artes Digitales De Barcelona</b></a> with temporary exhibitions that vary according to the dates and the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#framis\\"><b>Can Framis Museum</b></a> with contemporary Catalan works of art. And of course you will have to walk through the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#ca\\"><b>Gardens of Ca l?Aranyó</b></a> a unique place in Barcelona. In this neighborhood you can walk to the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#bogatell\\"><b>Bogatell Beach</b></a>.</p><p>In the evening I recommend a <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#caber\\"><b>Cabernet Bar</b></a>. An ideal option if you feel like eating while you have a drink and enjoy a more nocturnal atmosphere. I recommend the garlic shrimp.</p>                	<p>Today we will go to the Gothic Quarter<b>,</b> specifically in the Plaza Sant Jaume we have <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#conesa\\"><b>Conesa</b></a> one of the best sandwich shops in the city, the gluten-free option will have 1 euro added for the bread. In the area you can visit the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#neri\\"><b>Sant Felipe Neri Square.</b></a> It is a small square with a baroque church damaged by the bombs of the Civil War.</p><p>We will then walk down to<a href=\\"#plor1\\"><strong> George Orwell Square</strong></a>  known as ?Tripi Street? and dedicated to the novelist and journalist who lived in Barcelona from 1936 to 1937. In the area you will find <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#vegee\\">Vegetalia</a>, </b>a restaurant with a wide variety of gluten-free dishes, we recommend the vegetable paella and the Thai wok with rice noodles. Another option is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#voca\\"><strong>A</strong><b> vocados</b></a> on Ferran Street (if you dine there, I encourage you to try the cocktails from <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#snoo\\"><b>Snooker</b></a>).</p><p>For the afternoon and as a way of getting to know the neighborhood in depth we will visit <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#mayorbcn\\"><b>The Major Synagogue of Barcelona </b></a> built between the 3rd and 4th century, it is one of the oldest in Europe, preserving its medieval architecture. Admission is free and well worth a visit.</p><p>Once you have seen this we will go up through the gothic quarter to contemplate the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#arcediano\\"><b>Archdeacon?s House </b></a>is close to The Cathedral of Barcelona that I also recommend to visit. The house of the Archdeacon is characterized as a 15th century Renaissance mansion with Gothic details and a small courtyard. Admission is free.</p><p>When it?s time for dinner I recommend you a restaurant in Via Laietana, it?s called <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#manduca\\"><b>Manduca Gluten Free</b></a>. You will find a wide variety of healthy themed food. I would try their smoothies and pasta with mushrooms. </p><p>The Gluten free options are very diverse so I will leave you with several recommendations:</p><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#fileruso\\"><b>Russian steak</b><br /></a>(finger-licking meats).</li><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#nectari\\"><b>Nectari</b></a><br />(Michelin star). </li></ul><p>If you want to dine at affordable prices:</p><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#marius\\"><b>Cal Marius</b></a>: gastrotaberna gluten-free and suitable beers. Located in Diagonal.</li><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#m2\\"><b>M2 Gluten Free</b><br /></a>variety of international and national cuisine. </li><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#martita\\"><b>La Martita</b></a>: Mediterranean cuisine with vegan options. </li></ul><p>If you feel like sweets, you can go to:</p><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#jansana\\">Jansana.</a> </b>It offers you a wide variety of 100% gluten-free breads, cakes, pastries and desserts. Made with fresh ingredients and following traditional recipes, their products will satisfy the most demanding palates.</li><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#chock\\"><b>Chöck Barcelona</b></a> Taste its famous ?krönuts?, a reinterpretation of the croissant filled with cream and chocolate coating, or choose from a wide variety of donuts, cakes, ice creams and other delicacies made with the best cocoa.</li></ul><p>Enjoy! </p>\t\t	553	\N	\N	14.9	\N	\N	N	en	4111,4099,4114,4101,1179,4105,971,4106,4118,4103,4096,998,4122,4107,4087,4100,4081,4104,4109,4091,4086,1211,4095,4121,4120,4119,4088,4115,4089,4098,4117,4092,4082,4094,4116,1008,4112,4083,4097,4085,4113,1040	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1MRNoqax-WMq-Mc0WNoZpavf9QY1yhyA&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Un paseo por los mejores rooftops de Medellín	\N	\N	Gluten free in Barcelona	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	3Dias	190	N
554	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-22 06:51:17	25956	2024-11-15 00:00:00	BCN14 - Gluten Free	Gluten Free 1 Dia	gluten-free-1-dia	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><b><strong>Destinos sin gluten:</strong></b> <b><strong>recomendaciones seleccionadas para una experiencia sin preocupaciones</strong></b></span>\\r\\n\\r\\nSumamos dos ingredientes esenciales para crear una experiencia sin preocupaciones: la comodidad y la recomendación exclusiva de nuestros anfitriones locales. Te invitamos a explorar la Barcelona menos transitada del Eixample y el fascinante barrio de Poblenou, donde la belleza se fusiona con la tranquilidad y las espectaculares vistas de la costa mediterránea.	190	bristol-.jpeg	3	<p>¡Descubre Barcelona en un día lleno de historia, arte y delicias culinarias!</p><p>Comienza tu día en Barcelona con un delicioso desayuno en el acogedor <a href=\\"#bristol1\\"><b>Bristol Café</b></a>. Disfruta de su ambiente relajado y saborea exquisitos cafés y pasteles antes de comenzar tu aventura.</p><p>Después de recargar energías, dirígete al impresionante<b> </b><a href=\\"#maca3\\"><b>Palau Macaya</b></a>, una joya arquitectónica que te dejará maravillado con su diseño modernista. Continúa tu recorrido cultural visitando la encantadora <a href=\\"#fransales\\"><b>Parroquia de San Francisco de Sales</b></a> y la majestuosa<b> </b><a href=\\"#purisima\\"><b>Basílica de la Purísima Concepción</b></a>, donde podrás admirar la magnificencia de la arquitectura sacra.</p><p>Para el almuerzo, te recomendamos dos opciones irresistibles. Dirígete al <a href=\\"#malatxabar\\"><b>Malatxa Bar</b></a> para disfrutar de tapas creativas y sabores auténticos en un ambiente vibrante, o visita <a href=\\"#naturpi\\"><b>Pizza Natura</b></a> para deleitarte con sus pizzas saludables y sin gluten, una opción perfecta para todos los gustos y necesidades dietéticas.</p><p>En la tarde, sumérgete en el mundo del diseño en <a href=\\"#museoarte\\"><b>Design Museum of Barcelona</b></a>, donde encontrarás exposiciones fascinantes que celebran la creatividad y la innovación. Después, relájate en los hermosos <a href=\\"#ca\\"><b>Jardins de Ca l’Aranyó</b></a>, un remanso de tranquilidad en medio de la ciudad. Continúa tu paseo por la animada<b> </b><a href=\\"#poblenou2\\"><b>Rambla del Poblenou</b></a> llena de vida y puntos locales de interés. Para finalizar disfruta del atardecer y la brisa marina en la<b> </b><a href=\\"#bogatell\\"><b>Playa Bogatell</b></a>.</p><p>Para la cena, te espera una experiencia culinaria única en Barcelona. Dirígete al <a href=\\"#caber\\"><b>CABERNET BAR TAPES COPES I VINS</b></a> para disfrutar de una selección de tapas y vinos en un ambiente acogedor y sofisticado, o prueba la auténtica cocina catalana en <a href=\\"#polmo\\"><b>Monopol</b></a>, donde cada plato es una obra maestra gastronómica.</p><p>¡Disfruta de un día inolvidable explorando los tesoros de Barcelona y deleitándome con su deliciosa gastronomía!</p><p><br style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" /><br style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" /></p>\t\t	\N	\N	554	\N	\N	6.9			N	es	1085,1315,1107,1322,1089,1326,1099,1083,1084,1320,1106,1323	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=15I5MEMog_cmhvK884Zm_WtnmXXlBd3k&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Destinos sin gluten:	\N	\N	Gluten Free 1 Dí­a							1Dia	191	N
555	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-22 07:10:32	23954	2024-11-15 00:00:00	BCN16 - Relax & Gourmet	Relax y Gourmet 1 Dia	relax-y-gourmet-1-dia	<strong><span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\">Vive la fusión perfecta de relajación y delicias gourmet en Barcelona, donde la serenidad se combina con experiencias culinarias irresistibles. ?????</span></strong>\\r\\n<p style=\\"text-align: center;\\"><span style=\\"color: #000000;\\">Sumérgete en un oasis de serenidad y indulgencia gourmet en el corazón de Barcelona. Descubre un mundo de tranquilidad mientras te deleitas con las delicias gastronómicas más irresistibles que Barcelona tiene para ofrecer, cada momento está diseñado para nutrir cuerpo y alma. ¡Deja que tus sentidos se eleven en este viaje de relajación incomparable!\\"</span></p>	191	relax-2-bcn.png	3	<p>¡Buenos días! Os invito a entrar en ambiente e iniciar el día de la mejor manera en <a href=\\"#tartela\\"><b>Tartela</b></a>, con productos espectaculares de foto.</p><p>Después de desayunar nos dirigimos a Plaza España y nos situaremos delante de las imponentes <a href=\\"#torres\\"><b>Torres Venecianas</b></a> que nos abrirá paso a contemplar por una parte la Fuente de Montjuic (ahora en desuso debido a la sequera en Barcelona) y por otra parte el imponente <a href=\\"#art\\"><b>Museo Nacional d?Art de Barcelona</b></a>. En este punto solo os puedo recomendar que os dejéis llevar por la belleza del lugar. </p><p>Tras pasear y observar los alrededores nos dirigimos al <a href=\\"#teatro\\"><b>Teatro Griego </b></a>con una belleza sin igual, donde pasar la mañana. En sus alrededores hay un jardín e incluso un pequeño estanque. Te servirá para relajarte y cada cierto tiempo suelen hacer actuaciones culturales, te recomiendo entrar en su página web y mirar la programación.</p><p>Una vez hayas terminado y concluido, vuestro lugar es<a href=\\"#amposta\\"><b> Bodega Amposta</b></a> un restaurante de tapas y platos principales con una ambientación elegante que nos preparará para nuestro último lugar. </p><p>Ya es hora de mimar un poco nuestro cuerpo y sentidos, por ello una temática egipcia os hará entrar en situación, <a href=\\"#isis\\"><strong>Isis Spa</strong></a>, desde baños egipcios a tratamientos faciales. Un lugar para relajar tu mente y cuerpo.</p><p>Por la tarde visitar <a href=\\"#bossvi\\"><strong>Bossvi</strong></a> una tienda de decoración de interiores enfocada en las plantas artificiales. Dejaros llevar por su ambiente único en Barcelona, donde solo admirar es un deleite.</p><p>Además podéis ir a <a href=\\"#ramonet\\"><b>Los Jardines de Muñoz Ramonet </b></a>es un jardín histórico del siglo XX fue concebido para uso privado pero actualmente es de uso público y promueven respetar el ambiente del jardín. Ofrece reposo y evasión entre la urbe y el tráfico. Cuenta con un palacete y un estanco, por los alrededores abundan esculturas.</p><p>La otra opción es más cultural y es <a href=\\"#tapies\\"><b>el Museo de la Fundación Antoni Tàpies</b></a>, un edificio modernista con un museo contemporáneo en las que se exhiben pinturas y obras del autor. La entrada general cuesta 8 euros.</p><p>A modo de terminar el día os recomiendo cenar en dos lugares, por una parte <strong><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#antigua\\">Antigua</a> </strong>un restaurante con comida mediterránea muy buena, rica y con buenas cantidades. Destaca por sus instalaciones y sus emplatados. La otra opción algo más desenfadada es <a href=\\"#saona\\"><strong>Saona Travessera de Gràcia</strong></a> A diferencia del restaurante anterior el local es más luminoso y está centrado en pequeñas tapas. Són dos conceptos totalmente distintos, pero igual de buenos. A vuestro criterio. </p><p>Para finalizar cerca esta <a href=\\"#solange\\"><strong>Solange Cocktail Bar</strong></a> Coctelería tranquila con un ambientazo para concluir el día de la manera más elegante. Un trato muy profesional y os ofreceran la mejor opción.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	555	\N	\N	6.9	\N	\N	N	es	1050,1068,1345,1347,1061,1048,1065,1051,1350,1339,1066,1340	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1PkzvNCQEaGyss8uuPUiqYnJ79jPPFx4&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Vive la fusión perfecta de relajación y delicias gourmet en Barcelona, donde la serenidad se combina con experiencias culinarias irresistibles. ?????	\N	\N	Relax y Gourmet 1 Dia	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1Dia	192	N
556	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-18 21:05:37	25959	2024-11-15 00:00:00	BCN17 - Foodie & Traveler	Foodie & Traveler 1 Dia	foodie--traveler-1-dia	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><b><strong>Discover the gastronomic treasures hidden in Barcelona, from its traditional tapas to its most avant-garde restaurants.</strong></b></span>\\r\\n\\r\\nStart the day in the vibrant Eixample neighborhood and tour the most emblematic corners of Montjuic, from the historic botanical gardens to the panoramic views from the Castle. Explore the bohemian charm of Gràcia, marveling at the architectural creations of Mario Català Nebot and the symbolic sculptures of Passeig de Sant Joan. Let Barcelona seduce you with its unparalleled magic and immerse yourself in the cultural richness of the city.	192	gluten.jpeg	3	<p>Hoy empezaremos en el Eixample, y nos dirigiremos a la parada de Urgell en la L1 del metro de Barcelona. Una vez aquí desayunamos en <a href=\\"#eixa1\\"><b>Eixampeling</b></a>, es una cafetería alegre y colorida donde rodearnos de las mejores vibras, para luego dirigirnos a Plaza España y disfrutar de Montjuic.</p><p>Dentro de Montjuic hay demasiadas cosas por ver, por lo tanto nos ocupará toda la mañana. Algunas de mis recomendaciones son las siguientes: <a href=\\"#historic1\\"><b>Jardí Botànic Històric</b></a>, justo detrás del imponente Museo Nacional de Arte de Cataluña. La entrada es gratuita, describo el lugar como uno de esos rincones ocultas en Barcelona, que poco conocen y aparte de el lugar en sí que es super bonito, el hecho de ser poco conocido le da su encanto. </p><p>Al terminar nos dirigimos  a los <a href=\\"#griego1\\"><b>Jardines del Teatro Griego</b></a>, un indispensable en él encontrarás un mini anfiteatro digno de ser visitado.</p><p>Otra alternativa es el <a href=\\"#casti\\"><b>Castillo de Montjuic</b></a><b> </b>que se construyó originalmente en el siglo XVII como fortaleza militar, y ha sido escenario de importantes acontecimientos históricos, como el bombardeo de Barcelona en 1842 y la Guerra Civil Española. Se encuentra en una colina que domina la ciudad de Barcelona, por lo que ofrece unas vistas panorámicas impresionantes. Desde las almenas del castillo, puedes ver toda la ciudad, el puerto y el mar Mediterráneo.</p><p>A Partir de aquí te recomiendo comer en un lugar privilegiado de Barcelona, poco conocido si no frecuentas la zona es el <a href=\\"#oleum1\\"><b>Restaurant Òleum</b></a> ubicado dentro del Museo. De principio a fin es toda una experiencia. Y es que el ambiente da a ello, qué mejor que comer dentro de un museo. En caso de querer tener otra opción la mía es <a href=\\"#amposta1\\"><b>Bodega Amposta</b></a>, algo más alejado pero excelente en cuanto a calidad-precio, además es un restaurante acogedor. </p><p>Por la tarde propongo el barrio de Gràcia, un barrio con un ambiente especial con un pasado mucho más rural, respira su espíritu catalanista y su cultura más callejera. Es considerado un pueblo dentro de una ciudad. </p><p>La tarde está enfocada en elementos culturales y símbolos del barrio de Gràcia. Nuestro primer punto de referencia será el <a href=\\"#nebot1\\"><b>Edificio de viviendas de Mario Català Nebot</b></a>, en sus inicios nadie le entendía, pero con el paso del tiempo sus creaciones se han convertido en objeto de culto con ventanas psicodélicas y formas onduladas. Muchos barceloneses la llaman la piscina de Barcelona. </p><p>Luego iremos al Passeig de Sant Joan, aquí encontraremos dos esculturas con simbolismos por un lado la <a href=\\"#roja1\\"><b>Fuente de Caperucita Roja</b></a>, es una curiosa imagen de bronce de 1921. Muestra una caperucita Roja empoderada como si hubiese sometido al Lobo. A unos metros encontramos <a href=\\"#hercules1\\"><b>La Fuente de Hércules</b></a>, dicen que es unas de las estatuas más antiguas de Barcelona, se inauguró en 1802 se construyó para celebrar la boda y la visita del rey Carlos IX.</p><p>Por último y no por ello menos especial <a href=\\"#plgitano\\"><strong>Plaça del Poble Gitano</strong></a> es historia de Gràcia y un homenaje al corazón gitano del barrio.</p><p>Y de aquí nos dirigimos a <a href=\\"#sol1\\"><b>Plaza del Sol</b></a> emblemática y lugar de encuentro del barrio de Gràcia ideal para tomar algo en un ambiente único. Qué mejor que ponerte en escena e ir a <a href=\\"#cafe1\\"><b>Cafè del sol</b></a>, su bar más mítico. Además por sus alrededores hay edificios de estilo modernista.</p><p>Para finalizar cena en <a href=\\"#nua1\\"><b>Nüa</b></a>, un restaurante futurista y healthy que me encanta. Y para terminar el día un cóctel en <b><a href=\\"#19681\\">Marcelino 1968</a>.</b></p>\t\t	\N	\N	556	\N	\N	6.9	\N	\N	N	es	1068,1362,1354,1357,1351,1358,1352,1353,1359,1364,1363,1360,1261,1355	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1b6lCIDOaUh0wmRcIu6kaeP-8FIwEGz8&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Discover the gastronomic treasures hidden in Barcelona, from its traditional tapas to its most avant-garde restaurants.	\N	\N	Foodie & Traveler 1 Dia	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1Dia	193	N
557	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-22 07:10:32	23965	2024-11-15 00:00:00	BCN18 - Bohemian & Vintage	Bohemian & Vintage 1 Dia	bohemian--vintage-1-dia	<strong><span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\">Experiencia ideal para amantes de lo vintage y el second hand en la que descubriréis lugares que os enamorarán.</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"color: #000000;\\">¡Embárcate en una aventura bohemia y vintage por las calles encantadas de Barcelona! Descubre joyas ocultas en El Gòtic y El Born, donde cada rincón es un tesoro esperando ser encontrado. Desde desayunos reconfortantes  hasta paseos entre boutiques únicas, cada momento está impregnado de nostalgia y estilo. Luego, sumérgete en el alma creativa de Gràcia, explorando sus tiendas vintage y disfrutando de la vida en la Plaza del Sol. Termina tu día con delicias culinarias viviendo Barcelona con un toque retro y una pizca de magia.</span>	193	vintage-bcn.png	3	<p>¡Bienvenidos a Barcelona! Soy Violeta y soy amante de todo lo vintage, en esta experiencia os dejo mis lugares favoritos que espero que disfrutéis tanto cómo lo hago yo.</p><p>Empezaremos el día recorriendo el barrio de El Gotic y el barrio del Born, si queréis desayunar por la zona mi recomendación es <a href=\\"#brunch1\\"><b>The Benedict Brunch Barcelona</b></a>, tienen una carta muy variada con todo tipo de desayunos y dulces… para llenar bien el estómago! Otra opción es <a href=\\"#pic1\\"><b>Picnic</b></a> (Carrer del Comerç), cuando entres, te encontrarás con un local pequeñito, muy bien iluminado en el que te sentirás en un ambiente muy agradable y familiar, tienen menú brunch muy variado de viernes a domingo, no te lo pierdas!!</p><p>Born: En el barrio del Born, donde encontraréis galerías de arte contemporáneo y tiendas de diseñadores independientes, Después podemos pasear por las calles de el born, lo que más encontramos en las tiendas del Born es la figura del artesano/diseñador/anticuario independiente, con un discurso propio muy marcado y alejado de los cánones artísticos y de moda impuestos. para visitar algunas de sus tiendas como <a href=\\"#ziggy1\\"><b>Ziggy Vintage</b></a>, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#segura1\\"><b>Carlos</b><b> </b><b>Segura</b></a>… ya que estáis por la zona os recomiendo visitar la Galería Maxó o, si os apetece dulce, el <a href=\\"#choco1\\"><b>Museo del Chocolate</b></a>.</p><p>Gotic: Una vez tenemos el estómago lleno, podemos pasear hacia el Gotic y perdernos por sus calles donde encontraremos una muy buena variedad de tiendas vintage, mis favoritas en esta zona son <a href=\\"#blue1\\"><strong>Blue Goose </strong></a><b></b>(abre a las 12), Le Swing Vintage… y no os podéis perder los vestidos de novia de <a href=\\"#arca1\\"><b>L´Arca</b></a>! Ya que estáis por la zona, os recomiendo visitar el <a href=\\"#fun1\\"><b>Big Fun Museum</b></a><b> </b>(un original museo con ilusiones ópticas donde hacerse fotos y retratos de personajes famosos hechos con comida<b>)</b>, o el <a href=\\"#puig1\\"><b>Jardín de la Casa Ignacio de Puig</b></a>, un pequeño oasis secreto en el centro de la ciudad.</p><p>Para comer por la zona os recomiendo tapear o tomar un vermut en la taberna <a href=\\"#porta\\"><b>El Portalón</b></a>. Otra opcion es <a href=\\"#gallo\\"><strong>Gallo Nero</strong></a>, un restaurante italiano ofrece una variedad de opciones para todos los gustos, desde pizzas clásicas hasta platos más elaborados como la bistecca alla fiorentina (filete a la parrilla) o el ragù alla toscana (estofado de carne). Además, tiene sus postres caseros como el tiramisú o la panna cotta.</p><p>Nada mejor para pasar la tarde que desplazarnos al barrio de Gracia, uno de los barrios más bohemios y con más encanto de la ciudad. Aquí las posibilidades son infinitas, podemos empezar visitando mis tiendas favoritas como <b><a href=\\"#100armarios\\">Revolviendo 1000 armarios</a>  </b>y <a href=\\"#leopardo1\\"><b>Leopardo Leopardi Concept Store</b></a>. Otras opciones son  <a href=\\"#rev\\"><strong>Revolution Vintage Clothing</strong></a> y en la iconica Plaza del diamant en honor al clasico libro catalan, encontramos <a href=\\"#mah\\"><strong>Mahalo Vintage Gracia</strong></a>.</p><p>Si habéis venido a gracia de lunes a viernes también podéis visitar la <b><a href=\\"#saturnalia1\\">Librería Saturnalia</a>. </b>Podéis acabar tomando algo en la plaza del sol que es uno de los puntos de encuentro en el barrio y tiene ambientazo todas las tardes. Os recomiendo cenar en <a href=\\"#nina\\"><strong>Nina</strong></a> con tapas excelentes y un trato muy profesional. </p><p>Por si os apetece tomar algo hay un lugar muy top en la plaza de la revolución, se llama <a href=\\"#cani\\"><strong>Bar Canigó</strong></a> </p><p>Otra opción es tapear y tomar algo en <a href=\\"#coco1\\"><b>Coco ?s Secrets</b></a>, un lugar con mucho encanto en Barcelona. La decoración no te dejará indiferente, tienen noches temáticas cada semana, algunos días espectáculos y música en directo! </p>\t\t	\N	\N	557	\N	\N	6.9	\N	\N	N	es	1382,1372,1370,1368,1383,1374,1375,1373,1377,1253,1371,1379,1369,1381,1366,1378,1376,1365,1367	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1lDyLE8_N8mEDAuqHIJ-7bYucc8k_tc0&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Experiencia ideal para amantes de lo vintage y el second hand en la que descubriréis lugares que os enamorarán.	\N	\N	Bohemian & Vintage 1 Dia	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1Dia	194	N
558	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-22 07:10:32	23967	2024-11-15 00:00:00	BCN20 - Book Lovers	Book Lovers 1 Dia	book-lovers-1-dia	<strong><span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\">Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"color: #000000;\\">¡Adéntrate en un mundo de aventura y magia entre páginas! Únete a nosotros, apasionados de los libros, en un recorrido por los rincones más encantadores y librerias de Barcelona. Descubre rincones históricos inspirados en obras como \\"La sombra del viento\\" de Carlos Ruiz Zafón y déjate llevar por el encanto literario del barrio de Gràcia. Termina el día con una cena en un restaurante con un jardín mágico y alarga la noche en un teatro lleno de diversión , donde el arte y el entretenimiento se fusionan. ¡Déjate envolver por las historias que Barcelona tiene para ofrecer!.</span>	194	Llibreriacafee-Laie.jpg	3	<p>Buenos días Book lovers,</p><p>Comenzamos con la joya de la corona, si os digo que conozco un sitio que es un restaurante, una cafetería y una librería a la vez? ¿Sorprendente? Esta es mi recomendación para vosotros. Se llama <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#laie\\">Laie Librería Café</a> </b>y cuenta con una terraza donde se puede estar al aire libre. Mi definición es que es un lugar ideal para los amantes de los libros :) Además por si os apetece luego también hacen menús diarios. </p><p><a href=\\"#comics\\"><b>Norma Comics</b></a> es el paraíso del mundo del manga y nuestra siguiente visita. El edificio cuenta con dos plantas y te encontrarás miles de cosas por ver. Seas amante o no es una visita que vale la pena y más aún sabiendo que cuenta con 13.612 reseñas web y tiene un escalofriante 4,7 en estrellas. Es algo muy difícil de conseguir. </p><p>En la parte posterior del edificio está la Librería<a href=\\"#gigamesh\\"><b> Gigamesh </b></a>especializada en literatura fantástica y de terror. Con muy buenas reseñas web. Y además una de mis favoritas por mi afición al terror.</p><p>Nos dirigimos al born para adentrarnos en un lugar histórico y no precisamente por su contexto. Si no porque es un lugar que aparece en el libro de “<i>La sombra del viento de Carlos Ruiz Zafón</i>” Para quien no conozca el libro ni el autor os explico… prometo ser breve.</p><p>Fue un novelista español famoso por su obra más emblemática <i>La sombra del viento</i>. Con más de 15 millones de ejemplares vendidos se considera una de las 100 obras más importantes escritas en español de los últimos 25 años. Por ello os sugiero hacer este recorrido por el born.</p><p>Comenzaremos en el Centro Cultural de Born esto te hará entrar en ambiente, pasea por los alrededores y dirígete a la <a href=\\"#maria\\"><b>Basílica de Santa María del Mar</b></a>, en esta basílica un personaje de la obra va día tras día a confesarse, imaginate… El personaje se llama Bernarda. Luego subir por el Carrer Montcada y entrar en la Librería<b><a href=\\"#picasso\\"> Laie Museo Picasso</a>,</b> un lugar que en toda su esencia es arte. Y hablando de arte acabar en la <a href=\\"#maxo\\"><b>Galería Maxó</b></a> para inmortalizar la mañana. En su interior hay una máquina de hacer fotos con la temática de la galería por un precio de 3€, así os llevaréis un pequeño recuerdo.</p><p>Para comer os doy dos opciones, <a href=\\"#nou\\"><strong>Nou Celler</strong></a> un restaurante de comida catalana con menú diario muy rico o <a href=\\"#pedrito\\"><strong>San Pedrito Restaurante Y Licoreria</strong></a> un restaurante de comida mexicana con una temática y un ambiente muy agradable.</p><p>Por la tarde nos dirigimos al Barrio de Gràcia. Este bello barrio ha sido descrito en un clásico de la literatura catalana. En honor a ello tiene una plaça con su nombre, ah y se me olvidaba… también una escultura. El libro en cuestión se llama <i>La plaça del diamant. </i></p><p>Disfrutaremos del barrio mientras caminamos hacia nuestro destino, como era de esperar <a href=\\"#diamant\\"><b>la Plaça del Diamant</b></a>, un lugar histórico y conocido por la famosa novela. En ella encontraremos una escultura en honor a <i>la Colometa</i>, la protagonista de la novela. </p><p>Seguimos con la siguiente plaza es <a href=\\"#la\\"><strong>Plaça de la Virreina</strong></a> es una zona concurrida llena de vida, contemplar la <a href=\\"#joan\\"><strong>Parròquia de Sant Joan de Gràcia</strong></a> y luego visitar <a href=\\"#haiku\\"><strong>Haiku Barcelona ? Librería y tienda japonesa</strong></a> antes de ir a nuestro siguiente destino. Haiku tiene muchas curiosidad, donde seguro os comprareis algo al entrar. </p><p>Al terminar id a la <a href=\\"#sol\\"><strong>Plaça del Sol</strong></a> y contemplar los edificios modernistas además de <a href=\\"#saturnalia\\"><strong>Llibreria Saturnàlia</strong></a> una librería local peculiar. Os invito a tomar algo por los alrededores o cenar en <a href=\\"#gracia\\"><strong>Jardinet de Gràcia</strong></a> un restaurante top con una decoración floral en el centro. No os olvidéis de probar la burrata. Para finalizar el día con un ambiente de ocio vuestro lugar es <a href=\\"#teatreneu\\"><strong>Teatreneu </strong></a>dentro de un Teatro muy popular en Gràcia. </p><p>Buena suerte!!!</p>\t\t	\N	\N	558	\N	\N	6.9	\N	\N	N	es	1254,1085,1389,1235,1395,1255,1393,1259,1237,1239,1253,1234,1390,1394,1261,1078	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1_K3zv9M89Zw_BBfM9Apv5amvxElRA-E&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.	\N	\N	Book Lovers 1 Dia	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1Dia	195	N
559	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-22 01:58:35	24386	2024-11-15 00:00:00	BCN06 - Relax & Gourmet	Relax & gourmet en Barcelona	relax--gourmet-en-barcelona	<p><strong>Experience the perfect fusion of relaxation and gourmet delights in Barcelona, where serenity meets irresistible culinary experiences.&nbsp;</strong></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Enjoy rejuvenating treatments, enchanting landscapes and moments of tranquility in the most exclusive places in the city. Leave stress behind and let yourself be carried away by a unique wellness experience in Barcelona.</p>\\r\\n	\N	Llibreriacafee-Laie.jpg	3	<p>Hello! Welcome to Barcelona! My city can be an oasis of serenity, I am going to recommend my favorite places so that you can enjoy a few days of relaxation, tranquility and good food that you will not forget? I hope you like it!! Remember that for spas and restaurants it is important to check schedules and book in advance to ensure availability.</p><p>Today we will move through the Eixample and the Gothic Quarter. As a way to start the day, I recommend <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#billy\\"><b>Billy Brunch </b></a>(Bailen street). They serve very good coffee in various shapes, pancakes, toasts with various toppings and a lot of variety.</p><p>After having breakfast in this pleasant place, we will head to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#evasiom\\"><b>Evasiom Spa</b></a>, a spa with Thai massage. It is characterized by its specialty in aromatherapy, it is based on working with and using essential oils that are beneficial to our body. Beyond this, you really manage to disconnect with different smells that allow you to enter a relaxing atmosphere. </p><p>On the way to Evasiom Spa you have the option of observing the modernist works of the city that are passing through such as<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#punxes\\"><b>the House of Spikes (la Casa de les Punxes)</b></a>  and <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#comalat\\"><b>the Comalat House (la Casa Comalat),</b></a> this way you will avoid the crowds.</p><p>What do you think of Evasiom Spa? Relaxing right? very good, now I have two recommendations to activate the body a little, so I will recommend:</p><ol><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a href=\\"#ramonet\\"><b>The Gardens of Muñoz Ramonet</b><b> </b></a>It is a historic garden from the 20th century, it was conceived for private use but is currently for public use and they promote respect for the garden?s environment. It offers rest and escape between the city and traffic. It has a mansion and a tobacconist?s shop, and sculptures abound in the surrounding area.</li><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\">The other option is more cultural and is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#antoni\\"><b> the Antoni Tàpies Foundation Museum</b></a>, a modernist building with a contemporary museum exhibiting paintings and works by the author. General admission costs 8 euros.</li></ol><p>I think it?s time to eat and for that I have a place that will make you pamper your taste buds. The recommendation is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#antigua\\"><b>Antigua </b></a>(Carrer de Marià Cubí), Antigua is an exclusive Mediterranean restaurant where wines and exquisite meat and seafood dishes are served.</p><p>Another more casual option is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#saona\\"><b>Saona Travessera de Gràcia</b></a> with friendly service and a welcoming atmosphere. They have a half-day tasting menu with 5 courses and it is the recommended option, otherwise choose à la carte.</p><p>In the afternoon we will move through the Gothic Quarter. Visit the little known <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#augusto\\"><b>MUHBA Temple of Augustus</b></a>(closes at 2 on Mondays), inside it has the columns of the temple of Augustus that have been restored and date from the 1st century BC. C. Another option according to the experience is to visit <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#frederic\\"><b>the Frederic Marès Museum</b> <b> </b></a> It is a cultural treasure in the heart of Barcelona. Thanks to its majestic building and the collection of pieces on display, it will take you back in time and immerse yourself in the life and creativity of Frederic Marès. </p><p>To relax after this visit, a good place for pause and tranquility is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#salteiro\\"><b>Salteiro</b></a>, very top and its main element is tea. As for the environment, it is softly lit and you will find books and curious objects. </p><p>If you prefer to have a drink and admire the Cathedral from a terrace high up, your place is<a href=\\"#cola\\"><b>Hotel Colón</b></a> It is in front of the Cathedral. Once inside, when you are at the top, you will have an exclusive panoramic view and an atmosphere that will give way to enjoying the experience. If you want to have something I suggest booking before you go. </p><p>For dinner and at night I recommend <a href=\\"#disfru2\\"><b>To Enjoy</b></a> the Mediterranean gastronomy, offers top experimental menus in the Eixample neighborhood. If you prefer sushi <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#shunka\\"><b>Shunka Restaurant</b></a> It is one of the best in the city. Located in the Gothic quarter.</p>                	<p>We continue with our relaxation and care routine, the first thing of all is to have breakfast and that is why I recommend a very TOP place, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#papa\\"><b>LA PAPA BARCELONA</b> <b> </b></a> a gourmet place with more careful preparations. It has two offices in Barcelona, ??one at 92 Aribau Street and the other at 190 Pau de Claris Street. Everything is soooo good</p><p>After leaving LA PAPA BARCELONA with a smile… spa time! Here are some of my favorites, don?t forget to book so you don?t run out of space!: </p><p>?<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#aire\\"><b>Spa Aire de Barcelona</b></a>, with a perfect location in the old town, set in ancient Arab baths to fully enjoy the hot bath, the hamam, you can book a fantastic massage.  </p><p>?<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sentits\\"><b>9 sentits</b></a>. They have different services such as massages for couples with different rituals and aromatic baths, individual wellness massages, wine therapy? </p><p>-My last recommendation is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#isis\\"><b>Isis Spa</b></a>in front of <b><a href=\\"#egipcio\\">the Egyptian Museum of Barcelona</a> (</b>which is also worth visiting if you have time). Inspired and set in Egypt.</p><p>After this relaxing session, to eat we can go to <a href=\\"#xera\\"><b>Xera Restaurant</b> <b> </b></a> Located in El Raval, it offers modern Catalan cuisine. It is a great experience, proof of this they have another restaurant next to them called <a href=\\"#rao\\"><b>RAÓ restaurant</b> <b> </b></a> with avant-garde cuisine that captivates its diners with ceviches, fish and innovative dishes.</p><p>In the afternoon we go to Plaza España and we will stand in front of the imposing Venetian Towers that will open the way for us to contemplate, on the one hand, the Montjuic Fountain (now disused due to the drying plant in Barcelona) and on the other hand, the imposing <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#art\\"><b>National Museum of Art. ?Art of Barcelona</b></a>. At this point I can only recommend that you let yourself be carried away by the beauty of the place. </p><p>After walking and observing the surroundings we headed to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#teatro\\"><b>the Greek Theater</b> <b> </b></a> with unparalleled beauty, where to spend the afternoon. In its surroundings there is a garden and even a small pond. It will help you relax and from time to time they usually do cultural performances, I recommend you go to their website and look at the programming.</p><p>I recommend ending the afternoon at the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#olimpico\\"><b>Montjuic Olympic Ring</b></a> where the 1992 games were held. It is a very large area, therefore, you will have privacy and there will be no crowds.  </p><p>For dinner and concluding, your place is <a href=\\"#amposta\\"><b>Bodega Amposta</b><b> </b></a> a place for tapas and main dishes with an elegant setting that will prepare us for our last place.  <a href=\\"#hcolon\\">The <strong>Catalonian</strong> <b>Hotel</b></a>, is very little known but inside the hotel, on the ground floor, there is a cocktail bar that is open 24 hours a day and you can even order food.</p>                	<p>Today I thought of something different? but don?t worry, before venturing out, it will be better to have breakfast and calm your senses. Therefore, for greater delight, I have considered that a less frequented place will be ideal for you, since it is located in a hidden corner in the Gothic Quarter. This place claims to be a coffee specialist and will surprise you with its presentations and large exterior windows. I invite you to start the day in <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#side\\"><b> </b><b>Right Side Coffee Bar</b></a> .</p><p>Previously I told you that I had thought of something different and that is why I decided to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#tattva\\"><b>Tattva Yoga Studio</b><b> </b></a> 500 meters from the Right Side Coffee Bar, a yoga center with an unbeatable atmosphere awaits us. The yoga center is super beautiful, it has a special energy and so do the teachers.  </p><p>Just go there and you?ll thank yourself and the amazing teachers later. I recommend calling before to find out. If you can?t book here, another option in the area is  <a href=\\"#lotus\\"><b>Happy Lotus Massage Therapy & Yoga Barcelona</b></a> which is open on weekends (you must book an appointment).</p><p>After leaving we went to Born to walk through the Plaça Comercial where you will find the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#born\\"><b>Born Cultural Center</b><b> </b></a> It is a beautiful building from the end of the 20th century. Inside it has exhibitions and there is the  <a href=\\"#yacimiento\\"><b>Born site</b></a> , excavated ruins of the 18th century city, very well preserved. </p><p>There are many bars in the surrounding area if you want to have a vermouth. My personal recommendation is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#drstra\\"><strong>Dr. Stravinsky</strong></a> , one of the 50 best bars in the world. Therefore I will give you another option:  <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#bubita\\"><b>Bubita Sangria Bar</b><b> </b></a>a slightly more discreet place where you will be just as well.</p><p>Finally, I recommend eating at <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#buon\\"><b>Buon Appetito</b></a>, a restaurant that serves pizza, pasta and salads and offers a daily menu that is the most affordable option. Another option in the area is  <a href=\\"#san\\"><b>San Pedrito</b></a> , Mexican cuisine restaurant with a great atmosphere.</p><p>In the afternoon take the opportunity to take a walk along Passeig de Colom <b>.</b> </p><p>If you want to enjoy the city and the port of Barcelona with the best views, I recommend <a href=\\"#sagardi\\"><b>Sagardi 1881</b></a>. It is at the top of the  Museum of History of Catalonia. Once at the top you will have an exclusive view of the port, with a live DJ and a Mediterranean gastronomic offer.  </p><p>Then go to Passeig de Joan Borbó until you reach Barceloneta beach, this will be our new destination. Walk to the  <a href=\\"#vela\\"><b>Hotel Vela (Hotel W)</b></a>  and place yourself in the back of it. It is an ideal area to end the afternoon watching the sunset. Also, if you feel like it, it is 5 minutes away.  <a href=\\"#velissima\\"><b>Velissima Barcelona</b><b> </b></a>Italian restaurant, where you can have a drink or eat. Other recommendations are in front of the hotel where there are numerous restaurants to choose from: Gallito, Wok Home, Pez Vela….</p><p>To enjoy!</p>\t\t	559	\N	\N	14.9			N	en	4212,1142,4202,4201,4211,4196,4229,4225,4226,4228,4198,963,4227,4087,4208,4197,4205,4218,4224,4207,4232,4213,4219,4204,4217,4216,1009,4231,4230,1016,4203,4209,4223,4210,4221,4200,4233,4215	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=18FGazF_DO_-equdA4yx6Jltr23fn2hQ&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Experience the perfect fusion of relaxation and gourmet delights in Barcelona, where serenity meets irresistible culinary experiences.&nbsp;	\N	\N	Relax & gourmet en Barcelona							3Dias	196	N
560	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-18 21:05:37	22185	2024-11-15 00:00:00	BCN10 - Book Lovers	Book Lovers	book-lovers	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Experiencia ideal para amantes de los libros en la que descubriréis librerías con mucha personalidad, agradables cafeterías dónde relajarse y planes de lo más culturetas.</span>	196	young-woman-sitting-blanket-reading-book.jpg	3	<p>Welcome! I am your host, if you like reading as much as I do, I am sure you will enjoy this experience. I will recommend libraries, hidden bookstores in the city and places that few know about so that you can get to know that hidden side that few know about.  </p><p>Hello Book Lovers ?</p><p>Ready for the journey? In the morning we will move through the Arc de Triomf area, a monument built as the main entrance to the Universal Exhibition that was held in the city in 1888.  </p><p>I suggest having breakfast at <a href=\\"#sand\\"><b>SandwiChez</b></a>, an elegant and quiet cafeteria where, on the one hand, you can start the day without stress and if you feel like reading a little. In any case, in case you feel like having breakfast on a terrace, this is  <a href=\\"#granja\\"><b>Granja Cafeteria</b></a> , a little further away but where you will be super comfortable.</p><p>At this point book lovers we enter our journey for them I recommend our first place,<b> </b><a href=\\"#arus\\"><b>Arús Library</b></a>  library from the past with the smell of old wood, its marble statue impresses. It is a neighborhood library inaugurated in 1895. It is quite an old gem. Mainly keeps old books and collections. There is the possibility of taking a guided tour of its two upper floors and seeing one of Joan Proubasta?s Sherlorc Holmes collections, one of the most important private collections in Spain and one of the 10 most important in the world. General admission costs 16 euros.</p><p>I recommend you look at the opening hours. It is closed on Saturdays and Sundays. On Thursdays and Fridays they open at 3:30 p.m.</p><p>Otherwise, and in order to understand another type of reading, I recommend you visit <a href=\\"#comics\\"><b>Norma Comics</b></a>  It is the paradise of the manga world. The building has two floors and you will find thousands of things to see. Whether you are a lover or not, it is a worthwhile visit and even more so knowing that it has 13,612 web reviews and still has a chilling 4.7 star rating. And it is something very difficult to achieve.  </p><p>At the back of the building is the Bookstore<b> </b><a href=\\"#gigamesh\\"><b>Gigamesh</b></a><b> </b>specialized in fantasy and horror literature. With very good web reviews. And also one of my favorites because of my love of horror.</p><p>Lastly, I recommend you go to the<b> </b><a href=\\"#ciutadella\\"><b>Parc de la Ciutadella</b></a> and visit the Library of the Parliament of Catalonia <b>,</b>  an interesting historical building to see. I suggest you relax in the area.  </p><p>Now let?s go with the jewel in the crown, if I tell you that I know a place that is a restaurant, a cafeteria and a bookstore at the same time? Amazing? This is my book lovers recommendation, this place is called  <a href=\\"#laie\\"><b>Laie Bookstore Cafe</b></a>  And although it is a little further away, if you want to spend the morning-afternoon here, I recommend skipping the Parc de la Ciutadella and going directly. It also has a terrace where you can be outdoors. My definition is that it is an ideal place for book lovers :)</p><p>In the afternoon we will go through historical places and not precisely because of their context. If not because they are places that appear in the book of “<i>The Shadow of the Wind by Carlos Ruiz Zafón</i> “For those who do not know the book or the author, I will explain… I promise to be brief.</p><p>He was a Spanish novelist famous for his most emblematic work <i>The Shadow of the Wind.</i>. With more than 15 million copies sold, it is considered one of the 100 most important works written in Spanish of the last 25 years.</p><p>For this reason, I suggest you take this tour of the Born and the Gothic as a way to end the afternoon. Take advantage.</p><p>We will start at the Born Cultural Center<b> </b>This will get you in the mood, walk around and head to the <a href=\\"#maria\\"><b>Basilica of Santa María del Mar</b></a>, in this basilica a character from the play goes day after day to confess, imagine? The character?s name is Bernarda. Go up Carrer Montcada and enter the Bookstore<b> <a href=\\"#picasso\\">Laie Picasso Museum</a> ,</b>  a place that in all its essence is art. From here we head to C. de l?Argenteria and from here to Plaça Sant Jaume described by the protagonist of the novel. From here I recommend passing through the Pont del Bisbe and go to <a href=\\"#llibres\\"><b>Stock Llibres</b></a><b> </b>a small treasure that Barcelona offers us, a small but very well stocked bookstore.</p><p>From here I recommend you rest and end the day at <a href=\\"#antic\\"><b>Antic Teatre</b></a>. A lively place in which to clear your mind.</p>                	<p>For this day you can start the day with breakfast in the cafeteria of the <a href=\\"#byron\\"><b>Byron Bookstore</b></a><b> </b>located in the Eixample neighborhood, where you can telework if necessary. Nearby are two of my favorite bookstores.  <a href=\\"#finestres\\"><b>The Finestres Bookstore</b></a> , very nice and cozy and<a href=\\"#altair\\"><b> </b></a>You will really enjoy <a href=\\"#altair\\"><b>the Altair Bookstore</b></a> if you like to travel, because it specializes in guides and maps.</p><p>Afterwards, the plan that I recommend is to visit the Raval, if you feel like it, it can be very cool to discover the exhibitions at the <a href=\\"#cccb\\"><b>CCCB</b></a> or the <a href=\\"#macba\\"><b>MACBA</b></a>. Stop to eat at  <a href=\\"#central\\"><b>Central Bar</b></a>, has a small patio ideal if the weather is good. A vegetarian option is  <a href=\\"#biocenter\\"><b>Biocenter</b></a> , a spacious and colorful restaurant with delicious vegetarian tapas.</p><p>In the afternoon seems like the ideal time to go to the theater. You can see the programming in the  <a href=\\"#poliorama\\"><b>Teatre Poliorama</b></a> , <a href=\\"#biblioteca\\"><b>Teatre La Biblioteca</b></a> or enjoy a musical performance at the <a href=\\"#liceu\\"><b>Gran Teatre del Liceu</b></a> or the spectacular <a href=\\"#palau\\"><b>Palau de la Música</b></a><b> </b>Inside there is a hidden cafeteria that few know about where you can have a coffee while reading a book. Or go to Antic Teatre with an interior patio ideal for having a drink while reading.</p><p>Another option is to go to the Gracia neighborhood and stop by some of its most picturesque shops such as the <a href=\\"#saturnalia\\"><b>Saturnalia Bookstore</b></a> , in the same square where it is located you can have a drink or dinner at the <a href=\\"#teatreneu\\"><b>Bar Teatreneu</b></a> or in <a href=\\"#gracia\\"><b>Jardinet de Gràcia.</b></a>  a top restaurant with a floral decoration in the center. Don?t forget to try the burrata.  </p>                	<p>For this day I propose two plans. A good option is to go to  <a href=\\"#sant\\"><b>Sant Antoni Sunday Market</b></a>  where you will find books, vinyls and more to spend the morning. I hope you are in luck book lovers, because they are only open on Sundays from 8:30 a.m. to 2:00 p.m. If the indicated date does not coincide, don?t worry, I have an alternative.  </p><p>But if you agree, I recommend several gastronomic options:</p><ul><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\">For breakfast: <a href=\\"#desa\\"><b>La Desayuneria</b></a> , creative breakfasts.</li><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\">To eat: <a href=\\"#tombs\\"><b>Els tres Tombs</b></a> in case you want to have something while you read or relax</li></ul><p>In case your plan fails, we head to the Gràcia neighborhood. And as on the first day, this beautiful neighborhood has been described in a classic of Catalan literature. In honor of it, it has a plaza with its name, oh and I forgot? also a sculpture. The book in question is called  <i>The diamond square.  </i></p><p>Therefore I have several ideas in mind. Once in Gràcia, we will enjoy the neighborhood as we walk towards our destination, as expected  <a href=\\"#diamant\\"><b>the Diamant Square</b></a>, a historical place and known for the famous novel. In it we will find a sculpture in honor of  <i>La Colometa</i> , the protagonist of the novel. </p><p>Once you have finished, I recommend doing a ceramics workshop. It?s in the area and it?s called  <a href=\\"#ceramica\\"><b>La Ceramicaria Gràcia</b></a><b> </b>I recommend calling and making a reservation. An enriching experience where you can elevate your imagination.</p><p>Then finish in<a href=\\"#sol\\"><b> </b><b>Plaza del Sol</b></a> and eat at a local restaurant.</p><p>In the afternoon and as a curious fact, in August 2023, the <a href=\\"#marquez\\"><b>Gabriel García Márquez Library</b></a>  won the international award for best new public library. Located in the Sant Martí neighborhood. It is quite an experience where you can read your favorite book in a hammock, and it also has an outdoor area in case you feel like reading outdoors.</p><p>In the area, if you feel like eating, there is <a href=\\"#verneda\\"><b>La Verneda Restaurant</b></a> , where they make homemade dishes.</p><p>To enjoy! And remember that you have more experiences on the web.</p>\t\t	560	\N	\N	14.9	\N	\N	N	en	4244,4236,4241,4251,4245,4250,933,1191,4265,4258,4238,4235,4254,4263,4266,4240,4242,932,4237,956,4252,1158,1225,1218,4243,1146,4257,4247,4260,4262,4246,4261,4253	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1Ec4ArI9K5yw-XQJCdWaR0jBfaGL-NkM&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.	\N	\N	Book Lovers	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	3Dias	197	N
561	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-18 21:05:37	24591	2024-11-15 00:00:00	BCN07 - Foodie & Traveler - DEMO	Foodie & Traveler	foodie--traveler	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Experiencia ideal para amantes de los libros en la que descubriréis librerías con mucha personalidad, agradables cafeterías dónde relajarse y planes de lo más culturetas.</span>	\N	young-woman-sitting-blanket-reading-book.jpg	3	<p>Welcome to Barcelona! I am your host and in this experience I am going to recommend my favorite restaurants and places in the city so that you can get to know Barcelona. Before starting, I recommend that if the third day is a Sunday, you start with day three first and leave day one for the third day. This way you can visit all the planned places. :)</p><p>To maintain that traveler essence we will move away from that central and iconic part of Barcelona. Therefore, as a way to begin the experience, I recommend visiting the upper neighborhoods of the city, specifically we will move through the Les Corts district, it is the third smallest neighborhood in the city but it is charming.  </p><p>As a way to start the day by delighting our senses of sight and taste, I recommend having breakfast at <a href=\\"#mommy\\"><b>¡Oh Mommy</b></a>  a brunch restaurant located in the center of Les Corts. I could define this place with one word: delightful.  </p><p>After this feast, we begin our adventure and to do so we will move to the <a href=\\"#cervantes1\\"><b>Cervantes Park</b></a>  located in Pedralbes. It is synonymous with peace and beauty. In Cervantes Park you can breathe fresh air and in the company of its rose gardens, its grass areas and its vegetation it is like a green lung within the Pedralbes neighborhood.</p><p>I recommend spending the morning here, but if the traveler spirit drives you to do more, I have more recommendations for you :)  </p><p>On the one hand, the <a href=\\"#palacio1\\"><b>Gardens of the Pedralbes Palace</b></a><b> </b>a place with landscaped gardens and fountains, and the garden is crowned by a historic palace. This Garden will be an ideal place to end our tour by heading to the  <a href=\\"#nou1\\"><b>Camp Nou</b></a> , a great international symbol of the city of Barcelona. </p><p>I recommend going down Carrer de Marti i Franquès, to soak up the atmosphere that is lived and felt in Pedralbes, one of the best neighborhoods in Barcelona.  </p><p>I recommend you visit the field facilities and its surroundings. To finish, I recommend eating at<b> </b><a href=\\"#turuleca1\\"><b>The Turuleca</b></a>, a Peruvian gastronomy restaurant with dishes with a lot of color and a lot of flavor. A gastronomy very well criticized by the international media. Your essentials are the ceviche with the famous tiger?s milk and its sautéed loin ?</p><p>In the afternoon I recommend something more central and that is why you can take a walk along Passeig de Gracia and see its most iconic buildings, ( <a href=\\"#pedrera1\\"><b>La Pedrera</b></a><b> </b><b>and</b><b> </b><a href=\\"#batllo1\\"><b>Casa Batlló</b></a> ) with Casa Batlló I recommend looking at it from the <a href=\\"#estacion1\\"><b>Servicio Estación</b></a> building , where you can see the back of the building and it is a little-known place. </p><p>Near La Pedrera I recommend you go to the <a href=\\"#dutti1\\"><b>Massimo Dutti store</b></a>  which is located in a modernist building with a garden inside. Then go to Plaza Cataluña and finish walking along Las Ramblas. Over there eat at the restaurant  <a href=\\"#canaletas1\\"><b>gutters</b></a>. In the middle of Las Ramblas it is  Ale-Hop , entering is another modernist palace.</p><p>Now with a full belly you can go to <a href=\\"#catedral1\\"><b>the Cathedral Square</b></a>  and stop for a photo at the “The Kiss” mural. Continue along Via Laietana to the port and walk along the  <a href=\\"#fusta1\\"><b>Moll de Fusta</b></a>, just in front of the port. Walk until you reach the  Columbus Statue and from here go to the <a href=\\"#raval2\\"><b>Barceló Raval Hotel</b></a>, is 11 minutes walking. Its rooftop has spectacular 360º views where it is incredible to see the sunset, and this is where you can end the day, but if you prefer it to be a place of passage, you can end up in  <a href=\\"#nacional1\\"><b>El Nacional</b></a> with a glass of cava.</p>                	<p>Today we will start in Eixample, and we will go to the Urgell stop on L1 of the Barcelona metro. Once here we had breakfast at  <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#eixa1\\"><b>Eixampeling</b></a> is a happy and colorful cafe where we can surround ourselves with the best vibes, and then head to Plaza España and enjoy Montjuic.</p><p>Inside Montjuic there are too many things to see, so it will take us all morning. Some of my recommendations are the following:  <a href=\\"#historic1\\"><b>Historical Botanical Garden</b></a>, just behind the imposing National Museum of Art of Catalonia. Admission is free, I describe the place as one of those hidden corners in Barcelona, ??that little is known about and apart from the place itself which is super beautiful, the fact that it is little known gives it its charm.  </p><p>At the end we headed to the <a href=\\"#griego1\\"><b>Greek Theater Gardens</b></a> , an essential place where you will find a mini amphitheater worth visiting.</p><p>From here I recommend eating in a privileged place in Barcelona, ??little known if you don?t frequent the area, is the <a href=\\"#oleum1\\"><b>Restaurant Òleum</b></a>  located inside the Museum. From start to finish it is quite an experience. And the atmosphere lends itself to it, what better than eating inside a museum. In case you want to have another option, mine is  <a href=\\"#amposta1\\"><b>Bodega Amposta</b></a> , a little further away but excellent in terms of quality-price, it is also a cozy restaurant. </p><p>In the afternoon I propose the Gràcia neighborhood, a neighborhood with a special atmosphere with a much more rural past, breathing its Catalan spirit and its more street culture. It is considered a town within a city.  </p><p>The afternoon is focused on cultural elements and symbols of the Gràcia neighborhood. Our first point of reference will be the  <a href=\\"#nebot1\\"><b>Residential building by Mario Català Nebot</b></a> , in the beginning no one understood him, but with the passage of time his creations have become an object of worship with psychedelic windows and wavy shapes. Many Barcelonans call it the Barcelona pool. </p><p>Then we will go to Passeig de Sant Joan, here we will find two sculptures with symbolism, on the one hand the Little <a href=\\"#roja1\\"><b>Red Riding Hood Fountain</b></a>, is a curious bronze image from 1921. It shows an empowered Little Red Riding Hood as if she had subdued the Wolf. A few meters away we find  <a href=\\"#hercules1\\"><b>The Fountain of Hercules</b></a> , they say it is one of the oldest statues in Barcelona, ??it was inaugurated in 1802 and was built to celebrate the wedding and visit of King Charles IX.</p><p>And from here we head to <a href=\\"#sol1\\"><b>Plaza del Sol</b></a>  emblematic and meeting place of the Gràcia neighborhood, ideal for a place to pause while enjoying the sunrise of Barcelona. What better than to put yourself on the scene and go to  <a href=\\"#cafe1\\"><b>Coffee of the sun</b></a>, its most legendary bar. In addition, there are modernist style buildings in its surroundings.</p><p>To finish dinner in <a href=\\"#nua1\\"><b>Nüa</b></a>, a futuristic and healthy restaurant that I love. And to end the day a cocktail at  <a href=\\"#19681\\"><b>Marcelino 1968</b></a> .</p>                	<p>Good morning! For this day I have thought of something vintage? for them we will have to go to Glòries, this on L1 of the Barcelona metro. In the area have breakfast in  <a href=\\"#wapa1\\"><b>Wapa Barcelona Restaurant</b></a> , is next to the Agbar Tower and is a quiet place to start the day. </p><p> </p><p>Once ready we will go to one of the largest second-hand markets in Barcelona. Is he  <a href=\\"#dels1\\"><b>Mercat dels Encants</b></a>, it is very curious to see and you will find a lot of curiosities. There is always something good to see.</p><p>If you still want more, a little further away you will find <a href=\\"#encants1\\"><b>Petits Encants</b></a> , in Arc del Triomf, an antique store with a large number of curiosities.</p><p>And eat at <a href=\\"#elsa1\\"><b>Elsa and Fred</b></a><b> </b>where you can make the menu of the day for 15 euros or order à la carte. A cozy restaurant with grilled dishes.</p><p>In the afternoon our destination is Barcelona. A good morning starts with a delicious brunch facing the sea in  <a href=\\"#cala1\\"><b>The Cala</b></a>  (Barceloneta). After touring the  Maritime ride by bike, there is a place called Rent Bike BCN located in Barceloneta or Online Bike Rental located in El Born, where you can rent a bike to enjoy the experience and take a tour around El Born and discover its corners.</p><p>Another option is to go to <a href=\\"#puerto1\\"><b>Torre de Jaime I ? Teleférico del Puerto de Barcelona</b></a><b> </b>and enjoy the views and good weather of Barcelona. </p><p>To eat, <a href=\\"#xampa\\"><b>Xampanyet</b></a> is one of the usual bars that I like, otherwise you can <a href=\\"#bubbles1\\"><b>Rooster & Bubbles</b></a> with a more modern touch.</p><p>Enjoy Barcelona!</p>\t\t	561	\N	\N	14.9	\N	\N	N	en	1142,1127,1133,959,1134,1125,1147,1138,967,1126,1140,1139,1136,1144,1149,1132,1151,1135,1148,1152,1143,1141,1157,1131,1146,1154,1145,1137,1129,1128,1156,1155,1150,1124	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1_gJsoEH6VZjUsFC97FxycsUE7TIW72E&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.	\N	\N	Foodie & Traveler	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	3Dias	198	N
562	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-18 21:05:37	24593	2024-11-15 00:00:00	BCN08 - Bohemian & Vintage - DEMO	Bohemian & Vintage	bohemian--vintage	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Experiencia ideal para amantes de los libros en la que descubriréis librerías con mucha personalidad, agradables cafeterías dónde relajarse y planes de lo más culturetas.</span>	\N	young-woman-sitting-blanket-reading-book.jpg	3	<p>Welcome to Barcelona! I am Violeta and I am a lover of everything vintage, in this experience I leave you my favorite places that I hope you enjoy as much as I do.</p><p>For the first day we will tour the El Gotic neighborhood, if you want to have breakfast in the area my recommendation is <a href=\\"#brunch1\\"><b>The Benedict Brunch Barcelona</b></a> , ??they have a very varied menu with all kinds of breakfasts and sweets?to fill your stomach well! </p><p>Once we have a full stomach, we can walk towards the Gotic and get lost in its streets where we will find a very good variety of vintage stores, my favorites in this area are  <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#blue1\\"><strong>Blue Goose</strong></a> (opens at 12), Le Swing Vintage? and you can?t miss the wedding dresses from  <a href=\\"#arca1\\"><b>L?Arca</b></a>! Since you are in the area, I recommend visiting the  <a href=\\"#fun1\\"><b>Big Fun Museum</b></a><b> </b>(an original museum with optical illusions where you can take photos and portraits of famous people made with food <b>)</b> , or the <a href=\\"#puig1\\"><b>Casa Ignacio de Puig Garden</b></a> , a small secret oasis in the center of the city.</p><p>To eat in the area I recommend having tapas or having a vermouth at the <a href=\\"#porta\\"><b>El Portalón</b></a> tavern , or if you prefer something healthier although it is a better known option, I really like the <a href=\\"#greens1\\"><b>Honest Greens</b></a> which is next to Plaza Catalunya., </p><p>After eating you can tour the Workshops Street. On this street there are countless vintage stores to spend hours in, one that I love to visit is  <a href=\\"#revo\\"><b>Revolver</b></a> where you can find new and second-hand records from all eras, and of course <b><a href=\\"#kilo1\\">Flamingo?s Vintage Kilo</a> ,</b> where the price of clothing is determined by the weight of the garment! In this area I also recommend having a drink at the <a href=\\"#moritz1\\"><b>Moritz Brewery</b></a> .</p><p>To end the day you can go to the Eixample neighborhood and pay tribute to yourself at <a href=\\"#or1\\"><b>O ??Retorniño</b></a>, a Galician restaurant specializing in fish and seafood, is a little further away but it is well worth it! If you fancy a closer and more sophisticated bar, you have  <a href=\\"#loli1\\"><b>The Lolita Barcelona</b></a> .</p>                	<p>This morning is a good time to visit <a href=\\"#mercate1\\"><b>El Mercat dels Encants</b></a><b> </b>/ Carrer de los Castillejos, 158 (Monday, Wednesday, Friday and Saturday), a market where I would dare to say that you can find anything you are looking for. For breakfast in the area, I like it  <b><a href=\\"#guli1\\">Giulietta Cafe</a> .</b> </p><p>After visiting the market you can head towards Poblenou for a walk, here we can visit <a href=\\"#cartes1\\"><b>IDEAL the Barcelona Digital Arts Center</b></a><b> </b>It has 3D projections of Klimt or Monet and it?s really cool to see <b>.</b> Or if you want to continue shopping, my favorites in the area are <a href=\\"#vpoble1\\"><b>Vintage Poblenou</b></a> and the Scandinavian furniture store <a href=\\"#noak1\\"><b>NOAK Room</b></a> is also worth it .</p><p>To eat in the area I recommend <a href=\\"#tavernicola1\\"><b>La Tavernicola</b></a><b> </b>a restaurant with Argentine dishes that you will love, or if you prefer you can go for a walk on the Rambla de Poblenou and end up eating at <a href=\\"#can2\\"><b>Can Recasens</b></a><b> </b>which is a very original restaurant with a shop selling typical products at the entrance <b>,</b> You will love their charcuterie or cheese boards! At the end, if you continue straight along the Rambla del Poblenou, you will arrive at the promenade where I love to stop to read or sit and look at the sea while the sun shines on me.  </p><p>There is nothing better to spend the afternoon than traveling to the Gracia neighborhood, one of the most bohemian and charming neighborhoods in the city. Here the possibilities are endless, we can start by visiting my favorite stores like  <b><a href=\\"#100armarios\\">Rummaging 1000 closets</a></b> and <a href=\\"#leopardo1\\"><b>Leopardo Leopardi Concept Store</b></a> <b>.</b> If you have come to grace from Monday to Friday you can also visit the <a href=\\"#saturnalia1\\"><b>Saturnalia Bookstore</b></a> <b>.</b> You can end up having a drink in Plaza del Sol , which is one of the meeting points in the neighborhood and has a great atmosphere every afternoon. </p><p>To end the day I recommend having tapas and a drink at <a href=\\"#coco1\\"><strong>Coco?s Secrets</strong></a>, a very charming place in Barcelona. The decoration will not leave you indifferent, they have theme nights every week, some days shows and live music! Another option is the  <a href=\\"#cpages1\\"><b>Café Pagés</b></a> if you fancy something more traditional. </p>                	<p>For this last day we cannot forget the Born neighborhood, where you will find contemporary art galleries and independent designer shops. For breakfast in the area, my recommendation is  <a href=\\"#pic1\\"><b>Picnic</b></a>  (Carrer del Comerç), when you enter, you will find a small, very well-lit place where you will feel in a very pleasant and familiar atmosphere. They have a very varied brunch menu from Friday to Sunday, don?t miss it!!</p><p>Afterwards we can walk through the streets of El Born, what we find most in the shops of El Born is the figure of the independent artisan/designer/antique dealer, with his own very marked discourse and far from the imposed artistic and fashion canons. to visit some of their stores like  <a href=\\"#ziggy1\\"><b>Ziggy Vintage</b> , <b>Carlos Segura</b></a> … since you are in the area, I recommend visiting the Maxó Gallery or, if you feel like something sweet, the <a href=\\"#choco1\\"><b>Chocolate Museum</b></a>. To have tapas you can have something on one of the terraces of the Mercat de Santa Caterina.</p><p>If today were Sunday (a day when you can find many stores closed), don?t worry, I have a great alternative plan! He  <a href=\\"#antoni1\\"><b>Sant Antoni Sunday Market</b></a>, the best book market in Barcelona, ??old books, collector?s books, out-of-print books, postcard collecting, historical documents, comics, posters, movies, trading cards, video games, used and second-hand books? a real gem! If you are here at lunchtime you can have tapas at  <a href=\\"#tombs1\\"><b>The Three Tombs</b></a> . </p><p>If you still have energy in the afternoon, you can take a walk through the Raval, the bohemian neighborhood par excellence of Barcelona, ??visit the <a href=\\"#monica1\\"><b>Santa Mónica art center</b></a>  which is full of talented and upcoming artists. Here the street par excellence for vintage shops is Carrer de la  Riera Baixa (closed on Sundays), where you will find some that I usually frequent like <a href=\\"#80s\\"><b>Club 80?s</b></a> or the record store <a href=\\"#wah1\\"><b>Wah Wah Records</b></a>. In the area if you want to have a drink you have a bar with authentic Catalan tradition, the  <a href=\\"#marsella1\\"><b>Marseille bar</b></a> .</p><p>End of our route, I hope you enjoy Barcelona and come back soon to see more of this beautiful city?see you soon!!</p>\t\t	562	\N	\N	14.9	\N	\N	N	en	1228,1200,1198,1220,1215,1223,1224,1219,1226,1205,1168,1210,1203,1211,1199,1217,1230,1206,1213,1207,1221,1028,1216,1225,1227,1218,1197,1208,1209,1202,1214,1212,1229,1222	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1bE0yPBWbP4bxkgme2fWAiH4uciDNl8w&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.	\N	\N	Bohemian & Vintage	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	3Dias	199	N
563	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-18 21:05:37	24595	2024-11-15 00:00:00	BCN06 - Relax & Gourmet - DEMO	Relax & gourmet en Barcelona	relax--gourmet-en-barcelona	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Experiencia ideal para amantes de los libros en la que descubriréis librerías con mucha personalidad, agradables cafeterías dónde relajarse y planes de lo más culturetas.</span>	\N	young-woman-sitting-blanket-reading-book.jpg	3	<p>Hello! Welcome to Barcelona! My city can be an oasis of serenity, I am going to recommend my favorite places so that you can enjoy a few days of relaxation, tranquility and good food that you will not forget? I hope you like it!! Remember that for spas and restaurants it is important to check schedules and book in advance to ensure availability.</p><p>Today we will move through the Eixample and the Gothic Quarter. As a way to start the day, I recommend <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#billy\\"><b>Billy Brunch </b></a>(Bailen street). They serve very good coffee in various shapes, pancakes, toasts with various toppings and a lot of variety.</p><p>After having breakfast in this pleasant place, we will head to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#evasiom\\"><b>Evasiom Spa</b></a>, a spa with Thai massage. It is characterized by its specialty in aromatherapy, it is based on working with and using essential oils that are beneficial to our body. Beyond this, you really manage to disconnect with different smells that allow you to enter a relaxing atmosphere. </p><p>On the way to Evasiom Spa you have the option of observing the modernist works of the city that are passing through such as<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#punxes\\"><b>the House of Spikes (la Casa de les Punxes)</b></a>  and <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#comalat\\"><b>the Comalat House (la Casa Comalat),</b></a> this way you will avoid the crowds.</p><p>What do you think of Evasiom Spa? Relaxing right? very good, now I have two recommendations to activate the body a little, so I will recommend:</p><ol><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\"><a href=\\"#ramonet\\"><b>The Gardens of Muñoz Ramonet</b><b> </b></a>It is a historic garden from the 20th century, it was conceived for private use but is currently for public use and they promote respect for the garden?s environment. It offers rest and escape between the city and traffic. It has a mansion and a tobacconist?s shop, and sculptures abound in the surrounding area.</li><li style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\" aria-level=\\"1\\">The other option is more cultural and is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#antoni\\"><b> the Antoni Tàpies Foundation Museum</b></a>, a modernist building with a contemporary museum exhibiting paintings and works by the author. General admission costs 8 euros.</li></ol><p>I think it?s time to eat and for that I have a place that will make you pamper your taste buds. The recommendation is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#antigua\\"><b>Antigua </b></a>(Carrer de Marià Cubí), Antigua is an exclusive Mediterranean restaurant where wines and exquisite meat and seafood dishes are served.</p><p>Another more casual option is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#saona\\"><b>Saona Travessera de Gràcia</b></a> with friendly service and a welcoming atmosphere. They have a half-day tasting menu with 5 courses and it is the recommended option, otherwise choose à la carte.</p><p>In the afternoon we will move through the Gothic Quarter. Visit the little known <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#augusto\\"><b>MUHBA Temple of Augustus</b></a>(closes at 2 on Mondays), inside it has the columns of the temple of Augustus that have been restored and date from the 1st century BC. C. Another option according to the experience is to visit <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#frederic\\"><b>the Frederic Marès Museum</b> <b> </b></a> It is a cultural treasure in the heart of Barcelona. Thanks to its majestic building and the collection of pieces on display, it will take you back in time and immerse yourself in the life and creativity of Frederic Marès. </p><p>To relax after this visit, a good place for pause and tranquility is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#salteiro\\"><b>Salteiro</b></a>, very top and its main element is tea. As for the environment, it is softly lit and you will find books and curious objects. </p><p>If you prefer to have a drink and admire the Cathedral from a terrace high up, your place is<a href=\\"#cola\\"><b>Hotel Colón</b></a> It is in front of the Cathedral. Once inside, when you are at the top, you will have an exclusive panoramic view and an atmosphere that will give way to enjoying the experience. If you want to have something I suggest booking before you go. </p><p>For dinner and at night I recommend <a href=\\"#disfru2\\"><b>To Enjoy</b></a> the Mediterranean gastronomy, offers top experimental menus in the Eixample neighborhood. If you prefer sushi <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#shunka\\"><b>Shunka Restaurant</b></a> It is one of the best in the city. Located in the Gothic quarter.</p>                	<p>We continue with our relaxation and care routine, the first thing of all is to have breakfast and that is why I recommend a very TOP place, <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#papa\\"><b>LA PAPA BARCELONA</b> <b> </b></a> a gourmet place with more careful preparations. It has two offices in Barcelona, ??one at 92 Aribau Street and the other at 190 Pau de Claris Street. Everything is soooo good</p><p>After leaving LA PAPA BARCELONA with a smile… spa time! Here are some of my favorites, don?t forget to book so you don?t run out of space!: </p><p>?<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#aire\\"><b>Spa Aire de Barcelona</b></a>, with a perfect location in the old town, set in ancient Arab baths to fully enjoy the hot bath, the hamam, you can book a fantastic massage.  </p><p>?<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sentits\\"><b>9 sentits</b></a>. They have different services such as massages for couples with different rituals and aromatic baths, individual wellness massages, wine therapy? </p><p>-My last recommendation is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#isis\\"><b>Isis Spa</b></a>in front of <b><a href=\\"#egipcio\\">the Egyptian Museum of Barcelona</a> (</b>which is also worth visiting if you have time). Inspired and set in Egypt.</p><p>After this relaxing session, to eat we can go to <a href=\\"#xera\\"><b>Xera Restaurant</b> <b> </b></a> Located in El Raval, it offers modern Catalan cuisine. It is a great experience, proof of this they have another restaurant next to them called <a href=\\"#rao\\"><b>RAÓ restaurant</b> <b> </b></a> with avant-garde cuisine that captivates its diners with ceviches, fish and innovative dishes.</p><p>In the afternoon we go to Plaza España and we will stand in front of the imposing Venetian Towers that will open the way for us to contemplate, on the one hand, the Montjuic Fountain (now disused due to the drying plant in Barcelona) and on the other hand, the imposing <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#art\\"><b>National Museum of Art. ?Art of Barcelona</b></a>. At this point I can only recommend that you let yourself be carried away by the beauty of the place. </p><p>After walking and observing the surroundings we headed to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#teatro\\"><b>the Greek Theater</b> <b> </b></a> with unparalleled beauty, where to spend the afternoon. In its surroundings there is a garden and even a small pond. It will help you relax and from time to time they usually do cultural performances, I recommend you go to their website and look at the programming.</p><p>I recommend ending the afternoon at the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#olimpico\\"><b>Montjuic Olympic Ring</b></a> where the 1992 games were held. It is a very large area, therefore, you will have privacy and there will be no crowds.  </p><p>For dinner and concluding, your place is <a href=\\"#amposta\\"><b>Bodega Amposta</b><b> </b></a> a place for tapas and main dishes with an elegant setting that will prepare us for our last place.  <a href=\\"#hcolon\\">The <strong>Catalonian</strong> <b>Hotel</b></a>, is very little known but inside the hotel, on the ground floor, there is a cocktail bar that is open 24 hours a day and you can even order food.</p>                	<p>Today I thought of something different? but don?t worry, before venturing out, it will be better to have breakfast and calm your senses. Therefore, for greater delight, I have considered that a less frequented place will be ideal for you, since it is located in a hidden corner in the Gothic Quarter. This place claims to be a coffee specialist and will surprise you with its presentations and large exterior windows. I invite you to start the day in <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#side\\"><b> </b><b>Right Side Coffee Bar</b></a> .</p><p>Previously I told you that I had thought of something different and that is why I decided to <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#tattva\\"><b>Tattva Yoga Studio</b><b> </b></a> 500 meters from the Right Side Coffee Bar, a yoga center with an unbeatable atmosphere awaits us. The yoga center is super beautiful, it has a special energy and so do the teachers.  </p><p>Just go there and you?ll thank yourself and the amazing teachers later. I recommend calling before to find out. If you can?t book here, another option in the area is  <a href=\\"#lotus\\"><b>Happy Lotus Massage Therapy & Yoga Barcelona</b></a> which is open on weekends (you must book an appointment).</p><p>After leaving we went to Born to walk through the Plaça Comercial where you will find the <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#born\\"><b>Born Cultural Center</b><b> </b></a> It is a beautiful building from the end of the 20th century. Inside it has exhibitions and there is the  <a href=\\"#yacimiento\\"><b>Born site</b></a> , excavated ruins of the 18th century city, very well preserved. </p><p>There are many bars in the surrounding area if you want to have a vermouth. My personal recommendation is <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#drstra\\"><strong>Dr. Stravinsky</strong></a> , one of the 50 best bars in the world. Therefore I will give you another option:  <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#bubita\\"><b>Bubita Sangria Bar</b><b> </b></a>a slightly more discreet place where you will be just as well.</p><p>Finally, I recommend eating at <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#buon\\"><b>Buon Appetito</b></a>, a restaurant that serves pizza, pasta and salads and offers a daily menu that is the most affordable option. Another option in the area is  <a href=\\"#san\\"><b>San Pedrito</b></a> , Mexican cuisine restaurant with a great atmosphere.</p><p>In the afternoon take the opportunity to take a walk along Passeig de Colom <b>.</b> </p><p>If you want to enjoy the city and the port of Barcelona with the best views, I recommend <a href=\\"#sagardi\\"><b>Sagardi 1881</b></a>. It is at the top of the  Museum of History of Catalonia. Once at the top you will have an exclusive view of the port, with a live DJ and a Mediterranean gastronomic offer.  </p><p>Then go to Passeig de Joan Borbó until you reach Barceloneta beach, this will be our new destination. Walk to the  <a href=\\"#vela\\"><b>Hotel Vela (Hotel W)</b></a>  and place yourself in the back of it. It is an ideal area to end the afternoon watching the sunset. Also, if you feel like it, it is 5 minutes away.  <a href=\\"#velissima\\"><b>Velissima Barcelona</b><b> </b></a>Italian restaurant, where you can have a drink or eat. Other recommendations are in front of the hotel where there are numerous restaurants to choose from: Gallito, Wok Home, Pez Vela….</p><p>To enjoy!</p>\t\t	563	\N	\N	14.9	\N	\N	N	en	4212,1142,4202,4201,4211,4196,4229,4225,4226,4228,4198,963,4227,4087,4208,4197,4205,4218,4224,4207,4232,4213,4219,4204,4217,4216,1009,4231,4230,1016,4203,4209,4223,4210,4221,4200,4233,4215	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=18FGazF_DO_-equdA4yx6Jltr23fn2hQ&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.	\N	\N	Relax & gourmet en Barcelona	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	3Dias	200	N
564	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-18 21:05:37	24597	2024-11-15 00:00:00	BCN12 - Modernismo - DEMO	Secretos Modernistas	secretos-modernistas	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Experiencia ideal para amantes de los libros en la que descubriréis librerías con mucha personalidad, agradables cafeterías dónde relajarse y planes de lo más culturetas.</span>	\N	young-woman-sitting-blanket-reading-book.jpg	3	<p>Para desayunar os propongo comenzar en uno de mis lugares favoritos de la Barcelona modernista que es <a href=\\"#chelo1\\"><b>Chelo Café</b></a> si hace sol no dudéis en salir a la terraza. Después y para ir entrando al tema os propongo un paseo por las ramblas, entrar en el <a href=\\"#boque1\\"><b>Mercat de la Boqueria</b></a><b> </b>y en la tienda Alehop. Esta tienda que a priori pasaría desapercibida, pero es un palacete modernista con unos techos sorprendentes.</p><p>Después os propongo entrar en el colegio de abogados y (actual archivo de Barcelona) se llama oficialmente el <a href=\\"#arcadia\\"><b>Palacio de l’ Arcadia</b></a>, podéis ver el claustro e ir a tomar algo a “<a href=\\"#gats4\\"><b>Els cuatre gats</b></a>” el lugar bohemio de la ciudad donde se reunían los genios del modernismo y donde por primera vez Picasso expuso una de sus obras. Ya que estáis por la zona no podemos obviar el <a href=\\"#paau\\"><b>Palau de la Música</b></a> y del edificio del <a href=\\"#seda\\"><b>Palacio de la Seda</b></a>. Podéis ir hasta estos monumentos y hacer un par de fotos o si os apetece visitarlos.</p><p>Para comer os propongo <a href=\\"#sk2\\"><b>Restaurante Sk</b></a> para tomar un menú de los de toda la vida a precio económico o <a href=\\"#soso1\\"><b>La Sosenga</b></a> con un precio un poco más elevado, pero también muy recomendable. </p><p>Después de reponer fuerzas si os apetece conocer alguna de las famosas casas de Gaudí este es el momento para que podáis hacerlo, mi favorita es la <a href=\\"#llo1\\"><b>Casa Batlló</b></a>, si os parece caro el precio, podéis entrar por la tienda e ir a los baños típicos modernistas o entrar en el edificio de al lado llamado Servicio Estación y subir a la planta más alta y admirar las terrazas de la Casa Batlló.</p><p>Por la tarde iremos a dar un paseo por la zona de Montjuic para admirar edificios modernistas como <a href=\\"#ramona\\"><b>La fábrica</b> <b>CasaRamona</b></a> construido entre el año 1909 y 1912. Desde 2002 es la sede de CaixaForum. </p><p>O hacer un recorrido por el Eixample y visitar las siguientes casas no tan conocidas: <a href=\\"#morera1\\"><b>Casa Lleó i Morera</b></a>, <b><a href=\\"#calvet1\\">Casa Calvet</a>, <a href=\\"#llopis\\">Casa Manuel Llopis Bofill</a>, <a href=\\"#bruno\\">Casa Bruno Cuadros</a></b>. Después podéis ir a tomar una copa y ver el atardecer en <a href=\\"#fuster1\\"><b>Casa Fuster</b></a>, actualmente un hotel. Construido por Lluís Domènech i Montaner, referente mundial del modernismo catalan.</p><p>Para la cena os propongo dos opciones ambas están en la parte modernista y se llaman <a href=\\"#diaz\\"><b>Casa Diaz</b></a><b> </b>o<b><a href=\\"#portoles1\\"> Restaurante Portoles</a>.</b></p><p>Después os propongo ir al <a href=\\"#ayre\\"><b>Ayre Hotel Rosellón</b></a>, las vistas son espectaculares y tendréis las mejores vistas para observar la Sagrada Familia, recomiendo reservar. </p>\t\t	\N	\N	564	\N	\N	6.9	\N	\N	N	es	2914,2827,2910,2908,2912,2911,2907,2909,2889,2892,2906,2894,2890,2891,2896,1252,2913,2893	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=1B0-jnpErRlHkQ79sfs96piCCfP4h6TQ&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Adéntrate en el universo literario donde las bibliotecas y librerías son los tesoros ocultos que narran la historia de la ciudad.	\N	\N	Secretos Modernistas	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1Dia	201	N
565	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-22 07:10:32	26145	2024-11-15 00:00:00	SV21 Cofrade 1 Day	Dive into the Cofrade Atmosphere in 1 Day	dive-into-the-cofrade-atmosphere-in-1-day	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Culture, Tapas and Devotion in Seville</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nExplore Seville\\ s vibrant cofrade culture as you visit its most iconic spots. This itinerary immerses you in the devotion and fervor that define the city. Plus, savor authentic local cuisine at places frequented by Seville\\ s cofrades. This unique experience will connect you with Seville\\ s history, tradition, culture, and flavors, taking you to the essence of this unforgettable city.	201	Cofrade-2.jpeg	1	<p>Welcome to Seville! Today we start the day in one of the most brotherly neighborhoods in Seville: Triana!</p><p>We will begin with breakfast at the <a href=\\"#baronesa\\"><b>La Baronesa</b></a> bar , then we will visit the <a href=\\"#santaana\\"><b>Real Parroquia Señora Santa Ana</b></a> , known for its baroque architecture and its devotion to Santa Ana, the mother of the Virgin Mary, and then continue to the <a href=\\"#capilladelosmarineros\\"><b>Capilla de los Marinrosa</b></a>, which houses the image of the Hope of Triana, one of the most revered images in Seville. You also can?t miss the <a href=\\"#cristoexpiracion\\"><strong>Basilica del Stmo. Cristo de la Expiración.</strong></a></p><p>Afterwards we will cross the iconic <b><a href=\\"#puentedetriana\\">Puente de Isabel II</a> ,</b> that connects the Triana neighborhood with the historic center of Seville. When crossing, I propose to put heading towards the <a href=\\"#magdalena\\"><b>Basílica de Santa María Magdalena.</b></a> If you are late in the area and want to have some tapas, I recommend the <a href=\\"#matacandela\\"><b>Taberna Cofrade Matacandela</b></a> .</p><p>After lunch, don?t forget to visit the <a href=\\"#catedral\\"><strong>Catedral de Sevilla</strong></a> , and then head to the <a href=\\"#lablanca\\"><strong>Iglesia de Santa María la Blanca</strong></a> . </p><p>Since you are in the center, other less known but worth seeing parishes in the Las Setas area are <b><a href=\\"#sanpedroapostol\\">San Pedro Apóstol</a> , <a href=\\"#santacatalina\\">Santa Catalina</a> or the <a href=\\"#buensuceso\\">Iglesia del Buen Suceso.</a></b><b>.</b> If you want to have some tapas in the area in a totally friendly atmosphere, be sure to go to <b><a href=\\"#losclaveles\\">Los Claveles</a> or <a href=\\"#elrinconcillo\\">Rinconcillo</a> ,</b> or if you want to dine at a place well known for its “piripis”, <a href=\\"#bodeguitaromeroymejias\\"><strong>Bodeguita Romero & Mejía</strong></a><strong>s</strong> . And, to end the day, you cannot miss the <a href=\\"#garlochi\\"><b>Garlochí</b></a> cocktail bar with a picturesque and brotherhood theme.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	565	\N	\N	6.9	\N	\N	N	en	60,32,122,4402,4399,133,4397,4396,4392,4393,4400,4401,4391,4403,4404,332	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=16QkCEh0W5Va2avofHBPcv2c5v_ZB2FY&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Culture, Tapas and Devotion in Seville	\N	\N	Dive into the Cofrade Atmosphere in 1 Day	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1Dia	202	N
566	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-22 07:10:32	26212	2024-11-15 00:00:00	SV33 Casas Palacio 1 día	Ruta De Las Casas Palacio 1 Dia	ruta-de-las-casas-palacio-1-dia	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Sumérgete en la majestuosidad del pasado de Sevilla con estas joyas arquitectónicas, llenas de historia y elegancia, que te transportarán a una época de esplendor.</span></strong>\\n\\nA través de esta experiencia, tendrás la oportunidad de sentir la esencia de la vida aristocrática en Sevilla y conocer las fascinantes historias que se esconden tras sus muros centenarios. Una experiencia inolvidable que te conectará con el rico patrimonio cultural y gastronómico de esta encantadora ciudad.	202	duenas.jpg	1	<p>Comenzamos en el barrio de Macarena, desayunando en <a href=\\"#feria\\"><strong>Feria83</strong> </a>. Nuestra primera parada es el palacio <a href=\\"#algaba\\"><b>de los Marqueses de la Algaba.</b></a> Hoy es un edificio gubernamental, pero se puede visitar. Entonces, la siguiente parada es la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#duenas\\"><b>Casa Palacio de Dueñas</b></a> de la muy querida por los sevillanos fallecida Duquesa de Alba. Aquí encontrará, además del edificio, un museo de pertenencias de la difunta duquesa. Seguimos hacia la Calle Cuna, concretamente en el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#lebrija\\"><b>Palacio de la Condesa de Lebrija.</b></a> Una visita que no te puedes perder, tanto por el edificio como por las joyas que alberga en su interior procedentes de Itálica, entre los que se incluyen enormes mosaicos enteros.</p><p>Continuamos hacia el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#monsalves\\"><b>Palacio de los Monsalves.</b></a>Este edificio se propone como una ampliación del <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#bellasartes\\"><b>Museo de Bellas Artes</b></a> de Sevilla, que si está abierto recomendamos visitar porque sólo su edificio es un antiguo convento mercedario y alberga en su interior una colección de arte barroco, además de obras de Murillo, Velázquez y Zurbarán. Ya que estás por la zona te sugiero que visites el Museo de Bellas Artes ya que es gratuito para los ciudadanos de la UE y cuesta sólo 1,50 euros para el resto.</p><p>Nosotros mereces un descanso para almorzar, nos dirigiremos a la bulliciosa plaza de la Alfalfa donde te damos dos opciones: tapear de pie en sus típicas tascas como<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#trastienda\\"><b> la trastienda </b></a>oh <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#alfalfa\\"><b>la bodega de la alfalfa</b></a> o sentarse a comer en <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#escalona\\"><b>la escalona</b></a> donde podrás probar sin miedo cualquiera de sus tapas, aunque las más populares son la carrillá, sus croquetas o su tataki de atún.</p><p>Con energías renovadas, continuaremos caminando por el Barrio de Santa Cruz, sus edificios son antiguas casas palacio hoy convertidas en apartamentos o casas de vecindad particulares, acércate a sus rejas y patios para descubrir pequeños tesoros escondidos, mientras llegas al <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#pilatos\\"><b>Casa Pilatos</b></a> uno de los mejor conservados de la ciudad, propiedad de los duques de Medinaceli.</p><p>Posteriormente continuamos nuestra caminata hasta <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#fabiola\\"><b>Casa Fabiola.</b></a> Hoy se ha convertido en una sala de exposiciones de arte tradicional. Para finalizar la tarde recomiendo una visita al antiguo <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#venerables\\"><b>Hospital de los Venerables</b></a> y al <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#caridad\\"><b>Hospital de la Caridad</b></a> y tomar algo en la terraza del <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#donamaria\\"><b>Hotel Doña María</b></a> que tiene unas vistas espectaculares.</p><p>Para finalizar esta experiencia, cenaremos en la Plaza del Salvador, donde nos sentaremos en las mesas altas del centro para disfrutar de una cerveza fría, las tapas más típicas de la ciudad como unas ricas patatas y las vistas a una de las plazas más bonitas y llenas de vida del centro de la ciudad (tienes la oportunidad de disfrutar de las mejores tapas de la ciudad). <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#bodeguita\\"><b>La Antigua Bodeguita</b></a> o la <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#salvador\\"><b>Freiduría Salvador</b></a> .</p><p>Por cierto, para cenar te recomendamos un restaurante más sofisticado, no dejes de visitar el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#sanfernando\\"><strong>restaurante San Fernando</strong></a> y entrar en el Hotel Alfonso XIII (recomiendo reservar con antelación para asegurar disponibilidad).</p><p>¡Que aproveche!</p>\t\t	\N	\N	566	\N	\N	6.9			N	es	927,919,4407,926,928,915,929,925,917,918,916,911,902,924,903,910,930	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=1LgB-md4uRlIQPtGRTrHeoKocdgWVmIM&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Sumérgete en la majestuosidad del pasado de Sevilla con estas joyas arquitectónicas, llenas de historia y elegancia, que te transportarán a una época de esplendor.	\N	\N	Ruta De Las Casas Palacio 1 Dí­a							1Dia	203	N
567	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-22 07:10:32	26214	2024-11-15 00:00:00	SV37 Vintage 1 día	Vintage 1 Dia	vintage-1-dia	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Disfruta del lado más vintage y retro de Sevilla</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\nPrepáraos para una emocionante aventura en Sevilla mientras descubrís tiendas de segunda mano, rincones de coleccionista y mercadillos con encanto. Esta experiencia os permitirá sumergiros en el corazón de la capital de Híspalis desde una perspectiva única, donde desenterraréis tesoros ocultos, descubriréis joyas históricas y experimentaréis el auténtico encanto de la ciudad. Acompañadnos en este viaje lleno de nostalgia y hallazgos extravagantes mientras exploramos los rincones más estrafalarios de Sevilla. Perfecto para los viajeros que buscan una aventura única.	203	sevilla-vintage-1-dia.jpg	1	<p>El primer día comienza en la zona más alternativa de Sevilla, el <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#setas\\"><strong>Metropol Parasol</strong></a> (Las Setas). Un buen lugar para comenzar la ruta es <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#regina\\"><strong>Calle Regina</strong></a> una calle reinventada en los últimos años, donde se pueden encontrar tiendas de artesanía, ropa, cafés, restaurantes? Te recomiendo desayunar fuerte para coger energía en <a href=\\"#cacharreria\\"><strong>La Cacharrería</strong></a> te encantará su ambiente, decoración, desayunos, brunch, zumos, tartas?</p><p>Seguimos calle abajo y llegamos a la calle Feria, una de las más animadas de la ciudad, donde se mezclan los comercios tradicionales de barrio con las tiendas modernas. Además, si vienes un jueves, vivirás la calle en todo su esplendor con el <a href=\\"#jueves\\"><strong>histórico mercado de antigüedades ?El Jueves</strong></a>? Aquí tienes una lista de tiendas para visitar: para ropa, están <a href=\\"#wonder\\"><strong>Wonder Vintage</strong></a> , Nonna´s Vintage, Ropero, Antro Vintage, Pipa Vintage.<b>…</b>; para libros, está <a href=\\"#baena\\"><strong>Librería Baena</strong></a>? Puedes tomarte su tiempo y pasar un día maravilloso en la zona.</p><p>Una visita obligada es el <a href=\\"#feria\\"><strong>Mercado de Feria</strong></a> donde encontrará un mercado tradicional de frutas, verduras, carne y pescado. También puedes comer algo en <a href=\\"#jaleo\\"><strong>Jaleo Guadalquibeer</strong></a>. Justo detrás, se puede visitar el <a href=\\"#algaba\\"><strong>Palacio de los Marqueses de la Algaba</strong></a> o el <a href=\\"#luis\\"><strong>Conjunto Monumental de San Luis de los Franceses</strong></a>. Para comer en la zona, recomiendo ?<a href=\\"#ambigu\\"><strong>El Ambigú</strong></a>.?</p><p>Por la tarde comenzamos en la Catedral. Justo enfrente, tienes uno de los rincones con encanto que esconde Sevilla,<a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#cabildo\\"><strong>Plaza del Cabildo</strong></a>. En esta bonita plaza semicircular, encontrarás varias tiendas interesantes y curiosas como <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#ortega\\"><strong>Anticuario Lola Ortega</strong></a> o <a href=\\"#felix\\"><strong>Poster Félix</strong></a>. Además, si vienes un domingo, puedes encontrar un mercado de monedas y sellos. <a href=\\"#stamp\\"><strong>de monedas y sellos</strong></a>. </p><p>Desde aquí, bajaremos por Postigo del Aceite, hacia el barrio del Arenal. Aquí, recomiendo visitar el <a href=\\"#postigo\\"><strong>Mercado de Artesanía El Postigo</strong></a>. A continuación, caminaremos hasta la Plaza del Salvador, donde se encuentran las tiendas de ropa de segunda mano <a href=\\"#moda\\"><strong>Moda-re</strong></a> y <a href=\\"#peninsula\\"><strong>Península Vintage</strong></a>. También puedes visitar la encantadora librería de segunda mano <a href=\\"#boteros\\"><strong>Boteros</strong></a>. Para comer en esta zona, recomiendo el restaurante <a href=\\"#sal\\"><strong>Sal Gorda</strong></a>. </p><p>A continuación, bajaremos por la calle Sierpes hasta llegar a la calle Amor de Dios, donde se encuentra la <a href=\\"#read\\"><strong>librería Re-Read</strong></a> y las clásicas tiendas de discos <a style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\" href=\\"#latimore\\"><strong>Latimore</strong></a> y Record Sevilla. Concluiremos nuestra ruta de compras en la calle San Eloy para visitar la tienda de ropa <a href=\\"#mosaico\\"><strong>Mosaico</strong></a> seguro que encuentras alguna sorpresa o ganga. Puede terminar el día tomando una copa o cenando en la terraza de <a href=\\"#justa\\"><strong>Justa y Rufina</strong></a>.</p>\t\t	\N	\N	567	\N	\N	6.9			N	es	2055,2063,2064,2061,3862,2056,2041,2079,2059,2076,2078,2058,2073,904,2072,2057,2074,2080,903,2075,2069,4437,2077,2070	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=1xbIGb9o9_8M2n-k2n7PNg-sv1YVMcz4&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Disfruta del lado más vintage y retro de Sevilla	\N	\N	Vintage 1 Dí­a							1Dia	204	N
568	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-18 21:05:37	27768	2024-11-15 00:00:00	MED01 Rooftops	Viewpoints 3 Days	viewpoints-3-days	<span style=\\"color: #f41b8c;\\"><strong>Tour Medellín\\ s top viewpoints and discover places to enjoy from the heights.</strong></span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"color: #000000;\\">Take a look at the top 10 viewpoints and patches in Medellín and enjoy views that will take your breath away! Also enjoy the gastronomic recommendations of our local hosts!</span>	204	miradores.png	4	<p>We started the plan in El Poblado, since it is one of the areas of the city that enjoys the best panoramic views, thanks to its privileged location surrounded by green mountains. I suggest you start by having breakfast at<b>  Lavato laundry & Brunch,  </b>a place where, while enjoying the best cuisine, you can telework and even do your laundry. Afterwards you can take a walk through the Poblado neighborhood, the  <b>lleras park</b>  and provence street. We begin our route with  <b>La Drift Rooftop,</b>  It is a modern oasis located on the terrace of the Click Clack Hotel, it is like being on a beach between mountains, they have the half-round club. Here I recommend the best dish made with Lionfish in the city, if sea food is your thing. Since we have so many terraces in the city, I suggest this list as a top roof so you can choose the one that most attracts your attention.  </p></p><p><b>Marquee</b>  It is a luxurious boutique hotel, in the heart of Lleras Park. Every last Saturday of the month, you can go to the iconic Marquee Brunch<b>. TRUE</b>  at Landmark hotel, known as true, safe, indubitable, a place where lies have no place because they are real through not hiding what they like most: eating, drinking and having fun. Here you have an unmissable Nikkei Style! I like it for late nights.</p><p>At night you can go have a drink at <b>Envy Rooftop</b>  at the Charlee Hotel, The loudest and tastiest roof in Medellín, located on the Floor (P) of the hotel, is ideal for seeing Medellín from above. On the last Sunday of every month they have a brunch that you won?t be able to miss, with an unlimited buffet and free mimosas, live DJs and lots of fun.  </p>                	<p>These are our recommendations for this day in Medellín!  <b>Los Rooftops by Los Patios.</b><br /><br />If you are in El Poblado and your plan is a sunny day, a pool and a cocktail, the <b>rooftop of Los Patios Suites</b> is the one for a dream tan ??<br /><br />If you want to party with the best tropical vibe ? , we suggest <b>Ziruma,</b> the only rooftop tiki bar in the city <a href=\\"https://www.instagram.com/zirumarooftop/?hl=es-la\\"><b>@zirumarooftop</b></a> has two floors with excellent views, happy hour every day and daily activities full of flavor ?<br /><br />In Laureles we have the rooftop with the best view in the sector, Medellín at 360, swimming pool, Turkish, gastronomy and signature cocktails, all in one place <b>Ocaso Rooftop Gastro bar</b> ?? <a href=\\"https://www.instagram.com/ocasorooftop/?hl=es-la\\"><b>@ocasorooftop</b></a></p></p><p>Another option that you should not miss is to go to dinner at <b>Hangar M45 Azotea</b>, is a Medellín themed restaurant that is one of the most viral of the moment. Where you can try Colombian cuisine, sushi or grilled meat. In addition to enjoying an eccentric experience riding in a helicopter. Their tables are airplane chairs. Without a doubt it is the terrace of the moment. Don?t forget to take a photo at Hangar M45 and tag Liiffe.com on social networks.</p><p><br />So which one do you arrive at?  </p>                	<p>Today where is the patch? If you want to start the day with the best energy, go to  <b>Goose and Beaver,</b>  the best bistro in the city. Super recommended!!! They can bring their furry friends, especially if they go to the Ciudad del Río headquarters. My favorites there are the veggie dishes and the chocolate with cardamom.</p><p><br />Taking advantage if they are in the Ciudad del Río sector, located in El Poblado. Go see the rooms of the MAMM, Museum of Modern Art of Medellín, they open from 11 Am. Also ask about the store, they sell very nice Colombian items to take with you as a souvenir.</p><p></p><p>Then I suggest you continue exploring the rooftops that best suit your needs and preferences.  <b>social mosquito</b>, a spring paradise, is the breeze that brought flavor, rhythm and tumbao to a little terrace near the sun. We all like pool parties, but not all of us like to get wet, they offer ideal plans for the partyseo.  </p></p><p>If you want to leave the town, I recommend a rooftop closer to the sky, <b>Zélebre</b>, formerly 360 rooftop. They have a nice headquarters in Laureles. Thursdays are perfect for a cocktail patch, ask for the recommended one of the day. Place with open ceilings ideal for eating, drinking, patching and taking a nice postcard.  </p></p><p>Being in the Laureles area, do not hesitate to go and visit <b>Panorama Roof bar,</b> They have a terrace, brunch and bar in one place, they have two locations, the other is in Provence. They have spaces designed so you can organize your parties and events, special decoration touches and dynamic spaces equipped for your activities, with catering service to serve your guests.<br /><br />Finally you could take a walk, for a unique and safe place to enjoy the center of Medellín in a different way.  <b>Gastrobar canvas.</b>  They are the rooftop of the Gallery Hotel. A quiet and charming little corner, surrounded by little plants  ???  that make us pause and breathe. Come up and enjoy a menu designed for any time of the day  ? ? ????</p>\t\t	568	\N	\N	14.9	\N	\N	N	en	1780,1793,1776,1790,1789,1781,1782,1777,1766,1785,1778,1788,1791,1792,1779,1786,1783,1745,1784	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/1/embed?mid=10Cqjo8yvblJioQTregiArKux8y5VsiU&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Tour Medellín\\ s top viewpoints and discover places to enjoy from the heights.	\N	\N	Viewpoints 3 Days	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	3Dias	205	N
569	S	anonimo	2024-11-15 00:03:14	2024-11-22 07:10:32	17571	2024-11-15 00:00:00	MED07 Afterwork	Afterwork 3 Dias	afterwork-3-dias	<strong><span style=\\"color: #ff008c;\\">Parchemos, conversemos y disfrutemos de la ciudad de la eterna primavera en un recorrido afterwork</span></strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">A través de esta experiencia conocerás diferentes ?parches? de la ciudad, donde podrás disfrutar de una rica cerveza, un vino, pintar, asistir a teatro o algún stand up comedy. En esta oportunidad te recomiendo actividades en diferentes sectores de la ciudad para que después de tu trabajo puedas ?tardear? con un par de amigos paisas con los que quieras compartir. Con estas recomendaciones podrás visitar estos barrios en días distintos, caminar sus calles y llevarte unos buenos recuerdos de viaje como un auténtico paisa!</span>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\\"font-weight: 400;\\">Es una experiencia ideal para nómadas digitales en Medellín y para quienes nos visitan en alguna feria u evento, que luego de su jornada de trabajo quieren disfrutar y conocer de la ciudad.</span>	205	afterwork-3.jpg	4	<p>Medellín, the city of eternal spring, as it is known in Colombia; It has various places to enjoy after a long day of work.</p><p>Beer, music, dance, theater, are some of the options that add rhythm and flavor to the warm afternoons of the city. Today I want to recommend several of these places so that you can enjoy your stay in the Medellín of my soul. I am sure that you will connect with many of these places.  </p><p>On the first day: <b>The Center</b></p><p>Touring the center of the city of Medellín is perhaps one of the patches that I like to do the most in my city. I am a very cosmopolitan woman and I love recognizing the stories of every corner of these streets that have so much life, so much diversity and so much color.</p><p>Our first stop is without a doubt <b>“ <a href=\\"#inverso\\">Inverso</a> ”</b>  a coliving that has spaces that allow you to spend time differently; They have a daily agenda with different activities that will allow you to disconnect and have a pleasant time, among them are: Afro dance – movements for the soul, yoga classes, film clubs and many more.</p><p>One of my favorites is afro dance <b>,</b>  Well, here the body and soul are allowed to flow through African rhythms, to the beat of each song. Without a doubt, a magical moment full of tranquility and fun; Remember to reserve your spot before participating.</p><p>When you leave there, I recommend going to <b>“ <a href=\\"#playa\\">Mercado la Playa</a> ”</b>, a place with an important gastronomic diversity, a space that believes in the art behind each prepared dish, this place is undoubtedly a movement that combines the cultural experiences of the center of Medellín, with moments that will be kept in the memory of all who visit them. In reality, it is “A Patch”  </p><p>One of my favorite restaurants is Bendito chicharrón, a place that offers a wide variety of preparations with chicharrón on its menu; However, if you want you can also eat a delicious meat at “Calisto Parrilla & BBQ” you will not regret it. </p><p>In this market, you will also find establishments that allow you to enjoy a delicious beer or a delicious cocktail. “Osadía Bar and Beer” offers you various alternatives with which you can accompany an interesting conversation with friends or locals in our city.</p><p>If you are one of the people who likes the Theater, a few blocks from Mercado de la Playa is <b>“ <a href=\\"#teatro\\">The Little Theater</a> ”</b>  a space founded in 1975, which is the cultural heritage of the city and is framed in a Republican-style house that is the architectural heritage of Medellín, here they offer different plays every day, which have an entry model with contribution voluntary and that frame many traditional stories of the city and important works at an international level. If you are in Medellín and enjoy panel art, you must come to this place.</p><p>When you leave the construction site, if you want to try some more traditional food, I recommend walking a couple of streets and going to <b>“ <a href=\\"#lienzo\\">Lienzo Rooftop Restaurante</a> ”</b> located on Bomboná Street <b>,</b> there  You can enjoy a wonderful view of the city center while you dine on one of the local delicacies. To start, I recommend a trio from the Pacific and as the main course I would order a delicious Peruvian salmon, you will surely “want to lick your fingers.”</p><p>To finish and enjoy the cool night of Medellín, you can stay there and order a shot or a gin and tonic, surely a drink on this terrace will go down very well; or you can also walk again to the <b><a style=\\"color: #f41b8c; text-decoration: underline;\\" href=\\"#pablo\\">Pablo Tobón Theater</a> ,</b>  where you can enjoy good pola and live music, craft fairs and many more artistic and cultural exhibitions. In short, it is a great patch to share, chat and experience the center of Medellín.</p>                	<p>On the second day: <b>Laureles</b> is the coolest neighborhood in the world, according to Time Out.</p><p>Walking through the circular paths of the Laureles neighborhood of Medellín is to feel the freshness of the city and learn about an important part of the history of the city of eternal spring.</p><p>The first “patch” that I want to recommend to you for this day is to live the <a href=\\"#laberinto\\"><strong>experience</strong></a> “Of the beer labyrinth between circular and transversal” offered by Click Urban , a local tour operator that has a wide variety of innovative activities on offer.</p><p>In this experience you will learn about the diversity of craft beers that we have in the city, made with exotic flavors and own blends that will lead you to delight in every sip of this ancient drink on the warm afternoons of the city.</p><p>To eat, in Laureles there are various options, a very good one is to go to <a href=\\"#simons\\"><b>Simons pizza</b></a> , a place where you can enjoy live music, beer and the pizza of your choice on the weekends, it is a very good patch for a Thursday or Friday at night.</p><p>On the other hand, if you like Korean food, <a href=\\"#oppa\\"><b>Oppa</b></a> It is a great option. In this restaurant located in the Laureles neighborhood, you will find a wide variety of delicious Korean dishes that you will want to try. My favorite is ramen, because I love spicy food, however, there are many other delicious options on the menu that you can choose from.</p><p>If you like to paint, drink coffee, snack on food and enjoy art; The plan is in <b>“ <a href=\\"#parche\\">Coffee Parche</a> ”,</b> a place that allows you to let your imagination fly by painting different ceramic figures of your choice that you can take with you at the end of the experience.</p><p>This location is located in the Los Colores neighborhood, within the commune of Laureles, very close to the stadium, in the Mixy Mall shopping center.</p><p>There you can also enjoy the bakery or the delicious pizzas that are on the place?s menu.</p><p>After living this great artistic experience, I would walk a couple of blocks, enjoy the streets full of beautiful trees and fruits of the area, and in the Mall Los Colores, I would enter <b><a href=\\"#forno\\">Il forno</a> ,</b> a local restaurant specializing in Italian food <b>,</b> and I would eat a delicious tomato soup, a solomito risotto or a delicious Mediterranean salad, the truth is, the gastronomy of this restaurant is delicious. </p><p>To end the night, two blocks from the restaurant, very close to the OR supermarket, you will find <a href=\\"#calamardo\\"><b>Calamardo Cocktails</b></a> , a simple place, but ideal to enjoy a delicious drink and a good chat in the beautiful natural environment of the area.</p>                	<p>On day 3: <b>Manila</b></p><p>The Manila neighborhood of the city of Medellín is characterized by being the home of many artists, restaurants and independent businesses. As you walk the streets of this sector of the city you can find various craft and local markets where you can eat and buy travel souvenirs.</p><p>A place in this sector that immerses us in art and shopping is <a href=\\"#milnueve\\"><b>Milnueve 32</b></a>, a place where you can breathe art in every corner and which is named after the year of birth of the famous Colombian sculptor Fernando Botero. At Milnueve 32 you can buy all kinds of materials for the work of art you want to create, access painting classes, buy second-hand clothes and jewelry, have a coffee, eat a small brunch, read a book, among others. It is a place that you do not want to miss visiting in Medellín.</p><p>To continue, I invite you to have a coffee at <b>“ <a href=\\"#zorba\\">Zorba</a> ”,</b>  a very bohemian place where you can enjoy different options of pizza, gelatos and desserts; while you listen to live music with different artists who can perform anything from a tango to a Latin American music song, jazz, soul or play percussion. It is the perfect “patch” to chat with friends and spend an afternoon.  </p><p>For dinner, you must go to <b>“ <a href=\\"#lavocaderia\\">Lavocadería</a> ”</b>  It is perhaps one of my favorite restaurants. The main color of this place is the variety of dishes prepared with avocado; a quite different and innovative gastronomy option for the palate. My favorites are the stuffed sirloin or the avoburger. When you see the menu, you will have excellent options to taste delicious dishes. Without a doubt, it is an unmissable place to visit.</p><p>This restaurant also offers you the opportunity to take travel souvenirs, go to the gift shop and choose the one you like the most; Also, I recommend asking about the tour – avocado course  that they do on a farm in eastern Antioquia. You will see that it is a great patch to do during your stay in Medellín.</p><p>To end the night, I would walk to <b><a href=\\"#masaya\\">Masaya</a> ,</b>  a rooftop very close to the Manila neighborhood, where you can see the city, enjoy the pool and have a delicious cocktail with your travel companions. The perfect ending to a great night.</p><p>Walking through these neighborhoods of the city is to enjoy the wonderful climate of Medellín and the kindness of its people. Enjoy your adventure!</p>\t\t	569	\N	\N	14.9			N	en	4468,4475,4472,4476,1707,1710,1703,4474,4471,4467,4470,4473,4477,4469,1706	&lt;iframe src=\\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/4/embed?mid=1mVbJJ4_GguT6YEFw2IpV5SavyuRc7NY&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1\\" width=\\"640\\" height=\\"480\\"&gt;	\N	\N	\N	N	N	Parchemos, conversemos y disfrutemos de la ciudad de la eterna primavera en un recorrido afterwork	\N	\N	Afterwork 3 Dí­as							3Dias	206	N
